text: Et vir fratrem suum deridebit, et veritatem non loquentur: docuerunt enim linguam suam loqui mendacium; ut inique agerent laboraverunt.
verse_text: Sagitta vulnerans lingua eorum, dolum locuta est. In ore suo pacem cum amico suo loquitur, et occulte ponit ei insidias.

text: Quia haec dicit Dominus Deus Israel ad domos urbis hujus, et ad domos regis Juda, quae destructae sunt, et ad munitiones, et ad gladium
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus Deus Israel: Ecce ego convertam vasa belli quae in manibus vestris sunt, et quibus vos pugnatis adversum regem Babylonis et Chaldaeos qui obsident vos in circuitu murorum: et congregabo ea in medio civitatis hujus.

text: And set the towers thereof vpon the gates of it, an hundred cubites high, and the breadth thereof in the foundation threescore cubites.
verse_text: Per quadrum vero earum latus utrumque vicenorum pedum spatio tendebatur, posuitque portas ejus in altitudinem turrium:

text: But the louing kindnesse of the Lord endureth for euer and euer vpon them that feare him, and his righteousnes vpon childrens children,
verse_text: For his louing kindnes is great toward vs, and the trueth of the Lord endureth for euer. Praise yee the Lord.

text: Sacrificing in the field: I will give thy strength, and all thy treasures to the spoil, and thy high places for sin in all thy borders.
verse_text: Thy substance and thy treasures will I giue to the spoile without price, and that for all thy sinnes, euen in all thy borders.

text: Moreouer Ieremiah sayd vnto all the people, and to all the women; Heare the word of the Lord, all Iudah, that are in the land of Egypt.
verse_text: And say vnto them, Heare the word of the Lord, ye Kings of Iudah, and al Iudah, and all the inhabitants of Ierusale, that enter in by these gates.

text: Of an offence before a iudge and ruler, of iniquitie before a congregation and people, of vniust dealing before thy partner and friend:
verse_text: Melior est homo qui abscondit stultitiam suam, quam homo qui abscondit sapientiam suam.

text: Then went Ieremiah vnto Gedaliah the sonne of Ahikam, to Mizpah, and dwelt there with him among the people that were left in the lande.
verse_text: Now it came to passe in the seuenth moneth, that Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah the sonne of Elishamah of the seede royall, and the princes of the king, euen tenne men with him, came vnto Gedaliah the sonne of Ahikam to Mizpah, and there they did eate bread together in Mizpah.

text: Let all those that seeke thee, reioyce, and be glad in thee: and let such as loue thy saluation, say continually, Let God be magnified.
verse_text: But let all those that put their trust in thee, reioyce: let them euer shout for ioy; because thou defendest them: let them also that loue thy name, be ioyfull in thee.

text: cujus oculi aperti sunt super omnes vias filiorum Adam, ut reddas unicuique secundum vias suas, et secundum fructum adinventionum ejus.
verse_text: qui do unicuique juxta viam suam, et juxta fructum adinventionum suarum.

text: He that is hasty to give credit, is light of heart, and shall be lessened: and he that sinneth against his own soul, shall be despised.
verse_text: He that useth many words shall hurt his own soul: and he that taketh authority to himself unjustly shall be hated.

text: And concerning the Iudges, euery one by name, whose heart went not a whoring, nor departed from the Lord, let their memory be blessed.
verse_text: Et dedit Dominus ipsi Caleb fortitudinem, et usque in senectutem permansit illi virtus, ut ascenderet in excelsum terrae locum, et semen ipsius obtinuit haereditatem,

text: So all the people that Ishmael had caried away captiue from Mizpah cast about and returned, and went vnto Iohanan the sonne of Kareah.
verse_text: But Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah escaped from Iohanan with eight men, and went to the Ammonites.

text: Incline thine eare to me, make hast to deliuer me. Be vnto me for a God protector: and for a house of refuge, that thou mayst saue me.
verse_text: But I am poore and needy, make haste vnto me, O God: Thou art my helpe and my deliuerer, O Lord make no tarrying.

text: Et scripsit Jeremias omne malum quod venturum erat super Babylonem, in libro uno: omnia verba haec quae scripta sunt contra Babylonem.
verse_text: Et locutus est Jeremias propheta ad Sedeciam regem Juda universa verba haec in Jerusalem.

text: For which crime they were given up to their enemies, to the sword, and to pillage, and to confusion: but we know no other God but him.
verse_text: And there was no one that triumphed over this people, but when they departed from the worship of the Lord their God.

text: Why art thou cast downe, my soule, and vnquiet within me? waite on God: for I will yet giue him thankes for the helpe of his presence.
verse_text: Why art thou cast downe, O my soule? and why art thou disquieted within me? hope in God, for I shall yet praise him, who is the health of my countenance, and my God.

text: Iniquitas adversum me et caro mea super Babylonem, dicit habitatio Sion: et sanguis meus super habitatores Chaldaeae, dicit Jerusalem.
verse_text: Propterea haec dicit Dominus exercituum ad prophetas: Ecce ego cibabo eos absinthio, et potabo eos felle: a prophetis enim Jerusalem egressa est pollutio super omnem terram.

text: And Jeremias went to Godolias the son of Ahicam to Masphath: and dwelt with him in the midst of the people that were left in the land.
verse_text: Then Johanan the son of Caree, and all the captains of the army, that had been scattered about in the countries, came to Godolias to Masphath.

text: If a seruant say to his master, I will not doe as it pleaseth thee, though afterward hee doe it, hee angereth him that nourisheth him.
verse_text: Melior est homo qui minuitur sapientia, et deficiens sensu, in timore, quam qui abundat sensu, et transgreditur legem Altissimi.

text: Rex quoque colebat eum, et ibat per singulos dies adorare eum: porro Daniel adorabat Deum suum. Dixitque ei rex: Quare non adoras Bel?
verse_text: Et dixit rex Danieli: Ecce nunc non potes dicere quia iste non sit deus vivens: adora ergo eum.

text: Let them be confounded and put to shame, that seeke my soule: let them bee turned backewarde and put to rebuke, that desire mine hurt.
verse_text: Let them be confounded and put to shame that seeke after my soule: let them be turned backe and brought to confusion, that deuise my hurt.

text: Whether a man be rich or poore, if he haue a good heart towards the Lord, he shall at all times reioyce with a cheerefull countenance.
verse_text: divitis autem et pauperis cor bonum, in omni tempore vultus illorum hilaris.

text: et cum in faciem ejus intendisset, adoravit eum, prosternens se super terram. Et elevaverunt eam servi Holofernis, jubente domino suo.
verse_text: Sed cum nullum motum jacentis sensu aurium caperet, accessit proximans ad cortinam, et elevans eam, vidensque cadaver absque capite Holofernis in suo sanguine tabefactum jacere super terram, exclamavit voce magna cum fletu, et scidit vestimenta sua.

text: But the mercy of the Lord is from euerlasting to euerlasting vpon them that feare him: and his righteousnesse vnto childrens children:
verse_text: But the mercie of our Lord from euerlasting, and vnto euerlasting vpon them that feare him. And his iustice is vpon the childrens children, to them that keepe his testament.

text: eunuches which was in the kings house, heard that they had put Ieremiah in the dungeon (the king then sitting in the gate of Beniamin)
verse_text: And Ieremiah the Prophet was shutte vp in the court of the prison, which was in the King of Iudahs house.

text: Grex dispersus Israel: leones ejecerunt eum. Primus comedit eum rex Assur: iste novissimus exossavit eum Nabuchodonosor rex Babylonis.
verse_text: quia venit super eam, id est super Babylonem, praedo, et apprehensi sunt fortes ejus, et emarcuit arcus eorum, quia fortis ultor Dominus reddens retribuet.

text: Unto the seruant that is wise, shall they that are free doe seruice: and hee that hath knowledge, will not grudge when he is reformed.
verse_text: Gloria divitum, honoratorum, et pauperum, timor Dei est.

text: Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego answered and said to the king; O Nebuchad-nezzar, we are not carefull to answere thee in this matter.
verse_text: Then Nebuchad-nezzar in his anger and wrath commanded that they should bring Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego: so these men were brought before the King.

text: Remember not the sinnes of my youth, nor my transgressions: according to thy mercie remember thou me, for thy goodnesse sake, O Lord.
verse_text: Heare me, O Lord, for thy louing kindnesse is good: turne vnto mee according to the multitude of thy tendermercies.

text: The foole hath sayd in his heart, There is no God: they are corrupt, they haue done abominable workes, there is none that doeth good.
verse_text: To him that excelleth on Mahalath. A Psalme of David to give instruction. The foole hath saide in his heart, There is no God. they haue corrupted and done abominable wickednes: there is none that doeth good.

text: But concerning them that rebell, let not thine eye spare them: but put them to the slaughter, and spoile them wheresoeuer thou goest.
verse_text: Et profectus est ipse, et omnis exercitus cum quadrigis, et equitibus, et sagittariis: qui cooperuerunt faciem terrae sicut locustae.

text: Audivit autem Johanan filius Caree, et omnes principes bellatorum qui erant cum eo, omne malum quod fecerat Ismahel filius Nathaniae,
verse_text: Surrexit autem Ismahel filius Nathaniae, et decem viri qui cum eo erant, et percusserunt Godoliam filium Ahicam filii Saphan gladio, et interfecerunt eum quem praefecerat rex Babylonis terrae.

text: Sicuti enumerari non possunt stellae caeli, et metiri arena maris, sic multiplicabo semen David servi mei, et Levitas ministros meos.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus: Si mensurari potuerint caeli sursum, et investigari fundamenta terrae deorsum, et ego abjiciam universum semen Israel, propter omnia quae fecerunt, dicit Dominus.

text: Quoniam pius et misericors est Deus, et remittet in die tribulationis peccata, et protector est omnibus exquirentibus se in veritate.
verse_text: Da misericordi, et ne suscipias peccatorem: et impiis et peccatoribus reddet vindictam, custodiens eos in diem vindictae.

text: Let death sense vpon them: let them goe downe quicke into the graue: for wickednes is in their dwellings, euen in the middes of them.
verse_text: For the enemie hath persecuted my soule: he hath smitten my life downe to the earth: he hath layde me in the darkenes, as they that haue bene dead long agoe:

text: This they did on the thirteenth day of the moneth Adar, and rested the fourteenth day thereof, and kept it a day of feasting and ioy.
verse_text: But the Iewes that were at Shushan, assembled together on the thirteenth day therof, and on the fourteenth thereof; and on the fifteenth day of the same, they rested, and made it a day of feasting and gladnesse.

text: Thus were the visions of mine head in my bed. And beholde, I sawe a tree in the middes of the earth and the height thereof was great:
verse_text: Saw a dreame, which made me afraide, and the thoughtes vpon my bed, and the visions of mine head troubled me.

text: Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego answered and said to the King, O Nebuchad-nezzar, we are not carefull to answere thee in this matter.
verse_text: Then Nebuchad-nezzar in his anger and wrath commanded that they should bring Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego: so these men were brought before the King.

text: Wherewith he was very angry, and called all the princes of Moab, and the captaines of Ammon, and all the gouernours of the Sea coast.
verse_text: et furore nimio exarsit in iracundia magna, vocavitque omnes principes Moab et duces Ammon,

text: Then said Ieremiah vnto all the people, to the men, and to the women, and to all the people which had giuen him that answere, saying,
verse_text: The which Ieremiah the Prophet spake vnto all the people of Iudah, and to all the inhabitants of Ierusalem, saying,

text: Where are nowe your prophets, which prophecied vnto you, saying, The King of Babel shall not come against you, nor against this land?
verse_text: Then answered I, Ah Lord God, beholde, the prophets say vnto them, Ye shall not see the sworde, neither shall famine come vpon you, but I wil giue you assured peace in this place.

text: Let them be confounded and consumed that are against my soule: let them be couered with reproofe and confusion, that seeke mine hurt.
verse_text: Let them be ashamed and brought to confusion together, that reioyce at mine hurt: let them bee cloathed with shame and dishonour, that magnifie themselues against me.

text: And one said to the man clothed in linnen, which was vpon the waters of the riuer; How long shall it bee to the end of these wonders?
verse_text: And I heard the man clothed in linnen, which was vpon the waters of the riuer, when he held vp his right hand, and his left hand vnto heauen, and sware by him that liueth for euer, that it shalbe for a time, times, and an halfe: and when hee shall haue accomplished to scatter the power of the holy people, all these things shall bee finished.

text: Ishmael also slewe all the Iewes that were with Gedaliah at Mizpah, and all the Caldeans that were found there, and the men of warre.
verse_text: Then Ishmael caryed away captiue all the residue of the people that were in Mizpah, euen the Kings daughters, and all the people that remained in Mizpah, whom Nebuzar-adan the chiefe steward had committed to Gedaliah the sonne of Ahikam, and Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah caried them away captiue, and departed to goe ouer to the Ammonites.

text: Psalmus David, priusquam liniretur. Dominus illuminatio mea et salus mea: quem timebo? Dominus protector vitae meae: a quo trepidabo?
verse_text: Ego autem mendicus sum et pauper; Dominus sollicitus est mei. Adjutor meus et protector meus tu es; Deus meus, ne tardaveris.

text: But I trust in thy mercie: mine heart shall reioyce in thy saluation: I will sing to the Lord, because he hath delt louingly with me.
verse_text: The Lord is my strength, and my shield, my heart trusted in him, and I am helped: therefore my heart greatly reioyceth, and with my song will I praise him.

text: Let not the greedinesse of the belly, nor lust of the flesh take hold of me, and giue not ouer me thy seruant into an impudent minde.
verse_text: Aufer a me ventris concupiscentias, et concubitus concupiscentiae ne apprehendant me, et animae irreverenti et infrunitae ne tradas me.

text: Then said Ozias to her, All that thou hast spoken, hast thou spoken with a good heart, and there is none that may gainesay thy words.
verse_text: Et dixerunt illi Ozias et presbyteri: Omnia quae locuta es, vera sunt, et non est in sermonibus tuis ulla reprehensio.

text: Let them be ashamed and confounded that seeke after my soule: let them be turned backward, and put to confusion, that desire my hurt.
verse_text: Let them be confounded and ashamed together, that seeke my soule, to take it away. Let them be turned backward, and be ashamed that wil me euils.

text: The woorde that the Lord spake to Ieremiah the Prophet, howe Nebuchad-nezzar king of Babel shoulde come and smite the lande of Egypt.
verse_text: The word of the Lord that came to Ieremiah the Prophet against the Philistines, before that Pharaoh smote Gaza.

text: and all the remnant of Iudah that are gone into the lande of Egypt to dwell there, shall know whose words shall stad, mine or theirs.
verse_text: And I will take the remnant of Iudah, that haue set their faces to goe into the lande of Egypt there to dwell, and they shall all bee consumed and fall in the lande of Egypt:

text: The word of the Lord that came to Ieremiah the Prophet against Elam in the beginning of the reigne of Zedekiah king of Iudah, saying,
verse_text: The worde which came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, in the dayes of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, saying,

text: Heare me spedely, O Lord, for my spirit faeleth: hide not thy face from me, els I shall be like vnto them that go downe into the pit.
verse_text: Vnto thee will I cry, O Lord, my rocke, be not silent to mee: lest if thou be silent to me, I become like them that goe downe into the pit.

text: For they haue sent some to Ierusalem, because they also that dwelt there haue done the like, to bring them a license from the Senate.
verse_text: Ego enim ancilla tua Deum colo, etiam nunc apud te: et exiet ancilla tua, et orabo Deum,

text: The Lord is in his holy palace: the Lordes throne is in the heauen: his eyes wil consider: his eye lids will try the children of men.
verse_text: For he hath looked downe from the height of his Sanctuarie: out of the heauen did the Lord beholde the earth,

text: Sit homo ille ut sunt civitates quae subvertit Dominus, et non poenituit eum: audiat clamorem mane, et ululatum in tempore meridiano,
verse_text: domus David. Haec dicit Dominus: Judicate mane judicium, et eruite vi oppressum de manu calumniantis, ne forte egrediatur ut ignis indignatio mea, et succendatur, et non sit qui extinguat, propter malitiam studiorum vestrorum.

text: And they drew up Jeremias with the cords, and brought him forth out of the dungeon. And Jeremias remained in the entry of the prison.
verse_text: So they drewe vp Ieremiah with coards and tooke him vp out of the dungeon, and Ieremiah remained in the court of the prison.

text: Doubtlesse kindnesse and mercie shall follow me all the dayes of my life, and I shall remaine a long season in the house of the Lord.
verse_text: The Lord shall blesse thee out of Zion: and thou shalt see the good of Ierusalem, all the dayes of thy life.

text: Venit autem Jeremias de Topheth, quo miserat eum Dominus ad prophetandum, et stetit in atrio domus Domini, et dixit ad omnem populum:
verse_text: Cumque illuxisset in crastinum, eduxit Phassur Jeremiam de nervo, et dixit ad eum Jeremias: Non Phassur vocavit Dominus nomen tuum, sed Pavorem undique.

text: Because thou hast deliuered my soule from death, and my feete from falling: that I may please before God, in the light of the liuing.
verse_text: Bring my soule out of prison, that I may praise thy Name: the righteous shall compasse me about: for thou shalt deale bountifully with me.

text: Sicut subvertit Dominus Sodomam et Gomorrham, et vicinas ejus, ait Dominus, non habitabit ibi vir, et non incolet eam filius hominis.
verse_text: Factae sunt civitates ejus in stuporem, terra inhabitabilis et deserta, terra in qua nullus habitet, nec transeat per eam filius hominis.

text: Behold, the heauen, and the heauen of heauens, the deepe and the earth, and all that therein is, shall be mooued when he shall visit.
verse_text: Ecce caelum et caeli caelorum, abyssus, et universa terra, et quae in eis sunt, in conspectu illius commovebuntur.

text: I wil confesse to thee for euer, because thou hast done it: and I wil expect thy name, because it is good in the sight of thy saints:
verse_text: I wil voluntarily sacrifice to thee, and wil confesse to thy name o Lord, because it is good:

text: Therefore thus saith the Lord, Aske now among the heathen, who hath heard such thinges? the virgin of Israel hath done very filthily.
verse_text: For thus hath the Lord of hostes said; Hew yee downe trees and cast a mount against Ierusalem: this is the citie to be visited, she is wholly oppression in the midst of her.

text: He hath made the earth by his power, and established the world by his wisedome, and hath stretched out the heauen by his discretion.
verse_text: He that maketh the earth by his power, that prepareth the world by his wisdom, and stretcheth out the heavens by his knowledge.

text: Therefore her yong men shall fall in her streetes, and all her men of warre shall be cut off in that day, sayeth the Lord of hostes.
verse_text: Therefore shall her young men fall in her streets: and all her men of war shall hold their peace in that day, saith the Lord.

text: And they shall answer: Because they have forsaken the covenant of the Lord their God, and have adored strange gods, and served them.
verse_text: And I will pronounce my judgements against them, touching all their wickedness, who have forsaken me, and have sacrificed to strange gods, and have adored the work of their own hands.

text: And he burnt the house of the Lord, and the king's house, and all the houses of Jerusalem, and every great house he burnt with fire.
verse_text: And the Chaldeans burnt the king's house, and the houses of the people with fire, and they threw down the wall of Jerusalem.

text: Confesse ye to the God of heauen: because his mercie is for euer. Confesse ye to the Lord of lordes: because his mercie is for euer.
verse_text: Praise ye the Lord. O giue thankes vnto the Lord, for he is good: for his mercie endureth for euer.

text: Let them be confounded, and fayle that detract from my soule: let them be couered with confusion, and shame, that seeke euils to me.
verse_text: Let them blush and be ashamed together, that reioyce at my euils. Let them be clothed with confusion and shame; that speake great things vpon me.

text: So the people honoured him with ten thousands, and praised him in the blessings of the Lord, in that hee gaue him a crowne of glory.
verse_text: nam invocavit Dominum omnipotentem, et dedit in dextera ejus tollere hominem fortem in bello, et exaltare cornu gentis suae.

text: and all the remnant of Juda that are gone into the land of Egypt to dwell there, shall know whose word shall stand, mine, or theirs.
verse_text: And there shall be none that shall escape, and remain of the remnant of the Jews that are gone to sojourn in the land of Egypt:

text: Then Ieremiah sayd vnto all the people, to the men and to the women, and to all the people which had giuen him that answere, saying;
verse_text: The which Ieremiah the Prophet spake vnto all the people of Iudah, and to all the inhabitants of Ierusalem, saying,

text: Take the girdle that thou hast got, which is vpon thy loines, and arise, goe to Euphrates, and hide it there in a hole of the rocke.
verse_text: Thus sayth the Lord vnto mee, Goe, and buy thee a linen girdle, and put it vpon thy loynes, and put it not in water.

text: et dices ad eos: Audite verbum Domini, reges Juda, et omnis Juda, cunctique habitatores Jerusalem, qui ingredimini per portas istas.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus ad me: Vade, et sta in porta filiorum populi, per quam ingrediuntur reges Juda, et egrediuntur, et in cunctis portis Jerusalem:

text: For thou hast deliuered my soule from death, and also my feete from falling, that I may walke before God in the light of the liuing.
verse_text: Because thou hast deliuered my soule from death, mine eyes from teares, and my feete from falling.

text: Therefore thus saith the Lord of hosts: Behold I will melt, and try them: for what else shall I do before the daughter of my people?
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel: Behold I will visit the king of Babylon and his land, as I have visited the king of Assyria.

text: Goe, and tell Hananiah, saying, Thus saith the Lord, Thou hast broken the yokes of wood, but thou shalt make for them yokes of yron.
verse_text: Send to all them of the captiuitie, saying, Thus saith the Lord, concerning Shemaiah the Nehelamite, Because that Shemaiah hath prophecied vnto you, and I sent him not, and he caused you to trust in a lye.

text: He that made the earth by his power, that hath prepared the world by his wisdom, and stretched out the heavens by his understanding.
verse_text: He hath made the earth by his power, and established the worlde by his wisedome, and hath stretched out the heauen by his discretion.

text: The word of the Lord that came to Jeremias the prophet against Elam, in the beginning of the reign of Sedecias king of Juda, saying:
verse_text: The word that Jeremias the prophet spoke to Baruch the son of Nerias, when he had written there words in a book, out of the mouth of Jeremias, in the fourth year of Joakim the son of Josias king of Juda, saying:

text: For goe ye to the yles of Chittim, and beholde, and sende vnto Kedar. and take diligent heede, and see whether there be such things.
verse_text: Run to and from by the streetes of Ierusalem, and beholde nowe, and knowe, and inquire in the open places thereof, if ye can finde a man, or if there be any that executeth iudgement, and seeketh the trueth, and I will spare it.

text: Therfore thou shalt not pray for this people, neither lift vp crie or praier for them neither intreat me, for I will not heare thee.
verse_text: Therefore pray not thou for this people, neither lift vp a cry or prayer for them: for I will not heare them in the time that they crie vnto mee for their trouble.

text: By an accusation to the king from an vnrighteous tongue, my soule drew neere euen vnto death, my life was neere to the hell beneath:
verse_text: a pressura flammae quae circumdedit me, et in medio ignis non sum aestuatus;

text: And a bruite shal truble him from the East, and from the North: and he shal come in a great multitude to destroy and kil very manie.
verse_text: And his strength & his hart shal be stirred vp against the king of the South in a great armie: and the king of the South shal be prouoked to battel with manie aydes, and exceding strong: & they shal not stand because they shal take counsels against him.

text: Remember that a wicked eye is an euill thing: and what is created more wicked then an eye? therefore it weepeth vpon euery occasion.
verse_text: Non dicas sic: Multa sunt, quae super illam sunt.

text: For loe, they haue layd waite for my soule: the mightie men are gathered against me, not for mine offence, nor for my sinne, O Lord.
verse_text: O God the wicked are risen vp vpon me, and the synagogue of the mightie haue sought my soule: and they haue not set thee in their sight.

text: So were all the sonnes of Aaron in their glory, and the oblations of the Lord in their hands, before all the congregation of Israel.
verse_text: In accipiendo autem partes de manu sacerdotum, et ipse stans juxta aram: et circa illum corona fratrum: quasi plantatio cedri in monte Libano,

text: Et quaecumque inter omnes oculis regis placuerit, ipsa regnet pro Vasthi. Placuit sermo regi: et ita, ut suggesserant, jussit fieri.
verse_text: His ita gestis, postquam regis Assueri indignatio deferbuerat, recordatus est Vasthi, et quae fecisset, vel quae passa esset:

text: As a drop of water vnto the Sea, and a grauell stone in comparison of the sand, so are a thousand yeeres to the dayes of eternitie.
verse_text: Vidit praesumptionem cordis eorum, quoniam mala est: et cognovit subversionem illorum, quoniam nequam est.

text: A labouring man that is giuen to drunkennesse shal not be rich, and hee that contemneth small things shall fall by little & little.
verse_text: Operarius ebriosus non locupletabitur: et qui spernit modica paulatim decidet.

text: So the people continued feasting in Ierusalem before the Sanctuarie, for the space of three moneths, and Iudeth remained with them.
verse_text: Vae genti insurgenti super genus meum: Dominus enim omnipotens vindicabit in eis; in die judicii visitabit illos.

text: How is Sheshach taken? and how is the praise of the whole earth surprised? how is Babylon become an astonishment among the nations?
verse_text: How is it overthrown, and they have howled! How hath Moab bowed down the neck, and is confounded! And Moab shall be a derision, and an example to all round about him.

text: That we may reioyce in thy saluation, and set vp the banner in the Name of our God, when the Lord shall performe all thy petitions.
verse_text: Let all those that seeke thee, reioyce, and be glad in thee: and let such as loue thy saluation, say continually, Let God be magnified.

text: The Lord will graunt his louing kindenesse in the day, and in the night shall I sing of him, euen a prayer vnto the God of my life.
verse_text: But I trust in thy mercie: mine heart shall reioyce in thy saluation: I will sing to the Lord, because he hath delt louingly with me.

text: Deus fortis super omnes, exaudi vocem eorum qui nullam aliam spem habent, et libera nos de manu iniquorum, et erue me a timore meo.
verse_text: Exaudi deprecationem meam, et propitius esto sorti et funiculo tuo, et converte luctum nostrum in gaudium, ut viventes laudemus nomen tuum, Domine: et ne claudas ora te canentium.

text: Then all the people together hasted, and fell downe to the earth vpon their faces to worship their Lord God almighty the most High.
verse_text: Effudit in fundamento altaris odorem divinum excelso Principi.

text: Et fecit Baruch filius Neriae juxta omnia quae praeceperat ei Jeremias propheta, legens ex volumine sermones Domini in domo Domini.
verse_text: Et locutus est Jeremias propheta ad Sedeciam regem Juda universa verba haec in Jerusalem.

text: In the beginning of the reigne of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, came this worde vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, saying,
verse_text: The worde which came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, in the dayes of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, saying,

text: Wo be vnto thee, O Moab: the people of Chemosh perisheth: for thy sonnes are taken captiues, and thy daughters led into captiuitie.
verse_text: Woe to thee, Moab, thou hast perished, O people of Chamos: for thy sons, and thy daughters are taken captives.

text: quia servierunt eis, cum essent gentes multae, et reges magni: et reddam eis secundum opera eorum, et secundum facta manuum suarum.
verse_text: Et dispergam eos in gentibus quas non noverunt ipsi et patres eorum, et mittam post eos gladium, donec consumantur.

text: Woe be vnto you vngodly men which haue forsaken the law of the most high God: for if you encrease, it shall be to your destruction.
verse_text: Filii abominationum fiunt filii peccatorum, et qui conversantur secus domos impiorum.

text: Now Phassur the son of Emmur, the priest, who was appointed chief in the house of the Lord, heard Jeremias prophesying these words.
verse_text: So Sophonias the priest read this letter, in the hearing of Jeremias the prophet.

text: Vnto the end, destroy not, to Dauid in the inscription of the title, when Saul sent, and watched his house to kil him. (1. Reg. 19)
verse_text: when he set fire on Mesopotamia of Syria, and in Sobal, and Ioab returned, and stroke Idumaea in the valley of saltpittes twelue thousand. (2. Reg. 8. & 10. & 1. Paral. 18.

text: So Iudeth saide, I will drinke now my lord, because my life is magnified in me this day, more then all the dayes since I was borne.
verse_text: Et dixit Judith: Bibam, domine, quoniam magnificata est anima mea hodie prae omnibus diebus meis.

text: Tu autem, Domine Sabaoth, qui judicas juste, et probas renes et corda, videam ultionem tuam ex eis: tibi enim revelavi causam meam.
verse_text: Et tu, Domine, nosti me, vidisti me, et probasti cor meum tecum. Congrega eos quasi gregem ad victimam, et sanctifica eos in die occisionis.

text: Propterea haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Ecce ego visitabo regem Babylonis et terram ejus, sicut visitavi regem Assur:
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel, omni transmigrationi quam transtuli de Jerusalem in Babylonem:

text: Et respondens Daniel coram rege, ait: Mysterium, quod rex interrogat, sapientes, magi, arioli, et aruspices nequeunt indicare regi:
verse_text: Est vir in regno tuo, qui spiritum deorum sanctorum habet in se, et in diebus patris tui scientia et sapientia inventae sunt in eo: nam et rex Nabuchodonosor pater tuus principem magorum, incantatorum, Chaldaeorum, et aruspicum constituit eum, pater, inquam, tuus, o rex:

text: Her voice shall sound like brass, for they shall hasten with an army, and with axes they shall come against her, as hewers of wood.
verse_text: They shall lay hold on arrow and shield: they are cruel, and will have no mercy. Their voice shall roar like the sea: and they shall mount upon horses, prepared as men for war, against thee, O daughter of Sion.

text: And the thing was knowen to Mordecai, who told it vnto Esther the Queene, and Esther certified the king thereof, in Mordecais name.
verse_text: Then called Esther for Hatach, one of the kings chamberlaines, whom he had appointed to attend vpon her, and gaue him a commaundement to Mordecai, to know what it was, and why it was.

text: Thou dist staine thy honour, and pollute thy seed, so that thou broughtest wrath vpon thy children, and wast grieued for thy folly.
verse_text: Collegisti quasi auricalcum aurum, et ut plumbum complesti argentum:

text: Dum confringuntur ossa mea, exprobraverunt mihi qui tribulant me inimici mei, dum dicunt mihi per singulos dies: Ubi est Deus tuus?
verse_text: Tota die exprobrabant mihi inimici mei, et qui laudabant me adversum me jurabant:

text: And I will visit them that dwell in the land of Egypt, as I have visited Jerusalem by the sword, and by famine, and by pestilence.
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord of hosts: Behold I will visit upon them: and their young men shall die by the sword, their sons and their daughters shall die by famine.

text: Thus sayth the Lord, Take heede to your soules, and beare no burden in the Sabbath day, nor bring it in by the gates of Ierusalem.
verse_text: And it shall come to passe, if yee diligently hearken vnto me, saith the Lord, to bring in no burden through the gates of this citie on the Sabbath day, but hallow the Sabbath day, to doe no worke therein:

text: Quid gloriaris in vallibus? defluxit vallis tua, filia delicata, quae confidebas in thesauris tuis, et dicebas: Quis veniet ad me?
verse_text: Quae sedes in Libano, et nidificas in cedris, quomodo congemuisti cum venissent tibi dolores, quasi dolores parturientis?

text: Let not them that are mine enemies wrongfully, reioyce ouer me: neither let them winke with the eye, that hate me without a cause.
verse_text: They are multiplied aboue the heares of my head, that hate me without cause. Mine enimies are made strong, that haue persecuted me vniustly: then did I pay the thinges that I tooke not.

text: Then came in all the kings wise men, but they could not reade the writing, nor make knowen to the king the interpretation thereof.
verse_text: And now there haue come into my sight the wise magicians, that they might read this writing, and might shew me the interpretation therof: and they could not declare me the sense of this word.

text: They haue denied the Lord, and saide, It is not he, neither shall the plague come vpon vs, neither shall we see sworde nor famine.
verse_text: Then said I Ah Lord God, behold, the prophets say vnto them; Ye shall not see the sword, neither shall ye haue famine, but I will giue you assured peace in this place.

text: Behold the gibbet which he hath prepared for Mardochai, who spoke for the king, standeth in Aman's house, being fifty cubits high.
verse_text: So Aman was hanged on the gibbet, which he had prepared for Mardochai:

text: Quia haec dicit Dominus super domum regis Juda: Galaad, tu mihi caput Libani, si non posuero te solitudinem, urbes inhabitabiles !
verse_text: adulteria tua, et hinnitus tuus, scelus fornicationis tuae: super colles in agro vidi abominationes tuas. Vae tibi, Jerusalem ! non mundaberis post me: usquequo adhuc?

text: Let all them, that seeke thee, reioyce and be glad in thee: and let them, that loue thy saluation, say alway, The Lord be praysed.
verse_text: And let all them that trust in thee, reioyce and triumph for euer, and couer thou them: and let them, that loue thy Name, reioyce in thee.

text: Yet the children of men are vanitie, the chiefe men are lies: to lay them vpon a balance they are altogether lighter then vanitie.
verse_text: But yet the children of men are vaine, the children of men are liers in balances: that they may deceiue by vanitie together.

text: Susceperuntque Judaei in solemnem ritum cuncta quae eo tempore facere coeperant, et quae Mardochaeus litteris facienda mandaverat.
verse_text: Scripsit itaque Mardochaeus omnia haec, et litteris comprehensa misit ad Judaeos qui in omnibus regis provinciis morabantur, tam in vicino positis, quam procul,

text: That I may see the good of thy chosen, that I may reioyce in the gladnesse of thy nation: that I may glory with thine inheritance.
verse_text: That I may shew foorth all thy prayse in the gates of the daughter of Sion: I will reioyce in thy saluation.

text: My children, keep discipline in peace: for wisdom that is hid, and a treasure that is not seen, what profit is there in them both?
verse_text: In the treasures of wisdom is understanding, and religiousness of knowledge: but to sinners wisdom is an abomination.

text: And all this land shall be a desolation, and an astonishment: and all these nations shall serve the king of Babylon seventy years.
verse_text: And when the seventy years shall be expired, I will punish the king of Babylon, and that nation, saith the Lord, for their iniquity, and the land of the Chaldeans: and I will make it perpetual desolations.

text: The voice thereof shall goe like a serpent, for they shall march with an armie, and come against her with axes, as hewers of wood.
verse_text: They shall holde the bowe and the buckeler: they are cruell and vnmercifull: their voyce shall roare like the sea, and they shall ride vpon horses, and be put in aray like men to the battell against thee, O daughter of Babel.

text: But I will deliuer thee in that day, sayth the Lord, and thou shalt not be giuen into the hand of the men of whom thou art afraid.
verse_text: Feare not for the King of Babel, of whom ye are afraide: be not afraid of him, saith the Lord: for I am with you, to saue you, and to deliuer you from his hand,

text: Et non audivit Johanan filius Caree, et omnes principes bellatorum, et universus populus, vocem Domini, ut manerent in terra Juda.
verse_text: Cumque vidisset omnis populus qui erat cum Ismahel Johanan filium Caree, et universos principes bellatorum qui erant cum eo, laetati sunt:

text: In the beginning of the reigne of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah came this worde vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, saying,
verse_text: The worde which came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, in the dayes of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, saying,

text: The Lord tooke away his sinnes, and exalted his horne for euer: he gaue him a couenant of kings, and a throne of glory in Israel.
verse_text: et stare fecit cantores contra altare, et in sono eorum dulces fecit modos.

text: For by one that hath vnderstanding, shall the city be replenished, but the kindred of the wicked, shall speedily become desolate.
verse_text: et utile est mori sine filiis, quam relinquere filios impios.

text: So Ieremiah wrote in a booke all the euill that should come vpon Babylon: euen all these wordes that are written against Babylon.
verse_text: And I will bring vpon that lande all my wordes which I haue pronounced against it, euen all that is written in this booke, which Ieremiah hath prophecied against all nations.

text: Therefore her yong men shal fall in her streets, and all the men of warre shall bee cut off in that day, saith the Lord of hosts.
verse_text: Therefore shall her young men fall in her streets: and all her men of war shall hold their peace in that day, saith the Lord.

text: Now know I that the Lord will helpe his anointed, and will heare him from his Sanctuarie, by the mightie helpe of his right hand.
verse_text: Then didst thou speake in vision to thy saintes, and saidst I haue put helpe on the mightie one: and haue exalted an elect one of my people.

text: Et morientur grandes et parvi in terra ista: non sepelientur, neque plangentur, et non se incident, neque calvitium fiet pro eis.
verse_text: Mortibus aegrotationum morientur: non plangentur, et non sepelientur: in sterquilinium super faciem terrae erunt, et gladio et fame consumentur: et erit cadaver eorum in escam volatilibus caeli et bestiis terrae.

text: Wait on the Lord, and keepe his way, and he shall exalt thee to inherit the land: when the wicked are cut off, thou shalt see it.
verse_text: Trust in the Lord, and do good, so shalt thou dwell in the land, and verely thou shalt be fed.

text: And he was cast out from the sonnes of men, yea and his hart was set with the beasts, and with the wild asses was his habitation:
verse_text: And they shall driue thee from men, and thy dwelling shall be with the beasts of the field;

text: Moreouer the buckgoate, is the king of the Graecians, and the greate horne, that was betwen his eyes, the same is the first king.
verse_text: And he shal rule ouer the treasures of gold, and of siluer, and in al the precious thinges of AEgypt: through Lybia also, and AEthyopia he shal passe.

text: They that feare the Lord, will seeke that which is well pleasing vnto him, and they that loue him, shall bee filled with the Law.
verse_text: Vae his qui perdiderunt sustinentiam, et qui dereliquerunt vias rectas, et diverterunt in vias pravas !

text: And I will send thee, and thy mother that bore thee, into a strange country, in which you were not born, and there you shall die:
verse_text: But thou, Phassur, and all that dwell in thy house, shall go into captivity, and thou shalt go to Babylon, and there thou shalt die, and there thou shalt be buried, thou and all thy friends, to whom thou hast prophesied a lie.

text: God be Iudge betweene vs and you: for you haue done vs great iniury in that you haue not required peace of the children of Assur.
verse_text: Forsitan enim indignationem suam abscindet, et dabit gloriam nomini suo.

text: Now therefore my seruants shall bring thee backe into the hill countrey, and shall set thee in one of the cities of the passages.
verse_text: Tunc Holofernes praecepit servis suis ut comprehenderent Achior, et perducerent eum in Bethuliam, et traderent eum in manus filiorum Israel.

text: But let all those that seeke thee, be ioyfull and glad in thee, and let all that loue thy saluation, say alwaies, God be praised.
verse_text: Let al that seeke thee, reioyce and be glad vpon thee: and let them that loue thy saluation, say alwayes: Our Lord be magnified:

text: And this whole land shall be a desolation, and an astonishment, and these nations shal serue the king of Babylon seuentie yeeres.
verse_text: And the land shall tremble and sorrow: for euery purpose of the Lord shalbe performed against Babylon, to make the land of Babylon a desolation without an inhabitant.

text: The word that the Lord spake, concerning Babel, and cocerning the land of the Caldeans by the ministerie of Ieremiah the Prophet.
verse_text: The wordes of the Lord that came to Ieremiah the Prophet, against the Philistims, before that Pharaoh smote Azzah.

text: Vpon one day in all the prouinces of King Ahashuerosh, euen in the thirteenth day of the twelft moneth, which is the moneth Adar.
verse_text: So Ester was taken vnto King Ahashuerosh into his house royall in the tenth moneth, which is the moneth Tebeth, in the seuenth yeere of his reigne.

text: Now know I, that the Lord saueth his Anointed: he wil heare him from his holy heauen, with the sauing strength of his right hand.
verse_text: The Lord wil perfit that which concerneth me: thy mercie, O Lord, endureth for euer: forsake not the works of thine owne hands.

text: Omnia ossa mea dicent: Domine, quis similis tibi? eripiens inopem de manu fortiorum ejus; egenum et pauperem a diripientibus eum.
verse_text: eripe me, et erue me de manu filiorum alienorum, quorum os locutum est vanitatem, et dextera eorum dextera iniquitatis.

text: And Olofernes tooke great delight in her, & dranke much more wine, then he had drunke at any time in one day, since he was borne.
verse_text: Et jucundus factus est Holofernes ad eam, bibitque vinum multum nimis, quantum numquam biberat in vita sua.

text: Remember not against vs the former iniquities, but make haste and let thy tender mercies preuent vs: for we are in great miserie.
verse_text: Remember not the sinnes of my youth, nor my rebellions, but according to thy kindenesse remember thou me, euen for thy goodnesse sake, O Lord.

text: Exsurge, Domine, in ira tua, et exaltare in finibus inimicorum meorum: et exsurge, Domine Deus meus, in praecepto quod mandasti,
verse_text: Exsurge in occursum meum, et vide: et tu, Domine Deus virtutum, Deus Israel, intende ad visitandas omnes gentes: non miserearis omnibus qui operantur iniquitatem.

text: Miserere mei, Deus, miserere mei, quoniam in te confidit anima mea. Et in umbra alarum tuarum sperabo, donec transeat iniquitas.
verse_text: Quare tristis es, anima mea? et quare conturbas me? Spera in Deo, quoniam adhuc confitebor illi, salutare vultus mei,

text: Qui cum venissent ad medium civitatis, interfecit eos Ismahel filius Nathaniae circa medium laci, ipse et viri qui erant cum eo.
verse_text: Cumque vidisset omnis populus qui erat cum Ismahel Johanan filium Caree, et universos principes bellatorum qui erant cum eo, laetati sunt:

text: And the Lord said: Because they have forsaken my law, which I gave them, and have not heard my voice, and have not walked in it.
verse_text: Thou shalt say to them: Because your fathers forsook me, saith the Lord: and went after strange gods, and served them, and adored them: and they forsook me, and kept not my law.

text: Accitoque Athach eunucho, quem rex ministrum ei dederat, praecepit ei ut iret ad Mardochaeum, et disceret ab eo cur hoc faceret.
verse_text: Exemplar quoque edicti, quod pendebat in Susan, dedit ei, ut reginae ostenderet, et moneret eam ut intraret ad regem et deprecaretur eum pro populo suo.

text: And all the armie of the Caldeans that were with the captaine of the guard, brake downe all the walles of Ierusalem round about.
verse_text: And the Caldeans burnt the kings house, and the houses of the people with fire, and brake downe the wals of Ierusalem.

text: Let the enemie persecute my soule, and take it, yea let him tread downe my life vpon the earth, and lay mine honour in the dust.
verse_text: For the enemie hath persecuted my soule, he hath smitten my life downe to the ground:

text: Thus saith the Lord of hostes the God of Israel; Amend your wayes, and your doings, and I will cause you to dwell in this place.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord of hostes, the God of Israel, Goe, and tell the men of Iudah, and the inhabitants of Ierusalem, Will ye not receiue doctrine to obey my wordes, saith the Lord?

text: My children, keepe discipline in peace: for wisedome that is hid, and a treasure that is not seene, what profit is in them both?
verse_text: Wisdom that is hid, and treasure that is not seen: what profit is there in them both?

text: But in the second day Holofernes brought foorth all his horsemen, in the sight of the children of Israel which were in Bethulia,
verse_text: Then Olofernes went foorth from the presence of his Lord, and called all the gouernours and Captaines, and the officers of the army of Assur.

text: A Psalme to give instruction committed to Asaph. Heare my doctrine, O my people: incline your eares vnto the wordes of my mouth.
verse_text: To him that excelleth on Shoshannim a song of love to give instruction, committed to the sonnes of Korah. Mine heart will vtter forth a good matter: I wil intreat in my workes of the King: my tongue is as the pen of a swift writer.

text: Damascus is undone, she is put to flight, trembling hath seized on her: anguish and sorrows have taken her as a woman in labour.
verse_text: Kerioth is taken, and the strong holds are surprised, & the mighty mens hearts in Moab at that day shall be as the heart of a woman in her pangs.

text: The feare of the Lord is all wisedome, and in all wisedome is the performance of the Law, and the knowledge of his omnipotencie.
verse_text: Est nequitia, et in ipsa execratio, et est insipiens qui minuitur sapientia.

text: Therefore behold the days come, saith the Lord, and I will visit her graven things, and in all her land the wounded shall groan:
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord: Behold I will judge thy cause, and will take vengeance for thee, and I will make her sea desolate, and will dry up her spring.

text: I have put a yoke of iron upon the neck of all these nations, to serve Nabuchodonosor king of Babylon, and they shall serve him:
verse_text: Even so will I break the yoke of Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon after two full years from off the neck of all the nations.

text: The heart of a man changeth his countenance, whether it be for good or euill: and a merry heart maketh a cheerefull countenance.
verse_text: Dives commotus confirmatur ab amicis suis: humilis autem cum ceciderit, expelletur et a notis.

text: Oratio David. Exaudi, Domine, justitiam meam; intende deprecationem meam. Auribus percipe orationem meam, non in labiis dolosis.
verse_text: Auribus percipe, Domine, orationem meam, et intende voci deprecationis meae.

text: Propterea haec dicit Dominus: Ecce ego tradam civitatem istam in manus Chaldaeorum, et in manus regis Babylonis, et capient eam.
verse_text: Clauserat enim eum Sedecias rex Juda, dicens: Quare vaticinaris, dicens: Haec dicit Dominus: Ecce ego dabo civitatem istam in manus regis Babylonis, et capiet eam:

text: quia haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel, ad vasa quae derelicta sunt in domo Domini, et in domo regis Juda et Jerusalem:
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus Deus Israel: Ecce ego convertam vasa belli quae in manibus vestris sunt, et quibus vos pugnatis adversum regem Babylonis et Chaldaeos qui obsident vos in circuitu murorum: et congregabo ea in medio civitatis hujus.

text: A drought is vpon her waters, and they shall be dried vp: for it is the lande of grauen images, and they dote vpon their idoles.
verse_text: A drought upon her waters, and they shall be dried up: because it is a land of idols, and they glory in monstrous things.

text: In the day of thine affliction it shall be remembred, thy sinnes also shal melt away, as the yce in þ faire warme weather.
verse_text: et si defecerit sensu, veniam da, et ne spernas eum in virtute tua: eleemosyna enim patris non erit in oblivione.

text: As for a wound it may be bound vp, and after reuiling there may be reconcilement: but he that bewrayeth secrets is without hope.
verse_text: Et sicut qui dimittit avem de manu sua, sic dereliquisti proximum tuum, et non eum capies.

text: Therefore hath the Lord recompensed me according to my righteousnesse, according to the cleannesse of my hands in his eye-sight.
verse_text: The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousnesse, according to the cleannesse of my hands hath hee recompensed me.

text: Nos autem a pessimo mortalium Judaeos neci destinatos, in nulla penitus culpa reperimus, sed e contrario justis utentes legibus,
verse_text: Quod cum didicissemus, videntes unam gentem rebellem adversus omne hominum genus perversis uti legibus, nostrisque jussionibus contraire, et turbare subjectarum nobis provinciarum pacem atque concordiam,

text: et tenentes legem nescierunt me, et pastores praevaricati sunt in me, et prophetae prophetaverunt in Baal, et idola secuti sunt.
verse_text: eo quod dereliquerint me, et alienum fecerint locum istum, et libaverunt in eo diis alienis quos nescierunt, ipsi et patres eorum, et reges Juda:

text: If it doe euill in my sight, that it obey not my voice, then I will repent of the good; wherewith I saide I would benefite them.
verse_text: But if this nation, against whom I haue pronounced, turne from their wickednesse, I will repent of the plague that I thought to bring vpon them.

text: Melior est homo qui minuitur sapientia, et deficiens sensu, in timore, quam qui abundat sensu, et transgreditur legem Altissimi.
verse_text: Melior est qui celat insipientiam suam, quam homo qui abscondit sapientiam suam.

text: But in the second day Holofernes brought foorth all his horsemen, in the sight of the children of Israel which were in Bethulia,
verse_text: Porro Holofernes, dum circuit per gyrum, reperit quod fons qui influebat, aquaeductum illorum a parte australi extra civitatem dirigeret: et incidi praecepit aquaeductum illorum.

text: Then tooke they Ieremiah, and cast him into the dungeon of Malchiah the sonne of Hammelech, that was in the court of the prison:
verse_text: Euen they sent, and tooke Ieremiah out of the court of the prison, and committed him vnto Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the sonne of Shaphan, that hee should carie him home:

text: My children, keepe discipline in peace: for wisedome that is hid, and a treasure that is not seene, what profit is in them both?
verse_text: Luctus hominum in corpore ipsorum: nomen autem impiorum delebitur.

text: quoniam a Deo profecta est sapientia. Sapientiae enim Dei astabit laus, et in ore fideli abundabit, et Dominator dabit eam illi.
verse_text: Timenti Dominum non occurrent mala: sed in tentatione Deus illum conservabit, et liberabit a malis. Sapiens non odit mandata et justitias,

text: Therefore her young men shall fall in her streets: and all the men of war shall be silent in that day, saith the Lord of hosts.
verse_text: Therefore shall her yong men fall in the streetes, and al her men of warre shalbe destroied in that day, sayeth the Lord.

text: And when she came out, shee besought the Lord God of Israel to direct her way, to the raising vp of the children of her people.
verse_text: Et ut ascendebat, orabat Dominum Deum Israel ut dirigeret viam ejus ad liberationem populi sui.

text: A Psalme of Dauid. Pleade thou my cause, O Lord, with them that striue with me: fight thou against them, that fight against me.
verse_text: Deliuer me from mine enemies, O my God: defend mee from them that rise vp against me.

text: A sworde is vpon the Caldeans, sayeth the Lord, and vpon the inhabitants of Babel, and vpon her princes, and vpon her wise men.
verse_text: Therefore behold, the dayes come, that I will doe iudgment vpon the grauen images of Babylon, and her whole land shall bee confounded, and all her slaine shall fall in the midst of her.

text: Who will set a guard before my mouth, and a sure seal upon my lips, that I fall not by them, and that my tongue destroy me not?
verse_text: Who will set scourges over my thoughts, and the discipline of wisdom over my heart, that they spare me not in their ignorances, and that their sins may not appear:

text: Moreouer Iohanan the sonne of Kareah, and all the captaines of the hoste, that were in the fieldes, came to Gedaliah to Mizpah,
verse_text: But in the seuenth moneth came Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah, the sonne of Elishama of the seede royall, and the princes of the King, and tenne men with him, vnto Gedaliah the sonne of Ahikam to Mizpah, and there they did eate bread together in Mizpah.

text: The sinnes of my youth, and my ignorances doe not remember. According to thy mercie remember thou me: for thy goodnesse o Lord.
verse_text: But I, my prayer to thee o Lord: a time of thy good pleasure o God. In the multitude of thy mercie heare me, in the truth of thy saluation:

text: And I will cast thee out, and thy mother that bare thee, into another countrey where ye were not borne, and there shall ye die.
verse_text: Therefore will I cast you out of this land into a land that yee knowe not, neither yee, nor your fathers, and there shall yee serue other Gods day and night, where I will not shewe you fauour.

text: Hee that telleth a tale to a foole, speaketh to one in a slumber: when hee hath told his tale, he will say, What is the matter?
verse_text: Qui narrat verbum non audienti, quasi qui excitat dormientem de gravi somno.

text: As we haue heard, so haue wee seene in the citie of the Lord of hosts, in the citie of our God, God will establish it for euer.
verse_text: As we haue heard, so haue we seene in the citie of the Lord of hostes, in the Citie of our God:

text: Constat enim Deum nostrum sic peccatis offensum, ut mandaverit per prophetas suos ad populum quod tradat eum pro peccatis suis.
verse_text: et quemadmodum ipse Holofernes iratus jusserit eum Israelitis hac de causa tradi, ut dum vicerit filios Israel, tunc et ipsum Achior diversis jubeat interire suppliciis, propter hoc quod dixisset: Deus caeli defensor eorum est.

text: Beware of a counseller, and know before what neede he hath (for he will counsell for himselfe) lest hee cast the lot vpon thee:
verse_text: Omnis consiliarius prodit consilium, sed est consiliarius in semetipso.

text: The most high is not pleased with the offerings of the wicked, neither is he pacified for sinne by the multitude of sacrifices.
verse_text: Oculi Domini super timentes eum: protector potentiae, firmamentum virtutis, tegimen ardoris, et umbraculum meridiani:

text: Behold, the dayes come, saith the Lord, that I will make a newe couenant with the house of Israel, and with the house of Iudah.
verse_text: Beholde, the dayes come, sayth the Lord, that I wil performe that good thing, which I haue promised vnto the house of Israel, and to the house of Iudah.

text: Then tooke they Ieremiah, and cast him into the dungeon of Malchiah the sonne of Hammelech that was in the court of the prison:
verse_text: Euen they sent, and tooke Ieremiah out of the court of the prison, and committed him vnto Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the sonne of Shaphan, that hee should carie him home:

text: Saue vs, O Lord our God, and gather vs from among the heathen to giue thankes vnto thy holy Name: and to triumph in thy praise.
verse_text: Saue vs o Lord our God: and geather vs out of the Nations: That we may confesse to thy holie name: & may glorie in thy prayse.

text: Rursum tolle volumen aliud, et scribe in eo omnes sermones priores qui erant in primo volumine, quod combussit Joakim rex Juda.
verse_text: Cumque legisset Judi tres pagellas vel quatuor, scidit illud scalpello scribae, et projecit in ignem qui erat super arulam, donec consumeretur omne volumen igni qui erat in arula.

text: Let the enemie persecute my soule, and take it, and treade downe my life in the earth, and bring downe my glorie into the dust.
verse_text: For the enemie hath persecuted my soule, he hath smitten my life downe to the ground: hee hath made mee to dwell in darkenesse, as those that haue bene long dead.

text: And the Kings power, that loueth iudgement: for thou hast prepared equitie: thou hast executed iudgement and iustice in Iaakob.
verse_text: Let nations be glad & reioice: because thou iudgest peoples in equitie, and the nations in earth thou doest direct.

text: Because manie dogges haue compassed me: the counsel of the malignant hath besieged me. They haue digged my handes and my feete:
verse_text: The sorrowes of death haue compassed me: and torrentes of iniquitie haue trubled me.

text: He is my goodnes and my fortresse, my towre and my deliuerer, my shield, and in him I trust, which subdueth my people vnder me.
verse_text: The Lord is my rocke, and my fortresse, and he that deliuereth me, my God and my strength: in him will I trust, my shield, the horne also of my saluation, and my refuge.

text: If thou giuest thy soule the desires that please her, she will make thee a laughing stocke to thine enemies, that maligne thee.
verse_text: Si praestes animae tuae concupiscentias ejus, faciat te in gaudium inimicis tuis.

text: Let al that seeke thee reioyce, and be glad in thee, and let them say alwayes: Our Lord be magnified: which loue thy saluation.
verse_text: Let all those that seeke thee, reioyce, and be glad in thee: and let such as loue thy saluation, say continually, Let God be magnified.

text: The word that the Lord spake to Ieremiah the Prophet, how Nebuchadrezzar King of Babylon should come & smite the land of Egypt.
verse_text: The word of the Lord that came to Ieremiah the Prophet against the Philistines, before that Pharaoh smote Gaza.

text: Behold their pride, and send thy wrath vpon their heads: giue into mine hand which am a widow, the power that I haue conceiued.
verse_text: Sic fiant et isti, Domine, qui confidunt in multitudine sua, et in curribus suis, et in contis, et in scutis, et in sagittis suis, et in lanceis gloriantur,

text: The Lord wil perfit that which concerneth me: thy mercie, O Lord, endureth for euer: forsake not the works of thine owne hands.
verse_text: Thy good spirite wil conduct me into the right way: for thy name sake o Lord thou wilt quicken me, in thine equitie.

text: Obserue and take good heed, for thou walkest in peril of thy ouerthrowing: when thou hearest these things, awake in thy sleepe.
verse_text: Ne improbus sis, ne impingaris: et ne longe sis ab eo, ne eas in oblivionem.

text: And with thee will I breake in pieces the horse and his rider, and with thee will I breake in pieces the charet, and his rider;
verse_text: Thou art my battel-axe and weapons of warre: for with thee will I breake in pieces the nations, and with thee will I destroy kingdomes;

text: quia peccatores peribunt. Inimici vero Domini mox ut honorificati fuerint et exaltati, deficientes quemadmodum fumus deficient.
verse_text: Ipsi peribunt, tu autem permanes; et omnes sicut vestimentum veterascent. Et sicut opertorium mutabis eos, et mutabuntur;

text: Ego autem, cum mihi molesti essent, induebar cilicio; humiliabam in jejunio animam meam, et oratio mea in sinu meo convertetur.
verse_text: Si non humiliter sentiebam, sed exaltavi animam meam: sicut ablactatus est super matre sua, ita retributio in anima mea.

text: He set singers also before the Altar, that by their voyces they might make sweet melody, and daily sing praises in their songs.
verse_text: In omni opere dedit confessionem Sancto, et Excelso in verbo gloriae.

text: The works of the Lord are done in iudgement from the beginning: and from the time he made them, hee disposed the parts thereof.
verse_text: In judicio Dei opera ejus ab initio, et ab institutione ipsorum distinxit partes illorum, et initia eorum in gentibus suis.

text: And the King of the South shall be moued with choler, and shall come forth and fight with him, euen with the King of the North:
verse_text: Also he shall stirre vp his power and his courage against the King of the South with a great armie, and the King of the South shall be stirred vp to battell with a very great and mightie armie:

text: Before the Lord: for he is come to iudge the earth: with righteousnesse shall hee iudge the world, and the people with equitie.
verse_text: And hee shall iudge the world in righteousnesse; he shall minister iudgement to the people in vprightnesse.

text: And the cisternes were emptied, and they had not water to drinke their fill, for one day; for they gaue them drinke by measure.
verse_text: ut non dicant inter gentes: Ubi est Deus eorum?

text: The word of the Lord which came to him in the days of Josias the son of Amon king of Juda, in the thirteenth year of his reign.
verse_text: The word of the Lord that came to Jeremias the prophet against Elam, in the beginning of the reign of Sedecias king of Juda, saying:

text: And there shall be none that shall escape, and remain of the remnant of the Jews that are gone to sojourn in the land of Egypt:
verse_text: And a few men that shall flee from the sword, shall return out of the land of Egypt into the land of Juda:

text: Psalmus ipsi David. Cantate Domino canticum novum, quia mirabilia fecit. Salvavit sibi dextera ejus, et brachium sanctum ejus.
verse_text: Laus cantici ipsi David, in die ante sabbatum, quando fundata est terra. Dominus regnavit, decorem indutus est: indutus est Dominus fortitudinem, et praecinxit se. Etenim firmavit orbem terrae, qui non commovebitur.

text: Whiles my bones are broken, mine enemies that truble me haue vpbrayded me: Whiles they say to me day by day: Where is thy God?
verse_text: Mine enemies reproch me all the day: and they that are mad against me, are sworne against me.

text: He that honoureth his father, shal haue a long life, and he that is obedient vnto the Lord, shall bee a comfort to his mother.
verse_text: He that honoureth his father shall have joy in his own children, and in the day of his prayer he shall be heard.

text: Set vp the standart in Zion: prepare to flee, and stay not: for I will bring a plague from the North, and a great destruction.
verse_text: Set ye vp a standart in the land, blow the trumpet among the nations: prepare the nations against her: call together against her the kingdomes of Ararat, Minni, & Ashchenaz: appoint a captaine against her: cause her horses to come vp as the rough caterpillers.

text: In God I wil praise the word, in our Lord wil I praise thee sayng, I haue hoped in God, I wil not feare what man can do to me.
verse_text: Our Lord is my helper, and my protectour: in him my hart hath hoped, and I was holpen. And my flesh florished againe: and with my wil I wil confesse to him.

text: And there was none that made the children of Israel any more afraide, in the dayes of Iudeth, nor a long time after her death.
verse_text: Post dies autem illos, unusquisque rediit in domum suam: et Judith magna facta est in Bethulia, et praeclarior erat universae terrae Israel.

text: Prepare the nations against her, the kings of Media, their captains, and all their rulers, and all the land of their dominion.
verse_text: And all the kings of the north far and near, every one against his brother: and all the kingdoms of the earth, which are upon the face thereof: and the king of Sesac shall drink after them.

text: For loe, the dayes come, saith the Lord, that I wil bring againe the captiuitie of my people Israel and Iudah, saith the Lord:
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord, Behold, I will bring againe the captiuitie of Iacobs tents, and haue mercie on his dwelling places:

text: And I heard the voice of a man betwen the bankes of Clai: and he cried, and sayd: Gabriel make this man vnderstand the vision.
verse_text: And he said to me: Daniel thou man of desires, vnderstand the wordes, that I speake to thee, and stand in thy place: for now am I sent to thee. And when he had said this word to me, I stood trembling.

text: A Psalme of David. Heare my prayer, O Lord, and hearken vnto my supplication: answer me in thy trueth and in thy righteousnes.
verse_text: TAV. Let my complaint come before thee, O Lord, and giue me vnderstanding, according vnto thy worde.

text: Et audivit Phassur filius Emmer, sacerdos, qui constitutus erat princeps in domo Domini, Jeremiam prophetantem sermones istos.
verse_text: Vocavit ergo Jeremias Baruch filium Neriae: et scripsit Baruch ex ore Jeremiae omnes sermones Domini quos locutus est ad eum, in volumine libri:

text: Ye that haue escaped the sword, go away, stand not still: remember the Lord afarre off: and let Ierusalem come into your mind.
verse_text: Put your selues in aray against Babylon round about: all ye that bend the bow, shoot at her; spare no arrows: for she hath sinned against the Lord,

text: Vox auditionis ecce venit, et commotio magna de terra aquilonis: ut ponat civitates Juda solitudinem, et habitaculum draconum.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum: Ecce afflictio egredietur de gente in gentem, et turbo magnus egredietur a summitatibus terrae.

text: Be vnto me for a God protector, and for a fensed place: that thou maist saue me. Because thou art my firmament, and my refuge.
verse_text: Be thou my strong rocke, whereunto I may alway resort: thou hast giuen commandement to saue me: for thou art my rocke, and my fortresse.

text: Therefore all the princes sent Iehudi the sonne of Nethaniah, the sonne of Shelemiah, the sonne of Cushi, vnto Baruch, saying;
verse_text: But the king commaunded Ierahmeel the sonne of Hammelech, and Seraiah the sonne of Azriel, & Shelennah the sonne of Abdiel, to take Baruch the scribe, and Ieremiah the Prophet:

text: They answered againe, and sayde, Let the King shewe his seruantes the dreame, and wee will declare the interpretation thereof.
verse_text: Then came in the Magicians, the Astrologers, the Caldeans, and the Southsayers: and I tolde the dreame before them; but they did not make knowen vnto mee the interpretation thereof.

text: Domine, Dominus noster, quam admirabile est nomen tuum in universa terra ! quoniam elevata est magnificentia tua super caelos.
verse_text: Quam magnificata sunt opera tua, Domine ! omnia in sapientia fecisti; impleta est terra possessione tua.

text: Dixit autem eis Baruch: Ex ore suo loquebatur quasi legens ad me omnes sermones istos, et ego scribebam in volumine atramento.
verse_text: Dixit autem ad eos Jeremias propheta: Audivi. Ecce ego oro ad Dominum Deum vestrum secundum verba vestra: omne verbum quodcumque responderit mihi indicabo vobis, nec celabo vos quidquam.

text: And hee was driuen from the sonnes of men, and his heart was made like the beastes, and his dwelling was with the wilde asses:
verse_text: That they shall driue thee from men, and thy dwelling shalbe with the beasts of the fielde:

text: Our Lord hath looked forth from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there be that vnderstandeth, and seeketh after God.
verse_text: God looked downe from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there were any that did vnderstand, that did seeke God.

text: Say not, I haue sinned, and what harme hath happened vnto mee? for the Lord is long suffering, he wil in no wise let thee goe.
verse_text: Ne dixeris: Peccavi: et quid mihi accidit triste? Altissimus enim est patiens redditor.

text: And hee will recompence them their wickednes, and destroy them in their owne malice: yea, the Lord our God shall destroy them.
verse_text: Destroy thou them, O God, let them fall by their owne counsels: cast them out in the multitude of their transgressions, for they haue rebelled against thee.

text: Verbum quod factum est ad Jeremiam a Domino, in anno decimo Sedeciae regis Juda, ipse est annus decimusoctavus Nabuchodonosor.
verse_text: Quod factum est verbum Domini ad eum in diebus Josiae filii Amon, regis Juda, in tertiodecimo anno regni ejus.

text: Susurro coinquinabit animam suam, et in omnibus odietur, et qui cum eo manserit odiosus erit: tacitus et sensatus honorabitur.
verse_text: Et qui se jungit fornicariis erit nequam: putredo et vermes haereditabunt illum: et extolletur in exemplum majus, et tolletur de numero anima ejus.

text: Moreouer Iohanan the sonne of Kareah, and all the captaines of the forces that were in the fields, came to Gedaliah to Mizpah,
verse_text: But Iohanan the sonne of Kareah, and all the captaines of the forces, tooke all the remnant of Iudah, that were returned from all nations whither they had bene driuen, to dwell in the land of Iudah,

text: He that honoureth his father, shal haue a long life, and he that is obedient vnto the Lord, shall bee a comfort to his mother.
verse_text: Qui honorat patrem suum jucundabitur in filiis, et in die orationis suae exaudietur.

text: Et transibunt domus eorum ad alteros, agri et uxores pariter, quia extendam manum meam super habitantes terram, dicit Dominus:
verse_text: Cumque impleti fuerint septuaginta anni, visitabo super regem Babylonis et super gentem illam, dicit Dominus, iniquitatem eorum, et super terram Chaldaeorum, et ponam illam in solitudines sempiternas.

text: How is Sesach taken, and the renowned one of all the earth surprised? How is Babylon become an astonishment among the nations?
verse_text: How is the hammer of the whole earth broken, and destroyed! how is Babylon turned into a desert among the nations!

text: Remoue out of the midst of Babylon, and goe foorth out of the land of the Caldeans, and be as the hee goats before the flocks.
verse_text: My people, goe ye out of the midst of her, and deliuer ye euery man his soule fr the fierce anger of the Lord,

text: How is Sheshach taken! and howe is the glory of the whole earth taken! how is Babel become an astonishment among the nations!
verse_text: How is it overthrown, and they have howled! How hath Moab bowed down the neck, and is confounded! And Moab shall be a derision, and an example to all round about him.

text: In finem. Psalmus David. Judica me, Domine, quoniam ego in innocentia mea ingressus sum, et in Domino sperans non infirmabor.
verse_text: Intende ad deprecationem meam, quia humiliatus sum nimis. Libera me a persequentibus me, quia confortati sunt super me.

text: For the Lord hath giuen the father honour ouer the children, and hath confirmed the authoritie of the mother ouer the sonnes.
verse_text: Judicium patris audite, filii, et sic facite, ut salvi sitis.

text: Wherefore the princes were angry with Ieremiah, and smote him, and layde him in prison in the house of Iehonathan the scribe:
verse_text: Then tooke they Ieremiah, and cast him into the dungeon of Malchiah the sonne of Hammelech, that was in the court of the prison:

text: If aduersitie come vpon thee, thou shalt find him there first, & though he pretend to helpe thee, yet shal he vndermine thee.
verse_text: Et si incurrerint tibi mala, invenies eum illic priorem.

text: Dixit autem Jeremias ad omnem populum, et ad universas mulieres: Audite verbum Domini, omnis Juda qui estis in terra AEgypti.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Pro eo quod misisti in nomine tuo libros ad omnem populum qui est in Jerusalem, et ad Sophoniam filium Maasiae sacerdotem, et ad universos sacerdotes, dicens:

text: Et agnoscent qui derelicti sunt, quoniam nihil melius est quam timor Dei, et nihil dulcius quam respicere in mandatis Domini.
verse_text: et da locum timori Altissimi: quia omnis sapientia timor Dei, et in illa timere Deum, et in omni sapientia dispositio legis.

text: Hee that is honoured in pouertie, how much more in riches? And he that is dishonourable in riches, how much more in pouertie?
verse_text: Fili, in mansuetudine serva animam tuam, et da illi honorem secundum meritum suum.

text: Ego autem mendicus sum et pauper; Dominus sollicitus est mei. Adjutor meus et protector meus tu es; Deus meus, ne tardaveris.
verse_text: Adjutor meus, tibi psallam, quia Deus susceptor meus es; Deus meus, misericordia mea.

text: Hee that taketh away his neighbours liuing, slayeth him: and hee that defraudeth the labourer of his hire, is a bloodshedder.
verse_text: Dominus solus sustinentibus se in via veritatis et justitiae.

text: Hee that sacrificeth of a thing wrongfully gotten, his offering is ridiculous, and the giftes of vniust men are not accepted.
verse_text: Ad quem respicit, et quis est fortitudo ejus?

text: Quod cum audisset Aman, et experimento probasset quod Mardochaeus non flecteret sibi genu, nec se adoraret, iratus est valde,
verse_text: Et postea ingressa est Esther ad regem, obsecrans ut conatus ejus litteris regis irriti fierent, et malum quod contra Judaeos cogitaverat, reverteretur in caput ejus. Denique et ipsum et filios ejus affixerunt cruci,

text: And I will deliver thee in that day, saith the Lord: and thou shalt not be given into the hands of the men whom thou fearest:
verse_text: And they shall fight against thee, and shall not prevail: for I am with thee, saith the Lord, to deliver thee.

text: Et assumpsi Jezoniam filium Jeremiae filii Habsaniae, et fratres ejus, et omnes filios ejus, et universam domum Rechabitarum,
verse_text: Et captivas duxit Ismahel omnes reliquias populi qui erant in Masphath, filias regis, et universum populum qui remanserat in Masphath, quos commendaverat Nabuzardan princeps militiae, Godoliae filio Ahicam: et cepit eos Ismahel filius Nathaniae, et abiit ut transiret ad filios Ammon.

text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel: Make your ways and your doings good: and I will dwell with you in this place.
verse_text: For this now hear the word of the Lord, ye remnant of Juda: Thus saith the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: If you set your faces to go into Egypt, and enter in to dwell there:

text: Qui interrogationem manifestat parabit verbum, et sic deprecatus exaudietur: et conservabit disciplinam, et tunc respondebit.
verse_text: et ipse diriget consilium ejus, et disciplinam, et in absconditis suis consiliabitur.

text: Thus shall you say every one to his neighbor, and to his brother: What hath the Lord answered? and what hath the Lord spoken?
verse_text: Thus shalt thou say to the prophet: What hath the Lord answered thee? and what hath the Lord spoken?

text: And I will make Ierusalem heapes, and a denne of dragons, and I wil make the cities of Iudah desolate, without an inhabitant.
verse_text: Behold, the noise of the bruit is come, and a great commotion out of the North countrey, to make the cities of Iudah desolate, and a denne of dragons.

text: Let thine hande be vpon the man of thy right hande, and vpon the sonne of man, whome thou madest strong for thine owne selfe.
verse_text: Thou spakest then in a vision vnto thine Holy one, and saydest, I haue layde helpe vpon one that is mightie: I haue exalted one chosen out of the people.

text: Abscondes eos in abscondito faciei tuae a conturbatione hominum; proteges eos in tabernaculo tuo, a contradictione linguarum.
verse_text: Quam magna multitudo dulcedinis tuae, Domine, quam abscondisti timentibus te; perfecisti eis qui sperant in te in conspectu filiorum hominum !

text: A wise man will feare in euery thing, and in the day of sinning he will beware of offence: but a foole will not obserue time.
verse_text: Homo sapiens in omnibus metuet, et in diebus delictorum attendet ab inertia.

text: Therefore shall her young men fall in her streets: and all her men of war shall hold their peace in that day, saith the Lord.
verse_text: Therefore shall her yong men fall in the streetes, and al her men of warre shalbe destroied in that day, sayeth the Lord.

text: I will now remember the works of the Lord, and declare the things that I haue seene: in the words of the Lord are his workes.
verse_text: Memor ero igitur operum Domini, et quae vidi annuntiabo. In sermonibus Domini opera ejus.

text: And hee was driuen from the sonnes of men, and his heart was made like the beasts, and his dwelling was with the wilde asses:
verse_text: And they shall driue thee from men, and thy dwelling shall be with the beasts of the field;

text: Behold I will deliver Pharao Ephree king of Egypt into the hand of his enemies, and into the hand of them that seek his life:
verse_text: And I will give them into the hands of their enemies, and into the hands of them that seek their life:

text: The tree grew, and was strong, and the height thereof reached vnto heauen, and the sight thereof to the end of all the earth.
verse_text: The tree which thou sawest high and strong, whose height reacheth to heauen, and the sight therof into al the earth:

text: Bee not at variance with a rich man, lest he ouerweigh thee: for gold hath destroyed many, and peruerted the hearts of kings.
verse_text: Non contendas cum viro locuplete, ne forte contra te constituat litem tibi:

text: as I delivered Sedecias king of Juda into the hand of Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon his enemy, and that sought his life.
verse_text: Behold I will deliver them up into the hands of Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon:

text: I wil say to God: Thou art my defender. Why hast thou forgotten me? and why goe I sorowful, whiles mine enemie afflicteth me?
verse_text: I wil confesse to thee on the harpe o God my God: why art thou sorowful o my soule? and dost thou trubel me?

text: For they haue healed the hurt of the daughter of my people with sweete woordes, saying, Peace, peace, when there is no peace.
verse_text: And they healed the breach of the daughter of my people disgracefully, saying: Peace, peace: and there was no peace.

text: Posuerunt eam in dissipationem, luxitque super me: desolatione desolata est omnis terra, quia nullus est qui recogitet corde.
