verse_text: Quare factus est dolor meus perpetuus, et plaga mea desperabilis renuit curari? facta est mihi quasi mendacium aquarum infidelium.

text: After this the worde of the Lord came vnto me, saying, Ieremiah, what seest thou? And I said, I see a rod of an almonde tree.
verse_text: And the worde of the Lord came vnto mee the second time, saying; What seest thou? And I said; I see a seething pot, and the face thereof was towards the North.

text: Canticum ipsi David, quando domus aedificabatur post captivitatem. Cantate Domino canticum novum; cantate Domino omnis terra.
verse_text: Canticum graduum. Ecce nunc benedicite Dominum, omnes servi Domini: qui statis in domo Domini, in atriis domus Dei nostri.

text: To him that excelleth on Neginoth. A Psalme or song committed to Asaph. God is knowen in Iudah: his Name is great in Israel.
verse_text: To him that excelleth upon Alamoth a song committed to the sonnes of Korah. God is our hope and strength, and helpe in troubles, ready to be found.

text: Nebuchad-nezzar the king, vnto all people, nations, and languages that dwell in all the earth, Peace be multiplied vnto you.
verse_text: Then Darius the king wrote to al peoples, tribes, and tongues dwelling in the whole earth: PEACE be multiplied vnto you.

text: Miserere mei, Deus, secundum magnam misericordiam tuam; et secundum multitudinem miserationum tuarum, dele iniquitatem meam.
verse_text: Delicta juventutis meae, et ignorantias meas, ne memineris. Secundum misericordiam tuam memento mei tu, propter bonitatem tuam, Domine.

text: et da locum timori Altissimi: quia omnis sapientia timor Dei, et in illa timere Deum, et in omni sapientia dispositio legis.
verse_text: Et agnoscent qui derelicti sunt, quoniam nihil melius est quam timor Dei, et nihil dulcius quam respicere in mandatis Domini.

text: Post dies autem decem, apparuerunt vultus eorum meliores, et corpulentiores prae omnibus pueris, qui vescebantur cibo regio.
verse_text: Et constituit eis rex annonam per singulos dies de cibis suis, et de vino unde bibebat ipse, ut enutriti tribus annis, postea starent in conspectu regis.

text: So they drew vp Ieremiah with cordes, and tooke him vp out of the dungeon, and Ieremiah remained in the court of the prison.
verse_text: Euen they sent, and tooke Ieremiah out of the court of the prison, and committed him vnto Gedaliah the sonne of Ahikam the sonne of Shaphan, that he should cary him home: so he dwelt among the people.

text: Sic homo qui jejunat in peccatis suis, et iterum eadem faciens: quid proficit humiliando se? orationem illius quis exaudiet?
verse_text: Omnis homo qui transgreditur lectum suum, contemnens in animam suam, et dicens: Quis me videt?

text: Erubescant et revereantur simul qui gratulantur malis meis; induantur confusione et reverentia qui magna loquuntur super me.
verse_text: Sed et lingua mea tota die meditabitur justitiam tuam, cum confusi et reveriti fuerint qui quaerunt mala mihi.

text: And Jeremias wrote in one book all the evil that was to come upon Babylon: all these words that are written against Babylon.
verse_text: And I will bring upon the land all my words, that I have spoken against it, all that is written in this book, all that Jeremias hath prophesied against all nations:

text: Is there no balme in Gilead? is there no physician there? why then is not the health of the daughter of my people recouered?
verse_text: Behold the voice of the crie of the daughter of my people because of them that dwel in a farre countrey: Is not the Lord in Zion? is not her king in her? why haue they prouoked me to anger with their grauen images, and with strange vanities?

text: then will I kindle a fire in the gates thereof, and it shall deuoure the palaces of Ierusalem, and it shall not be quenched.
verse_text: and I will kindle a fire in the forrest thereof, and it shall deuoure all things round about it.

text: Hee brought mee also out of the horrible pit, out of the myrie clay, and set my feete vpon the rocke, and ordered my goings.
verse_text: Thou which hast shewed mee great, and sore troubles, shalt quicken mee againe, and shalt bring mee vp againe from the depthes of the earth.

text: Quomodo capta est Sesach, et comprehensa est inclyta universae terrae ! quomodo facta est in stuporem Babylon inter gentes !
verse_text: confusa est mater vestra nimis, et adaequata pulveri, quae genuit vos: ecce novissima erit in gentibus, deserta, invia, et arens.

text: Then saide Iudeth vnto them, Heare me now, my brethren, & take this head, and hang it vpon the highest place of your walles.
verse_text: Dixit autem Judith ad omnem populum: Audite me, fratres: suspendite caput hoc super muros nostros:

text: For thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel: Houses, and fields, and vineyards shall be possessed again in this land.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel: Add your burnt offerings to your sacrifices, and eat ye the flesh.

text: Vpon thee haue I bene confirmed from the wombe: from my mothers bellie thou art my protector. In thee is my singing alwaies:
verse_text: I wil be glad and reioyce in thy mercie: for thou hast seene my trouble: thou hast knowen my soule in aduersities,

text: Now therefore call them vnto you, and deliuer the whole citie for a spoile to the people of Olofernes, and to all his armie.
verse_text: But in the second day Holofernes brought foorth all his horsemen, in the sight of the children of Israel which were in Bethulia,

text: The prayer of Dauid. HEARE o Lord my iustice: attend my petition: With thine eares heare my prayer, not in deceitful lippes.
verse_text: Heare the right, O Lord, attend vnto my crie, giue eare vnto my prayer, that goeth not out of fained lips.

text: Ipsi David. Confitebor tibi, Domine, in toto corde meo, quoniam audisti verba oris mei. In conspectu angelorum psallam tibi;
verse_text: ego autem in misericordia tua speravi. Exsultabit cor meum in salutari tuo. Cantabo Domino qui bona tribuit mihi; et psallam nomini Domini altissimi.

text: And hee that requiteth good turnes, is mindfull of that which may come heereafter: and when he falleth he shall find a stay.
verse_text: Cor sapientis intelligitur in sapientia, et auris bona audiet cum omni concupiscentia sapientiam.

text: Et erit universa terra haec in solitudinem, et in stuporem: et servient omnes gentes istae regi Babylonis septuaginta annis.
verse_text: Et laudabunt super Babylonem caeli et terra, et omnia quae in eis sunt: quia ab aquilone venient ei praedones, ait Dominus.

text: So they drewe vp Ieremiah with coards and tooke him vp out of the dungeon, and Ieremiah remained in the court of the prison.
verse_text: Then tooke they Ieremiah, and cast him into the dungeon of Malchiah the sonne of Hammelech, that was in the court of the prison: and they let downe Ieremiah with coards: and in the dungeon there was no water but myre: so Ieremiah stacke fast in the myre.

text: But they would not heare nor incline their eare to turne from their wickednes, and to burne no more incense vnto other gods.
verse_text: But they obeyed not, neither inclined their eare, but made their necke stiffe, that they might not heare nor receiue instruction.

text: Hee should haue fedde them also with the finest of the wheat: and with honie out of the rocke, should I haue satisfied thee.
verse_text: And he fedde them of the fatte of corne: and out of the rocke, with honie he filled them.

text: Then saide Ester, If it please the King, let the King and Haman come this day vnto the banket, that I haue prepared for him.
verse_text: And the King sayd, Cause Haman to make haste that he may doe as Ester hath sayde. So the King and Haman came to the banket that Ester had prepared.

text: Quod Mardochaeum non latuit, statimque nuntiavit reginae Esther: et illa regi ex nomine Mardochaei, qui ad se rem detulerat.
verse_text: Die illo dedit rex Assuerus Esther reginae domum Aman adversarii Judaeorum, et Mardochaeus ingressus est ante faciem regis. Confessa est enim ei Esther quod esset patruus suus.

text: All things that are of the earth shal turne to the earth againe: and that which is of the waters doeth returne into the Sea.
verse_text: Omnia quae de terra sunt in terram convertentur, et omnes aquae in mare revertentur.

text: Verbum quod factum est ad Jeremiam a Domino, postquam percussit rex Sedecias foedus cum omni populo in Jerusalem, praedicans
verse_text: Et scripsit Jeremias omne malum quod venturum erat super Babylonem, in libro uno: omnia verba haec quae scripta sunt contra Babylonem.

text: Et dixit Jeremias propheta ad Hananiam prophetam, in oculis sacerdotum, et in oculis omnis populi qui stabat in domo Domini:
verse_text: Et abiit Jeremias propheta in viam suam. Et factum est verbum Domini ad Jeremiam, postquam confregit Hananias propheta catenam de collo Jeremiae prophetae, dicens:

text: Thy substance and thy treasures wil I giue to be spoyled without gaine, and that for all thy sinnes euen in all thy borders.
verse_text: Sacrificing in the field: I will give thy strength, and all thy treasures to the spoil, and thy high places for sin in all thy borders.

text: And approched to his bed, and tooke hold of the haire of his head, and said, Strengthen mee, O Lord God of Israel, this day.
verse_text: dicens: Confirma me, Domine Deus Israel, et respice in hac hora ad opera manuum mearum, ut, sicut promisisti, Jerusalem civitatem tuam erigas: et hoc quod credens per te posse fieri cogitavi, perficiam.

text: And the king of the South shal be made strong, & there shal of his princes preuaile aboue him, and he shal rule in dominion:
verse_text: And ye King of ye South shalbe mightie, and one of his princes, and shall preuaile against him, and beare rule:

text: Non tendat qui tendit arcum suum, et non ascendat loricatus: nolite parcere juvenibus ejus; interficite omnem militiam ejus.
verse_text: Acuite sagittas, implete pharetras: suscitavit Dominus spiritum regum Medorum: et contra Babylonem mens ejus est ut perdat eam, quoniam ultio Domini est, ultio templi sui.

text: And the captaine of the gard took Ieremiah, and sayd vnto him, The Lord thy God hath pronounced this euill vpon this place.
verse_text: Then spake Azariah the sonne of Hoshaiah, and Iohanan the sonne of Kareah, and all the proud men, saying vnto Ieremiah, Thou speakest falsly: the Lord our God hath not sent thee to say, Goe not into Egypt, to soiourne there.

text: Simon the high priest the sonne of Onias, who in his life repaired the house againe, and in his dayes fortified the Temple:
verse_text: Simon, Oniae filius, sacerdos magnus, qui in vita sua suffulsit domum, et in diebus suis corroboravit templum.

text: Quoniam alieni insurrexerunt adversum me, et fortes quaesierunt animam meam, et non proposuerunt Deum ante conspectum suum.
verse_text: Ne tradideris me in animas tribulantium me, quoniam insurrexerunt in me testes iniqui, et mentita est iniquitas sibi.

text: The Kings strength also loueth iudgement, thou doest establish equitie: thou executest iudgement and righteousnes in Iacob.
verse_text: For thou hast maintained my right and my cause: thou art set in the throne, and iudgest right.

text: Quia persecutus est inimicus animam meam; humiliavit in terra vitam meam; collocavit me in obscuris, sicut mortuos saeculi.
verse_text: Quoniam gratis absconderunt mihi interitum laquei sui; supervacue exprobraverunt animam meam.

text: Et feriam eis pactum sempiternum, et non desinam eis benefacere: et timorem meum dabo in corde eorum, ut non recedant a me.
verse_text: Et ponam oculos meos super eos ad placandum, et reducam eos in terram hanc: et aedificabo eos, et non destruam: et plantabo eos, et non evellam.

text: Untill you come beyond Tanis, and Memphis, and to all the inhabitants of Egypt, vntill you come to the borders of Ethiopia.
verse_text: Ad hos omnes misit nuntios Nabuchodonosor rex Assyriorum:

text: He shal iudge among the heathen, he shal fil the places with the dead bodies: he shall wound the heads ouer many countries.
verse_text: taking away warres euen vnto the end of the earth. He shal destroy bow, & breake weapons: and shields he shal burne with fire.

text: Now therefore my lord, fight not against them in battell aray, and there shall not so much as one man of thy people perish.
verse_text: Cumque ista custodia per dies viginti fuisset expleta, defecerunt cisternae et collectiones aquarum omnibus habitantibus Bethuliam, ita ut non esset intra civitatem unde satiarentur vel una die, quoniam ad mensuram dabatur populis aqua quotidie.

text: So that their slaine shall fill their vallies, and brookes, and the riuer shall be filled with their dead, til it ouerflow.
verse_text: Omnemque expeditionem suam fecit praeire in multitudine innumerabilium camelorum, cum his quae exercitibus sufficerent copiose, boum quoque armenta, gregesque ovium, quorum non erat numerus.

text: sed eruens liberabo te, et gladio non cades, sed erit tibi anima tua in salutem, quia in me habuisti fiduciam, ait Dominus.
verse_text: quoniam tecum ego sum, ait Dominus, ut salvem te. Faciam enim consummationem in cunctis gentibus in quibus dispersi te: te autem non faciam in consummationem: sed castigabo te in judicio, ut non videaris tibi innoxius.

text: For thou art the God of my strength, why doest thou cast me off? why goe I mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?
verse_text: Because thou art God my strength: why hast thou repelled me? and why goe I sorowful, whiles the enemie afflicteth me?

text: et non audierunt me, nec inclinaverunt aurem suam: sed induraverunt cervicem suam, et pejus operati sunt quam patres eorum.
verse_text: Et non audierunt, nec inclinaverunt aurem suam: sed abierunt in voluntatibus et in pravitate cordis sui mali: factique sunt retrorsum, et non in ante,

text: An vnwise king destroyeth his people, but through the prudence of them which are in authoritie, the citie shalbe inhabited.
verse_text: Rex insipiens perdet populum suum: et civitates inhabitabuntur per sensum potentium.

text: Est correptio mendax in ira contumeliosi, et est judicium quod non probatur esse bonum: et est tacens, et ipse est prudens.
verse_text: Est nequitia, et in ipsa execratio, et est insipiens qui minuitur sapientia.

text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Bonas facite vias vestras, et studia vestra, et habitabo vobiscum in loco isto.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Vade, et dic viris Juda et habitatoribus Jerusalem: Numquid non recipietis disciplinam, ut obediatis verbis meis? dicit Dominus.

text: Hearken not to the words of the prophets that say to you: You shall not serve the king of Babylon: for they tell you a lie.
verse_text: I spoke also to the priests, and to this people, saying: Thus saith the Lord: Hearken not to the words of your prophets, that prophesy to you, saying: Behold the vessels of the Lord shall now in a short time be brought again from Babylon: for they prophesy a lie unto you.

text: I behaued my selfe as though he had bene my friend, or brother: I bowed downe heauily, as one that mourneth for his mother.
verse_text: Surely I haue behaued my selfe, like one wained from his mother, and kept silence: I am in my selfe as one that is wained.

text: Exclamavit autem voce magna Susanna, et dixit: Deus aeterne, qui absconditorum es cognitor, qui nosti omnia antequam fiant,
verse_text: appropinquansque lacui, Danielem voce lacrimabili inclamavit, et affatus est eum: Daniel serve Dei viventis, Deus tuus, cui tu servis semper, putasne valuit te liberare a leonibus?

text: Because of vnrighteous dealings, iniuries, and riches got by deceit, the kingdome is translated from one people to another.
verse_text: Regnum a gente in gentem transfertur propter injustitias, et injurias, et contumelias, et diversos dolos.

text: In the eighteenth yeere of Nebuchad-rezzar hee caried away captiue from Ierusalem eight hundredth, thirtie and two persons.
verse_text: In the three and twentieth yeere of Nebuchad-nezzar, Nebuzar-adan the chiefe stewarde caried away captiue of the Iewes seuen hundreth fourtie and fiue persons: all the persons were foure thousand and sixe hundreth.

text: Then they took Jeremias and cast him into the dungeon of Melchias the son of Amelech, which was in the entry of the prison:
verse_text: Now Abdemelech the Ethiopian, an eunuch that was in the king's house, heard that they had put Jeremias in the dungeon:

text: And in the fourth yeere of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, came this word vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, saying,
verse_text: The word which came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, in the daies of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, saying,

text: If thou blow the sparke, it shall burne: if thou spit vpon it, it shall bee quenched, and both these come out of thy mouth.
verse_text: Secundum enim ligna silvae sic ignis exardescit: et secundum virtutem hominis sic iracundia illius erit, et secundum substantiam suam exaltabit iram suam.

text: And I set before the sonnes of the house of the Rechabites, pots full of wine, and cuppes, and said vnto them, Drinke wine.
verse_text: Go vnto the house of the Rechabites, and speake vnto them, and bring them into the house of the Lord into one of the chambers, and giue them wine to drinke.

text: Haec dicit Dominus: Custodite animas vestras, et nolite portare pondera in die sabbati, nec inferatis per portas Jerusalem:
verse_text: et nolite ejicere onera de domibus vestris in die sabbati, et omne opus non facietis: sanctificate diem sabbati, sicut praecepi patribus vestris.

text: Let their bones flourish out of their place, and let the name of them that were honoured, be continued vpon their children.
verse_text: ut viderent omnes filii Israel quia bonum est obsequi sancto Deo.

text: The foole saith, I haue no friends, I haue no thanke for all my good deeds: and they that eate my bread speake euill of me.
verse_text: Hodie foeneratur quis, et cras expetit: odibilis est homo hujusmodi.

text: Now when they shall bring them word, they will forthwith doe it, and they shall be giuen thee to be destroyed the same day.
verse_text: et dicet mihi quando eis reddat peccatum suum, et veniens nuntiabo tibi, ita ut ego adducam te per mediam Jerusalem, et habebis omnem populum Israel, sicut oves quibus non est pastor, et non latrabit vel unus canis contra te:

text: Simon the high priest the sonne of Onias, who in his life repaired the house againe, and in his dayes fortified the Temple:
verse_text: So was Iesus the sonne of Iosedec: who in their time builded the house, and set vp an holy Temple to the Lord, which was prepared for euerlasting glory.

text: They prepared a snare for my feete: and bowed downe my soule. They digged a pit before my face: and they are falne into it.
verse_text: the proude haue hid a snare for me: And they haue stretched out ropes for a snare: they haue layd a stumbling blocke for me nere the way.

text: Keepe me, O Lord, from the hands of the wicked, preserue me from the violent man: who haue purposed to ouerthrow my goings.
verse_text: My times are in thy hand: deliuer me from the hand of mine enemies, and from them that persecute me.

text: Hee that fleeth from the feare shall fall into the pit, and he that getteth vp out of the pit shall be taken in the snare:
verse_text: and he that shall get up out of the pit, shall be taken in the snare:

text: Qui gaudet iniquitate, denotabitur: et qui odit correptionem, minuetur vita: et qui odit loquacitatem, extinguit malitiam.
verse_text: Qui peccat in animam suam, poenitebit: et qui jucundatur in malitia, denotabitur.

text: Great men, and Iudges, and Potentates shall bee honoured, yet is there none of them greater then he that feareth the Lord.
verse_text: In medio fratrum rector illorum in honore: et qui timent Dominum erunt in oculis illius.

text: We haue heard the fame thereof, our hands waxe feeble, anguish hath taken hold of vs, and paine as of a woman in trauaile.
verse_text: The king of Babylon hath heard the report of them, and his hands are grown feeble: anguish hath taken hold of him, pangs as a, woman in labour.

text: Because strgers haue risen vp against me, & the strong haue sought my soule: and they haue not set God before their eies.
verse_text: O God, the proud are risen against mee, and the assemblies of violent men haue sought after my soule: and haue not set thee before them.

text: He that toucheth pitch, shal be defiled therewith, and hee that hath fellowship with a proude man, shall be like vnto him.
verse_text: Qui tetigerit picem inquinabitur ab ea: et qui communicaverit superbo induet superbiam.

text: And say thou vnto them, Thus saith the Lord God of Israel, Cursed bee the man that obeyeth not the words of this Couenant,
verse_text: And command them to say vnto their masters, Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel, Thus shall ye say vnto your masters:

text: quia justus es in omnibus, quae fecisti nobis, et universa opera tua vera, et viae tuae rectae, et omnia judicia tua vera.
verse_text: Omnia ergo, quae induxisti super nos, et universa quae fecisti nobis, in vero judicio fecisti;

text: For as a scarcrow in a garden of Cucumbers keepeth nothing: so are their gods of wood, and laid ouer with siluer and gold.
verse_text: Whereupon when fire falleth vpon the house of gods of wood, or layd ouer with gold or siluer, their priests will fly away, & escape: but they themselues shall be burnt asunder like beames.

text: He that buildeth his house with other mens money, is like one that gathereth himselfe stones for the tombe of his buriall.
verse_text: Notus a longe potens lingua audaci, et sensatus scit labi se ab ipso.

text: Thus will I doe vnto this place, sayth the Lord, and to the inhabitantes thereof, and I will make this citie like Topheth.
verse_text: Wherefore thus saith the Lord God of hostes, Because ye speake such wordes, beholde, I will put my wordes into thy mouth, like a fire, and this people shall be as wood, and it shall deuoure them.

text: Propterea ecce dies veniunt, dicit Dominus, et non dicetur ultra: Vivit Dominus qui eduxit filios Israel de terra AEgypti,
verse_text: sed: Vivit Dominus, qui eduxit et adduxit semen domus Israel de terra aquilonis, et de cunctis terris ad quas ejeceram eos illuc, et habitabunt in terra sua.

text: And this whole land shalbe desolate, and an astonishment, and these nations shall serue the King of Babel seuentie yeeres.
verse_text: And it shall come to passe when seuentie yeeres are accomplished, that I will punish the king of Babylon and that nation, saith the Lord, for their iniquitie, and the land of the Caldeans, and will make it perpetuall desolations.

text: He that toucheth pitch, shal be defiled therewith, and hee that hath fellowship with a proude man, shall be like vnto him.
verse_text: He that loueth gold shall not bee iustified, and he that followeth corruption, shall haue enough thereof.

text: For the prayer of him that curseth thee in the bitterness of his soul, shall be heard, for he that made him will hear him.
verse_text: The Lord will not accept any person against a poor man, and he will hear the prayer of him that is wronged.

text: Ecce ego suscitabo super Babylonem et super habitatores ejus, qui cor suum levaverunt contra me, quasi ventum pestilentem:
verse_text: Quoniam ecce ego suscito, et adducam in Babylonem congregationem gentium magnarum de terra aquilonis, et praeparabuntur adversus eam, et inde capietur:

text: For thou Lord of thy goodnes hadest made my mountaine to stande strong: but thou didest hide thy face, and I was troubled.
verse_text: By the strength of thy hand I haue faynted in reprehensions: for iniquitie thou hast chastised man. And thou hast made his soule pyne away as a spider: but vaynly is euerie man trubled.

text: I will sing a new song vnto thee, O God: vpon a psalterie, and an instrument of ten strings will I sing praises vnto thee.
verse_text: Therefore will I praise thee for thy faithfulnesse, O God, vpon instrument and viole: vnto thee will I sing vpon the harpe, O Holy one of Israel.

text: Vivo ego, inquit Rex (Dominus exercituum nomen ejus), quoniam sicut Thabor in montibus, et sicut Carmelus in mari, veniet.
verse_text: quia venit super eam, id est super Babylonem, praedo, et apprehensi sunt fortes ejus, et emarcuit arcus eorum, quia fortis ultor Dominus reddens retribuet.

text: Deliuer mee from blood-guiltinesse, O God, thou God of my saluation: and my tongue shall sing alowd of thy righteousnesse.
verse_text: My lippes shall greatly reioyce when I sing vnto thee: and my soule, which thou hast redeemed.

text: Then Baruch answered them, He pronounced all these wordes vnto me with his mouth, and I wrote them with ynke in the booke.
verse_text: And they sayde vnto him, Sit downe now and read it in our eares. So Baruch read it in their eares.

text: The Lord looked downe from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there were any that would vnderstand, and seeke God.
verse_text: God hath looked forth from heauen, vpon the children of men: to see if there be that vnderstdeth, or seeketh after God.

text: Make with me a signe vnto God, that they may see which hate me, and may be confounded: because thou o Lord hast holpen me.
verse_text: Let them not be ashamed vpon me, which expect thee o Lord, Lord of hostes. Let them not be confounded vpon me that seeke thee, o God of Israel.

text: provinciae atque provinciae, populo et populo juxta linguas et litteras suas, et Judaeis, prout legere poterant et audire.
verse_text: et scriptum est, ut jusserat Aman, ad omnes satrapas regis, et judices provinciarum, diversarumque gentium, ut quaeque gens legere poterat et audire pro varietate linguarum ex nomine regis Assueri:

text: Blesse the Lord yee his Angels, that excell in strength, that do his commandements: hearkening vnto the voice of his word.
verse_text: Blesse the Lord all his works in all places of his dominion: blesse the Lord, O my soule.

text: Flee from the middes of Babel, and depart out of the lande of the Caldeans, and be ye as the hee goates before the flocke.
verse_text: The voyce of them that flee, and escape out of the lande of Babel to declare in Zion the vengeance of the Lord our God, and the vengeance of his Temple.

text: And to those amongst the nations that were of Carmel, and Galaad, and the higher Galile, and the great plaine of Esdrelon,
verse_text: et ad gentes quae sunt in Carmelo et Cedar, et inhabitantes Galilaeam in campo magno Esdrelon,

text: Deliuer him that suffreth wrong, from the hand of the oppressour, and be not faint hearted when thou sittest in iudgement.
verse_text: Libera eum qui injuriam patitur de manu superbi, et non acide feras in anima tua.

text: For they shall also pray vnto the Lord, that hee would prosper that, which they giue, for ease and remedy to prolong life.
verse_text: ipsi vero Dominum deprecabuntur, ut dirigat requiem eorum, et sanitatem, propter conversationem illorum.

text: The chariots of God are twentie thousand, euen thousands of Angels: the Lord is among them as in Sinai, in the holy place.
verse_text: The earth shooke, and the heauens dropped at the presence of this God: euen Sinai was moued at the presence of God, euen the God of Israel.

text: Si defecerint leges istae coram me, dicit Dominus, tunc et semen Israel deficiet, ut non sit gens coram me cunctis diebus.
verse_text: In diebus illis, et in tempore illo, ait Dominus, quaeretur iniquitas Israel, et non erit, et peccatum Juda, et non invenietur: quoniam propitius ero eis quos reliquero.

text: Canticum graduum. Ecce nunc benedicite Dominum, omnes servi Domini: qui statis in domo Domini, in atriis domus Dei nostri.
verse_text: Jubilate Deo, omnis terra; servite Domino in laetitia. Introite in conspectu ejus in exsultatione.

text: Qui dominatur in virtute sua in aeternum; oculi ejus super gentes respiciunt: qui exasperant non exaltentur in semetipsis.
verse_text: Ecce oculi Domini super metuentes eum, et in eis qui sperant super misericordia ejus:

text: Beatus quem elegisti et assumpsisti: inhabitabit in atriis tuis. Replebimur in bonis domus tuae; sanctum est templum tuum,
verse_text: Visitasti terram, et inebriasti eam; multiplicasti locupletare eam. Flumen Dei repletum est aquis; parasti cibum illorum: quoniam ita est praeparatio ejus.

text: And after tenne daies their faces appeared better & more corpulent then al the children, that did eate of the kings meate.
verse_text: And there were two ancients appointed iudges in that yeare, of whom our Lord spake: That iniquities came out of Babylon from the seniour iudges, that semed to rule the people.

text: Velociter exaudi me, Domine; defecit spiritus meus. Non avertas faciem tuam a me, et similis ero descendentibus in lacum.
verse_text: Intende ad deprecationem meam, quia humiliatus sum nimis. Libera me a persequentibus me, quia confortati sunt super me.

text: There are certain Iewes whom thou hast set ouer the affaires of the prouince of Babylon, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego:
verse_text: Then Daniel made request to the King, and hee set Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego ouer the charge of the prouince of Babel:

text: I will be glad, and reioyce in thy mercie: for thou hast considered my trouble; thou hast knowen my soule in aduersities;
verse_text: For thou, Lord, hast made me glad through thy worke: I will triumph in the workes of thy hands.

text: The pastures are cloathed with flockes; the valleis also are couered ouer with corne; they shout for ioy, they also sing.
verse_text: The rammes of the shepe are clothed, and the valleis shal abounde with corne: they wil crie, yea they wil say an hyme.

text: Et si coactus fueris in edendo multum, surge e medio, evome, et refrigerabit te, et non adduces corpori tuo infirmitatem.
verse_text: Si est tibi intellectus, responde proximo: sin autem, sit manus tua super os tuum, ne capiaris in verbo indisciplinato, et confundaris.

text: Da misericordi, et ne suscipias peccatorem: et impiis et peccatoribus reddet vindictam, custodiens eos in diem vindictae.
verse_text: nam duplicia mala invenies in omnibus bonis quaecumque feceris illi, quoniam et Altissimus odio habet peccatores, et impiis reddet vindictam.

text: Esto mihi in Deum protectorem, et in locum munitum, ut salvum me facias: quoniam firmamentum meum et refugium meum es tu.
verse_text: Misericordia mea et refugium meum; susceptor meus et liberator meus; protector meus, et in ipso speravi, qui subdit populum meum sub me.

text: Clamaveruntque ad Deum: et illis vociferantibus, fons parvus creavit in fluvium maximum, et in aquas plurimas redundavit.
verse_text: Parvus fons, qui crevit in fluvium, et in lucem solemque conversus est, et in aquas plurimas redundavit: Esther est quam rex accepit uxorem, et voluit esse reginam.

text: Et si ingrediebatur ut videret, vana loquebatur; cor ejus congregavit iniquitatem sibi. Egrediebatur foras et loquebatur.
verse_text: in columna nubis loquebatur ad eos. Custodiebant testimonia ejus, et praeceptum quod dedit illis.

text: Therefore they were exceedingly afraid of him, and were troubled for Ierusalem, and for the Temple of the Lord their God.
verse_text: Tremor et horror invasit sensus eorum, ne hoc faceret Jerusalem et templo Domini, quod fecerat ceteris civitatibus et templis earum.

text: ubi sunt prophetae vestri, qui prophetabant vobis, et dicebant: Non veniet rex Babylonis super vos, et super terram hanc?
verse_text: quia non misi eos, ait Dominus, et ipsi prophetant in nomine meo mendaciter, ut ejiciant vos, et pereatis, tam vos quam prophetae qui vaticinantur vobis.

text: and the God whom his fathers knewe not, he shal worshipe with gold, and siluer, and precious stone, and precious thinges.
verse_text: And he shal rule ouer the treasures of gold, and of siluer, and in al the precious thinges of AEgypt:

text: Nunc ergo scientes scietis quia gladio, et fame, et peste moriemini in loco ad quem voluistis intrare ut habitaretis ibi.
verse_text: Verumtamen scitote et cognoscite quod, si occideritis me, sanguinem innocentem tradetis contra vosmetipsos, et contra civitatem istam, et habitatores ejus: in veritate enim misit me Dominus ad vos, ut loquerer in auribus vestris omnia verba haec.

text: Blessed bee the Lord God of Israel from euerlasting to euerlasting: and let all the people say, Amen. Praise ye the Lord.
verse_text: Blessed be our Lord the God of Israel from the beginning of the world, and for euermore: Be it, be it.

text: Quia stulte egerunt pastores, et Dominum non quaesierunt: propterea non intellexerunt, et omnis grex eorum dispersus est.
verse_text: Et extenderunt linguam suam quasi arcum mendacii et non veritatis: confortati sunt in terra, quia de malo ad malum egressi sunt, et me non cognoverunt, dicit Dominus.

text: Dixi: Custodiam vias meas: ut non delinquam in lingua mea. Posui ori meo custodiam, cum consisteret peccator adversum me.
verse_text: Quia dixi: Nequando supergaudeant mihi inimici mei; et dum commoventur pedes mei, super me magna locuti sunt.

text: For yet a little while, and the wicked shall not bee: yea, thou shalt diligently consider his place, and it shall not be.
verse_text: And yet a litle while, and the sinner shal not be: and thou shalt seeke his place, and shal not find it.

text: Praysing, to Dauid himselfe. I Wil exalt thee my God the king: and I wil blesse thy name for euer, and for euer and euer.
verse_text: Euerie day wil I blesse thee: and wil praise thy name for euer, and for euer and euer.

text: Praise yee the Lord. I will praise the Lord with my whole heart: in the assembly of the vpright, and in the Congregation.
verse_text: I will praise thee with my whole heart: before the gods will I sing praise vnto thee.

text: Also Edom shall be desolate: euery one that goeth by it, shall be astonished, and shall hisse at all the plagues thereof,
verse_text: And Edom shall be desolate: every one that shall pass by it, shall be astonished, and shall hiss at all its plagues.

text: It is much better to reprooue, then to be angry secretly, and he that confesseth his fault, shall be preserued from hurt.
verse_text: Concupiscentia spadonis devirginabit juvenculam:

text: To him that excelleth. A Psalme of David. Heare my voyce, O God, in my prayer: preserue my life from feare of the enemie.
verse_text: To him that excelleth upon Nehiloth. A Psalme of Dauid. Heare my wordes, O Lord: vnderstande my meditation.

text: Therefore let vs waite for saluation of him, and call vpon him to helpe vs, and he will heare our voyce if it please him.
verse_text: dicamus flentes Domino, ut secundum voluntatem suam sic faciat nobiscum misericordiam suam: ut sicut conturbatum est cor nostrum in superbia eorum, ita etiam de nostra humilitate gloriemur:

text: And they that eate bread with him, shal destroy him, and his armie shal be oppressed: & there shal fal slaine very manie.
verse_text: And the learned in the people shal teach very manie: and they shal fal by sword, and by flame, and by captiuitie, and by spoyle of dayes.

text: Quae sedes in Libano, et nidificas in cedris, quomodo congemuisti cum venissent tibi dolores, quasi dolores parturientis?
verse_text: Arrogantia tua decepit te, et superbia cordis tui, qui habitas in cavernis petrae, et apprehendere niteris altitudinem collis: cum exaltaveris quasi aquila nidum tuum, inde detraham te, dicit Dominus.

text: They that reioyce at the fall of the righteous shalbe taken in the snare, and anguish shall consume them before they die.
verse_text: Et qui foveam fodit incidet in eam: et qui statuit lapidem proximo offendet in eo: et qui laqueum alii ponit, peribit in illo.

text: For in the diuision of the nations of the whole earth, he set a ruler ouer euery people, but Israel is the Lords portion.
verse_text: Non sunt absconsa testamenta per iniquitatem illorum, et omnes iniquitates eorum in conspectu Dei.

text: Then they chose out of them an hundred men, to accompany her and her mayd, and they brought her to the tent of Olofernes.
verse_text: Cumque intrasset ante faciem ejus, statim captus est in suis oculis Holofernes.

text: Man, when he was in honour, did not vnderstand: he was compared to beasts without vnderstanding, and became like to them.
verse_text: Man is in honour, and vnderstandeth not: he is like to beasts that perish.

text: In the beginning of the reign of Joakim the son of Josias king of Juda, this word came to Jeremias from the Lord, saying:
verse_text: The word that Jeremias the prophet spoke to Baruch the son of Nerias, when he had written there words in a book, out of the mouth of Jeremias, in the fourth year of Joakim the son of Josias king of Juda, saying:

text: The Lord will performe his worke toward me: O Lord, thy mercie endureth for euer: forsake not the workes of thine handes.
verse_text: But I trust in thy mercie: mine heart shall reioyce in thy saluation: I will sing to the Lord, because he hath delt louingly with me.

text: And he informed me, and talked with me, and sayd, O Daniel, I am now come forth to giue thee knowledge and vnderstanding.
verse_text: And hee said vnto me, O Daniel, a man greatly beloued, vnderstand the wordes that I speake vnto thee, and stand vpright: for vnto thee am I now sent; and when he had spoken this word vnto me, I stood trembling.

text: Go, and tell Hananias: Thus saith the Lord: Thou hast broken chains of wood, and thou shalt make for them chains of iron.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord to me: Make thee bands, and chains: and thou shalt put them on thy neck.

text: Therefore shall her yong men fall in the streetes, and al her men of warre shalbe destroied in that day, sayeth the Lord.
verse_text: Therefore shall her young men fall in her streets: and all her men of war shall hold their peace in that day, saith the Lord.

text: A rich man beginning to fall, is held vp of his friends: but a poore man being downe, is thrust also away by his friends.
verse_text: Si communicabit lupus agno aliquando, sic peccator justo.

text: Et stabit in loco ejus despectus, et non tribuetur ei honor regius: et veniet clam, et obtinebit regnum in fraudulentia.
verse_text: Et confortabitur rex austri: et de principibus ejus praevalebit super eum, et dominabitur ditione: multa enim dominatio ejus.

text: The pastures are clad with sheepe: the valleis also shalbe couered with corne: therefore they shoute for ioye, and sing.
verse_text: The beautiful places of the desert shal be fat: and the litle hills shal be girded aboute with exultation,

text: Delight not in the thing that the vngodly haue pleasure in, but remember they shall not goe vnpunished vnto their graue.
verse_text: Cum aliena muliere ne sedeas omnino, nec accumbas cum ea super cubitum:

text: Surely goodnes and mercie shall followe me all the daies of my life: and I will dwell in the house of the Lord for euer.
verse_text: I will sing of the mercies of the Lord for euer: with my mouth will I make knowen thy faithfulnesse to all generations.

text: Saying, We will fal into the hands of the Lord, and not into the hands of men: for as his maiestie is, so is his mercie.
verse_text: Qui timent Dominum non erunt incredibiles verbo illius: et qui diligunt illum conservabunt viam illius.

text: God looked downe from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there were any that did vnderstand, that did seeke God.
verse_text: Our Lord hath looked forth from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there be that vnderstandeth, and seeketh after God.

text: Yee that feare the Lord, praise him; all yee the seede of Iacob glorifie him, and feare him all yee the seede of Israel.
verse_text: Giue vnto the Lord (O yee kinreds of the people:) giue vnto the Lord glory and strength.

text: Let death seaze vpon them, and let them goe downe quicke into hell: for wickednes is in their dwellings, and among them.
verse_text: Like sheepe they lie in graue: death deuoureth them, and the righteous shall haue domination ouer them in the morning: for their beautie shall consume, when they shall goe from their house to graue.

text: For the blessing of the father establisheth the houses of children, but the curse of the mother rooteth out foundations.
verse_text: In opere, et sermone, et omni patientia, honora patrem tuum,

text: And of merchants indifferent selling, of much correction of children, and to make the side of an euill seruant to bleed.
verse_text: de corruptione emptionis et negotiatorum, et de multa disciplina filiorum, et servo pessimo latus sanguinare.

text: Ideo haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Ecce ego ponam faciem meam in vobis in malum: et disperdam omnem Judam.
verse_text: Propterea haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Ecce ego visitabo regem Babylonis et terram ejus, sicut visitavi regem Assur:

text: The Kings of the earth band themselues, and the princes are assembled together against the Lord, and against his Christ.
verse_text: The Kings of the earth set themselues, and the rulers take counsell together, against the Lord, and against his Anoynted, saying,

text: The voice of reioycing and saluation is in the tabernacles of the righteous: the Right hand of the Lord doeth valiantly.
verse_text: Yet there is a Riuer, whose streames shall make glad the citie of God: euen the Sanctuarie of the Tabernacles of the most High.

text: Also I set watchmen ouer you, which said, Take heede to the sound of the trumpet: but they said, We will not take heede.
verse_text: And the Lord hath sent vnto you all his seruantes the Prophets, rising early and sending them, but yee would not heare, nor encline your eares to obey.

text: Ego scio, ait Dominus, jactantiam ejus, et quod non sit juxta eam virtus ejus, nec juxta quod poterat conata sit facere.
verse_text: idcirco haec dicit Dominus: Ecce ego visitabo super Semeiam Nehelamiten, et super semen ejus: non erit ei vir sedens in medio populi hujus, et non videbit bonum quod ego faciam populo meo, ait Dominus, quia praevaricationem locutus est adversus Dominum.

text: The poore shall eate and be satisfied: they that seeke after the Lord, shall prayse him: your heart shall liue for euer.
verse_text: My soule shall make her boast in the Lord: the humble shall heare thereof, and be glad.

text: Et cum evulsero eos, convertar, et miserebor eorum, et reducam eos: virum ad haereditatem suam, et virum in terram suam.
verse_text: Et pavere faciam AElam coram inimicis suis, et in conspectu quaerentium animam eorum: et adducam super eos malum, iram furoris mei, dicit Dominus, et mittam post eos gladium donec consumam eos.

text: Exsultabo, et laetabor in misericordia tua, quoniam respexisti humilitatem meam; salvasti de necessitatibus animam meam.
verse_text: Si ambulavero in medio tribulationis, vivificabis me; et super iram inimicorum meorum extendisti manum tuam, et salvum me fecit dextera tua.

text: Inclina ad me aurem tuam; accelera ut eruas me. Esto mihi in Deum protectorem, et in domum refugii, ut salvum me facias:
verse_text: Respice, et exaudi me, Domine Deus meus. Illumina oculos meos, ne umquam obdormiam in morte;

text: God hath looked forth from heauen, vpon the children of men: to see if there be that vnderstdeth, or seeketh after God.
verse_text: God looked downe from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there were any that would vnderstand, and seeke God.

text: Good is set against euill, and life against death: so is the godly against the sinner, and the sinner against the godly.
verse_text: Omnes viae ejus secundum dispositionem ejus: sic homo in manu illius qui se fecit, et reddet illi secundum judicium suum.

text: With-hold not thou thy tender mercies from me, O Lord: let thy louing kindnesse, and thy trueth continually preserue me.
verse_text: Heare my voyce according to thy louing kindenesse: O Lord, quicken me according to thy iudgement.

text: Oratio humiliantis se nubes penetrabit, et donec propinquet non consolabitur, et non discedet donec Altissimus aspiciat.
verse_text: Perseverantia illius non permanebit, sed obtinebit vias injustorum, et in flamma sua non comburet justos.

text: Giue testimonie vnto those that thou hast possessed from the beginning, and raise vp prophets that haue bin in thy name.
verse_text: Miserere civitati sanctificationis tuae, Jerusalem, civitati requiei tuae.

text: Then Darius the king wrote to al peoples, tribes, and tongues dwelling in the whole earth: PEACE be multiplied vnto you.
verse_text: Nebuchad-nezzar King vnto all people, nations and languages, that dwell in all the world, Peace be multiplied vnto you:

text: And all the kings of Tyre, and all the kings of Sidon: and the kings of the land of the islands that are beyond the sea.
verse_text: And all the kings of Arabia, and all the kings of the mingled people that dwell in the desert:

text: Therefore from the beginning I was resolved, and I have meditated, and thought on these things and left them in writing.
verse_text: And I will shew forth good doctrine in equity, and will seek to declare wisdom: and attend to my words in thy heart, whilst with equity of spirit I tell thee the virtues that God hath put upon his works from the beginning, and I shew forth in truth his knowledge.

text: And when Haman sawe that Mordecai bowed not the knee vnto him, nor did reuerence vnto him, then Haman was full of wrath.
verse_text: Then went Haman foorth that day, ioyfull, and with a glad heart: but when Haman saw Mordecai in the kings gate, that hee stood not vp, nor mooued for him, hee was full of indignation against Mordecai.

text: Bringing forth grasse for beastes, and herbe for the seruice of men. That thou mayst bring forth bread out of the earth:
verse_text: Who couereth the heauen with cloudes: and prepareth rayne for the earth. Who bringeth forth grasse in the mountaines: and herbe for the seruice of men.

text: Exspecta Dominum, et custodi viam ejus, et exaltabit te ut haereditate capias terram: cum perierint peccatores, videbis.
verse_text: Jacta super Dominum curam tuam, et ipse te enutriet; non dabit in aeternum fluctuationem justo.

text: Hee put vpon him perfect glory: and strengthened him with rich garments, with breeches, with a long robe, and the Ephod:
verse_text: Statuit ei testamentum aeternum, et dedit illi sacerdotium gentis, et beatificavit illum in gloria:

text: For loe, they that withdrawe themselues from thee, shall perish: thou destroyest all them that goe a whoring from thee.
verse_text: Thou hast troden downe all them that erre from thy Statutes: for their deceit is falshood.

text: Honour a Phisitian with the honour due vnto him, for the vses which you may haue of him: for the Lord hath created him.
verse_text: Honora medicum propter necessitatem: etenim illum creavit Altissimus.

text: Nominatio vero Dei non sit assidua in ore tuo, et nominibus sanctorum non admiscearis, quoniam non erit immunis ab eis.
verse_text: Non statuas illum penes te, nec sedeat ad dexteram tuam, ne forte conversus in locum tuum, inquirat cathedram tuam, et in novissimo agnosces verba mea, et in sermonibus meis stimuleris.

text: Though I be poore and needie, the Lord thinketh on mee: thou art mine helper and my deliuerer: my God, make no tarying.
verse_text: But I am needie and poore: o God helpe me thou art my helper, and deliuerer: o Lord be not slacke.

text: Deliuer me from blood, O God, which art the God of my saluation, and my tongue shall sing ioyfully of thy righteousnes.
verse_text: O God the Lord, the strength of my saluation: thou hast couered my head in the day of battell.

text: And the king tooke his ring from his hand, and gaue it vnto Haman the sonne of Ammedatha the Agagite, the Iewes enemie.
verse_text: After these things did King Ahashuerosh promote Haman the sonne of Hammedatha the Agagite, and exalted him, and set his seate aboue all the princes that were with him.

text: If thou be among great men, make not thy selfe equall with them, and when ancient men are in place, vse not many words.
verse_text: Audi tacens, et pro reverentia accedet tibi bona gratia.

text: Yet heare the word of the Lord, O Zedekiah king of Iudah: Thus saith the Lord of thee, Thou shalt not die by the sword:
verse_text: Thus sayth the Lord God of Israel, Goe, and speake to Zedekiah King of Iudah, and tell him, Thus sayth the Lord, Beholde, I will giue this citie into the hand of the King of Babel, and he shall burne it with fire,

text: Errour and darkenesse had their beginning together with sinners: and euill shall waxe old with them that glory therein.
verse_text: Error et tenebrae peccatoribus concreata sunt: qui autem exsultant in malis consenescunt in malo.

text: And Iehoiakim the king sent men into Egypt, namely Elnathan the sonne of Achbor, and certeine men with him, into Egypt.
verse_text: Then arose Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah, and the ten men that were with him, and smote Gedaliah the son of Ahikam the sonne of Shaphan with the sword, and slew him, whome the king of Babylon had made gouernour ouer the land.

text: And render vnto our neighbours seuen fold into their bosome, their reproach wherewith they haue reproched thee, O Lord.
verse_text: Remember this, that the enemie hath reproached, O Lord, and that the foolish people haue blasphemed thy Name.

text: Thus saith the Lord, This citie shall surely be giuen into the hand of the king of Babylons armie, which shall take it.
verse_text: And now therefore, thus sayth the Lord the God of Israel concerning this citie, whereof ye say, It shall be deliuered into the hand of the king of Babylon, by the sword, and by the famine, and by the pestilence:

text: who wrote in it from the mouth of Jeremias all the words of the book which Joakim the king of Juda had burnt with fire:
verse_text: The word that came to Jeremias from the Lord in the tenth year of Sedecias king of Juda:

text: And as one that letteth a bird go out of his hand, so hast thou let thy neighbour go, and thou shalt not get him again.
verse_text: Go not on the way with a bold man, lest he burden thee with his evils: for he goeth according to his own will, and thou shalt perish together with his folly.

text: Avertantur retrorsum, et erubescant, qui volunt mihi mala; avertantur statim erubescentes qui dicunt mihi: Euge, euge !
verse_text: Erubescant et revereantur simul qui gratulantur malis meis; induantur confusione et reverentia qui magna loquuntur super me.

text: They compassed me on euery side, and there was no man to helpe me: I looked for the succour of men, but there was none:
verse_text: de altitudine ventris inferi, et a lingua coinquinata, et a verbo mendacii, a rege iniquo, et a lingua injusta.

text: Cum invocarem exaudivit me Deus justitiae meae, in tribulatione dilatasti mihi. Miserere mei, et exaudi orationem meam.
verse_text: In tribulatione invocasti me, et liberavi te. Exaudivi te in abscondito tempestatis; probavi te apud aquam contradictionis.

text: Bowe downe thine eare to me: make haste to deliuer mee: be vnto me a stronge rocke, and an house of defence to saue me.
verse_text: Nowe I am poore and needie: O God, make haste to me: thou art mine helper, and my deliuerer: O Lord, make no tarying.

text: Who so is liberall of his meat, men shall speake well of him, and the report of his good housekeeping will be beleeued.
verse_text: Vigilia, cholera et tortura viro infrunito,

text: Then was Nebuchad-nezzar full of rage, and the forme of his visage was changed against Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego:
verse_text: Then Nebuchad-nezzar in his rage and furie commaunded to bring Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego:

text: He that beleeueth in the Lord, taketh heed to the commandement, and he that trusted in him, shall fare neuer the worse.
verse_text: Fili, sine consilio nihil facias, et post factum non poenitebis.

text: After, hee went into the tent, where Iudeth lodged, and when hee found her not, he leaped out to the people, and cried,
verse_text: Quod cum audissent principes virtutis Assyriorum, sciderunt omnes vestimenta sua, et intolerabilis timor et tremor cecidit super eos, et turbati sunt animi eorum valde.

text: Now when the men heard her wordes, and beheld her countenance, they wondered greatly at her beautie, and said vnto her;
verse_text: Et cum audissent viri illi verba ejus, considerabant faciem ejus, et erat in oculis eorum stupor, quoniam pulchritudinem ejus mirabantur nimis.

text: Whom being his first borne, hee nourisheth with discipline, and giuing him the light of his loue, doth not forsake him.
verse_text: Eleemosyna viri quasi signaculum cum ipso, et gratiam hominis quasi pupillam conservabit.

text: And in the fourth day Olofernes made a feast to his owne seruants only, and called none of the officers to the banquet.
verse_text: Et factum est, in quarto die Holofernes fecit coenam servis suis, et dixit ad Vagao eunuchum suum: Vade, et suade Hebraeam illam ut sponte consentiat habitare mecum.

text: O Lord, father and God of my life, giue me not a proud looke, but turne away from thy seruants alwaies a haughty minde:
verse_text: Domine, pater et Deus vitae meae, ne derelinquas me in cogitatu illorum.

text: Then will I goe vnto the Altar of God, vnto God my exceeding ioy: yea vpon the harpe will I praise thee, O God, my God.
verse_text: And now shall mine head be lifted vp aboue mine enemies round about me: therefore will I offer in his tabernacle sacrifices of ioy, I will sing, yea, I will sing praises vnto the Lord.

text: There is one that slippeth in his speach, but not from his heart, and who is he that hath not offended with his tongue?
verse_text: et non omni verbo credas. Est qui labitur lingua, sed non ex animo:

text: And I haue seene foolishnesse in the prophets of Samaria, that prophecied in Baal, and caused my people Israel to erre.
verse_text: The priests said not, Where is the Lord? and they that should minister the Lawe, knewe me not: the pastours also offended against me, and the Prophets prophesied in Baal, and went after things that did not profite.

text: And the word of the Lord came to Jeremias the second time, while he was yet shut up in the court of the prison, saying:
verse_text: Moreouer, the word of the Lord came vnto Ieremiah the second time (while hee was yet shut vp in the court of the prison) saying;

text: A wise daughter shall bring an inheritance to her husband: but shee that liueth dishonestly, is her fathers heauinesse.
verse_text: Filia prudens haereditas viro suo: nam quae confundit, in contumeliam fit genitoris.

text: As is a house that is destroyed, so is wisedome to a foole: and the knowledge of the vnwise, is as talke without sense.
verse_text: Verbum sapiens quodcumque audierit scius, laudabit, et ad se adjiciet: audivit luxuriosus, et displicebit illi, et projiciet illud post dorsum suum.

text: Dum appropiant super me nocentes ut edant carnes meas, qui tribulant me inimici mei, ipsi infirmati sunt et ceciderunt.
verse_text: Multiplicati sunt super capillos capitis mei qui oderunt me gratis. Confortati sunt qui persecuti sunt me inimici mei injuste; quae non rapui, tunc exsolvebam.

text: et in omnibus his non est reversa ad me praevaricatrix soror ejus Juda in toto corde suo, sed in mendacio, ait Dominus.
verse_text: Haec sors tua, parsque mensurae tuae a me, dicit Dominus, quia oblita es mei, et confisa es in mendacio.

text: Lauda, anima mea, Dominum. Laudabo Dominum in vita mea; psallam Deo meo quamdiu fuero. Nolite confidere in principibus,
verse_text: ego autem in misericordia tua speravi. Exsultabit cor meum in salutari tuo. Cantabo Domino qui bona tribuit mihi; et psallam nomini Domini altissimi.

text: et in misericordia tua disperdes inimicos meos, et perdes omnes qui tribulant animam meam, quoniam ego servus tuus sum.
verse_text: Tu autem, Domine, ne longe facias miserationes tuas a me; misericordia tua et veritas tua semper susceperunt me.

text: The Lord looked downe from heauen vpon the children of men; to see if there were any that did vnderstand and seeke God.
verse_text: Our Lord hath looked forth from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there be that vnderstandeth, and seeketh after God.

text: The Lord is in his holy Temple, the Lords Throne is in heauen: his eyes beholde, his eye lids trie the children of men.
verse_text: From the place of his habitation, he looketh vpon all the inhabitants of the earth.

text: Now Abdemelech the Ethiopian, an eunuch that was in the king's house, heard that they had put Jeremias in the dungeon:
verse_text: Wherefore the princes were angry with Jeremias, and they beat him, and cast him into the prison that was in the house of Jonathan the scribe:

text: Ascendite muros ejus, et dissipate: consummationem autem nolite facere: auferte propagines ejus, quia non sunt Domini.
verse_text: Clamate adversus eam, ubique dedit manum: ceciderunt fundamenta ejus, destructi sunt muri ejus, quoniam ultio Domini est: ultionem accipite de ea: sicut fecit, facite ei.

text: Now when I had deliuered the booke of the possession vnto Baruch, the sonne of Neriah, I prayed vnto the Lord, saying,
verse_text: Then tooke Ieremiah another roule, and gaue it to Baruch the scribe the sonne of Neriah, who wrote therein from the mouth of Ieremiah, all the words of the booke which Iehoiakim king of Iudah had burnt in the fire, and there were added besides vnto them, many like words.

text: The worde which came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, in the dayes of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, saying,
verse_text: And in the fourth yeere of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, came this word vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, saying,

text: For the wicked hath made boast of his owne heartes desire, and the couetous blesseth himselfe: he contemneth the Lord.
verse_text: The wicked in his pride doeth persecute the poore: let them be taken in the deuices that they haue imagined.

text: If she goe not as thou wouldest haue her, cut her off from thy flesh, and giue her a bill of diuorce, and let her goe.
verse_text: Brevis omnis malitia super malitiam mulieris: sors peccatorum cadat super illam.

text: And he taught me, and spake to me, & sayd: Daniel now am I come forth to teach thee, and that thou mightst vnderstand.
verse_text: And he said to me: Feare not Daniel: because since the first day that thou didst set thy hart to vnderstand to afflict thy self in the sight of thy God, thy wordes haue bene heard: and I am come for thy wordes.

text: Et percussit Phassur Jeremiam prophetam, et misit eum in nervum quod erat in porta Benjamin superiori, in domo Domini.
verse_text: Audivit autem Abdemelech AEthiops, vir eunuchus, qui erat in domo regis, quod misissent Jeremiam in lacum. Porro rex sedebat in porta Benjamin:

text: Turne away from mee vaine hopes, and concupiscence, and thou shalt hold him vp that is desirous alwaies to serue thee.
verse_text: Extollentiam oculorum meorum ne dederis mihi, et omne desiderium averte a me.

text: And she made her a tent vpon the top of her house, and put on sackecloth on her loynes, and ware her widowes apparell.
verse_text: Et in superioribus domus suae fecit sibi secretum cubiculum, in quo cum puellis suis clausa morabatur,

text: And she made her a tent vpon the top of her house, and put on sackecloth on her loynes, and ware her widowes apparell.
verse_text: So she arose, and decked her selfe with her apparell, and all her womans attire, and her maid went and laid soft skinnes on the ground for her, ouer against Olofernes, which she had receiued of Bagoas for her daily vse, that she might sit, and eate vpon them.

text: Si autem non exieris ad principes regis Babylonis, tradetur civitas haec in manus Chaldaeorum, et succendent eam igni:
verse_text: et Sedecias rex Juda non effugiet de manu Chaldaeorum, sed tradetur in manus regis Babylonis:

text: Et post te consurget regnum aliud minus te argenteum: et regnum tertium aliud aereum, quod imperabit universae terrae.
verse_text: In diebus autem regnorum illorum suscitabit Deus caeli regnum, quod in aeternum non dissipabitur, et regnum ejus alteri populo non tradetur: comminuet autem, et consumet universa regna haec, et ipsum stabit in aeternum.

text: In the eightenth yere of Nebuchad-nezzar he caried away captiue from Ierusalem eight hundreth thirtie and two persons.
verse_text: In the three and twentieth yeere of Nebuchad-nezzar, Nebuzar-adan the chiefe stewarde caried away captiue of the Iewes seuen hundreth fourtie and fiue persons: all the persons were foure thousand and sixe hundreth.

text: Exsultent et laetentur qui volunt justitiam meam; et dicant semper: Magnificetur Dominus, qui volunt pacem servi ejus.
verse_text: Sed et lingua mea tota die meditabitur justitiam tuam, cum confusi et reveriti fuerint qui quaerunt mala mihi.

text: Though his father die, yet he is as though hee were not dead: for hee hath left one behinde him that is like himselfe.
verse_text: Mortuus est pater ejus, et quasi non est mortuus: similem enim reliquit sibi post se.

text: The neying of his horses was heard from Dan, the whole lande trembled at the noyse of the neying of his strong horses:
verse_text: At the noise and stamping of ye hoofes of his strong horses, at the noise of his charets, and at the rumbling of his wheeles:

text: Juravit Dominus exercituum per animam suam: Quoniam replebo te hominibus quasi brucho, et super te celeuma cantabitur.
verse_text: Et sanctificabo super te, interficientem virum et arma ejus: et succident electas cedros tuas, et praecipitabunt in ignem.

text: Blessed is the man that doeth meditate good things in wisdome, and that reasoneth of holy things by his vnderstanding.
verse_text: Omne opus corruptibile in fine deficiet, et qui illud operatur ibit cum illo.

text: But every one shall die for his own iniquity: every man that shall eat the sour grape, his teeth shall be set on edge.
verse_text: In those days they shall say no more: The fathers have eaten a sour grape, and the teeth of the children are set on edge.

text: Et dixit Dominus: Quia dereliquerunt legem meam quam dedi eis, et non audierunt vocem meam, et non ambulaverunt in ea,
verse_text: Et ingressi sunt, et possederunt eam, et non obedierunt voci tuae, et in lege tua non ambulaverunt: omnia quae mandasti eis ut facerent non fecerunt, et evenerunt eis omnia mala haec.

text: It is not meet to despise the poore man that hath vnderstanding, neither is it conuenient to magnifie a sinnefull man.
verse_text: Semen hominum honorabitur hoc, quod timet Deum: semen autem hoc exhonorabitur, quod praeterit mandata Domini.

text: Beatus vir qui in sapientia morabitur, et qui in justitia sua meditabitur, et in sensu cogitabit circumspectionem Dei:
verse_text: et ipse tamquam imbres mittet eloquia sapientiae suae, et in oratione confitebitur Domino:

text: O Lord haue mercie vpon the people, that is called by thy name, and vpon Israel, whom thou hast named thy first borne.
verse_text: Contere caput principum inimicorum, dicentium: Non est alius praeter nos.

text: Homo enim iracundus incendit litem, et vir peccator turbabit amicos, et in medio pacem habentium immittet inimicitiam.
verse_text: Mittens lapidem in volatilia, dejiciet illa: sic et qui conviciatur amico, dissolvit amicitiam.

text: Adhuc illis loquentibus, venerunt eunuchi regis, et cito eum ad convivium, quod regina paraverat, pergere compulerunt.
verse_text: Praecepitque ei rex, ut in aula palatii moraretur, datis ei pro delatione muneribus.

text: Hee that keepeth the law, bringeth offerings enow: he that taketh heed to the commandement, offereth a peace offering.
verse_text: Qui conservat legem multiplicat oblationem.

text: Quoniam ecce peccatores intenderunt arcum; paraverunt sagittas suas in pharetra, ut sagittent in obscuro rectos corde:
verse_text: Subito sagittabunt eum, et non timebunt; firmaverunt sibi sermonem nequam. Narraverunt ut absconderent laqueos; dixerunt: Quis videbit eos?

text: O inhabitant of Aroer, stand by the way and espie, aske him that fleeth, and her that escapeth, and say, What is done?
verse_text: Run to and from by the streetes of Ierusalem, and beholde nowe, and knowe, and inquire in the open places thereof, if ye can finde a man, or if there be any that executeth iudgement, and seeketh the trueth, and I will spare it.

text: For this gird yourselves with haircloth, lament and howl: for the fierce anger of the Lord is not turned away from us.
verse_text: Cut off thy hair, and cast it away: and take up a lamentation on high: for the Lord hath rejected and forsaken the generation of his wrath,

text: Hide not thy face from me in the time of my trouble: incline thine eares vnto me: when I call, make haste to heare me.
verse_text: And hide not thy face from thy seruant, for I am in trouble: heare me speedily.

text: My voyce shalt thou heare in the morning, O Lord; in the morning will I direct my prayer vnto thee, and will looke vp.
verse_text: But vnto thee haue I cryed, O Lord, and early shall my prayer come before thee.

text: Let them therfore confesse before the Lord his louing kindnesse, and his wonderfull woorkes before the sonnes of men.
verse_text: Let the mercies of our Lord co nfesse to him: and his meruelous workes to the children of men.

text: Let them therefore cofesse before the Lord his louing kindnesse, and his wonderfull woorkes before the sonnes of men.
verse_text: Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodnesse; and for his wonderfull workes to the children of men:

text: Let them therefore confesse before ye Lord his louing kindnesse, and his wonderfull woorkes before the sonnes of men.
verse_text: Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodnesse; and for his wonderfull workes to the children of men:

text: Wherewith thine enemies haue reproached, O Lord: wherewith they haue reproached the foote-steppes of thine Annointed.
verse_text: O God, the proud are risen against mee, and the assemblies of violent men haue sought after my soule: and haue not set thee before them.

text: Remember the Commaundements, & beare no malice to thy neighbour: the Couenant of the highest, and winke at ignorance.
verse_text: tabitudo enim et mors imminent in mandatis ejus.

text: Et erit Asor in habitaculum draconum, deserta usque in aeternum: non manebit ibi vir, nec incolet eam filius hominis.
verse_text: Et erit Babylon in tumulos, habitatio draconum, stupor et sibilus, eo quod non sit habitator.

text: Thankesgiuing perisheth from the dead, as from one that is not: the liuing and sound in heart, shall praise the Lord.
verse_text: Quam magna misericordia Domini, et propitiatio illius convertentibus ad se !

text: to be a curse, and an astonishment, and a hissing, and a reproach to all the nations to which I have driven them out:
verse_text: so shall my indignation be kindled against you, when you shall enter into Egypt, and you shall be an execration, and an astonishment, and a curse, and a reproach:

text: Who so teacheth a foole, is as one that gleweth a potsheard together, and as hee that waketh one from a sound sleepe.
verse_text: Qui docet fatuum, quasi qui conglutinat testam.

text: The word which came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, in the daies of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, saying,
verse_text: In the beginning of the reigne of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah came this worde vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, saying,

text: Propterea ecce dies veniunt, ait Dominus, et visitabo super sculptilia ejus, et in omni terra ejus mugiet vulneratus.
verse_text: Idcirco cadent juvenes ejus in plateis ejus, et omnes viri bellatores ejus conticescent in die illa, ait Dominus.

text: Let not the water flood drowne mee, neither let the deepe swallowe me vp: and let not the pit shut her mouth vpon me.
verse_text: Deliuer mee out of the myre, that I sinke not: let me be deliuered from them that hate me, and out of the deepe waters.

text: They wil curse, and thou shalt blesse: let them that rise vp against me, be confounded: but thy seruant shal reioyce.
verse_text: So all that hope in thee, shall not be ashamed: but let them be confounded, that transgresse without cause.

text: Qui autem gloriatur in paupertate, quanto magis in substantia ! et qui gloriatur in substantia, paupertatem vereatur.
verse_text: Melior est qui operatur et abundat in omnibus, quam qui gloriatur et eget pane.

text: Then giue place to the phisitian, for the Lord hath created him: let him not go from thee, for thou hast need of him.
verse_text: etenim illum Dominus creavit, et non discedat a te, quia opera ejus sunt necessaria.

text: Sic in decem millibus glorificavit eum: et laudavit eum in benedictionibus Domini, in offerendo illi coronam gloriae:
verse_text: Statuit ei testamentum aeternum, et dedit illi sacerdotium gentis, et beatificavit illum in gloria:

text: The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousnesse, according to the cleannesse of my hands hath hee recompensed me.
verse_text: Therefore hath the Lord recompensed me according to my righteousnesse, according to the cleannesse of my hands in his eye-sight.

text: To labour & to be content with that a man hath, is a sweet life: but hee that findeth a treasure, is aboue them both.
verse_text: Vita sibi sufficientis operarii condulcabitur, et in ea invenies thesaurum.

text: Emitte lucem tuam et veritatem tuam: ipsa me deduxerunt, et adduxerunt in montem sanctum tuum, et in tabernacula tua.
verse_text: et dedisti mihi protectionem salutis tuae: et dextera tua suscepit me, et disciplina tua correxit me in finem, et disciplina tua ipsa me docebit.

text: Quare tristis es, anima mea? et quare conturbas me? Spera in Deo, quoniam adhuc confitebor illi, salutare vultus mei,
verse_text: Dicam Deo: Susceptor meus es; quare oblitus es mei? et quare contristatus incedo, dum affligit me inimicus?

text: Audivit rex Babylonis famam eorum, et dissolutae sunt manus ejus: angustia apprehendit eum, dolor quasi parturientem.
verse_text: Infirmata est quae peperit septem; defecit anima ejus: occidit ei sol cum adhuc esset dies: confusa est, et erubuit: et residuos ejus in gladium dabo in conspectu inimicorum eorum, ait Dominus.

text: Hee that is mercifull, will lende vnto his neighbour, and hee that strengthneth his hande, keepeth the Commandements.
verse_text: Qui facit misericordiam foeneratur proximo suo: et qui praevalet manu mandata servat.

text: Lay vp thy treasure according to the commandements of the most high, and it shall bring thee more profite then golde.
verse_text: Verumtamen super humilem animo fortior esto, et pro eleemosyna non trahas illum.

text: What good doth the offering vnto an idole? for neither can it eat nor smell: so is he that is persecuted of the Lord.
verse_text: Quid proderit libatio idolo? nec enim manducabit, nec odorabit.

text: For it is a miserable life to goe from house to house: for where thou art a stranger, thou darest not open thy mouth.
verse_text: Repromissio nequissima multos perdidit dirigentes, et commovit illos quasi fluctus maris.

text: Whereas thy seruant worketh truely, entreate him not euill, nor the hireling that bestoweth himselfe wholly for thee.
verse_text: Noli praevaricari in amicum pecuniam differentem, neque fratrem carissimum auro spreveris.

text: He ruleth the worlde with his power: his eyes beholde the nations: the rebellious shall not exalt them selues. Selah.
verse_text: Let the people be glad and reioyce: for thou shalt iudge the people righteously, and gouerne the nations vpon the earth. Selah.

text: For strangers are risen vp against me, and oppressors seeke after my soule; they haue not set God before them. Selah.
verse_text: O God, the proude are risen against me, and the assemblies of violent men haue sought my soule, and haue not set thee before them.

text: God looked downe from heauen vpon the children of men, to see if there were any that would vnderstand, and seeke God.
verse_text: God hath looked forth from heauen, vpon the children of men: to see if there be that vnderstdeth, or seeketh after God.

text: And he chose Dauid his seruant, and tooke him from the flockes of sheepe: from after the ewes with yong he tooke him.
verse_text: From following the ewes great with young, hee brought him to feed Iacob his people, and Israel his inheritance.

text: In the beginning of the reigne of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, came this worde from the Lord, saying,
verse_text: The worde which came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, in the dayes of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah King of Iudah, saying,

text: Dixisti: Vae misero mihi ! quoniam addidit Dominus dolorem dolori meo: laboravi in gemitu meo, et requiem non inveni.
verse_text: Vae mihi super contritione mea: pessima plaga mea. Ego autem dixi: Plane haec infirmitas mea est, et portabo illam.

text: As a naile sticketh fast betweene the ioynings of the stones: so doth sinne sticke close betweene buying and selling.
verse_text: Sicut in medio compaginis lapidum palus figitur, sic et inter medium venditionis et emptionis angustiabitur peccatum:

text: Thus sayth the Lord, This citie shall surely be giuen into the hand of the King of Babels armie, which shall take it.
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord, Beholde, I wil giue this citie into the hand of the Caldeans, and into the hand of Nebuchad-nezzar, King of Babel, and he shall take it.

text: Recordatus est misericordiae suae, et veritatis suae domui Israel. Viderunt omnes termini terrae salutare Dei nostri.
verse_text: Et memor fuit testamenti sui, et poenituit eum secundum multitudinem misericordiae suae:

text: Misericordia autem Domini ab aeterno, et usque in aeternum super timentes eum. Et justitia illius in filios filiorum,
verse_text: et eduxit Israel per medium ejus, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus;

text: Miserere animae tuae placens Deo, et contine: congrega cor tuum in sanctitate ejus, et tristitiam longe repelle a te.
verse_text: et si humiliatus vadat curvus, adjice animum tuum, et custodi te ab illo.

text: Prayse the Lord, ye his Angels, that excell in strength, that doe his commandement in obeying the voyce of his worde.
verse_text: That they might keepe his statutes, and obserue his Lawes. Prayse ye the Lord.

text: And to turne away thy face from thy kinsman, or to take away a portion or a gift, or to gaze vpon another mans wife,
verse_text: Erubescite a patre et a matre de fornicatione: et a praesidente et a potente de mendacio:

text: He that hateth to be reprooued, is in the way of sinners: but hee that feareth the Lord, will repent from his heart.
verse_text: Deprecatio pauperis ex ore usque ad aures ejus perveniet, et judicium festinato adveniet illi.

text: The congregation of the wicked is like tow wrapped together: and the end of them is a flame of fire to destroy them.
verse_text: Qui aedificat domum suam impendiis alienis, quasi qui colligat lapides suos in hieme.

text: Who so honoureth his father, shal haue ioy of his owne children, and when he maketh his prayer, hee shall bee heard.
verse_text: Who so feareth the Lord, it shall goe well with him at the last, & he shall finde fauour in the day of his death.

text: And if thou seest a man of vnderstanding, get thee betimes vnto him, and let thy foote weare the steps of his doore.
verse_text: If thou be among the vndiscreet, obserue the time: but be continually among men of vnderstanding.

text: They haue hands, but they handle not, feete haue they, but they walke not: neither speake they through their throat.
verse_text: They haue a mouth, and speake not: they haue eyes and see not.

text: He that pricketh the eye, wil make teares to fall: and he that pricketh the heart, maketh it to shewe her knowledge.
verse_text: Loramentum ligneum colligatum in fundamento aedificii non dissolvetur, sic et cor confirmatum in cogitatione consilii.

text: Custodi me, Domine, de manu peccatoris, et ab hominibus iniquis eripe me. Qui cogitaverunt supplantare gressus meos:
verse_text: Exsurge, Domine: praeveni eum, et supplanta eum: eripe animam meam ab impio; frameam tuam

text: The tree which thou sawest high and strong, whose height reacheth to heauen, and the sight therof into al the earth:
verse_text: The tree grew, and was strong, and the height thereof reached vnto heauen, and the sight thereof to the end of all the earth.

text: Is there no balm in Galaad? or is no physician there? Why then is not the wound of the daughter of my people closed?
verse_text: Go up into Galaad, and take balm, O virgin daughter of Egypt: in vain dost thou multiply medicines, there shall be no cure for thee.

text: a voce inimici, et a tribulatione peccatoris. Quoniam declinaverunt in me iniquitates, et in ira molesti erant mihi.
verse_text: Inimici autem mei vivunt, et confirmati sunt super me: et multiplicati sunt qui oderunt me inique.

text: The charets of God are twentie thousande thousand Angels, and the Lord is among them, as in the Sanctuarie of Sinai.
verse_text: The chariote of God is ten thousand folde, thousands of them that reioyce, our Lord in them, in Sina in the holie place.

text: Aspexi, et ecce Carmelus desertus, et omnes urbes ejus destructae sunt a facie Domini, et a facie irae furoris ejus.
verse_text: quoniam furor Domini erat in Jerusalem et in Juda, usquequo projiceret eos a facie sua: et recessit Sedecias a rege Babylonis.

text: With him that feareth the Lord, it shall go well in the latter end, and in the day of his death he shall be blessed.
verse_text: A wise man shall be filled with blessing, and all they that see him, shall count him happy.

text: They burnt the chosen citie of the Sanctuarie, and made the streets desolate according to the prophecie of Ieremias:
verse_text: nam reliquerunt legem Altissimi reges Juda, et contempserunt timorem Dei.

text: The goods of the vniust shall bee dried vp like a riuer, and shall vanish with noise, like a great thunder in raine.
verse_text: Substantiae injustorum sicut fluvius siccabuntur, et sicut tonitruum magnum in pluvia personabunt.

text: And Edom shall be desolate: every one that shall pass by it, shall be astonished, and shall hiss at all its plagues.
verse_text: Also Edom shall be desolate: euery one that goeth by it, shall be astonished, and shall hisse at all the plagues thereof,

text: Plantasti eos, et radicem miserunt: proficiunt, et faciunt fructum: prope es tu ori eorum, et longe a renibus eorum.
verse_text: Tu autem, Domine, scis omne consilium eorum adversum me in mortem: ne propitieris iniquitati eorum, et peccatum eorum a facie tua non deleatur: fiant corruentes in conspectu tuo; in tempore furoris tui abutere eis.

text: O King, thou art a king of Kings: for the God of heauen hath giuen thee a kingdome, power, and strength, and glorie.
verse_text: O thou king, the most high God gaue Nebuchad-nezzar thy father a kingdome, and maiestie, and glory, and honour.

text: There is a companion, which reioyceth in the prosperity of a friend: but in the time of trouble will be against him.
verse_text: For there is a friend for his own occasion, and he will not abide in the day of thy trouble.

text: They haue healed also the hurt of the daughter of my people sleightly, saying, Peace, peace, when there is no peace.
verse_text: And they healed the breach of the daughter of my people disgracefully, saying: Peace, peace: and there was no peace.

text: And I heard the voice of his wordes: and hearing I lay astonished vpon my face, and my visage cleaued to the ground.
verse_text: Yet heard I the voyce of his wordes: and when I heard the voyce of his wordes, I slept on my face: and my face was toward the ground.

text: In the beginning of the reigne of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah king of Iudah, came this word from the Lord, saying;
