verse_text: And it came to passe in the fourth yeere of Iehoiakim the sonne of Iosiah king of Iudah, that this word came vnto Ieremiah from the Lord, saying;

text: There is a companion, which reioyceth in the prosperity of a friend: but in the time of trouble will be against him.
verse_text: Sodalis amico conjucundatur in oblectationibus, et in tempore tribulationis adversarius erit.

text: They compassed me as bees, and were inflamed as fyre in thornes: and in the name of our Lord I was reuenged on them.
verse_text: Thou shalt put them as an ouen of fyre in the time of thy countenance: our Lord in his wrath shal truble them, and fyre shal deuoure them.

text: and ye shall be an execration, and an astonishment, and a curse, and a reproch, and ye shall see this place no more.
verse_text: and they shall be for an execration, and for a wonder, and for a curse, and for a reproach.

text: Sicut ficus hae bonae, sic cognoscam transmigrationem Juda, quam emisi de loco isto in terram Chaldaeorum, in bonum.
verse_text: Ego percussi foedus cum patribus vestris in die qua eduxi eos de terra AEgypti, de domo servitutis, dicens:

text: These things are grievous to a man of understanding: the upbraiding of houseroom, and the reproaching of the lender.
verse_text: For a passionate man kindleth strife, and a sinful man will trouble his friends, and bring in debate in the midst of them that are at peace.

text: Why leape ye, ye high hilles? this is the Hil which God desireth to dwell in, yea the Lord will dwel in it for euer.
verse_text: This is my rest for euer and euer: here wil I dwel because I haue chosen it.

text: Kepe me o Lord from the hand of the sinner: and from vniust men deliuer me. Who haue deuised to supplant my steppes:
verse_text: And from them that rise vp against me thou wilt exalt me: from the vniust man thou wilt deliuer me.

text: Therefore shall her yong men fall in the streets, & all her men of war shall be cut off in that day, saith the Lord.
verse_text: Therefore her yong men shall fall in her streetes, and all her men of warre shall be cut off in that day, sayeth the Lord of hostes.

text: And if thou seest a man of vnderstanding, get thee betimes vnto him, and let thy foote weare the steps of his doore.
verse_text: Et si videris sensatum, evigila ad eum, et gradus ostiorum illius exterat pes tuus.

text: Who so honoureth his father, shal haue ioy of his owne children, and when he maketh his prayer, hee shall bee heard.
verse_text: Et sicut qui thesaurizat, ita et qui honorificat matrem suam.

text: A Psalme or song for the Sabbath day. It is a good thing to praise the Lord, and to sing vnto thy Name, O most High,
verse_text: Praise ye the Lord: for it is good to sing praises vnto our God: for it is pleasant, and praise is comely.

text: The mountaines also, and foundations of the earth shall bee shaken with trembling, when the Lord looketh vpon them.
verse_text: Montes simul, et colles, et fundamenta terrae, cum conspexerit illa Deus, tremore concutientur.

text: For thus saith the Lord to the men of Iudah and Ierusalem, Breake vp your fallow ground, and sow not among thornes.
verse_text: For thus sayth the Lord, Enter not into the house of mourning, neither goe to lament nor bemoane them: for I haue taken away my peace from this people, sayth the Lord, euen louing kindnesse and mercies.

text: Thus sayth the Lord of hostes, the God of Israel, Put your burnt offerings vnto your sacrifices, and eat the flesh.
verse_text: For thus saith the Lord of hostes the God of Israel; Houses and fields, and Uineyards shalbe possessed againe in this land.

text: Dissipati sunt, nec compuncti; tentaverunt me, subsannaverunt me subsannatione; frenduerunt super me dentibus suis.
verse_text: Multiplicati sunt super capillos capitis mei qui oderunt me gratis. Confortati sunt qui persecuti sunt me inimici mei injuste; quae non rapui, tunc exsolvebam.

text: He that hath no experience, knoweth little: and he that hath been experienced in many things, multiplieth prudence.
verse_text: The wisdom of a scribe cometh by his time of leisure: and he that is less in action, shall receive wisdom.

text: Numquid resina non est in Galaad? aut medicus non est ibi? quare igitur non est obducta cicatrix filiae populi mei?
verse_text: Quare prophetavit in nomine Domini, dicens: Sicut Silo erit domus haec, et urbs ista desolabitur eo quod non sit habitator? Et congregatus est omnis populus adversus Jeremiam in domo Domini.

text: Et dispergam eos in gentibus quas non noverunt ipsi et patres eorum, et mittam post eos gladium, donec consumantur.
verse_text: Et ego congregabo reliquias gregis mei de omnibus terris ad quas ejecero eos illuc: et convertam eos ad rura sua, et crescent et multiplicabuntur.

text: And Asor shall be a habitation for dragons, desolate for ever: no man shall abide there, nor son of man inhabit it.
verse_text: Therefore shall dragons dwell there with the fig fauns: and ostriches shall dwell therein, and it shall be no more inhabited for ever, neither shall it be built up from generation to generation.

text: He called vpon the mighty Lord, when his enemies pressed vpon him on euery side, when he offered the sucking lambe.
verse_text: Dilectus a Domino Deo suo Samuel, propheta Domini, renovavit imperium, et unxit principes in gente sua.

text: And whilest they sinned not before their God, they prospered, because the God that hateth iniquitie, was with them.
verse_text: Et non fuit qui insultaret populo isti, nisi quando recessit a cultu Domini Dei sui.

text: There is not such a woman from one end of the earth to the other, both for beautie of face, and wisedome of wordes.
verse_text: et quoniam bona est promissio tua, si fecerit mihi hoc Deus tuus, erit et Deus meus, et tu in domo Nabuchodonosor magna eris, et nomen tuum nominabitur in universa terra.

text: Dies autem tertiusdecimus mensis Adar primus apud omnes interfectionis fuit, et quartadecima die caedere desierunt.
verse_text: At hi, qui in urbe Susan caedem exercuerant, tertiodecimo et quartodecimo die ejusdem mensis in caede versati sunt:

text: Blessed art thou, that beholdest the depths, and sittest vpon the Cherubs: and laudable, and superexalted for euer.
verse_text: Blessed art thou in the throne of thy kingdom, and passing laudable, and superexalted for euer.

text: They knew not, neither did they vnderstand, they walke in darkenesse: al the fundations of the earth shal be moued.
verse_text: There are the workers of iniquitie fallen: they are cast downe, and shal not be able to rise.

text: The Lord openeth the eyes of the blinde, the Lord raiseth them that are bowed downe: the Lord loueth the righteous.
verse_text: Which executeth iudgement for the oppressed, which giueth food to the hungry: the Lord looseth the prisoners.

text: Forgiue thy neighbour the hurt that he hath done vnto thee, so shall thy sinnes also be forgiuen when thou prayest.
verse_text: Relinque proximo tuo nocenti te, et tunc deprecanti tibi peccata solventur.

text: The hoare frost also as salt hee powreth on the earth, and being congealed, it lieth on the toppe of sharpe stakes.
verse_text: et sicut avis deponens ad sedendum, aspergit nivem, et sicut locusta demergens descensus ejus.

text: Audite verbum Domini, reges Juda, et omnis Juda, cunctique habitatores Jerusalem, qui ingredimini per portas istas.
verse_text: Vade, et sta in porta filiorum populi, per quam ingrediuntur reges Juda, et egrediuntur, et in cunctis portis Jerusalem:

text: Leaders of the people by their counsels, and learning meet for the people, wise and eloquent in their instructions.
verse_text: et imperantes in praesenti populo, et virtute prudentiae populis sanctissima verba:

text: The which Ieremiah the Prophet spake vnto all the people of Iudah, and to all the inhabitants of Ierusalem, saying,
verse_text: Then the prophet Ieremiah said vnto the prophet Hananiah in the presence of the priests, and in the presence of all the people, that stood in the house of the Lord,

text: For both the prophet and the Priest doe wickedly: and their wickednesse haue I found in mine House, saith the Lord.
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord God of Israel vnto the pastors that feede my people, Yee haue scattered my flock and thrust them out, and haue not visited them: beholde, I will visite you for the wickednesse of your works, saith the Lord.

text: A wise man shall promote himselfe to honour with his words: and hee that hath vnderstanding, will please great men.
verse_text: Potior fur quam assiduitas viri mendacis: perditionem autem ambo haereditabunt.

text: The affliction of an hour maketh one forget great delights, and in the end of a man is the disclosing of his works.
verse_text: For of sadness cometh death, and it overwhelmeth the strength, and the sorrow of the heart boweth down the neck.

text: They that saile on the Sea, tell of the danger thereof, and when wee heare it with our eares, wee marueile thereat.
verse_text: Medicina omnium in festinatione nebulae: et ros obvians ab ardore venienti humilem efficiet eum.

text: Blessed is he that shall be exercised in these things, and hee that layeth them vp in his heart, shall become wise.
verse_text: qui sedent in monte Seir, et Philisthiim, et stultus populus qui habitat in Sichimis.

text: Heare me, O Lord, for thy louing kindnesse is good: turne vnto mee according to the multitude of thy tendermercies.
verse_text: Heare my voice according vnto thy louing kindnesse: O Lord quicken me according to thy iudgement.

text: After this I saw in the visions by night, and beholde, the fourth beast was fearefull and terrible and very strong.
verse_text: After this I beheld in the vision of the night, and loe a fourth beast terrible and meruelous, and strong excedingly, it had great yron teeth, eating and breaking, and treading the rest with her fete:

text: Who so bringeth an offering of the goods of the poore, doeth as one that killeth the sonne before his fathers eyes.
verse_text: deprecatio offensionis, et adjutorium casus: exaltans animam, et illuminans oculos, dans sanitatem, et vitam, et benedictionem.

text: Benedicite, omnes religiosi, Domino Deo deorum: laudate et confitemini ei, quia in omnia saecula misericordia ejus.
verse_text: Benedicite, sancti et humiles corde, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Et fama turbabit eum ab oriente et ab aquilone: et veniet in multitudine magna ut conterat et interficiat plurimos.
verse_text: secundum voluntatem suam, et dirigetur dolus in manu ejus: et cor suum magnificabit, et in copia rerum omnium occidet plurimos: et contra principem principum consurget, et sine manu conteretur.

text: Hee sawe by an excellent spirit what should come to passe at the last, and hee comforted them that mourned in Sion.
verse_text: Dejecit castra Assyriorum, et contrivit illos angelus Domini:

text: Nabuchodonosor rex, omnibus populis, gentibus, et linguis, qui habitant in universa terra, pax vobis multiplicetur.
verse_text: Tunc rex ait: Paveant omnes habitantes in universa terra Deum Danielis: quia ipse est salvator, faciens signa et mirabilia in terra: qui liberavit Danielem de lacu leonum.

text: And the priests, and the prophets, and all the people heard Jeremias speaking these words in the house of the Lord.
verse_text: Then Jeremias spoke to all the princes, and to all the people, saying: The Lord sent me to prophesy concerning this house, and concerning this city all the words you have heard.

text: the voice of thy thunder in a wheele. Thy lightenings shined to the rounde world: the earth was moued and trubled.
verse_text: The earth was shaken & trembled: the fundations of mountaines were trubled, and were moued, because he was wrath with them.

text: Who wil iustifie him that sinneth against his owne soule? and who will honour him that dishonoureth his owne life?
verse_text: He that is hasty to giue credit is light minded, and he that sinneth shall offend against his owne soule.

text: But Ismahel the son of Nathanias fled with eight men, from the face of Johanan, and went to the children of Ammon.
verse_text: But Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah escaped from Iohanan with eight men, and went to the Ammonites.

text: Si reverteris, Israel, ait Dominus, ad me convertere: si abstuleris offendicula tua a facie mea, non commoveberis.
verse_text: Vade, et clama sermones istos contra aquilonem, et dices: Revertere, aversatrix Israel, ait Dominus, et non avertam faciem meam a vobis, quia sanctus ego sum, dicit Dominus, et non irascar in perpetuum.

text: And they bowed themselues downe to worship the second time, that they might receiue a blessing from the most High.
verse_text: Et rogavit populus Dominum excelsum in prece, usque dum perfectus est honor Domini, et munus suum perfecerunt.

text: Benedicite Domino, omnes angeli ejus: potentes virtute, facientes verbum illius, ad audiendam vocem sermonum ejus.
verse_text: Cantate Deo; psalmum dicite nomini ejus: iter facite ei qui ascendit super occasum. Dominus nomen illi; exsultate in conspectu ejus. Turbabuntur a facie ejus,

text: Gilead shalbe mine, and Manasseh shalbe mine: Ephraim also shalbe the strength of mine head: Iudah is my lawgiuer.
verse_text: Galaad is mine, and Manasses is mine: and Ephraim the protection of my head. Iuda is my king:

text: Let his heart bee changed from mans, and let a beasts heart be giuen vnto him, and let seuen times passe ouer him.
verse_text: That they shall driue thee from men, and thy dwelling shall be with the beasts of the field, and they shall make thee to eate grasse as oxen, and they shall wet thee with the dew of heauen, and seuen times shall passe ouer thee, till thou know that the most high ruleth in the kingdome of men, and giueth it to whomsoeuer he will.

text: Vpon the wicked he shall raine snares, fire, and brimstone, and stormie tempest: this is the porcion of their cup.
verse_text: He shal rayne snares vpon sinners: fyre and brimstone, and blast of stormes the portion of their cuppe.

text: Prima sabbati. Psalmus David. Domini est terra, et plenitudo ejus; orbis terrarum, et universi qui habitant in eo.
verse_text: Psalmus Asaph. Deus deorum Dominus locutus est, et vocavit terram a solis ortu usque ad occasum.

text: Quod facum est verbum Domini ad Jeremiam prophetam adversus AElam, in principio regni Sedeciae regis Juda, dicens:

text: Judge ye judgement in the morning, and deliver him that is oppressed by violence out of the hand of the oppressor:
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord, Execute ye iudgement and righteousnesse, and deliuer the spoiler out of the hand of the oppressour:

text: Remember that thou wast begot of them, and how canst thou recompense them the things that they haue done for thee?
verse_text: Mulier si est tibi secundum animam tuam, non projicias illam: et odibili non credas te. In toto corde tuo

text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel: Add your burnt offerings to your sacrifices, and eat ye the flesh.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel: Make your ways and your doings good: and I will dwell with you in this place.

text: Thus saith the Lord vnto me; Goe and get thee a linen girdle, and put it vpon thy loynes, and put it not in water.
verse_text: Take the girdle that thou hast bought, which is vpon thy loynes, and arise, goe towarde Perath, and hide it there in the cleft of the rocke.

text: Then Iudeth began to sing this thankesgiuing in all Israel, and all the people sang after her this song of praise.
verse_text: Tunc cantavit canticum hoc Domino Judith, dicens:

text: Then euery man of Israel cryed to God with great feruencie, and with great vehemency did they humble their soules:
verse_text: Et induerunt se sacerdotes ciliciis, et infantes prostraverunt contra faciem templi Domini, et altare Domini operuerunt cilicio:

text: Who wil iustifie him that sinneth against his owne soule? and who will honour him that dishonoureth his owne life?
verse_text: Noli extollere te in faciendo opere tuo, et noli cunctari in tempore angustiae.

text: Quam sufficiens est homini eruditio vinum exiguum ! et in dormiendo non laborabis ab illo, et non senties dolorem.
verse_text: Noli attendere ad possessiones iniquas, et ne dixeris: Est mihi sufficiens vita: nihil enim proderit in tempore vindictae et obductionis.

text: A Psalme of David. Blessed be the Lord my strength, which teacheth mine hands to fight, and my fingers to battell.
verse_text: A Psalme of Dauid, against Goliath. BLESSED be our Lord my God, who teacheth my handes to battel; and my fingers to warre.

text: Let these thinges be written vnto an other generation: and the people, that shal be created, shal praise our Lord.
verse_text: that an other generation may know. The children that shal be borne, and shal rise vp, and shal tel their children.

text: Set vp the standards toward Zion: retyre, stay not; for I will bring euil from the North, and a great destruction.
verse_text: O ye children of Beniamin, prepare to flee out of the middes of Ierusalem, and blowe the trumpet in Tekoa: set vp a standart vpon Beth-haccerem: for a plague appeareth out of the North and great destruction.

text: Mount Sion is founded with the exultation of the whole earth, the sides of the North, the citie of the great king.
verse_text: Princes of peoples are gathered together with the God of Abraham: because the strong goddes of the earth, are excedingly aduanced.

text: Bring out also the speare and stop the way against them, that persecute me: say vnto my soule, I am thy saluation.
verse_text: Arise, O Lord, disappoint him, cast him downe: deliuer my soule from the wicked, which is thy sword:

text: Giue vnto the most high, according as hee hath enriched thee, and as thou hast gotten, giue with a cheerefull eye.
verse_text: Bono animo gloriam redde Deo, et non minuas primitias manuum tuarum.

text: Wisedome, knowledge, and vnderstanding of the Lawe, are of the Lord: loue, & the way of good workes, are from him.
verse_text: sapientia, et disciplina, et scientia legis, apud Deum: dilectio, et viae bonorum, apud ipsum.

text: Then came all the Kings wise men, but they could neither reade the writing, nor shewe the King the interpretation.
verse_text: Therefore made I a decree, to bring in all the wise men of Babylon before mee, that they might make knowen vnto me the interpretation of the dreame.

text: Shal I not visit them for these things, saith the Lord? or shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?
verse_text: Shall I not visit for these things, sayth the Lord, and shall not my soule bee auenged on such a nation as this?

text: For they haue healed the hurt of the daughter of my people slightly, saying, Peace, peace, when there is no peace.
verse_text: And they healed the breach of the daughter of my people disgracefully, saying: Peace, peace: and there was no peace.

text: For the glory of a man, is from the honour of his father, and a mother in dishonour, is a reproch to the children.
verse_text: A son ill taught is the confusion of the father: and a foolish daughter shall be to his loss.

text: For the relieuing of thy father shall not be forgotten: and in stead of sinnes it shall be added to build thee vp.
verse_text: Fili, suscipe senectam patris tui, et non contristes eum in vita illius:

text: For the glory of a man, is from the honour of his father, and a mother in dishonour, is a reproch to the children.
verse_text: Benedictio patris firmat domos filiorum: maledictio autem matris eradicat fundamenta.

text: Vnderstand these things you that forget God: lest sometime he take you violently and there be none to deliuer you.
verse_text: Least he deuoure my soule like a lion, and teare it in pieces, while there is none to helpe.

text: et percussit eos rex Babylonis, et interfecit eos in Reblatha in terra Emath: et translatus est Juda de terra sua.
verse_text: Et occidit rex Babylonis filios Sedeciae in Reblatha, in oculis ejus: et omnes nobiles Juda occidit rex Babylonis.

text: quoniam suavis est Dominus, in aeternum misericordia ejus, et usque in generationem et generationem veritas ejus.
verse_text: Qui fecit caelos in intellectu, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: et intelligam in via immaculata: quando venies ad me? Perambulabam in innocentia cordis mei, in medio domus meae.
verse_text: Dixi: Custodiam vias meas: ut non delinquam in lingua mea. Posui ori meo custodiam, cum consisteret peccator adversum me.

text: He that tilleth his land, shall increase his heape: and he that pleaseth great men, shal get pardon for iniquity.
verse_text: Mores hominum mendacium sine honore, et confusio illorum cum ipsis sine intermissione.

text: For the which cause our fathers were giuen to the sword, & for a spoile, and had a great fall before our enemies.
verse_text: pro quo scelere dati sunt in gladium, et in rapinam, et in confusionem inimicis suis: nos autem alterum deum nescimus praeter ipsum.

text: He that toucheth pitch, shall be defiled with it: and he that hath fellowship with the proud, shall put on pride.
verse_text: He that loveth gold, shall not be justified: and he that followeth after corruption, shall be filled with it.

text: And render to our neighboures seuenfold in their bosome: their reproch wherewith they haue reproched thee o Lord.
verse_text: Because the zele of thy house hath eaten me: and the reproches of them that reproched thee, fel vpon me.

text: Haue respect to me, and haue mercie on me, giue thine empire to thy seruant: and saue the sonne of thy handmaide.
verse_text: Turne vnto me, and haue mercy vpon me: giue thy strength vnto thy seruant, and saue the sonne of thine handmayd.

text: Thus speaketh the Lord God of Israel, saying, Write thee all the wordes, that I haue spoken vnto thee in a booke.
verse_text: And say thou vnto them, Thus sayeth the Lord God of Israel, Cursed be the man that obeyeth not the wordes of this couenant,

text: Exaudi me, Domine, quoniam benigna est misericordia tua; secundum multitudinem miserationum tuarum respice in me.
verse_text: Vau Et veniat super me misericordia tua, Domine; salutare tuum secundum eloquium tuum.

text: Ideo cadent juvenes ejus in plateis ejus, et omnes viri praelii conticescent in die illa, ait Dominus exercituum.
verse_text: propterea haec dicit Dominus exercituum: Ecce ego visitabo super eos: juvenes morientur in gladio; filii eorum et filiae eorum morientur in fame.

text: Who so feareth the Lord, it shall goe well with him at the last, & he shall finde fauour in the day of his death.
verse_text: He that honoureth his father, shal haue a long life, and he that is obedient vnto the Lord, shall bee a comfort to his mother.

text: How great is the louing kindnes of the Lord our God, and his compassion vnto such as turne vnto him in holinesse?
verse_text: Nec enim omnia possunt esse in hominibus, quoniam non est immortalis filius hominis, et in vanitate malitiae placuerunt.

text: Through thee will wee push downe our enemies: through thy Name will wee tread them vnder that rise vp against vs.
verse_text: In thee we shal turne out our enemies with the horne, & in thy name we shal contemne them that ryse vp against vs.

text: As one that letteth a bird goe out of his hand, so hast thou let thy neighbour goe; and shalt not get him againe.
verse_text: Quod si denudaveris absconsa illius, non persequeris post eum.

text: Wine and women will make men of vnderstanding to fall away, and he that cleaueth to harlots will become impudent.
verse_text: Vinum et mulieres apostatare faciunt sapientes, et arguent sensatos.

text: Whether it be to friend or foe, talk not of other mens liues, and if thou canst without offence reueale them not.
verse_text: Amico et inimico noli narrare sensum tuum: et si est tibi delictum, noli denudare:

text: Heare my prayer, O Lord, giue eare to my supplications: in thy faithfulnesse answere me, and in thy righteousnes.
verse_text: Pleade my cause, and deliuer me: quicken me according vnto thy word.

text: Let burning coales fall vpon them, let them be cast into the fire: into deepe pits, that they rise not vp againe.
verse_text: Let death seaze vpon them, and let them goe downe quicke into hell: for wickednes is in their dwellings, and among them.

text: These things are grieuous to a man of vnderstanding: the vpbraiding of house-roome, and reproching of the lender.
verse_text: But a griefe of heart and sorrow, is a woman that is ielous ouer another woman, and a scourge of the tongue which communicateth withall.

text: Idcirco cadent juvenes ejus in plateis ejus, et omnes viri bellatores ejus conticescent in die illa, ait Dominus.
verse_text: Propterea ecce dies veniunt, ait Dominus, et visitabo super sculptilia ejus, et in omni terra ejus mugiet vulneratus.

text: To him that excelleth. A Psalme of David. Deliuer me, O Lord, from the euill man: preserue me from the cruel man:
verse_text: A Psalme of Dauid. IVDGE me o God, & discerne my cause from the nation not holie, from the vniust and deceitful man deliuer me.

text: Shall I not visit them for these things, saith the Lord ? shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?
verse_text: Shall I not visit for these things, sayth the Lord, and shall not my soule bee auenged on such a nation as this?

text: And he said vnto them, Beware of all vnrighteousnes, and he gaue euery man commandement concerning his neighbour,
verse_text: In unamquamque gentem praeposuit rectorem:

text: These things are grieuous to a man of vnderstanding: the vpbraiding of house-roome, and reproching of the lender.
verse_text: Initium vitae hominis, aqua et panis, et vestimentum, et domus protegens turpitudinem.

text: Draw out also the speare, and stop the way against them that persecute me: say vnto my soule, I am thy saluation.
verse_text: Arise, O Lord, disappoint him, cast him downe: deliuer my soule from the wicked, which is thy sword:

text: Tollens ergo princeps militiae Jeremiam, dixit ad eum: Dominus Deus tuus locutus est malum hoc super locum istum:
verse_text: Venit autem Jeremias de Topheth, quo miserat eum Dominus ad prophetandum, et stetit in atrio domus Domini, et dixit ad omnem populum:

text: Thus speaketh the Lord God of Israel, saying; Write thee all the wordes that I haue spoken vnto thee, in a booke.
verse_text: And say thou vnto them, Thus sayeth the Lord God of Israel, Cursed be the man that obeyeth not the wordes of this couenant,

text: The proude haue layde a snare for me, and spred a nette with cordes in my pathway, and set grennes for me. Selah.
verse_text: They haue prepared a net for my steppes, my soule is bowed downe: they haue digged a pit before me, into the midst whereof they are fallen themselues. Selah.

text: My mouth shall shew foorth thy righteousnesse, and thy saluation all the day: for I know not the numbers thereof.
verse_text: And my tongue shall speake of thy righteousnesse, and of thy praise all the day long.

text: The feare of the Lord goeth before the obtayning of authoritie: but roughnesse and pride, is the loosing thereof.
verse_text: Memoria superborum perdidit Deus, et reliquit memoriam humilium sensu.

text: Vae duplici corde, et labiis scelestis, et manibus malefacientibus, et peccatori terram ingredienti duabus viis !
verse_text: de altitudine ventris inferi, et a lingua coinquinata, et a verbo mendacii, a rege iniquo, et a lingua injusta.

text: Who so feareth the Lord, it shall goe well with him at the last, & he shall finde fauour in the day of his death.
verse_text: Timenti Dominum bene erit in extremis, et in die defunctionis suae benedicetur.

text: In manu artificum opera laudabuntur, et princeps populi in sapientia sermonis sui, in sensu vero seniorum verbum.
verse_text: in lingua enim sapientia dignoscitur: et sensus, et scientia, et doctrina in verbo sensati, et firmamentum in operibus justitiae.

text: Because they haue hid the destruction of their snare for me without cause: in vaine haue they vpbrayded my soule.
verse_text: the proude haue hid a snare for me: And they haue stretched out ropes for a snare: they haue layd a stumbling blocke for me nere the way.

text: Gilead shalbe mine, and Manasseh shalbe mine: Ephraim also shalbe the strength of mine head: Iuda is my lawgiuer.
verse_text: Galaad is mine, and Manasses is mine: and Ephraim the protection of my head. Iuda is my king:

text: But I am poore and needy, make haste vnto me, O God: Thou art my helpe and my deliuerer, O Lord make no tarrying.
verse_text: Though I be poore and needie, the Lord thinketh on mee: thou art mine helper and my deliuerer: my God, make no tarying.

text: When the dead is at rest, let his remembrance rest, & be comforted for him, when his spirit is departed from him.
verse_text: Memor esto judicii mei: sic enim erit et tuum: mihi heri, et tibi hodie.

text: egressus est Jeremias de Jerusalem ut iret in terram Benjamin, et divideret ibi possessionem in conspectu civium.
verse_text: Venit autem Jeremias ad Godoliam filium Ahicam in Masphath, et habitavit cum eo in medio populi qui relictus fuerat in terra.

text: But if thou hide thy face, they are troubled: if thou take away their breath, they dye and returne to their dust.
verse_text: But thou turning away the face, they shal be trubled: thou shalt take away their spirite, and they shal faile, and shal returne into their dust.

text: In via ruinae non eas, et non offendes in lapides: nec credas te viae laboriosae, ne ponas animae tuae scandalum.
verse_text: Fili, ne in multis sint actus tui: et si dives fueris, non eris immunis a delicto. Si enim secutus fueris, non apprehendes: et non effugies, si praecucurreris.

text: Rise not vp (in anger) at the presence of an iniurious person, least he lie in waite to entrap thee in thy words.
verse_text: Non te praetereat narratio seniorum, ipsi enim didicerunt a patribus suis:

text: Introeat in conspectu tuo gemitus compeditorum; secundum magnitudinem brachii tui posside filios mortificatorum:
verse_text: Respice in testamentum tuum, quia repleti sunt qui obscurati sunt terrae domibus iniquitatum.

text: And the residue that dwelt at Bethulia, fell vpon the campe of Assur, and spoiled them, & were greatly enriched.
verse_text: Omnis itaque regio, omnisque urbs electam juventutem armatam misit post eos, et persecuti sunt eos in ore gladii, quousque pervenirent ad extremitatem finium suorum.

text: Extend thy louing kindnes vnto them that knowe thee, and thy righteousnesse vnto them that are vpright in heart.
verse_text: And they that know thy Name, will trust in thee: for thou, Lord, hast not failed them that seeke thee.

text: And when shee had left off speaking, the people shouted with a lowd voice, & made a ioyful noise in their citie.
verse_text: Porro hi qui in tabernaculo erant, venientes, et ante ingressum cubiculi perstrepentes, excitandi gratia, inquietudinem arte moliebantur, ut non ab excitantibus, sed a sonantibus Holofernes evigilaret.

text: Shall I not visit for these things, sayth the Lord, and shall not my soule bee auenged on such a nation as this?
verse_text: Shal I not visit them for these things, saith the Lord? or shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?

text: There is that destroyeth his owne soule through bashfulnesse, and by accepting of persons ouerthroweth himselfe.
verse_text: Ex ore fatui reprobabitur parabola: non enim dicit illam in tempore suo.

text: Confusi sunt sapientes; perterriti et capti sunt: verbum enim Domini projecerunt, et sapientia nulla est in eis.
verse_text: Super eum rugierunt leones, et dederunt vocem suam: posuerunt terram ejus in solitudinem. Civitates ejus exustae sunt, et non est qui habitet in eis.

text: But they have gone after the perverseness of their own heart, and after Baalim, which their fathers taught them.
verse_text: And you also have done worse than your fathers: for behold every one of you walketh after the perverseness of his evil heart, so as not to hearken to me.

text: Hear ye therefore the word of the Lord, all ye of the captivity, whom I have sent out from Jerusalem to Babylon.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel, to all that are carried away captives, whom I have caused to be carried away from Jerusalem to Babylon:

text: And it came to pass when they had left off speaking, that Holofernes being in a violent passion, said to Achior:
verse_text: And all these words pleased Holofernes, and his servants, and they admired her wisdom, and they said one to another:

text: The Lord hardened Pharaoh, that hee should not know him, that his powerfull workes might be knowen to the world.
verse_text: Omnis misericordia faciet locum unicuique, secundum meritum operum suorum, et secundum intellectum peregrinationis ipsius.

text: Speciosus forma prae filiis hominum, diffusa est gratia in labiis tuis: propterea benedixit te Deus in aeternum.
verse_text: Dilexisti justitiam, et odisti iniquitatem; propterea unxit te Deus, Deus tuus, oleo laetitiae, prae consortibus tuis.

text: Psalmus David. Judica me, Deus, et discerne causam meam de gente non sancta: ab homine iniquo et doloso erue me.
verse_text: In finem. Psalmus David. Judica me, Domine, quoniam ego in innocentia mea ingressus sum, et in Domino sperans non infirmabor.

text: A sword upon her diviners, and they shall be foolish: a sword upon her valiant ones, and they shall be dismayed.
verse_text: A sworde is vpon the soothsaiers, and they shall dote: a sword is vpon her strong men, and they shalbe afraide.

text: Quomodo confractus est et contritus malleus universae terrae? quomodo versa est in desertum Babylon in gentibus?
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum: Ecce afflictio egredietur de gente in gentem, et turbo magnus egredietur a summitatibus terrae.

text: God hath spoken in his holie: I shal reioyce, and shal diuide Sichem: and shal mesure the valley of tabernacles.
verse_text: God hath spoken in his holines: therefore I will reioyce: I shall deuide Shechem, and measure the valley of Succoth.

text: A wise sentence shall be reiected when it commeth out of a fools mouth: for he will not speake it in due season.
verse_text: Lapsus falsae linguae quasi qui in pavimento cadens: sic casus malorum festinanter veniet.

text: To slip vpon a pauement, is better then to slip with the tongue: so, the fall of the wicked shall come speedily.
verse_text: qui enim edunt panem illius, falsae linguae sunt. Quoties et quanti irridebunt eum !

text: I haue called vpon thee: surely thou wilt heare me, O God: incline thine eare to me, and hearken vnto my wordes.
verse_text: Therefore I saide vnto the Lord, Thou art my God: heare, O Lord, the voyce of my prayers.

text: He that feareth the Lord, will receive his discipline: and they that will seek him early, shall find a blessing.
verse_text: They that fear the Lord, will seek after the things that are well pleasing to him: and they that love him, shall be filled with his law.

text: Sollicitus sum propter Judaeos qui transfugerunt ad Chaldaeos, ne forte tradar in manus eorum, et illudant mihi.
verse_text: Ecce ego habito in Masphath, ut respondeam praecepto Chaldaeorum qui mittuntur ad nos:

text: Et factum est in anno quarto Joakim filii Josiae regis Juda, factum est verbum hoc ad Jeremiam a Domino, dicens:
verse_text: Quod facum est verbum Domini ad Jeremiam prophetam adversus AElam, in principio regni Sedeciae regis Juda, dicens:

text: For I haue said, Mercie shall bee built vp for euer: thy faithfulnesse shalt thou establish in the very heauens.
verse_text: Thy faithfulnesse is vnto all generations: thou hast established the earth, and it abideth.

text: Sicut adduxi super populum istum omne malum hoc grande, sic adducam super eos omne bonum quod ego loquor ad eos.
verse_text: et dispergam eos in omnem ventum, qui sunt attonsi in comam, et ex omni confinio eorum adducam interitum super eos, ait Dominus.

text: Like as a Partrich taken in a cage, so is the heart of the proud; and like as a spie, watcheth hee for thy fall.
verse_text: Ante mortem ne laudes hominem quemquam: quoniam in filiis suis agnoscitur vir.

text: donec venit antiquus dierum, et judicium dedit sanctis Excelsi, et tempus advenit, et regnum obtinuerunt sancti.
verse_text: In sententia vigilum decretum est, et sermo sanctorum, et petitio: donec cognoscant viventes quoniam dominatur Excelsus in regno hominum, et cuicumque voluerit, dabit illud, et humillimum hominem constituet super eum.

text: Yet do I remember the time past: I meditate in all thy workes, yea, I doe meditate in the workes of thine hands.
verse_text: O God, thou hast taught me from my youth euen vntill nowe: therefore will I tell of thy wonderous workes,

text: He rebuked the Red sea also, and it was dried vp: so hee led them through the depthes, as through the wildernes.
verse_text: He deuided the Sea, and led them through: he made also the waters to stand as an heape.

text: Therefore we have obeyed the voice of Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father, in all things that he commanded us:
verse_text: Because you have obeyed the commandment of Jonadab your father, and have kept all his precepts, and have done all that he commanded you:

text: Search and seeke, and shee shall bee made knowen vnto thee, and when thou hast got hold of her, let her not goe.
verse_text: In omni animo tuo accede ad illam, et in omni virtute tua conserva vias ejus.

text: He that honoureth his father shall have joy in his own children, and in the day of his prayer he shall be heard.
verse_text: With him that feareth the Lord, it shall go well in the latter end, and in the day of his death he shall be blessed.

text: Domine Deus noster, tu exaudiebas eos; Deus, tu propitius fuisti eis, et ulciscens in omnes adinventiones eorum.
verse_text: Vides, quoniam tu laborem et dolorem consideras, ut tradas eos in manus tuas. Tibi derelictus est pauper; orphano tu eris adjutor.

text: If thou set thy seruant to labour, thou shalt finde rest: but if thou let him goe idle, he shall seeke libertie.
verse_text: Cibaria, et virga, et onus asino: panis, et disciplina, et opus servo.

text: Turne vnto me, and haue mercy vpon me: giue thy strength vnto thy seruant, and saue the sonne of thine handmayd.
verse_text: And hide not thy face from thy seruant, for I am in trouble: make haste and heare me.

text: Marrie thy daughter, and so shalt thou haue performed a weightie matter: but giue her to a man of vnderstanding.
verse_text: Filii tibi sunt? erudi illos, et curva illos a pueritia illorum.

text: But we haue remained in tentes, and haue obeyed, and done according to all that Ionadab our father commanded vs.
verse_text: Thus haue wee obeyed the voyce of Ionadab the sonne of Rechab our father, in all that he hath charged vs, and wee drinke no wine all our dayes, neither wee, our wiues, our sonnes, nor our daughters.

text: But haue walked after the stubbernesse of their owne heart, and after Baalims, which their fathers taught them,
verse_text: (And ye haue done worse then your fathers: for beholde, you walke euery one after the stubbernesse of his wicked heart, and will not heare me)

text: And when he spake to me in these maner of wordes, I cast downe my countenance to the ground, and held my peace.
verse_text: Yet heard I the voice of his words: and when I heard the voice of his wordes, then was I in a deepe sleepe on my face, and my face toward the ground.

text: Ego autem, sicut oliva fructifera in domo Dei; speravi in misericordia Dei, in aeternum et in saeculum saeculi.
verse_text: Timor Domini sanctus, permanens in saeculum saeculi; judicia Domini vera, justificata in semetipsa,

text: And Jeremias said to Saraias: When thou shalt come into Babylon, and shalt see, and shalt read all these words,
verse_text: But if the princes shall hear that I have spoken with thee, and shall come to thee, and say to thee: Tell us what thou hast said to the king, hide it not from us, and we will not kill thee: and also what the king said to thee:

text: Misericordias Domini in aeternum cantabo; in generationem et generationem annuntiabo veritatem tuam in ore meo.
verse_text: Ego autem cantabo fortitudinem tuam, et exsultabo mane misericordiam tuam: quia factus es susceptor meus, et refugium meum in die tribulationis meae.

text: When Michaiah the sonne of Gemariah the sonne of Shaphan had heard out of the booke, all the words of the Lord;
verse_text: And Baruch the sonne of Neriah did according to all that Ieremiah the Prophet commanded him, reading in the booke the wordes of the Lord, in the Lords house.

text: A Psalme of David of Praise. O my God and King, I will extold thee, and will blesse thy Name for euer and euer.
verse_text: To him that excelleth vpon Muth Laben. A Psalme of Dauid. I will praise the Lord with my whole heart: I will speake of all thy marueilous workes.

text: Et omnia opera illorum velut sol in conspectu Dei: et oculi ejus sine intermissione inspicientes in viis eorum.
verse_text: Opera omnis carnis coram illo, et non est quidquam absconditum ab oculis ejus.

text: Samuel the Prophet of the Lord, beloued of his Lord, established a kingdom, & anointed princes ouer his people.
verse_text: Et judices singuli suo nomine, quorum non est corruptum cor, qui non aversi sunt a Domino,

text: For my people is foolish, they haue not knowen me, they are sottish children, and they haue none vnderstanding:
verse_text: they are foolish children, and haue none vnderstanding:

text: He called vpon the most high Lord, when the enemies pressed vpon him on euery side, & the great Lord heard him.
verse_text: But they called vpon the Lord which is mercifull, and stretched out their hands towards him, and immediatly the holy One heard them out of heauen, and deliuered them by the ministery of Esay.

text: Say not thou, It is through the Lord, that I fell away, for thou oughtest not to doe the things that he hateth.
verse_text: Non dixeris: Per Deum abest: quae enim odit ne feceris.

text: and they shall be consumed from the least even to the greatest, by the sword, and by the famine shall they die:
verse_text: the young men shall die by the sword, their sonnes and their daughters shall die by famine.

text: I saw a dreame that made me sore afrayd: and my cogitations in my bed, and the visions of my head disturbed me.
verse_text: I Daniel was troubled in my spirit, in the middes of my body, and the visions of mine head made me afraide.

text: Heare yee therefore the word of the Lord, all ye of the captiuitie, whom I haue sent from Ierusalem to Babylon.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord, the God of Israel, Like these good figges, so will I acknowledge them that are caried away captiue of Iudah, whom I haue sent out of this place into the land of the Caldeans for their good.

text: And the kings seruants said vnto him, Behold, Haman standeth in the court. And the King saide, Let him come in.
verse_text: And the king said, Who is in the court? (now Haman was come into the outward court of the kings house, to speake vnto the king, to hang Mordecai on the gallons that hee had prepared for him.)

text: Behold, we the seruants of Nabuchodonosor the great king lie before thee; vse vs as shall be good in thy sight.
verse_text: Desinat indignatio tua circa nos: melius est enim ut viventes serviamus Nabuchodonosor regi magno, et subditi simus tibi, quam morientes cum interitu nostro ipsi servitutis nostrae damna patiamur.

text: The wisedome of a learned man cmeth by opportunitie of leasure: & he that hath litle busines shal become wise.
verse_text: In requie mortui requiescere fac memoriam ejus, et consolare illum in exitu spiritus sui.

text: And if his vnderstanding faile, haue patience with him, and despise him not, when thou art in thy ful strength.
verse_text: Gloria enim hominis ex honore patris sui, et dedecus filii pater sine honore.

text: The children of sinners, are abhominable children: and they that are conuersant in the dwelling of the vngodly.
verse_text: Noli metuere judicium mortis: memento quae ante te fuerunt, et quae superventura sunt tibi: hoc judicium a Domino omni carni.

text: Where no hedge is, there the possession is spoiled: and he that hath no wife will wander vp and downe mourning.
verse_text: Si est lingua curationis, est et mitigationis et misericordiae: non est vir illius secundum filios hominum.

text: From following the ewes great with young, hee brought him to feed Iacob his people, and Israel his inheritance.
verse_text: He chose Dauid also his seruant, and tooke him from the shepefolds.

text: To depart from wickednesse is a thing pleasing to the Lord: and to forsake vnrighteousnesse, is a propitiation.
verse_text: Et propitiationem litare sacrificii super injustitias: et deprecatio pro peccatis, recedere ab injustitia.

text: Perdamque ex eis vocem gaudii et vocem laetitiae, vocem sponsi et vocem sponsae, vocem molae et lumen lucernae.
verse_text: Quia haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Ecce ego auferam de loco isto, in oculis vestris, et in diebus vestris, vocem gaudii et vocem laetitiae, vocem sponsi et vocem sponsae.

text: And he spoke kindly to him, and he set his throne above the thrones of the kings that were with him in Babylon.
verse_text: And spake kindly vnto him, and set his throne aboue the throne of the Kings, that were with him in Babel,

text: Et introibo ad altare Dei, ad Deum qui laetificat juventutem meam. Confitebor tibi in cithara, Deus, Deus meus.
verse_text: In petra exaltavit me, et nunc exaltavit caput meum super inimicos meos. Circuivi, et immolavi in tabernaculo ejus hostiam vociferationis; cantabo, et psalmum dicam Domino.

text: Quoniam si bene direxeritis vias vestras, et studia vestra; si feceritis judicium inter virum et proximum ejus;
verse_text: Circuite vias Jerusalem, et aspicite, et considerate, et quaerite in plateis ejus, an inveniatis virum facientem judicium, et quaerentem fidem: et propitius ero ei.

text: Thus saith the Lord, the God of Israel, saying: Write thee all the words that I have spoken to thee, in a book.
verse_text: And thou shalt say to them: Thus saith the Lord the God of Israel: Cursed is the man that shall not hearken to the words of this covenant,

text: Shall I not visite for these things, sayth the Lord? or shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?
verse_text: Shall I not visit them for these things, saith the Lord ? shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?

text: Giue place thou stranger to an honourable man, my brother commeth to be lodged, and I haue neede of mine house.
verse_text: Recupera proximum secundum virtutem tuam, et attende tibi ne incidas.

text: Who will justify him that sinneth against his own soul? and who will honour him that dishonoureth his own soul?
verse_text: He that sinneth against his own soul, shall repent: and he that is delighted with wickedness, shall be condemned.

text: The power of the earth is in the hand of the Lord, and in due time hee will set ouer it one that is profitable.
verse_text: In manu Dei potestas terrae: et utilem rectorem suscitabit in tempus super illam.

text: And Daniel answered and sayde, The Name of God be praysed for euer and euer: for wisedome and strength are his,
verse_text: And at the ende of these dayes I Nebuchad-nezzar lift vp mine eyes vnto heauen, and mine vnderstanding was restored vnto me, and I gaue thankes vnto the most High, and I praysed and honoured him that liueth for euer, whose power is an euerlasting power, and his kingdome is from generation to generation.

text: Levate oculos vestros et videte, qui venitis ab aquilone: ubi est grex qui datus est tibi, pecus inclytum tuum?
verse_text: generatio vestra. Videte verbum Domini: numquid solitudo factus sum Israeli, aut terra serotina? quare ergo dixit populus meus: Recessimus; non veniemus ultra ad te?

text: He called vpon the most high Lord, when the enemies pressed vpon him on euery side, & the great Lord heard him.
verse_text: An non in iracundia ejus impeditus est sol, et una dies facta est quasi duo?

text: Blessed be the Lord God of Israel for euer and euer, and let all the people say, So be it. Praise yee the Lord.
verse_text: And blessed be his glorious Name for euer: and let all the earth be filled with his glorie. So be it, euen so be it. HERE END THE prayers of Dauid, the sonne of Ishai.

text: As the Sunne when it ariseth in the high heauen: so is the beautie of a good wife in the ordering of her house.
verse_text: Gratia mulieris sedulae delectabit virum suum, et ossa illius impinguabit.

text: O Lord, father and gouernour of all my whole life, leaue me not to their counsels, and let me not fall by them.
verse_text: Domine, pater et dominator vitae meae, ne derelinquas me in consilio eorum, nec sinas me cadere in illis.

text: The kings of the earth stood vp, and the princes came together in one against our Lord, and against his Christ.
verse_text: The Kings of the earth set themselues, and the rulers take counsell together, against the Lord, and against his Anoynted, saying,

text: Who so casteth a stone at the birds, frayeth them away, and he that vpbraideth his friend, breaketh friendship.
verse_text: Cogitatus sensati in omni tempore metu non depravabitur.

text: The talke of him that sweareth much, maketh the haire stand vpright: and their braules make one stop his eares.
verse_text: Narratio peccantium odiosa, et risus illorum in deliciis peccati.

text: A sworde is vpon the soothsaiers, and they shall dote: a sword is vpon her strong men, and they shalbe afraide.
verse_text: A sworde is vpon their horses and vpon their charets, and vpon all the multitude that are in the middes of her, and they shall be like women: a sworde is vpon her treasures, and they shall be spoyled.

text: A silent and louing woman is a gift of the Lord, and there is nothing so much worth, as a mind well instructed.
verse_text: Ab omni irreverentia oculorum ejus cave, et ne mireris si te neglexerit.

text: As the Sunne shining vpon the Temple of the most High, and as the rainebow giuing light in the bright cloudes.
verse_text: et quasi sol refulgens, sic ille effulsit in templo Dei.

text: But if it do euill in my sight and heare not my voyce, I will repent of ye good that I thought to do for them.
verse_text: If so bee they will hearken, and turne euery man from his euill way, that I may repent me of the euil which I purpose to doe vnto them, because of the euil of their doings.

text: In the congregation of the vngodly, shall a fire be kindled, and in a rebellious nation, wrath is set on fire.
verse_text: The congregation of sinners is like tow heaped together, and the end of them is a flame of fire.

text: Subito cecidit Babylon, et contrita est. Ululate super eam: tollite resinam ad dolorem ejus, si forte sanetur.
verse_text: Curavimus Babylonem, et non est sanata: derelinquamus eam, et eamus unusquisque in terram suam: quoniam pervenit usque ad caelos judicium ejus, et elevatum est usque ad nubes.

text: In the congregation of the vngodly, shall a fire be kindled, and in a rebellious nation, wrath is set on fire.
verse_text: Multa talia vidit oculis meus, et fortiora horum audivit auris mea.

text: His mercy is manifest to euery creature, and hee hath separated his light from the darkenesse with an Adamant.
verse_text: Non dicas: A Deo abscondar: et ex summo, quis mei memorabitur?

text: Keepe thy word & deale faithfully with him, and thou shalt alwaies finde the thing that is necessary for thee.
verse_text: Be faithfull to thy neighbour in his pouertie, that thou mayest reioyce in his prosperitie: abide stedfast vnto him in the time of his trouble, that thou mayest bee heire with him in his heritage: for a meane estate is not alwayes to be contemned, nor the rich that is foolish, to be had in admiration.

text: Doe not the workers of iniquitie knowe that they eate vp my people as they eate bread? they call not vpon God.
verse_text: Haue all the workers of iniquity no knowledge? who eate vp my people as they eate bread, and call not vpon the Lord.

text: Doe good vnto thy friend before thou die, and according to thy abilitie, stretch out thy hand and giue to him.
verse_text: Ante mortem benefac amico tuo, et secundum vires tuas exporrigens da pauperi.

text: For this thing my hart hath beene glad, and my tongue hath reioyced: moreouer also my flesh shal rest in hope.
verse_text: Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory reioyceth: my flesh also shall rest in hope.

text: Woe to thee, Moab, thou hast perished, O people of Chamos: for thy sons, and thy daughters are taken captives.
verse_text: For because thou hast trusted in thy bulwarks, and in thy treasures, thou also shalt be taken: and Chamos shall go into captivity, his priests, and his princes together.

text: Quod factum est verbum Domini ad eum in diebus Josiae filii Amon, regis Juda, in tertiodecimo anno regni ejus.
verse_text: In principio regni Joakim filii Josiae regis Juda, factum est verbum istud a Domino, dicens:

text: They inquire at the mouth of the wise man in the congregation, and they shall ponder his words in their heart.
verse_text: Cor fatui quasi vas confractum, et omnem sapientiam non tenebit.

text: Because I shal see thy heauens, the workes of thy fingers: the moone and the starres, which thou hast founded.
verse_text: They haue seene, O God, thy goings, the goings of my God, and my King, which art in the Sanctuarie.

text: Bowe downe thine eare to me, deliuer me speedily: be thou my strong rocke, for an house of defence to saue me.
verse_text: Be vnto me for a God protector, and for a fensed place: that thou maist saue me. Because thou art my firmament, and my refuge.

text: Confundantur et revereantur quaerentes animam meam; avertantur retrorsum et confundantur cogitantes mihi mala.
verse_text: Confundantur et deficiant detrahentes animae meae; operiantur confusione et pudore qui quaerunt mala mihi.

text: A wicked woman is giuen as a portion to a wicked man: but a godly woman is giuen to him that feareth the Lord.
verse_text: Columnae aureae super bases argenteas, et pedes firmi super plantas stabilis mulieris.

text: The rich hath great labour in gathering riches together, and when he resteth, he is filled with his delicates.
verse_text: Laboravit dives in congregatione substantiae, et in requie sua replebitur bonis suis.

text: Haec dicetis unusquisque ad proximum, et ad fratrem suum: Quid respondit Dominus? et quid locutus est Dominus?
verse_text: Et dices ad eos: Haec dicit Dominus: Numquid qui cadit non resurget? et qui aversus est non revertetur?

text: And by thee wil I breake horse and horseman, and by thee will I breake the charet and him that rideth therein.
verse_text: By thee also will I breake man and woman, and by thee wil I breake olde and yong, and by thee wil I breake the yong man and the mayde.

text: Better is the churlishnesse of a man, then a courteous woman, a woman I say, which bringeth shame and reproch.
verse_text: Melior est enim iniquitas viri quam mulier benefaciens, et mulier confundens in opprobrium.

text: Keepe thy word & deale faithfully with him, and thou shalt alwaies finde the thing that is necessary for thee.
verse_text: Confirma verbum, et fideliter age cum illo: et in omni tempore invenies quod tibi necessarium est.

text: For the hand of the artificer, the worke shall be commended: and the wise ruler of the people, for his speech.
verse_text: Non placeat tibi injuria injustorum, sciens quoniam usque ad inferos non placebit impius.

text: This shall be written for the generation to come: and the people, which shalbe created, shall prayse the Lord.
verse_text: They shall come, and shall declare his righteousnes vnto a people that shalbe borne, that he hath done this.

text: There shall no euill happen vnto him that feareth the Lord, but in temptation euen againe he will deliuer him.
verse_text: Timenti Dominum non occurrent mala: sed in tentatione Deus illum conservabit, et liberabit a malis. Sapiens non odit mandata et justitias,

text: This is the interpretation, O king, & this is the decree of the most Hie, which is come vpon my lord the king:
verse_text: This is the dreame: the interpretation also therof we wil tel before thee, o king.

text: By his commandment he maketh the snow to fall apace, and sendeth forth swiftly the lightnings of his judgment.
verse_text: By his greatness he hath fixed the clouds, and the hailstones are broken.

text: Et dabo eis cor unum, et viam unam, ut timeant me universis diebus, et bene sit eis, et filiis eorum post eos.
verse_text: Sed hoc erit pactum quod feriam cum domo Israel post dies illos, dicit Dominus: dabo legem meam in visceribus eorum, et in corde eorum scribam eam, et ero eis in Deum, et ipsi erunt mihi in populum:

text: The voyce of thy thunder was rounde about: the lightnings lightened the worlde: the earth trembled and shooke.
verse_text: His lightnings inlightned the world: the earth sawe, and trembled.

text: ne moreris propter temetipsum, Deus meus, quia nomen tuum invocatum est super civitatem et super populum tuum.
verse_text: et ostende faciem tuam super sanctuarium tuum, quod desertum est propter temetipsum.

text: Her sandals rauished his eyes, her beautie tooke his minde prisoner, and the fauchin passed through his necke.
verse_text: Exuit enim se vestimento viduitatis, et induit se vestimento laetitiae in exultatione filiorum Israel.

text: dixitque mihi: Ego ostendam tibi quae futura sunt in novissimo maledictionis: quoniam habet tempus finem suum.
verse_text: Respondit rex, et ait: Certe novi quod tempus redimitis, scientes quod recesserit a me sermo.

text: Let it not grieue thee to bowe downe thine eare to the poore, and giue him a friendly answere with meekenesse.
verse_text: Declina pauperi sine tristitia aurem tuam, et redde debitum tuum, et responde illi pacifica in mansuetudine.

text: And the sentence being gone forth, wisemen were slaine: & Daniel and his felowes were soughth for, to perish.
verse_text: Then Daniel answered with counsel and wisedome to Arioch the Kings chiefe stewarde, which was gone foorth to put to death the wise men of Babel.

text: Laudatio ipsi David. Exaltabo te, Deus meus rex, et benedicam nomini tuo in saeculum, et in saeculum saeculi.
verse_text: Sic psalmum dicam nomini tuo in saeculum saeculi, ut reddam vota mea de die in diem.

text: In the beginning of the reign of Joakim the son of Josias king of Juda, came this word from the Lord, saying:
verse_text: The word of the Lord which came to him in the days of Josias the son of Amon king of Juda, in the thirteenth year of his reign.

text: I will sing vnto the Lord a new song, O Lord thou art great and glorious, wonderful in strength & inuincible.
verse_text: Tunc ululaverunt castra Assyriorum, quando apparuerunt humiles mei, arescentes in siti.

text: haec enim dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Adhuc possidebuntur domus, et agri, et vineae in terra ista.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel: Adhuc dicent verbum istud in terra Juda et in urbibus ejus, cum convertero captivitatem eorum: Benedicat tibi Dominus, pulchritudo justitiae, mons sanctus:

text: Let thy hand be vpon the man of thy right hand: vpon the sonne of man, whom thou madest strong for thy selfe.
verse_text: Then thou spakest in vision to thy holy one, and saidst, I haue laid helpe vpon one that is mightie: I haue exalted one chosen out of the people.

text: The voice of thy thunder was in the heauen: the lightnings lightned the world, the earth trembled and shooke.
verse_text: The Lord also thundred in the heauen, and the Highest gaue his voyce, haylestones and coales of fire.

text: Doeth not the teares run downe the widowes cheeks? and is not her crie against him that causeth them to fall?
verse_text: Et noli inspicere sacrificum injustum, quoniam Dominus judex est, et non est apud illum gloria personae.

text: The children of the vngodly shall not bring forth many branches: but are as vncleane roots vpon a hard rocke.
verse_text: Nepotes impiorum non multiplicabunt ramos: et radices immundae super cacumen petrae sonant.

text: But thou goe, vntil the time prefixed: and thou shalt rest, and stand in thy lotte vnto the end of the dayes.
verse_text: But go thou thy way til the end be: for thou shalt rest and stand vp in thy lot, at the end of ye daies.

text: He that washeth himselfe after the touching of a dead body, if he touch it againe, what auaileth his washing?
verse_text: Panis egentium vita pauperum est: qui defraudat illum homo sanguinis est.

text: Then Nebuchad-nezzar in his anger and wrath commanded that they should bring Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego:
verse_text: Then was Nebuchad-nezzar full of furie, and the forme of his visage was changed against Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego:

text: Let thy speach be short, comprehending much in few words, be as one that knoweth, and yet holdeth his tongue.
verse_text: Sicut in fabricatione auri signum est smaragdi, sic numerus musicorum in jucundo et moderato vino.

text: And I saw him come vnto the ramme, and being moued against him, he smote the ramme, and brake his two hornes:
verse_text: and he brake his two hornes, and the ramme could not resist him:

text: He ruleth by his power for euer, his eyes behold the nations: let not the rebellious exalt themselues. Selah.
verse_text: And the heauens shall declare his righteousnes: for God is iudge himselfe. Selah.

text: The Sunne that giueth light, looketh vpon all things: and the worke thereof is full of the glory of the Lord.
verse_text: Sol illuminans per omnia respexit, et gloria Domini plenum est opus ejus.

text: The eye marueileth at the beauty of the whitenesse thereof, and the heart is astonished at the raining of it.
verse_text: Vox tonitrui ejus verberavit terram, tempestas aquilonis, et congregatio spiritus:

text: He that maketh too much of his sonne, shall binde vp his wounds, and his bowels wil be troubled at euery cry.
verse_text: Pro animabus filiorum colligabit vulnera sua, et super omnem vocem turbabuntur viscera ejus.

text: Saw a dreame, which made me afraide, and the thoughtes vpon my bed, and the visions of mine head troubled me.
verse_text: My spirit trembled, I Daniel was made sore afrayd at these thinges, and the visions of my head trubled me.

text: Et onagri steterunt in rupibus; traxerunt ventum quasi dracones: defecerunt oculi eorum, quia non erat herba.
verse_text: Propter terrae vastitatem, quia non venit pluvia in terram, confusi sunt agricolae: operuerunt capita sua.

text: And after the amities, he shal worke deceite with him: and he shal goe vp, and shal ouercome with few people.
verse_text: And his strength shal be made strong, but not in his owne strength: and more then can be beleued, shal he waste al thinges, and shal prosper, and doe. And he shal kil the strong, and the people of the saints

text: Audite vocem meam, et facite omnia quae praecipio vobis, et eritis mihi in populum, et ego ero vobis in Deum:
verse_text: et eritis mihi in populum, et ego ero vobis in Deum.

text: For without cause haue they hid for me their net in a pit, which without cause they haue digged for my soule.
verse_text: Because they haue hid the destruction of their snare for me without cause: in vaine haue they vpbrayded my soule.

text: For the children of Israel, and the children of Juda, have continually done evil in my eyes from their youth:
verse_text: Because the children of Juda have done evil in my eyes, saith the Lord.

text: Who so taketh pleasure in wickednesse shall be condemned, but he that resisteth pleasures, crowneth his life.
verse_text: Qui gaudet iniquitate, denotabitur: et qui odit correptionem, minuetur vita: et qui odit loquacitatem, extinguit malitiam.

text: They that were of vnderstanding in sayings, became also wise themselues, and powred forth exquisite parables.
verse_text: Sensati in verbis et ipsi sapienter egerunt, et intellexerunt veritatem et justitiam, et impleverunt proverbia et judicia.

text: Let my prayer bee set foorth before thee as incense: and the lifting vp of my hands as the Euening sacrifice.
verse_text: Heare the voyce of my supplications, when I cry vnto thee: when I lift vp my handes toward thy holy Oracle.

text: And they reioyced against me, and came together: scourges were gathered together vpon me, and I was ignorant.
verse_text: For I haue heard the rayling of great men: feare was on euery side, while they conspired together against mee, and consulted to take my life.

text: Salus animae in sanctitate justitiae melior est omni auro et argento: et corpus validum quam census immensus.
verse_text: Melior est mors quam vita amara, et requies aeterna quam languor perseverans.

text: An euill nurtured sonne is the dishonour of his father that begate him: and a daughter is borne to his losse.
verse_text: Confusio patris est de filio indisciplinato: filia autem in deminoratione fiet.

text: Haec dicit Dominus: Vade, et accipe lagunculam figuli testeam a senioribus populi et a senioribus sacerdotum,
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus ad me: Vade, et sta in porta filiorum populi, per quam ingrediuntur reges Juda, et egrediuntur, et in cunctis portis Jerusalem:

text: Then she came to the pillar of the bed, which was at Olofernes head, and tooke downe his fauchin from thence,
verse_text: Stetitque Judith ante lectum, orans cum lacrimis, et labiorum motu in silentio,

text: More to bee desired are they then gold, yea, then much fine gold: sweeter also then hony, and the hony combe.
verse_text: To be desired aboue gold and much pretious stone: and more sweete aboue honie and the honie combe.

text: Wisedome raineth downe skill and knowledge of vnderstanding, and exalteth them to honour that holde her fast.
verse_text: Timenti Dominum bene erit, et in diebus consummationis illius benedicetur.

text: Who didst raise vp a dead man from death, & his soule from the place of the dead by the word of the most Hie.
verse_text: qui sustulisti mortuum ab inferis de sorte mortis, in verbo Domini Dei:

text: Praise ye the Lord. I will prayse the Lord with my whole heart in the assemblie and Congregation of the iust.
verse_text: A Psalme of David. I will praise thee with my whole heart: euen before the gods will I praise thee.

text: He gaue them to glory in his marueilous actes for euer, that they might declare his works with vnderstanding.
verse_text: Addidit illis disciplinam, et legem vitae haereditavit illos.

text: Amico fideli nulla est comparatio, et non est digna ponderatio auri et argenti contra bonitatem fidei illius.
verse_text: Noli discedere a muliere sensata et bona, quam sortitus es in timore Domini: gratia enim verecundiae illius super aurum.

text: Also I set watchmen ouer you, saying, Hearken to the sound of the trumpet: but they said, We wil not hearken.
verse_text: To give ear to the words of my servants the prophets, whom I sent to you rising up early: and sending, and you have not hearkened:

text: And the Lord said to me: A conspiracy is found among the men of Juda, and among the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
verse_text: Say ye to the nations: Behold it is heard in Jerusalem, that guards are coming from a far country, and give out their voice against the cities of Juda.

text: But wee haue dwelt in tents, and haue obeyed, and done according to all that Ionadab our father commanded vs.
verse_text: Because the sonnes of Ionadab, the sonne of Rechab, haue performed the commaundement of their father, which he commaunded them, but this people hath not hearkened vnto me;

text: Thou hast made vs a reproche to our neighbours, a scorne and mocking stocke to them, that are round about vs.
verse_text: We are become a reproch to our neighboures: a scorne and mocke to them that are round about vs.

text: [Unto whom hath the knowledge of wisedome beene made manifest? and who hath vnderstood her great experience?]
verse_text: disciplina sapientiae cui revelata est et manifestata? et multiplicationem ingressus illius quis intellexit?

text: and Jeremias the prophet was shut up in the court of the prison, which was in the house of the king of Juda.
verse_text: And king Sedecias sent, and took Jeremias the prophet to him to the third gate, that was in the house of the Lord:

text: Which Jeremias the prophet spoke to all the people of Juda, and to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, saying:
verse_text: Then Jeremias spoke to all the princes, and to all the people, saying: The Lord sent me to prophesy concerning this house, and concerning this city all the words you have heard.

text: Looke not round about thee, in the streets of the citie, neither wander thou in the solitary places thereof.
verse_text: Noli circumspicere in vicis civitatis, nec oberraveris in plateis illius.

text: Ad agnitionem hominum virtus illorum: et dedit hominibus scientiam Altissimus, honorari in mirabilibus suis.
verse_text: ut nomen sanctificationis collaudent, et gloriari in mirabilibus illius; ut magnalia enarrent operum ejus.

text: Children and the building of a citie continue a mans name: but a blamelesse wife is counted aboue them both.
verse_text: Filii et aedificatio civitatis confirmabit nomen: et super haec mulier immaculata computabitur.

text: Thou hidest thy face, they are troubled, thou takest away their breath, they die: and returne to their dust.
verse_text: But thou turning away the face, they shal be trubled: thou shalt take away their spirite, and they shal faile, and shal returne into their dust.

text: For thine enemies haue reproched thee, O Lord, because they haue reproched the footesteps of thine Anointed.
verse_text: O God, the heathen are come into thine, inheritance, thy holy temple haue they defiled: they haue layd Ierusalem on heapes.

text: And Ieremiah sayd to Sheraiah, Whe thou commest vnto Babel, and shalt see, and shalt reade all these wordes,
verse_text: And thou shalt say to Iehoiakim king of Iudah, Thus sayth the Lord, Thou hast burnt this roule, saying, Why hast thou written therein, saying, The king of Babylon shall certainely come and destroy this land, and shall cause to cease from thence man and beast?

text: Now therefore, Lord Holofernes, we will goe vp, and they shall be a pray, to be deuoured of all thine armie.
verse_text: Nunc ergo mi domine, perquire si est aliqua iniquitas eorum in conspectu Dei eorum: ascendamus ad illos, quoniam tradens tradet illos Deus eorum tibi, et subjugati erunt sub jugo potentiae tuae.

text: The vision of dreames is the resemblance of one thing to another, euen as the likenesse of a face to a face.
verse_text: Hoc secundum hoc visio somniorum, ante faciem hominis similitudo hominis.

text: All that are of the earth shall turne to earth againe: so the vngodly shall goe from a curse to destruction.
verse_text: De patre impio queruntur filii, quoniam propter illum sunt in opprobrio.

text: The king therfore slewe them, & he deliuered Bel into the powre of Daniel: who ouerthrewe him, & his temple.
verse_text: Then Nabuchodonosor the king was astonied, and he arose hastely, & said to his nobles: Did we not cast three men fettered into the middes of the fire? Who answering the king, said: It is true o king.

text: Esther had not shewed her people, nor her kinred: for Mordecai had charged her, that she should not shew it.
verse_text: Ester had not yet shewed her kindred nor her people, as Mordecai had charged her: for Ester did after the worde of Mordecai, as when she was nourished with him.

text: And say vnto thee, Thy way is good: and afterward he stand on the other side, to see what shall befall thee.
verse_text: A consiliario serva animam tuam: prius scito quae sit illius necessitas: et ipse enim animo suo cogitabit:

text: Et post regnum eorum, cum creverint iniquitates, consurget rex impudens facie, et intelligens propositiones;
verse_text: Robur autem datum est ei contra juge sacrificium propter peccata: et prosternetur veritas in terra, et faciet, et prosperabitur.

text: Verumtamen Elnathan, et Dalaias, et Gamarias, contradixerunt regi, ne combureret librum: et non audivit eos.
verse_text: Igitur manus Ahicam filii Saphan fuit cum Jeremia, ut non traderetur in manus populi, et interficerent eum.

text: Declina pauperi sine tristitia aurem tuam, et redde debitum tuum, et responde illi pacifica in mansuetudine.
verse_text: Ne dederis in tristitia cor tuum, sed repelle eam a te, et memento novissimorum.

text: Al the works of the Lord are exceeding good, & whatsoeuer hee commandeth, shalbe accomplished in due season.
verse_text: Adhuc consiliabor ut enarrem: ut furore enim repletus sum.

text: Sperate in eo, omnis congregatio populi; effundite coram illo corda vestra: Deus adjutor noster in aeternum.
verse_text: Deus meus, impolluta via ejus; eloquia Domini igne examinata: protector est omnium sperantium in se.

text: Et reddet illis iniquitatem ipsorum, et in malitia eorum disperdet eos: disperdet illos Dominus Deus noster.
verse_text: Pones eos ut clibanum ignis in tempore vultus tui: Dominus in ira sua conturbabit eos, et devorabit eos ignis.

text: The beautie of heauen, the glory of the starres, an ornament giuing light in the highest places of the Lord.
verse_text: Vas castrorum in excelsis, in firmamento caeli resplendens gloriose.

text: But children being haughtie through disdaine, and want of nurture, doe staine the nobilitie of their kinred.
verse_text: Supra mortuum plora, defecit enim lux ejus: et supra fatuum plora, defecit enim sensus.

text: Admonish thy neighbour before thou threaten him, and not being angry giue place to the Law of the most high.
verse_text: quis est enim qui non deliquerit in lingua sua? Corripe proximum antequam commineris,

text: lest sometime mine enemie say: I haue preuailed against him. They that truble me, wil reioyce if I be moued:
verse_text: Least mine enimie say, I haue preuailed against him: and those that trouble mee, reioyce, when I am moued.

text: And the wrath of God ascended vpon them. And he killed their fat ones, and the chosen of Israel he hindered.
verse_text: And he shut vp his people in the sword: and he dispised his inheritance.

text: Heare ye therefore the word of the Lord all ye of the captiuitie, whome I haue sent from Ierusalem to Babel.
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord of the King, that sitteth vpon the throne of Dauid, and of all the people, that dwell in this citie, your brethren that are not gone forth with you into captiuitie:

text: Thinke vpon the wrath that shall be at the end; and the time of vengeance when he shall turne away his face.
verse_text: Memento irae in die consummationis, et tempus retributionis in conversatione faciei.

text: And all the Kings of Tyrus, and all the kings of Zidon, and the Kings of the Yles, that are beyonde the Sea,
verse_text: And all the kings of Arabia, and all the kings of the mingled people that dwell in the desert:

text: The singers also sang praises with their voices, with great variety of sounds was there made sweete melodie.
verse_text: Tunc exclamaverunt filii Aaron, in tubis productilibus sonuerunt: et auditam fecerunt vocem magnam in memoriam coram Deo.

text: And by him was built from the foundation the double height, the high fortresse of the wall about the Temple.
verse_text: Templi etiam altitudo ab ipso fundata est, duplex aedificatio, et excelsi parietes templi.

text: Remember that death will not be long in comming, and that the couenant of the graue is not shewed vnto thee.
verse_text: Memor esto quoniam mors non tardat, et testamentum inferorum, quia demonstratum est tibi: testamentum enim hujus mundi morte morietur.

text: Shall I not visit for these things, saith the Lord ? shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?
verse_text: Shall I not visit for these things, sayth the Lord, and shall not my soule bee auenged on such a nation as this?

text: Shall I not visite for these things, saith the Lord? Shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?
verse_text: Shal I not visit them for these things, saith the Lord? or shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?

text: With the mercifull thou wilt shew thy selfe mercifull, with an vpright man thou wilt shew thy selfe vpright.
verse_text: With the pure thou wilt shewe thy selfe pure, and with the froward thou wilt shewe thy selfe froward.

text: Heare ye the wordes of this couenant, and speake vnto the men of Iudah, and to the inhabitants of Ierusalem,
verse_text: Then the Lord saide vnto me, Cry all these words in the cities of Iudah, and in the streetes of Ierusalem, saying, Heare yee the words of this couenant, and doe them.

text: He behaued himselfe vprightly in the conuersion of the people, and tooke away the abominations of iniquitie.
verse_text: In omni ore quasi mel indulcabitur ejus memoria, et ut musica in convivio vini.

text: Thou hast protected me from the assemblie of the malignant: from the multitude of them that worke iniquitie.
verse_text: Keepe me from the snare, which they haue layde for me, and from the grennes of the workers of iniquitie.

text: The rich man hath done wrong, and yet he threatneth withall: the poore is wronged, and he must intreat also.
verse_text: Quid communicabit cacabus ad ollam? quando enim se colliserint, confringetur.

text: Pertransiens autem Syriam Sobal, et omnem Apameam, omnemque Mesopotamiam, venit ad Idumaeos in terram Gabaa,
verse_text: Et transivit Euphraten, et venit in Mesopotamiam: et fregit omnes civitates excelsas quae erant ibi, a torrente Mambre usquequo perveniatur ad mare:

text: Better is he that laboureth and aboundeth in all things, then hee that boasteth himselfe, and wanteth bread.
verse_text: Magnus, et judex, et potens est in honore: et non est major illo qui timet Deum.

text: Ne dicas: In multitudine munerum meorum respiciet Deus, et offerente me Deo altissimo, munera mea suscipiet.
verse_text: Dona iniquorum non probat Altissimus, nec respicit in oblationes iniquorum, nec in multitudine sacrificiorum eorum propitiabitur peccatis.

text: Hee shall be stayed vpon her, and shall not be moued, and shall rely vpon her, and shall not be confounded.
verse_text: et continebit illum, et non confundetur: et exaltabit illum apud proximos suos,

text: Precipitate o Lord, and diuide their tongues: because I haue sene iniquitie and contradiction in the citie.
verse_text: God wil shew vnto me concerning mine enimies, kil them not lest sometime my peoples forgete. Disperse them in thy strength: and depose them my protector o Lord.

text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel, Put your burnt offrings vnto your sacrifices, & eate flesh.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, Goe and tel the men of Iudah, and inhabitants of Ierusalem, Will yee not receiue instruction to hearken to my words, saith the Lord ?

text: Though they curse, yet thou wilt blesse: they shall arise and be confounded, but thy seruant shall reioyce.
verse_text: But thou, O God, shalt bring them downe into the pit of destruction: Bloody and deceitfull men shall not liue out halfe their dayes, but I will trust in thee.

text: Iuda my king: Moab the pot of my hope. Into Edom wil I stretch out my shoe: the foreners are subiect to me.
verse_text: Moab is my wash pot, ouer Edom wil I cast out my shooe: ouer Philistia will I triumph.

text: Speciem mulieris alienae multi admirati, reprobi facti sunt: colloquium enim illius quasi ignis exardescit.
verse_text: Nequitia mulieris immutat faciem ejus: et obcaecat vultum suum tamquam ursus, et quasi saccum ostendit. In medio proximorum ejus

text: He that gathereth by defrauding his owne soule, gathereth for others, that shall spend his goods riotously.
verse_text: Qui acervat ex animo suo injuste, aliis congregat, et in bonis illius alius luxuriabitur.
