text: ego quasi trames aquae immensae de fluvio: ego quasi fluvii dioryx, et sicut aquaeductus exivi de paradiso.
verse_text: Quasi arcus refulgens inter nebulas gloriae, et quasi flos rosarum in diebus vernis, et quasi lilia quae sunt in transitu aquae, et quasi thus redolens in diebus aestatis:

text: Euery man from his youth is giuen to euil, neither could they make to themselues fleshie hearts for stonie.
verse_text: Et omnia opera illorum velut sol in conspectu Dei: et oculi ejus sine intermissione inspicientes in viis eorum.

text: Shall I not visit them for these things, saith the Lord? or shall not my soul be revenged on such a nation?
verse_text: Shall I not visit for these things, saith the Lord ? shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?

text: But the Lord being gracious, and knowing his workemanship, neither left nor forsooke them, but spared them.
verse_text: Convertere ad Dominum, et relinque peccata tua:

text: But Ester shewed not her people and her kinred: for Mordecai had charged her, that shee should not tell it.
verse_text: Esther had not yet shewed her kindred, nor her people, as Mordecai had charged her: For Esther did the commandement of Mordecai, like as when she was brought vp with him.

text: And when Micheas the son of Gamarias the son of Saphan had heard out of the book all the words of the Lord,
verse_text: So Jeremias called Baruch the son of Nerias: and Baruch wrote from the mouth of Jeremias all the words of the Lord, which he spoke to him, upon the roll of a book.

text: Recordare quod steterim in conspectu tuo ut loquerer pro eis bonum, et averterem indignationem tuam ab eis.
verse_text: valeat deprecatio mea in conspectu tuo, et ne me remittas in domum Jonathan scribae, ne moriar ibi.

text: The iust haue cried, and our Lord hath heard them: and out of al their tribulations he hath deliuered them.
verse_text: They that feare our Lord, haue hoped in our Lord: he is their helper and their protector.

text: He that vseth many words shalbe abhorred; and hee that taketh to himselfe authoritie therein, shalbe hated.
verse_text: Qui multis utitur verbis laedet animam suam: et qui potestatem sibi sumit injuste, odietur.

text: Lord, what is man, that thou takest knowledge of him? or the sonne of man, that thou makest account of him?
verse_text: What is man, that thou art mindful of him? or the sonne of man, that thou visitest him?

text: Lord, thou hast heard the desire of the poore: thou preparest their heart: thou bendest thine eare to them,
verse_text: And they that know thy Name, will trust in thee: for thou, Lord, hast not failed them that seeke thee.

text: He that can rule his tongue shall liue without strife, and he that hateth babbling, shall haue lesse euill.
verse_text: Qui peccat in animam suam, poenitebit: et qui jucundatur in malitia, denotabitur.

text: To him that excelleth upon Nehiloth. A Psalme of Dauid. Heare my wordes, O Lord: vnderstande my meditation.
verse_text: To him that excelleth on Neginoth. A Psalme of David to give instruction. Heare my prayer, O God, and hide not thy selfe from my supplication.

text: Et conflata est indignatio mea et furor meus, et succensa est in civitatibus Juda, et in plateis Jerusalem:
verse_text: Ecce furor meus et indignatio mea conflatur super locum istum, super viros, et super jumenta, et super lignum regionis, et super fruges terrae:

text: Blessed is the nation, whose God is the Lord: and the people, whom he hath chosen for his owne inheritance.
verse_text: For the Lord hath chosen Iacob vnto himselfe: and Israel for his peculiar treasure.

text: Heare, O yee children, the discipline of the mouth: He that keepeth it, shall neuer be taken in his lippes.
verse_text: Doctrinam oris audite, filii: et qui custodierit illam non periet labiis, nec scandalizabitur in operibus nequissimis.

text: Glorificantes Dominum quantumcumque potueritis, supervalebit enim adhuc: et admirabilis magnificentia ejus.
verse_text: Benedicentes Dominum, exaltate illum quantum potestis: major enim est omni laude.

text: If thou have any thing, he will live with thee, and will make thee bare, and he will not be sorry for thee.
verse_text: And if he be able to pay, he will stand off, he will scarce pay one half, and will count it as if he had found it:

text: And the rough goat is the king of Grecia, and the great horne that is betweene his eyes, is the first king.
verse_text: The ramme, which thou sawest haue hornes, is the king of the Medes and Persians.

text: I Daniel was troubled in my spirit, in the middes of my body, and the visions of mine head made me afraide.
verse_text: I saw a dreame which made me afraid, and the thoughts vpon my bed, and the visions of my head troubled me.

text: Igitur manus Ahicam filii Saphan fuit cum Jeremia, ut non traderetur in manus populi, et interficerent eum.
verse_text: Et dixit rex Sedecias ad Jeremiam: Sollicitus sum propter Judaeos qui transfugerunt ad Chaldaeos, ne forte tradar in manus eorum, et illudant mihi.

text: He will not despise the supplication of the fatherlesse: nor the widowe when she powreth out her complaint.
verse_text: Noli offerre munera prava, non enim suscipiet illa.

text: Foure maner of things appeare: good and euill, life and death: but the tongue ruleth ouer them continually.
verse_text: Anima viri sancti enuntiat aliquando vera, quam septem circumspectores sedentes in excelso ad speculandum.

text: The word that the Lord spake against Babylon, and against the land of the Caldeans by Ieremiah the Prophet.
verse_text: The word of the Lord which came to Ieremiah the Prophet, against the Gentiles,

text: And any affliction, but the affliction from them that hate me: and any reuenge, but the reuenge of enemies.
verse_text: Timor Dei super omnia se superposuit.

text: He that reuengeth shall find vengeance from the Lord, and he will surely keepe his sinnes (in remembrance.)
verse_text: Qui vindicari vult, a Domino inveniet vindictam, et peccata illius servans servabit.

text: Manducaverunt et adoraverunt omnes pingues terrae; in conspectu ejus cadent omnes qui descendunt in terram.
verse_text: Reminiscentur et convertentur ad Dominum universi fines terrae; et adorabunt in conspectu ejus universae familiae gentium:

text: He that feareth the Lord, will honour his father, and will doe seruice vnto his parents, as to his masters.
verse_text: Qui honorat patrem suum vita vivet longiore, et qui obedit patri refrigerabit matrem.

text: Et tu dicis mihi, Domine Deus: Eme agrum argento, et adhibe testes, cum urbs data sit in manus Chaldaeorum?
verse_text: Numquid non vidisti quid populus hic locutus sit, dicens: Duae cognationes quas elegerat Dominus abjectae sunt? et populum meum despexerunt, eo quod non sit ultra gens coram eis.

text: Seeke not out the things that are too hard for thee, neither search the things that are aboue thy strength.
verse_text: quoniam magna potentia Dei solius, et ab humilibus honoratur.

text: Ecce dies veniunt, dicit Dominus, et aedificabitur civitas Domino, a turre Hananeel usque ad portam anguli.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus ad me: Vade, et sta in porta filiorum populi, per quam ingrediuntur reges Juda, et egrediuntur, et in cunctis portis Jerusalem:

text: a summo caelo egressio ejus. Et occursus ejus usque ad summum ejus; nec est qui se abscondat a calore ejus.
verse_text: Dominus in templo sancto suo; Dominus in caelo sedes ejus. Oculi ejus in pauperem respiciunt; palpebrae ejus interrogant filios hominum.

text: Quia apud te propitiatio est; et propter legem tuam sustinui te, Domine. Sustinuit anima mea in verbo ejus:
verse_text: Si ambulavero in medio tribulationis, vivificabis me; et super iram inimicorum meorum extendisti manum tuam, et salvum me fecit dextera tua.

text: Who so giueth eare vnto her, shall iudge the nations, and he that attendeth vnto her, shall dwell securely.
verse_text: Qui serviunt ei obsequentes erunt sancto: et eos qui diligunt illam, diligit Deus.

text: in Jerusalem. Montes in circuitu ejus; et Dominus in circuitu populi sui, ex hoc nunc et usque in saeculum.
verse_text: Confessio ejus super caelum et terram; et exaltavit cornu populi sui. Hymnus omnibus sanctis ejus; filiis Israel, populo appropinquanti sibi. Alleluja.

text: For I purposed to doe after her, and earnestly I followed that which is good, so shall I not be confounded:
verse_text: Cum adhuc junior essem, priusquam oberrarem, quaesivi sapientiam palam in oratione mea.

text: MY soule prayse thou our Lord, I wil praise our Lord in my life: I wil sing to my God as long as I shal be.
verse_text: I WIL blesse our Lord at al time: his prayse alwayes in my mouth.

text: In his dayes the cisterne to receiue water being in compasse as the sea, was couered with plates of brasse.
verse_text: In diebus ipsius emanaverunt putei aquarum, et quasi mare adimpleti sunt supra modum.

text: This city shall surely be delivered into the hand of the army of the king of Babylon, and he shall take it.
verse_text: Behold I will deliver this city into the hands of the Chaldeans, and into the hands of the king of Babylon, and they shall take it.

text: For many are deceiued by their owne vaine opinion, and an euill suspition hath ouerthrowen their iudgement.
verse_text: In supervacuis rebus noli scrutari multipliciter, et in pluribus operibus ejus non eris curiosus.

text: Quotiescumque autem poenituerunt se recessisse a cultura Dei sui, dedit eis Deus caeli virtutem resistendi.
verse_text: Quotiescumque autem praeter ipsum Deum suum, alterum coluerunt, dati sunt in praedam, et in gladium, et in opprobrium.

text: Dicam Deo: Susceptor meus es; quare oblitus es mei? et quare contristatus incedo, dum affligit me inimicus?
verse_text: Dum confringuntur ossa mea, exprobraverunt mihi qui tribulant me inimici mei, dum dicunt mihi per singulos dies: Ubi est Deus tuus?

text: My soule shalbe satisfied, as with marowe and fatnesse, and my mouth shall praise thee with ioyfull lippes,
verse_text: My lippes will reioyce when I sing vnto thee, and my soule, which thou hast deliuered.

text: But inquire not you of mine act: for I will not declare it vnto you, til the things be finished that I doe.
verse_text: Et dixit ad eam Ozias princeps Juda: Vade in pace, et Dominus sit tecum in ultionem inimicorum nostrorum. Et revertentes abierunt.

text: The inner parts of a foole, are like a broken vessell, and he will holde no knowledge as long as he liueth.
verse_text: Non erudietur qui non est sapiens in bono.

text: He that wanteth vnderstanding, will thinke vpon vaine things: and a foolish man erring, imagineth follies.
verse_text: Qui minoratur corde cogitat inania, et vir imprudens et errans cogitat stulta.

text: A couetous mans eye is not satisfied with his portion, and the iniquity of the wicked dryeth vp his soule.
verse_text: Insatiabilis oculus cupidi in parte iniquitatis: non satiabitur donec consumat arefaciens animam suam.

text: Thus sayth the Lord, After this maner will I destroy the pride of Iudah, and the great pride of Ierusalem.
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord of hostes the God of Israel; Behold, I will punish the king of Babylon and his land, as I haue punished the king of Assyria.

text: Psalmus David, filiorum Jonadab, et priorum captivorum. In te, Domine, speravi; non confundar in aeternum.
verse_text: Psalmus David, in consummatione tabernaculi. Afferte Domino, filii Dei, afferte Domino filios arietum.

text: Confundantur et deficiant detrahentes animae meae; operiantur confusione et pudore qui quaerunt mala mihi.
verse_text: Induantur qui detrahunt mihi pudore, et operiantur sicut diploide confusione sua.

text: I will reioyce in God, because of his word, I trust in God, and will not feare what flesh can doe vnto me.
verse_text: The Lord is my strength, and my shield, my heart trusted in him, and I am helped: therefore my heart greatly reioyceth, and with my song will I praise him.

text: Alleluia. PRAYSE ye our Lord because Psalme is good: to our God let there be pleasant, and comelie praise.
verse_text: Allelu ia. CONFESSE ye to our Lord because he is good: because his mercie is for euer.

text: Whatsoeuer is brought vpon thee, take cheerefully, and bee patient when thou art changed to a lowe estate.
verse_text: Omne quod tibi applicitum fuerit accipe: et in dolore sustine, et in humilitate tua patientiam habe:

text: Posuit David, puero suo, excitare regem ex ipso fortissimum, et in throno honoris sedentem in sempiternum.
verse_text: Invocavit Altissimum potentem, in oppugnando inimicos undique: et audivit illum magnus et sanctus Deus, in saxis grandinis virtutis valde fortis.

text: Confusus est Moab, quoniam victus est. Ululate, et clamate: annuntiate in Arnon, quoniam vastata est Moab,
verse_text: Annuntiate in gentibus, et auditum facite: levate signum, praedicate, et nolite celare: dicite: Capta est Babylon, confusus est Bel, victus est Merodach, confusa sunt sculptilia ejus, superata sunt idola eorum.

text: He hath turned the Sea into drie land: they passe through the riuer on foote: there did we reioyce in him.
verse_text: He deuided the Sea, and led them through: he made also the waters to stand as an heape.

text: Teach me to doe thy will, for thou art my God, thy spirit is good: leade me into the land of vprightnesse.
verse_text: Teach me thy way, O Lord, I will walke in thy trueth: vnite my heart to feare thy Name.

text: A thiefe is better then a man that is accustomed to lie: but they both shall haue destruction to heritage.
verse_text: Est qui prae confusione promittit amico, et lucratus est eum inimicum gratis.

text: Et propitiationem litare sacrificii super injustitias: et deprecatio pro peccatis, recedere ab injustitia.
verse_text: De propitiatio peccato noli esse sine metu, neque adjicias peccatum super peccatum.

text: Then shall her fetters be a strong defence for thee, and a firm foundation, and her chain a robe of glory:
verse_text: She shall heap upon him a treasure of joy and gladness, and shall cause him to inherit an everlasting name.

text: Extoll not thy selfe in the counsell of thine owne heart, that thy soule bee not torne in pieces as a bull
verse_text: Non te extollas in cogitatione animae tuae velut taurus, ne forte elidatur virtus tua per stultitiam:

text: Let this be the rewarde of mine aduersarie from the Lord, and of them, that speake euill against my soule.
verse_text: For the voyce of the enemie, and for the vexation of ye wicked, because they haue brought iniquitie vpon me, and furiously hate me.

text: My spirit trembled, I Daniel was made sore afrayd at these thinges, and the visions of my head trubled me.
verse_text: I Daniel was grieued in my spirit in the midst of my body, and the visions of my head troubled me.

text: Beatus qui habitat cum muliere sensata, et qui lingua sua non est lapsus, et qui non servivit indignis se.
verse_text: et est qui emittit verbum certum enarrans veritatem. Est qui nequiter humiliat se, et interiora ejus plena sunt dolo:

text: The fruite declareth if the tree haue beene dressed: so is the vtterance of a conceit in the heart of man.
verse_text: Vasa figuli probat fornax, et homines justos tentatio tribulationis.

text: For whe he maketh inquisition for blood, hee remembreth it, and forgetteth not the complaint of the poore.
verse_text: For the Lord heareth the poore, and despiseth not his prisoners.

text: I made my supplication in thy presence with my whole heart: be mercifull vnto me according to thy promise.
verse_text: Let my petition approch in thy sight o Lord: according to thy word giue me vnderstanding.

text: Winnow not with euery winde, and goe not into euery way: for so doth the sinner that hath a double tongue.
verse_text: subito enim veniet ira illius, et in tempore vindictae disperdet te.

text: Neuerthelesse, my louing kindnesse will I not vtterly take from him: nor suffer my faithfulnesse to faile.
verse_text: My mercie will I keepe for him for euermore, and my couenant shall stande fast with him.

text: Better is the poore being sound and strong of constitution, then a rich man that is afflicted in his body.
verse_text: Melior est pauper sanus, et fortis viribus, quam dives imbecillis et flagellatus malitia.

text: The Sunne when it appeareth, declaring at his rising, a marueilous instrument, the worke of the most High.
verse_text: Sol in aspectu annuntians in exitu, vas admirabile, opus Excelsi.

text: For better it is that thy children should seeke to thee, then that thou shouldst stand to their courtesie.
verse_text: Dum adhuc superes et aspiras, non immutabit te omnis caro.

text: As Babylon hath caused the slaine of Israel to fall: so at Babylon shall fall the slaine of all the earth.
verse_text: Thus the slaine shall fall in the land of the Caldeans, and they that are thrust through in her streetes.

text: Confundantur omnes iniqua agentes supervacue. Vias tuas, Domine, demonstra mihi, et semitas tuas edoce me.
verse_text: et in misericordia tua disperdes inimicos meos, et perdes omnes qui tribulant animam meam, quoniam ego servus tuus sum.

text: Haec dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus Israel, omni transmigrationi quam transtuli de Jerusalem in Babylonem:
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus Deus Israel: Sicut ficus hae bonae, sic cognoscam transmigrationem Juda, quam emisi de loco isto in terram Chaldaeorum, in bonum.

text: The offering of the righteous maketh the Altar fat, and the sweete sauour thereof is before the most high.
verse_text: Non apparebis ante conspectum Domini vacuus:

text: For hee lieth in wait, and turneth good into euill, and in things worthy praise, will lay blame vpon thee.
verse_text: Non omnem hominem inducas in domum tuam: multae enim sunt insidiae dolosi.

text: If a man commit himselfe vnto her, he shall inherite her, and his generation shall hold her in possession.
verse_text: Qui audit illam judicabit gentes: et qui intuetur illam permanebit confidens.

text: For the backbiter shall not be established vpon the earth: euill shall hunt the cruell man to destruction.
verse_text: A man ful of tongue shal not be directed in the earth: euils shal take the vniust man into destruction.

text: Anima enim nequam disperdet qui se habet, et in gaudium inimicis dat illum, et deducet in sortem impiorum.
verse_text: Et qui se jungit fornicariis erit nequam: putredo et vermes haereditabunt illum: et extolletur in exemplum majus, et tolletur de numero anima ejus.

text: For they prouoked him to anger with their high places: and moued him to ielousie with their grauen images.
verse_text: They incensed him to wrath in their hilles: and in their grauens they prouoked him to emulation.

text: There is a companion which helpeth his friend for the belly, and taketh vp the buckler against the enemie.
verse_text: Sodalis amico condolet causa ventris, et contra hostem accipiet scutum.

text: Without these cannot a citie be inhabited: and they shall not dwell where they will, nor goe vp and downe.
verse_text: Sic figulus sedens ad opus suum, convertens pedibus suis rotam, qui in sollicitudine positus est semper propter opus suum, et in numero est omnis operatio ejus.

text: The sun when he appeareth shewing forth at his rising, an admirable instrument, the work of the most High.
verse_text: Look upon the rainbow, and bless him that made it: it is very beautiful in its brightness.

text: Write ye therefore to the Jews, as it pleaseth you, in the king's name, and seal the letters with my ring.
verse_text: Go, and gather together all the Jews whom thou shalt find in Susan, and pray ye for me.

text: Then Daniel went to his house, and made the thing knowen to Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah his companions:
verse_text: And the King communed with them: and among them al was found none like Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah: therefore stoode they before the king.

text: A consiliario serva animam tuam: prius scito quae sit illius necessitas: et ipse enim animo suo cogitabit:
verse_text: cum operario annuali de consummatione anni, cum servo pigro de multa operatione. Non attendas his in omni consilio:

text: Better is he that laboureth, and aboundeth in all things, than he that boasteth himself and wanteth bread.
verse_text: Better is a man that hath less wisdom, and wanteth understanding, with the fear of God, than he that aboundeth in understanding, and transgresseth the law of the most High.

text: Quoniam praevenisti eum in benedictionibus dulcedinis; posuisti in capite ejus coronam de lapide pretioso.
verse_text: Quoniam dabis eum in benedictionem in saeculum saeculi; laetificabis eum in gaudio cum vultu tuo.

text: Therefore from the beginning I was resolued, and thought vpon these things, and haue left them in writing.
verse_text: Haec omnia sanctis in bona, sic et impiis et peccatoribus in mala convertentur.

text: Diuinations, and soothsayings, and dreames are vaine: and the heart fancieth as a womans heart in trauell.
verse_text: Divinatio erroris, et auguria mendacia, et somnia malefacientium, vanitas est:

text: Thou makest vs a reproche to our neighbours, a iest and a laughing stocke to them that are round about vs.
verse_text: Wee are a reproche to our neighbours, euen a scorne and derision vnto them that are round about vs.

text: Hee sheweth no mercy to a man, which is like himselfe: and doeth hee aske forgiuenesse of his owne sinnes?
verse_text: in hominem similem sibi non habet misericordiam, et de peccatis suis deprecatur.

text: As the Turpentine tree, I stretched out my branches, and my branches are the branches of honour and grace.
verse_text: Et radicavi in populo honorificato, et in parte Dei mei haereditas illius, et in plenitudine sanctorum detentio mea.

text: Offend not against the multitude of a city, and then thou shalt not cast thy selfe downe among the people.
verse_text: Non pecces in multitudinem civitatis, nec te immittas in populum:

text: The word that came to Jeremias from the Lord in the days of Joakim the son of Josias king of Juda, saying:
verse_text: The word that Jeremias the prophet spoke to Baruch the son of Nerias, when he had written there words in a book, out of the mouth of Jeremias, in the fourth year of Joakim the son of Josias king of Juda, saying:

text: By his commandement hee maketh the snow to fall apace, and sendeth swiftly the lightnings of his iudgment.
verse_text: Gyravit caelum in circuitu gloriae suae: manus Excelsi aperuerunt illum.

text: All nations whom thou hast made, shall come and worship before thee, O Lord: and shall glorifie thy Name.
verse_text: All thy workes shall praise thee, O Lord: and thy Saints shal blesse thee.

text: And plenty of vittaile for euery man of the army, and very much gold, and siluer, out of the Kings house.
verse_text: et cecidit timor illius super omnes inhabitantes terram.

text: And the word of the Lord came to me, saying: What seest thou, Jeremias? And I said: I see a rod watching.
verse_text: And the word of the Lord came to me a second time, saying: What seest thou? I see a boiling caldron, and the face thereof from the face of the north.

text: And let them hope in thee that know thy name: because thou hast not forsaken them that seeke thee o Lord.
verse_text: For thou, O God, hast heard my desires: thou hast giuen an heritage vnto those that feare thy Name.

text: O continue thy louing kindnesse vnto them that know thee; and thy righteousnesse to the vpright in heart.
verse_text: Doe good, O Lord, vnto those that be good: and to them that are vpright in their hearts.

text: But we have dwelt in tents, and have been obedient according to all that Jonadab our father commanded us.
verse_text: Therefore we have obeyed the voice of Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father, in all things that he commanded us: so as to drink no wine all our days: neither we, nor our wives, nor our sons, nor our daughters:

text: The words of Jonadab the son of Rechab, by which he commanded his sons not to drink wine, have prevailed:
verse_text: The commandement of Ionadab the sonne of Rechab that hee commanded his sonnes, that they should drinke no wine, is surely kept:

text: Species mulieris exhilarat faciem viri sui, et super omnem concupiscentiam hominis superducit desiderium.
verse_text: Posuit timorem illius super omnem carnem, et dominatus est bestiarum et volatilium.

text: If thy daughter be shamelesse, keepe her in straitly: lest she abuse her selfe through ouermuch libertie.
verse_text: Sicut boum jugum quod movetur, ita et mulier nequam: qui tenet illam quasi qui apprehendit scorpionem.

text: He knew all things ere euer they were created, so also after they were perfited, he looked vpon them all:
verse_text: Homo assuetus in verbis improperii in omnibus diebus suis non erudietur.

text: Let this be the reward of mine aduersaries from the Lord: and of them that speake euill against my soule.
verse_text: Let them be ashamed and confounded together, that seeke after my soule to destroy it: let them be driuen backward, and put to shame, that wish me euill.

text: Shall I not visit for these things, sayeth the Lord? and shall not my soul take revenge on such a nation?
verse_text: Shall I not visit for these things, saith the Lord ? shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?

text: And he deliuered them into the handes of the nations: and they that hated them, had the dominion of them.
verse_text: And their enimies afflicted them: and they were humbled vnder their handes:

text: in maledictionem, et in stuporem, et in sibilum, et in opprobrium cunctis gentibus ad quas ego ejeci eos,
verse_text: et eritis in jusjurandum, et in stuporem, et in maledictum, et in opprobrium, et nequaquam ultra videbitis locum istum.

text: my lottes are in thy handes. Deliuer me out of the handes of my enemies, and from them that persecute me.
verse_text: Vnder the shadowe of thy winges protect me: from the face of the impious, that haue afflicted me.

text: He that loueth gold shall not bee iustified, and he that followeth corruption, shall haue enough thereof.
verse_text: Qui aurum diligit non justificabitur, et qui insequitur consumptionem replebitur ex ea.

text: And I will gather together the remnant of my flock, out of all the lands into which I have cast them out:
verse_text: But the Lord liveth, who hath brought out, and brought hither the seed of the house of Israel from the land of the north, and out of all the lands, to which I had cast them forth:

text: To him that excelleth on Shoshannim a song of love to give instruction, committed to the sonnes of Korah.
verse_text: A Psalme to give instruction, committed to the sonnes of Korah.

text: And spake kindly vnto him, and set his throne aboue the throne of the Kings, that were with him in Babel,
verse_text: And he spoke kindly to him, and he set his throne above the thrones of the kings that were with him in Babylon.

text: And they cried to our Lord when they were in tribulation: and he deliuered them out of their necessities.
verse_text: Then they cried vnto the Lord in their trouble, and he deliuered them from their distresse.

text: The skill of the Phisitian shall lift vp his head: and in the sight of great men he shalbe in admiration.
verse_text: Disciplina medici exaltabit caput illius, et in conspectu magnatorum collaudabitur.

text: Hee shall shew foorth that which he hath learned, and shall glory in the Law of the couenant of the Lord.
verse_text: Si enim Dominus magnus voluerit, spiritu intelligentiae replebit illum:

text: quoniam eripuisti animam meam de morte, et pedes meos de lapsu, ut placeam coram Deo in lumine viventium.
verse_text: Si ambulavero in medio tribulationis, vivificabis me; et super iram inimicorum meorum extendisti manum tuam, et salvum me fecit dextera tua.

text: absconderunt superbi laqueum mihi. Et funes extenderunt in laqueum; juxta iter, scandalum posuerunt mihi.
verse_text: Locuti sunt adversum me lingua dolosa, et sermonibus odii circumdederunt me: et expugnaverunt me gratis.

text: Thy trueth is from generation to generation: thou hast layed the foundation of the earth, and it abideth.
verse_text: For the Lord is good: his mercy is euerlasting, and his trueth is from generation to generation.

text: Take heed of a mischieuous man, (for hee worketh wickednesse) lest hee bring vpon thee a perpetuall blot.
verse_text: Bona enim in mala convertens insidiatur, et in electis imponet maculam.

text: The king answered, & sayd: Surely I know that you redeme time, knowing that the word is departed from me.
verse_text: The I heard it, but I vnderstood it not: the said I, O my Lord, what shalbe ye end of these things?

text: Let him that escapeth, be consumed by the rage of the fire, and let them perish that oppresse the people.
verse_text: Tolle adversarium, et afflige inimicum.

text: And they sayd when they were come to the king: Deliuer vs Daniel, otherwise we wil kil thee, & thy house.
verse_text: Then the king commanded, and they brought Daniel, and cast him into the lake of lions. And the king said to Daniel: Thy God, whom thou doest wroshippe alwayes, he wil deliuer thee.

text: I sawe in the visions of my head vpon my bed, & behold, a watcher and an holy one came downe from heauen.
verse_text: Saw a dreame, which made me afraide, and the thoughtes vpon my bed, and the visions of mine head troubled me.

text: Hoc autem edictum, quod nunc mittimus, in cunctis urbibus proponatur, ut liceat Judaeis uti legibus suis.
verse_text: Summaque epistolae haec fuit, ut in omnibus terris ac populis qui regis Assueri subjacebant imperio, notum fieret paratos esse Judaeos ad capiendam vindictam de hostibus suis.

text: Some man holdeth his tongue, because hee hath not to answere, and some keepeth silence, knowing his time.
verse_text: Est tacens non habens sensum loquelae: et est tacens sciens tempus aptum.

text: And Ieremiah the Prophet was shutte vp in the court of the prison, which was in the King of Iudahs house.
verse_text: eunuches which was in the kings house, heard that they had put Ieremiah in the dungeon (the king then sitting in the gate of Beniamin)

text: He that is hasty to giue credit is light minded, and he that sinneth shall offend against his owne soule.
verse_text: Qui credit cito levis corde est, et minorabitur: et qui delinquit in animam suam, insuper habebitur.

text: A slouthfull man is compared to the filth of a dunghill: euery man that takes it vp, will shake his hand.
verse_text: De stercore boum lapidatus est piger: et omnis qui tetigerit eum excutiet manus.

text: The skill of the Phisitian shall lift vp his head: and in the sight of great men he shalbe in admiration.
verse_text: The wisdom of the humble shall exalt his head, and shall make him sit in the midst of great men.

text: With all maner of liuing things hath hee couered the face thereof, and they shall returne into it againe.
verse_text: Post haec Deus in terram respexit, et implevit illam bonis suis:

text: A slouthfull man is compared to the filth of a dunghill: euery man that takes it vp, will shake his hand.
verse_text: The talke of him that sweareth much, maketh the haire stand vpright: and their braules make one stop his eares.

text: A wicked soule shall destroy him that hath it, and shall make him to be laughed to scorne of his enemies.
verse_text: Anima enim nequam disperdet qui se habet, et in gaudium inimicis dat illum, et deducet in sortem impiorum.

text: Who so feareth the Lord shall direct his friendship aright, for as he is, so shall his neighbour be also.

text: If thou haue any thing, he will liue with thee, yea he will make thee bare, and will not be sorie for it.
verse_text: Till he hath receiued, he will kisse a mans hand: and for his neighbours money he will speake submissely: but when he should repay, he will prolong the time, and returne words of griefe, and complaine of the time.

text: For none shall hurt thee, but intreat thee well, as they doe the seruants of king Nabuchodonosor my lord.
verse_text: Et dixit illi Judith: Sume verba ancillae tuae, quoniam si secutus fueris verba ancillae tuae, perfectam rem faciet Dominus tecum.

text: For thou diddest preuent him with liberall blessings, and didest set a crowne of pure gold vpon his head.
verse_text: For thou Lord wilt blesse the righteous, and with fauour wilt compasse him, as with a shielde.

text: My son, if thou wilt attend to me, thou shalt learn: and if thou wilt apply thy mind, thou shalt be wise.
verse_text: If thou loue to heare, thou shalt receiue vnderstanding: and if thou bow thine eare, thou shalt be wise.

text: And now who are you, that haue tempted God this day, & stand in stead of God amongst the children of men?
verse_text: non est iste sermo qui misericordiam provocet, sed potius qui iram excitet, et furorem accendat.

text: The knowledge of a wise man shall abound like a flood: and his counsell is like a pure fountaine of life.

text: Lift vp your gates ye princes, and be ye lifted vp o eternal gates: and the king of glorie shal enter in,
verse_text: Lift vp your heads, O ye gates, euen lift them vp, ye euerlasting doores; and the king of glory shall come in.

text: In his time Sennacherib came vp, and sent Rabsaces, and lift vp his hand against Sion, & boasted proudly.

text: In the punishment of the proud there is no remedie: for the plant of wickednesse hath taken roote in him.

text: For this thy confidence shall not depart from the heart of men, which remember the power of God for euer.
verse_text: Et proferens de pera caput Holofernis, ostendit illis, dicens: Ecce caput Holofernis principis militiae Assyriorum, et ecce conopeum illius, in quo recumbebat in ebrietate sua, ubi per manum feminae percussit illum Dominus Deus noster.

text: My times are in thine hande: deliuer mee from the hande of mine enemies, and from them that persecute me.
verse_text: Keepe mee, O Lord, from the handes of the wicked: preserue mee from the cruell man, which purposeth to cause my steppes to slide.

text: And refraine not to speake, when there is occasion to doe good, and hide not thy wisedome in her beautie.
verse_text: Fili, conserva tempus, et devita a malo.

text: As fire and incense in the censer, and as a vessell of beaten gold set with all maner of precious stones,
verse_text: quasi ignis effulgens, et thus ardens in igne:

text: Therefore he cried with a lowd voice, with weeping, and sighing, and a mighty cry, and rent his garments.
verse_text: et dixit: Una mulier hebraea fecit confusionem in domo regis Nabuchodonosor: ecce enim Holofernes jacet in terra, et caput ejus non est in illo.

text: For the house of Israel, and the house of Iudah haue dealt very treacherously against me, saith the Lord.
verse_text: For the children of Israel, and the children of Iudah haue surely done euill before me from their youth: for the children of Israel haue surely prouoked me to anger with the workes of their hands, saith the Lord.

text: Shee shall exalt him aboue his neighbours, and in the midst of the congregation shall she open his mouth.
verse_text: et in medio ecclesiae aperiet os ejus, et adimplebit illum spiritu sapientiae et intellectus, et stola gloriae vestiet illum.

text: et incendit domum Domini, et domum regis, et omnes domos Jerusalem: et omnem domum magnam igni combussit:

text: Teach me to do thy will, for thou art my God: let thy good Spirit leade me vnto the land of righteousnes.
verse_text: Geue me a law o Lord in thy way: and direct me in the right path, because of mine enemies.

text: They shall breake out into the mention of thy great goodnes, and shall sing aloude of thy righteousnesse.
verse_text: And men shall speake of the might of thy terrible acts: and I wil declare thy greatnesse.

text: And there is hope in thine end, saith the Lord, that thy children shall come againe to their owne border.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord, Refraine thy voyce from weeping, and thine eyes from teares: for thy worke shalbe rewarded, saith the Lord, and they shall come againe from the land of the enemie:

text: If thou haue any thing, he will liue with thee, yea he will make thee bare, and will not be sorie for it.

text: Therefore the vngodly shall not stand in the iudgement, nor sinners in the Congregation of the righteous.
verse_text: Blessed is the man that walketh not in the counsell of the vngodly, nor standeth in the way of sinners, nor sitteth in the seat of the scornefull.

text: Nam et ego confitebor tibi in vasis psalmi veritatem tuam, Deus; psallam tibi in cithara, sanctus Israel.
verse_text: In petra exaltavit me, et nunc exaltavit caput meum super inimicos meos. Circuivi, et immolavi in tabernaculo ejus hostiam vociferationis; cantabo, et psalmum dicam Domino.

text: Deus, qui glorificatur in consilio sanctorum, magnus et terribilis super omnes qui in circuitu ejus sunt.
verse_text: Quoniam magnus Dominus, et laudabilis nimis: terribilis est super omnes deos.

text: There be many that say, Who wil shew vs any good? Lord lift thou vp the light of thy countenance vpon vs.
verse_text: Turne vs againe, O God, and cause thy face to shine that we may be saued.

text: There went vp a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth deuoured, coales were kindled by it.
verse_text: Smoke went out at his nostrels, and a consuming fire out of his mouth: coales were kindled thereat.

text: Ego vero egenus et pauper sum; Deus, adjuva me. Adjutor meus et liberator meus es tu; Domine, ne moreris.
verse_text: Ego autem in innocentia mea ingressus sum; redime me, et miserere mei.

text: I will praise thy Name continually, and will sing praise with thankesgiuing, and so my prayer was heard:
verse_text: Memoratus sum misericordiae tuae Domine, et operationis tuae, quae a saeculo sunt:

text: Testimonia tua credibilia facta sunt nimis; domum tuam decet sanctitudo, Domine, in longitudinem dierum.
verse_text: Quam magna multitudo dulcedinis tuae, Domine, quam abscondisti timentibus te; perfecisti eis qui sperant in te in conspectu filiorum hominum !

text: Huic David, quando terra ejus restituta est. Dominus regnavit: exsultet terra; laetentur insulae multae.
verse_text: Laus cantici ipsi David, in die ante sabbatum, quando fundata est terra. Dominus regnavit, decorem indutus est: indutus est Dominus fortitudinem, et praecinxit se. Etenim firmavit orbem terrae, qui non commovebitur.

text: By his faithfulnes he was found a true Prophet, and by his word he was knowen to be faithfull in vision.
verse_text: et nomen eorum permaneat in aeternum, permanens ad filios illorum, sanctorum virorum gloria.

text: Keepe me from the snare, which they haue set for me: and from the scandals of them that worke iniquitie.
verse_text: Thou hast protected me from the assemblie of the malignant: from the multitude of them that worke iniquitie.

text: For thou preuentest him with the blessings of goodnesse: thou settest a Crowne of pure gold on his head.

text: If thou loue to heare, thou shalt receiue vnderstanding: and if thou bow thine eare, thou shalt be wise.

text: Rex autem quod gestum erat, scripsit in commentariis: sed et Mardochaeus rei memoriam litteris tradidit.

text: He made a way to his anger: he spared not their soule from death, but gaue their life to the pestilence,
verse_text: He made a way to the path of his wrath, he spared not their liues from death: and their cattel he shut vp in death.

text: Ecce enim dies veniunt, dicit Dominus, et convertam conversionem populi mei Israel et Juda, ait Dominus:
verse_text: Propterea ecce dies veniunt, dicit Dominus, et mittam ei ordinatores et stratores laguncularum:

text: In principio regni Joakim filii Josiae regis Juda, factum est verbum istud ad Jeremiam a Domino, dicens:
verse_text: Verbum quod locutus est Jeremias propheta ad Baruch filium Neriae, cum scripsisset verba haec in libro ex ore Jeremiae, anno quarto Joakim filii Josiae regis Juda, dicens:

text: The words of Jeremias the son of Helcias, of the priests that were in Anathoth, in the land of Benjamin.
verse_text: And Jeremias went to Godolias the son of Ahicam to Masphath: and dwelt with him in the midst of the people that were left in the land.

text: In God I will praise his worde, In God I haue put my trust, I will not feare what flesh can doe vnto me.
verse_text: In God I wil praise my wordes, in God haue I hoped: I wil not feare what flesh may do to me.

text: Quoniam die ac nocte gravata est super me manus tua, conversus sum in aerumna mea, dum configitur spina.
verse_text: Miserere mei, Deus, quoniam conculcavit me homo; tota die impugnans, tribulavit me.

text: For a mans minde is sometime wont to tell him more then seuen watchmen, that sit aboue in an high towre.
verse_text: cum operario annuali de consummatione anni, cum servo pigro de multa operatione. Non attendas his in omni consilio:

text: Do good to the godly man, and thou shalt find a recompence, and if not from him, yet from the most high.
verse_text: Benefac justo, et invenies retributionem magnam: et si non ab ipso, certe a Domino.

text: The prayer of Dauid. Heare the right, O Lord, consider my crye: hearken vnto my prayer of lips vnfained.
verse_text: A Psalme of David. Heare my prayer, O Lord, and hearken vnto my supplication: answer me in thy trueth and in thy righteousnes.

text: Who turneth the sea into drie land, in the riuer they shal passe on foote, there we shal reioyce in him.
verse_text: Because in thee I shal be deliuered from tentation, and in my God I shal goe ouer the wal.

text: In the hand of God is the prosperitie of man: and vpon the person of the scribe shall he lay his honour.
verse_text: In manu Dei prosperitas hominis, et super faciem scribae imponet honorem suum.

text: The heauens are thine, and the earth is thine, the round earth, and the fulnes therof thou hast founded:
verse_text: The first of the Sabbath, the Psalme of Dauid. THE earth is our Lordes, and the fulnesse therof: the round world, and al that dwel therein.

text: This man shall bee punished in the streets of the citie, and where he suspecteth not, he shall be taken.

text: Loue thy friend, and be faithfull vnto him: but if thou bewrayest his secrets, follow no more after him.
verse_text: Qui denudat arcana amici fidem perdit, et non inveniet amicum ad animum suum.

text: A prayer of Moyses the man of God. Lord, thou art made a refuge for vs: from generation vnto generation.

text: He left behinde him an auenger against his enemies, and one that shall requite kindnesse to his friends.

verse_text: Ne manseris in operibus peccatorum: confide autem in Deo, et mane in loco tuo.

text: Some of them hath hee made high dayes, and hallowed them, and some of them hath hee made ordinary dayes.

text: every one that shall pass by it, shall be astonished, and shall hiss because of all the plagues thereof.

text: My soule hath thirsted after God the strong liuing: when shal I come and appeare before the face of God?
verse_text: My soule longeth, yea, and fainteth for the courtes of the Lord: for mine heart and my flesh reioyce in the liuing God.

text: et hoc ejulatu usque ad fores palatii gradiens. Non enim erat licitum indutum sacco aulam regis intrare.
verse_text: Et quae intraverat vespere, egrediebatur mane, atque inde in secundas aedes deducebatur, quae sub manu Susagazi eunuchi erant, qui concubinis regis praesidebat: nec habebat potestatem ad regem ultra redeundi, nisi voluisset rex, et eam venire jussisset ex nomine.

text: They haue compassed mee, yea, they haue compassed mee: but in the Name of the Lord I shall destroy them.
verse_text: All nations compassed me about: but in the Name of the Lord, will I destroy them.

text: Alia generantur, et alia dejiciuntur: sic generatio carnis et sanguinis, alia finitur, et alia nascitur.
verse_text: Confusio patris est de filio indisciplinato: filia autem in deminoratione fiet.

text: Keepe me from the snare, which they haue layde for me, and from the grennes of the workers of iniquitie.
verse_text: Keepe mee, O Lord, from the handes of the wicked: preserue mee from the cruell man, which purposeth to cause my steppes to slide.

text: Et quomodo fecit Babylon, ut caderent occisi in Israel, sic de Babylone cadent occisi in universa terra.
verse_text: Vos ergo audite verbum Domini, omnis transmigratio quam emisi de Jerusalem in Babylonem.

text: Then cryed I vnto thee, O Lord, and sayde, thou art mine hope, and my portion in the land of the liuing.
verse_text: But it is good for me, to drawe neere to God: I haue put my trust in the Lord God, that I maydeclare all thy workes.

text: Then went in Bagoas, and knocked at the doore of the tent: for he thought that he had slept with Iudeth.
verse_text: Sed cum nullum motum jacentis sensu aurium caperet, accessit proximans ad cortinam, et elevans eam, vidensque cadaver absque capite Holofernis in suo sanguine tabefactum jacere super terram, exclamavit voce magna cum fletu, et scidit vestimenta sua.

text: I haue called vpon thee, for thou wilt heare me, O God: incline thine eare vnto me, and heare my speach.
verse_text: Giue eare to my prayer, O God: and hide not thy selfe from my supplication.

text: Blessed is hee whose conscience hath not condemned him, and who is not fallen from his hope in the Lord.
verse_text: Felix qui non habuit animi sui tristitiam, et non excidit a spe sua.

text: I saw in the vision of my head vpon my bed, & behold a watchman, and an holie one descended from heauen.
verse_text: Saw a dreame, which made me afraide, and the thoughtes vpon my bed, and the visions of mine head troubled me.

text: Ecce ego ad te, superbe ! dicit Dominus Deus exercituum: quia venit dies tuus, tempus visitationis tuae.
verse_text: Descende de gloria, et sede in siti, habitatio filiae Dibon, quoniam vastator Moab ascendit ad te: dissipavit munitiones tuas.

text: and I will turn their mourning into joy, and will comfort them, and make them joyful after their sorrow.
verse_text: and I will bring them again into this place, and will cause them to dwell securely.

text: If thou loue to heare, thou shalt receiue vnderstanding: and if thou bow thine eare, thou shalt be wise.
verse_text: My sonne, if thou wilt, thou shalt bee taught: and if thou wilt apply thy minde, thou shalt be prudent.

text: And if for want of power hee be hindered from sinning, yet when he findeth opportunitie he wil doe euil.
verse_text: Est correptio mendax in ira contumeliosi, et est judicium quod non probatur esse bonum: et est tacens, et ipse est prudens.

text: Thus saith the Lord; After this maner will I marre the pride of Iudah, and the great pride of Ierusalem.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord of hosts, Behold, I will breake the bow of Elam, the chiefe of their might.

text: A faithful friend is the medicine of life and immortality: and they that fear the Lord, shall find him.
verse_text: The spirit of those that fear God; is sought after, and by his regard shall be blessed.

text: confusus est artifex omnis in sculptili, quoniam falsum est quod conflavit, et non est spiritus in eis.
verse_text: confusus est omnis conflator in sculptili:

text: God spake in his holie: I wil reioyce, and wil diuide Sichem, and I wil mesure the vale of tabernacles.
verse_text: God hath spoken in his holinesse, I wil reioyce: I will diuide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.

text: He brought floods also out of the stonie rocke; so that hee made the waters to descend like the riuers.
verse_text: He opened the rocke, and the waters flowed out, and ranne in the drye places like a riuer.

text: In finem. Psalmus David. Usquequo, Domine, oblivisceris me in finem? usquequo avertis faciem tuam a me?
verse_text: Psalmus ipsi David. Ad te, Domine, clamabo; Deus meus, ne sileas a me: nequando taceas a me, et assimilabor descendentibus in lacum.

text: Erubescant, et conturbentur vehementer, omnes inimici mei; convertantur, et erubescant valde velociter.
verse_text: Confundantur et revereantur quaerentes animam meam; avertantur retrorsum et confundantur cogitantes mihi mala.

text: His mouth is full of cursing, and of bitterness, and of deceit: under his tongue are labour and sorrow.
verse_text: His mouth is full of cursing and deceite and fraude: vnder his tongue is mischiefe and iniquitie.

text: Looke vpon the rainebow, and praise him that made it, very beautifull it is in the brightnesse thereof.
verse_text: In verbis Sancti stabunt ad judicium, et non deficient in vigiliis suis.

text: Shall I not visit for these things, saith the Lord? or shall not my soul take revenge on such a nation?
verse_text: Shall I not visit them for these things, saith the Lord ? shall not my soule be auenged on such a nation as this?

text: And the Lord said to me: from the north shall an evil break forth upon all the inhabitants of the land.
verse_text: And the land shall be in a commotion, and shall be troubled: for the design of the Lord against Babylon shall awake, to make the land of Babylon desert and uninhabitable.

text: Quia tu es, Deus, fortitudo mea: quare me repulisti? et quare tristis incedo, dum affligit me inimicus?
verse_text: Quare tristis es, anima mea? et quare conturbas me? Spera in Deo, quoniam adhuc confitebor illi, salutare vultus mei,

text: Super hoc accingite vos ciliciis; plangite, et ululate: quia non est aversa ira furoris Domini a nobis.
verse_text: Qui fugistis gladium, venite, nolite stare: recordamini procul Domini, et Jerusalem ascendat super cor vestrum.

text: In finem. Psalmus David, canticum Jeremiae et Ezechielis populo transmigrationis, cum inciperent exire.
verse_text: In finem, pro iis qui commutabuntur. Testimonium Asaph, psalmus.

text: Deus, vitam meam annuntiavi tibi; posuisti lacrimas meas in conspectu tuo, sicut et in promissione tua:
verse_text: Si ambulavero in medio tribulationis, vivificabis me; et super iram inimicorum meorum extendisti manum tuam, et salvum me fecit dextera tua.

text: My sonne, if thou wilt, thou shalt bee taught: and if thou wilt apply thy minde, thou shalt be prudent.
verse_text: Stolam gloriae indues eam, et coronam gratulationis superpones tibi.

text: A man that hath trauailed knoweth many things: and hee that hath much experience, wil declare wisedome.
verse_text: Qui non est tentatus quid scit? vir in multis expertus cogitabit multa: et qui multa didicit enarrabit intellectum.

text: The earth is moued at the noise of their fall: at the crie, the noise thereof was heard in the red Sea.
verse_text: At the noise of the taking of Babylon the earth is moued, and the cry is heard among the nations.

text: Withdrawe not thou thy tender mercie from mee, O Lord: let thy mercie and thy trueth alway preserue me.
verse_text: Turne not away thy face from me: decline not in wrath from thy seruant. Be thou my helper: forsake me not, neither despise me o God my Sauiour.

text: I wil euen giue them into the hand of their enemies, and into the handes of them that seeke their life:
verse_text: Thus sayth the Lord, Beholde, I will giue Pharaoh Hophra King of Egypt into the hand of his enemies, and into the hand of them that seeke his life:

text: As the climbing vp a sandie way is to the feete of the aged, so is a wife full of words to a quiet man.
verse_text: et omnem obductum, et non obductum odientium:

text: Zion heard of it, and was glad: and the daughters of Iudah reioyced, because of thy iudgements, O Lord.
verse_text: Let mount Zion reioyce, and the daughters of Iudah be glad, because of thy iudgements.

text: All wickednesse is but little to the wickednesse of a woman: let the portion of a sinner fall vpon her.
verse_text: et omnem nequitiam, et non nequitiam mulieris:

text: Who so casteth a stone on high, casteth it on his owne head, and a deceitfull stroke shall make wounds.
verse_text: Annuens oculo fabricat iniqua, et nemo eum abjiciet.

text: Hee that loueth his sonne, causeth him oft to feele the rodde, that hee may haue ioy of him in the end.
verse_text: Qui diligit filium suum assiduat illi flagella, ut laetetur in novissimo suo, et non palpet proximorum ostia.

text: And the King charged to doe so, and the decree was giuen at Shushan, and they hanged Hamans ten sonnes.
verse_text: Then said Esther, If it please the king, Let it bee granted to the Iewes which are in Shushan, to doe to morow also, according vnto this dayes decree, and let Hamans ten sonnes be hanged vpon the gallous.

text: Cocker thy childe, and hee shall make thee afraid: play with him, and he will bring thee to heauinesse.
verse_text: Lacta filium, et paventem te faciet: lude cum eo, et contristabit te.

text: For as I liue, and by the power of my kingdome, whatsoeuer I haue spoken, that will I doe by mine hand.
verse_text: Cumque pertransisset fines Assyriorum, venit ad magnos montes Ange, qui sunt a sinistro Ciliciae: ascenditque omnia castella eorum, et obtinuit omnem munitionem.

text: And they cried to our Lord when they were in tribulation, and he brought them out of their necessities.
verse_text: Then they cried vnto the Lord in their trouble, and he deliuered them from their distresse.

text: Drunkennesse increaseth the rage of a foole till he offend, it diminisheth strength, and maketh wounds.
verse_text: Diligentes in vino noli provocare: multos enim exterminavit vinum.

text: Wine measurably drunke, and in season, bringeth gladnesse of the heart and cheerefulnesse of the minde.
verse_text: Splendidum in panibus benedicent labia multorum, et testimonium veritatis illius fidele.

text: Speake thou that art the elder, for it becometh thee, but with sound iudgement, and hinder not musicke.
verse_text: ut laeteris propter illos, et ornamentum gratiae accipias coronam, et dignationem consequaris corrogationis.

text: Who so feareth the Lord, will receiue his discipline, and they that seeke him early, shall find fauour.
verse_text: Ante grandinem praeibit coruscatio: et ante verecundiam praeibit gratia, et pro reverentia accedet tibi bona gratia.

text: Eate as it becommeth a man those things which are set before thee: and deuoure not, lest thou be hated.
verse_text: Ne extendas manum tuam prior, et invidia contaminatus erubescas.

text: And the King sayde vnto them, I haue dreamed a dreame, and my spirite was troubled to knowe the dreame.
verse_text: Then answered the King, and sayde vnto Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, Art thou able to shew me the dreame, which I haue seene, and the interpretation thereof?

text: et extraxerunt Jeremiam funibus, et eduxerunt eum de lacu: mansit autem Jeremias in vestibulo carceris.
verse_text: miserunt, et tulerunt Jeremiam de vestibulo carceris, et tradiderunt eum Godoliae filio Ahicam filii Saphan, ut intraret in domum, et habitaret in populo.

text: It is the rudenesse of a man to hearken at the doore: but a wise man will be grieued with the disgrace.
verse_text: A man of counsell will be considerate, but a strange and proud man is not daunted with feare, euen when of himselfe he hath done without counsell.

text: I sate not in the assembly of the mockers, neither did I reioyce, but sate alone because of thy plague:
verse_text: I sat not in the assembly of jesters, nor did I make a boast of the presence of thy hand:

text: Corripe amicum, ne forte non intellexerit, et dicat: Non feci: aut, si fecerit, ne iterum addat facere.
verse_text: Si est tibi intellectus, responde proximo: sin autem, sit manus tua super os tuum, ne capiaris in verbo indisciplinato, et confundaris.

text: They shall be brought to Babel, and there they shalbe vntil the day that I visite them, saith the Lord:
verse_text: They shall be carried to Babylon, and there they shall be until the day of their visitation, saith the Lord:

text: There is that is hindred from sinning through want: and when hee taketh rest, he shall not be troubled.
verse_text: Homo acharis quasi fabula vana, in ore indisciplinatorum assidua erit.

text: In the prosperitie of a man, enemies will be grieued, but in his aduersitie, euen a friend will depart.
verse_text: In bonis viri, inimici illius in tristitia: et in malitia illius, amicus agnitus est.

text: When thou hast enough remember the time of hunger, and when thou art rich thinke vpon pouerty and need.
verse_text: Memento paupertatis in tempore abundantiae, et necessitatum paupertatis in die divitiarum.

text: It is the rudenesse of a man to hearken at the doore: but a wise man will be grieued with the disgrace.
verse_text: Ornamentum aureum prudenti doctrina, et quasi brachiale in brachio dextro.

text: From the morning vntill the euening the time is changed, and all things are soone done before the Lord.
verse_text: A mane usque ad vesperam immutabitur tempus, et haec omnia citata in oculis Dei.

text: Who so feareth the Lord, will receiue his discipline, and they that seeke him early, shall find fauour.
verse_text: He that serueth the Lord, shall be accepted with fauour, and his prayer shall reach vnto the cloudes.

text: The parables of knowledge are in the treasures of wisedome: but godlines is an abomination to a sinner.
verse_text: Radix sapientiae est timere Dominum, et rami illius longaevi.

text: Non te justifices ante Deum, quoniam agnitor cordis ipse est: et penes regem noli velle videri sapiens.
verse_text: Et noli inspicere sacrificum injustum, quoniam Dominus judex est, et non est apud illum gloria personae.

text: Blessed is the man that hath not slipt with his mouth, and is not pricked with the multitude of sinnes.
verse_text: Beatus vir qui non est lapsus verbo ex ore suo, et non est stimulatus in tristitia delicti.

text: What agreement is there betweene the Hyena and a dogge? and what peace betweene the rich and the poore?
verse_text: Omni vita tua dilige Deum, et invoca illum in salute tua.

text: I will thanke thee, O Lord and king, and praise thee O God my Sauiour, I doe giue praise vnto thy name:
verse_text: Oratio Jesu filii Sirach. Confitebor tibi, Domine rex, et collaudabo te Deum salvatorem meum.

text: he shall take thee and plucke thee out of thy tabernacle, and roote thee out of ye land of the liuing.
verse_text: Therfore wil God destroy thee for euer, he wil plucke thee out, & remoue thee out of thy tabernacle:

text: Because he hath stood on the righthand of the poore, that he might saue my soule from the persecutors.
verse_text: I know that the Lord will maintaine the cause of the afflicted: and the right of the poore.

text: Hee will keepe the sayings of the renowmed men: and where subtile parables are, he will be there also.
verse_text: Narrationem virorum nominatorum conservabit, et in versutias parabolarum simul introibit.

text: So they and all the countrey round about, receiued them with garlands, with dances, and with timbrels.
verse_text: Tunc descendit de montibus cum equitibus in virtute magna, et obtinuit omnem civitatem, et omnem inhabitantem terram.

text: Behold, he shal come vp like a lyon from the swelling of Iordane against the habitation of the strong:
verse_text: Behold he shall come up like a lion from the swelling of the Jordan to the strong and beautiful:

text: Now therefore why hast thou not reproued Ieremiah of Anathoth, which maketh himselfe a Prophet to you?
verse_text: Then said the Prophet Ieremiah vnto Hananiah the prophet, Heare nowe Hananiah: the Lord hath not sent thee, but thou makest this people to trust in a lye.

text: Et impii in testamentum simulabunt fraudulenter: populus autem sciens Deum suum, obtinebit, et faciet.
verse_text: Robur autem datum est ei contra juge sacrificium propter peccata: et prosternetur veritas in terra, et faciet, et prosperabitur.

text: Then was the King exceeding glad for him, and commanded that they should take Daniel out of the denne:
verse_text: Then the king commanded, and they brought Daniel, and cast him into the denne of Lions:

text: If thou haue a seruant, let him bee vnto thee as thy selfe, because thou hast bought him with a price.
verse_text: In opera constitue eum: sic enim condecet illum. Quod si non obaudierit, curva illum compedibus, et non amplifices super omnem carnem: verum sine judicio nihil facias grave.

text: Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is the strength of mine head; Iudah is my Lawgiuer.
verse_text: Galaad is mine, and Manasses is mine: and Ephraim the protection of my head. Iuda is my king:

text: At the same time was mine vnderstanding restored vnto me, and I returned to the honour of my kingdome:
verse_text: my glory and my beautie was restored vnto me, and my counsellours and my princes sought vnto me, and I was established in my kingdome, and my glory was augmented toward me.

text: and Ieremiah the prophet was shut vp in the court of the prison which was in the king of Iudahs house.
verse_text: eunuches which was in the kings house, heard that they had put Ieremiah in the dungeon (the king then sitting in the gate of Beniamin)

text: Forsake me not o Lord my God, depart not from me. Attend vnto my help, o Lord the God of my saluation.
verse_text: Forsake me not, O Lord: O my God, be not farre from me.

text: The affliction of an houre, maketh a man forget pleasure: and in his end, his deeds shalbe discouered.
verse_text: In die bonorum ne immemor sis malorum, et in die malorum ne immemor sis bonorum:

text: Hearken to me, my son, and learn the discipline of understanding, and attend to my words in thy heart.
verse_text: Give ear, my son, and take wise counsel, and cast not away my advice.

text: And they that know thy Name, will trust in thee: for thou, Lord, hast not failed them that seeke thee.
verse_text: For thou, O God, hast heard my vowes: thou hast giuen me the heritage of those that feare thy name.

text: The Lord hath sworne, and will not repent, thou art a Priest for euer: after the order of Melchizedek.
verse_text: Our Lord sware, and it shal not repent him: Thou art a Priest for euer according to the order of Melchisedech.

text: Unlesse a man hold himselfe diligently in the feare of the Lord, his house shall soone be ouerthrowen.
verse_text: conteretur cum delinquente delictum.

text: Iste est populus quem transtulit Nabuchodonosor: in anno septimo, Judaeos tria millia et viginti tres:
verse_text: in anno octavodecimo Nabuchodonosor, de Jerusalem animas octingentas triginta duas:

text: As with a sword in my bones, mine enemies reproch mee: while they say dayly vnto me, Where is thy God?
verse_text: My teares haue bin my meate day and night, while they dayly say vnto me, Where is thy God?

text: He shall also set his face to enter with the strength of his whole kingdome and vpright ones with him:
verse_text: He shall enter also into the glorious land, and many countreys shall be ouerthrowen:

text: donec reddat hominibus secundum actus suos, et secundum opera Adae, et secundum praesumptionem illius:
verse_text: Et postea resurget, et retribuet illis retributionem, unicuique in caput ipsorum, et convertet in interiores partes terrae.

text: But Gedaliah the sonne of Ahikam said vnto Iohanan the sonne of Kareah, Thou shalt not doe this thing:
verse_text: And Gedaliah the sonne of Ahikam, the sonne of Shaphan sware vnto them, and to their men, saying, Feare not to serue the Caldeans:

text: At the commandement of the holy One, they will stand in their order, and neuer faint in their watches.
verse_text: Species caeli gloria stellarum: mundum illuminans in excelsis Dominus.

text: Miserere mei, Domine, quoniam tribulor; conturbatus est in ira oculus meus, anima mea, et venter meus.
verse_text: Libera me, quia egenus et pauper ego sum, et cor meum conturbatum est intra me.

text: Now the worde of the Lord came vnto Ieremiah, while he was shut vp in the court of the prison, saying,
verse_text: And the word of the Lord came to Jeremias the second time, while he was yet shut up in the court of the prison, saying:

text: de furto, de veritate Dei, et testamento: de discubitu in panibus, et ab obfuscatione dati et accepti:
verse_text: De disciplina insensati et fatui, et de senioribus qui judicantur ab adolescentibus: et eris eruditus in omnibus, et probabilis in conspectu omnium vivorum.

text: He made him like to the glorious Saints, and magnified him, so that his enemies stood in feare of him.
verse_text: Similem illum fecit in gloria sanctorum, et magnificavit eum in timore inimicorum, et in verbis suis monstra placavit.

text: And I will give them into the hands of their enemies, and into the hands of them that seek their life:
verse_text: and I will destroy them with the sword in the sight of their enemies, and by the hands of them that seek their lives:

text: The sinner shall be left in his foolishnesse: both the euill speaker and the proud shall fall thereby.
verse_text: In vanitate sua apprehenditur peccator: et superbus et maledicus scandalizabitur in illis.

text: Now the word of the Lord came vnto Ieremiah, while hee was shut vp in the court of the prison, saying;
verse_text: And the word of the Lord came to Jeremias the second time, while he was yet shut up in the court of the prison, saying:

text: Though thou drewest a sword at thy friend, yet despaire not, for there way be a returning (to fauour.)
verse_text: Sicut pali in excelsis, et caementa sine impensa posita, contra faciem venti non permanebunt:

text: A tale out of season musick in mourning: but stripes and correction of wisedome are neuer out of time.
verse_text: Musica in luctu importuna narratio: flagella et doctrina in omni tempore sapientia.

text: A wise man wil hold his tongue till he see opportunitie: but a babler and a foole will regard no time.
verse_text: Homo sapiens tacebit usque ad tempus: lascivus autem et imprudens non servabunt tempus.

text: He tooke some of them away, and destroyed them, and hath made their memoriall to cease from the earth.
verse_text: Sedes ducum superborum destruxit Deus, et sedere fecit mites pro eis.

text: The king is not saued by much powre: and the gyant shal not be saued in the multitude of his strength.
verse_text: He shal not haue pleasure in the strength of an horse: nor in the legges of a man shal he be wel pleased.

text: There is a sinner that hath good successe in euill things; and there is a gaine that turneth to losse.
verse_text: Est processio in malis viro indisciplinato, et est inventio in detrimentum.

text: Behold I will deliver this city into the hands of the king of Babylon, and he shall burn it with fire.
verse_text: This city shall surely be delivered into the hand of the army of the king of Babylon, and he shall take it.

text: Thy habitation is in the midst of deceit: Through deceit they have refused to know me, saith the Lord.
verse_text: And they have bent their tongue, as a bow, for lies, and not for truth: they have strengthened themselves upon the earth, for they have proceeded from evil to evil, and me they have not known, saith the Lord.

text: Sicut boum jugum quod movetur, ita et mulier nequam: qui tenet illam quasi qui apprehendit scorpionem.
verse_text: Quasi qui apprehendit umbram et persequitur ventum, sic et qui attendit ad visa mendacia.

text: Therefore all their workes are as the Sunne before him, and his eyes are continually vpon their wayes.
verse_text: Et postea resurget, et retribuet illis retributionem, unicuique in caput ipsorum, et convertet in interiores partes terrae.

text: He directed his heart vnto the Lord, and in the time of the vngodly he established the worship of God.
verse_text: Ipse est directus divinitus in poenitentiam gentis, et tulit abominationes impietatis.

text: The heart of the prudent will vnderstand a parable, and an attentiue eare is the desire of a wise man.
verse_text: Cor nequam gravabitur in doloribus, et peccator adjiciet ad peccandum.

text: Then her wordes pleased Olofernes, and all his seruants, and they marueiled at her wisedome, and said,
verse_text: Now when Iudeth came in, and sate downe, Olofernes his heart was rauished with her, and his minde was moued, and he desired greatly her company, for hee waited a time to deceiue her, from the day that he had seene her.

text: And they that lay neere Olofernes, went out, and all his seruants, and they brought her into the tent.
verse_text: Then was there a concourse throughout all the campe: for her comming was noised among the tents, and they came about her, as she stood without the tent of Olofernes, till they told him of her.

text: And they that lay neere Olofernes, went out, and all his seruants, and they brought her into the tent.
verse_text: et cum in faciem ejus intendisset, adoravit eum, prosternens se super terram. Et elevaverunt eam servi Holofernis, jubente domino suo.

text: The affliction of an houre, maketh a man forget pleasure: and in his end, his deeds shalbe discouered.
verse_text: A furious man cannot be iustified, for the sway of his fury shalbe his destruction.

text: With thee is my praise in the great Church: I wil render my vowes in the sight of them that feare him.
verse_text: I will declare thy name to my bretheren: in the middes of the Church I wil prayse thee.

text: Sem and Seth were in great honour among men, and so was Adam aboue euery liuing thing in the creation.
verse_text: Nemo natus est in terra qualis Henoch, nam et ipse receptus est a terra:

text: And here is hope for thy last end, saith the Lord: and the children shall return to their own borders.
verse_text: But in the latter days I will cause the captives of Elam, to return, saith the Lord.

text: Then her wordes pleased Olofernes, and all his seruants, and they marueiled at her wisedome, and said,
verse_text: Et dixit ad illam Holofernes: Benefecit Deus, qui misit te ante populum, ut des illum tu in manibus nostris:
