text: Lex Domini immaculata, convertens animas; testimonium Domini fidele, sapientiam praestans parvulis.
verse_text: Qui custodit veritatem in saeculum; facit judicium injuriam patientibus; dat escam esurientibus. Dominus solvit compeditos;

text: Et amplificaverunt psallentes in vocibus suis, et in magna domo auctus est sonus suavitatis plenus.
verse_text: Et rogavit populus Dominum excelsum in prece, usque dum perfectus est honor Domini, et munus suum perfecerunt.

text: He that forsaketh his father, is as a blasphemer, and he that angreth his mother, is cursed of God.
verse_text: Nam pro peccato matris restituetur tibi bonum:

text: He that feareth the Lord will doe good, and he that hath the knowledge of the Law shal obtaine her.
verse_text: Qui timet Deum faciet bona, et qui continens est justitiae apprehendet illam:

text: Timor Domini sanctus, permanens in saeculum saeculi; judicia Domini vera, justificata in semetipsa,
verse_text: Dispersit, dedit pauperibus; justitia ejus manet in saeculum saeculi: cornu ejus exaltabitur in gloria.

text: The I heard it, but I vnderstood it not: the said I, O my Lord, what shalbe ye end of these things?
verse_text: The king answered, & sayd: Surely I know that you redeme time, knowing that the word is departed from me.

text: He that requiteth a good turne, offereth fine floure: and he that giueth almes, sacrificeth praise.
verse_text: Sacrificium salutare est attendere mandatis, et discedere ab omni iniquitate.

text: It is a stumbling block vnto them that sacrifice vnto it, and euery foole shall be taken therewith.
verse_text: Lignum offensionis est aurum sacrificantium: vae illis qui sectantur illud ! et omnis imprudens deperiet in illo.

text: And finishing the seruice at the altar, that he might adorne the offring of the most high Almighty,
verse_text: sic circa illum steterunt quasi rami palmae: et omnes filii Aaron in gloria sua.

text: For thou, O God, hast heard my vowes: thou hast giuen me the heritage of those that feare thy name.
verse_text: And let them hope in thee that know thy name: because thou hast not forsaken them that seeke thee o Lord.

text: The sinner shall not escape with his spoiles, and the patience of the godly shall not be frustrate.
verse_text: Secundum misericordiam suam, sic correptio illius homines secundum opera sua judicat.

text: Therfore will I giue thankes vnto thee, (O Lord) among the heathen: and sing prayses vnto thy name.
verse_text: I will bee glad and reioyce in thee: I will sing prayse to thy name, O thou most High.

text: Because thou my God hast heard my prayer: thou hast giuen inheritance to those that feare thy name.
verse_text: And they that know thy Name, will trust in thee: for thou, Lord, hast not failed them that seeke thee.

text: Praise ye the Lord. O giue thankes vnto the Lord, for he is good: for his mercie endureth for euer.
verse_text: Praise yee the Lord, because he is good: for his mercie endureth for euer.

text: For it is an easie thing vnto the Lord in the day of death, to reward a man according to his wayes.
verse_text: Ne dicas: Sufficiens mihi sum: et quid ex hoc pessimabor?

text: Cumque loqueretur ad me, collapsus sum pronus in terram: et tetigit me, et statuit me in gradu meo,
verse_text: Rursum ergo tetigit me quasi visio hominis, et confortavit me,

text: O rex, Deus altissimus regnum et magnificentiam, gloriam et honorem dedit Nabuchodonosor patri tuo.
verse_text: Nunc igitur, ego Nabuchodonosor laudo, et magnifico, et glorifico regem caeli: quia omnia opera ejus vera, et viae ejus judicia, et gradientes in superbia potest humiliare.

text: et circumcinxit eum zona gloriae, et induit eum stolam gloriae, et coronavit eum in vasis virtutis.
verse_text: quasi oliva pullulans, et cypressus in altitudinem se extollens, in accipiendo ipsum stolam gloriae, et vestiri eum in consummationem virtutis.

text: As the golden pillars are vpon the sockets of siluer: so are the faire feete with a constant heart.
verse_text: Mulier sensata et tacita, non est immutatio eruditae animae.

text: Breake thou the arme of the wicked and malicious: searche his wickednes, and thou shalt finde none.
verse_text: Thou shalt destroy them that speake lyes: the Lord will abhorre the bloodie man and deceitfull.

text: Thus shalt thou render them an euil reward: because they rebelled and met not thy person peaceably.
verse_text: Et nunc congregate universos qui in civitate sunt, ut sponte tradamus nos omnes populo Holofernis.

text: Because thou art the glorie of their streingth: and in thy good pleasure shal our horne be exalted.
verse_text: For thou art the glory of their strength, and by thy fauour our hornes shall be exalted.

text: As in the ouerthrowe of Sodom, and of Gomorah, and the places thereof neere about, saieth the Lord:
verse_text: As the Lord overthrew Sodom and Gomorrha, and their neighbour cities, saith the Lord:

text: Many when a thing was lent them, reckoned it to be found, and put them to trouble that helped them.
verse_text: Multi quasi inventionem aestimaverunt foenus, et praestiterunt molestiam his qui se adjuverunt.

text: The stroke of the whip maketh markes in the flesh, but the stroke of the tongue breaketh the bones.
verse_text: Civitates muratas divitum destruxit, et domus magnatorum effodit.

text: Let them curse, but blesse thou: when they arise, let them be ashamed, but let thy seruant reioyce.
verse_text: Let mee not be ashamed, O Lord, for I haue called vpon thee: let the wicked be ashamed, and let them be silent in the graue.

text: A faithfull friend is a strong defence: and hee that hath found such an one, hath found a treasure.
verse_text: An honest man is suretie for his neighbour: but hee that is impudent, will forsake him.

text: Qui timent Dominum inquirent quae beneplacita sunt ei, et qui diligunt eum replebuntur lege ipsius.
verse_text: Qui timent Dominum custodiunt mandata illius, et patientiam habebunt usque ad inspectionem illius,

text: Posuisti nos opprobrium vicinis nostris; subsannationem et derisum his qui sunt in circuitu nostro.
verse_text: Posuisti nos in contradictionem vicinis nostris, et inimici nostri subsannaverunt nos.

text: habitabo vobiscum in loco isto, in terra quam dedi patribus vestris a saeculo et usque in saeculum.
verse_text: faciam domui huic, in qua invocatum est nomen meum, et in qua vos habetis fiduciam, et loco quem dedi vobis et patribus vestris, sicut feci Silo:

text: for I wil turne their mourning into ioy, and wil comfort them, and giue them ioy for their sorowes.
verse_text: for I wil cause their captiuitie to returne, and haue compassion on them.

text: But Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah, escaped from Iohanan with eight men, and went to the Ammonites.
verse_text: Then they tooke all the men, and went to fight with Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah, and found him by the great waters that are in Gibeon.

text: In the waues of the sea, and in all the earth, and in euery people, and nation, I got a possession.
verse_text: Ego feci in caelis ut oriretur lumen indeficiens, et sicut nebula texi omnem terram.

text: A good understanding will hide his words for a time, and the lips of many shall declare his wisdom.
verse_text: The heart of the wise is understood in wisdom, and a good ear will hear wisdom with all desire.

text: Fili, accedens ad servitutem Dei sta in justitia et timore, et praepara animam tuam ad tentationem.
verse_text: Fili, in mansuetudine serva animam tuam, et da illi honorem secundum meritum suum.

text: A Psalme of David. I will praise thee with my whole heart: euen before the gods will I praise thee.
verse_text: Praise yee the Lord. I will praise the Lord with my whole heart: in the assembly of the vpright, and in the Congregation.

text: Benedicite, cete, et omnia quae moventur in aquis, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, fulgura et nubes, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Let my prayer be directed as incense in thy sight: the eleuation of my handes as euening sacrifice.
verse_text: Heare the voyce of my supplications, when I cry vnto thee: when I lift vp my handes toward thy holy Oracle.

text: I wil extol thee, O Lord, for thou hast lifted me vp; and hast not made my foes to reioyce ouer me.
verse_text: make ioyful the soule of thy seruant, because to thee o Lord haue I lifted vp my soule.

text: And they shall drinke, and be moued and be mad, because of the sworde that I will sende among them.
verse_text: For I will cause Elam to be afraied before their enemies, and before them that seeke their liues, and will bring vpon them a plague, euen the indignation of my wrath, saieth the Lord, and I wil sende the sworde after them till I haue consumed them.

text: As is the lust of an Eunuch to defloure a virgine; so is he that executeth iudgement with violence.
verse_text: Quam bonum est correptum manifestare poenitentiam ! sic enim effugies voluntarium peccatum.

text: But of the poor of the land, Nabuzardan the general left some for vinedressers, and for husbandmen.
verse_text: But Nabuzardan the general carried away captives some of the poor people, and of the rest of the common sort who remained in the city, and of the fugitives that were fled over to the king of Babylon, and the rest of the multitude.

text: I will visit upon that nation with the sword, and with famine, and with pestilence, saith the Lord:
verse_text: And I will send among them the sword, and the famine, and the pestilence:

text: they shall not bee mourned, neither gathered nor buried, but shalbe as the dongue vpon the grounde.
verse_text: they shall not be buried, neither shall men lament for them nor cut themselues, nor make themselues balde for them.

text: The fear of the Lord shall delight the heart, and shall give joy, and gladness, and length of days.
verse_text: The feare of the Lord maketh a merrie heart, and giueth ioy and gladnesse, and a long life.

text: Smoke went out at his nostrels, and a consuming fire out of his mouth: coales were kindled thereat.
verse_text: There went vp a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth deuoured, coales were kindled by it.

text: Keepe mee from the snare which they haue laide for me, and the grinnes of the workers of iniquitie.
verse_text: Keepe mee, O Lord, from the handes of the wicked: preserue mee from the cruell man, which purposeth to cause my steppes to slide.

text: My sonne, sow not vpon the furrowes of vnrighteousnesse, and thou shalt not reape them seuen folde.
verse_text: Fili, non semines mala in sulcis injustitiae, et non metes ea in septuplum.

text: A faithfull friend is a strong defence: and hee that hath found such an one, hath found a treasure.
verse_text: Amicus fidelis protectio fortis: qui autem invenit illum, invenit thesaurum.

text: Againe some friend is a companion at the table, and will not continue in the day of thy affliction.
verse_text: Est autem amicus socius mensae, et non permanebit in die necessitatis.

text: To be desired aboue gold and much pretious stone: and more sweete aboue honie and the honie combe.
verse_text: More to bee desired are they then gold, yea, then much fine gold: sweeter also then hony, and the hony combe.

text: They shal vtter the memorie of the abundance of thy swetnes: and in thy iustice they shal reioyce.
verse_text: They shal tel the glorie of thy kingdom: and shal speake thy might.

text: Ecce ego tradam civitatem istam in manus Chaldaeorum, et in manus regis Babylonis, et capient eam.
verse_text: Si autem non exieris ad principes regis Babylonis, tradetur civitas haec in manus Chaldaeorum, et succendent eam igni:

text: nequando dicat inimicus meus: Praevalui adversus eum. Qui tribulant me exsultabunt si motus fuero;
verse_text: Dum confringuntur ossa mea, exprobraverunt mihi qui tribulant me inimici mei, dum dicunt mihi per singulos dies: Ubi est Deus tuus?

text: Dominus de caelo prospexit super filios hominum, ut videat si est intelligens, aut requirens Deum.
verse_text: Et dicet homo: Si utique est fructus justo, utique est Deus judicans eos in terra.

text: The knowledge of wickednes is not wisedome, neither at any time the counsell of sinners, prudence.
verse_text: Est solertia certa, et ipsa iniqua:

text: Honour thy father and mother, both in word and deed, that a blessing may come vpon thee from them.
verse_text: Qui timet Dominum honorat parentes, et quasi dominis serviet his qui se genuerunt.

text: In die mandavit Dominus misericordiam suam, et nocte canticum ejus; apud me oratio Deo vitae meae.
verse_text: Misit de caelo, et liberavit me; dedit in opprobrium conculcantes me. Misit Deus misericordiam suam et veritatem suam,

text: Distrust not the feare of the Lord when thou art poore: and come not vnto him with a double heart.
verse_text: nam qui sine timore est non poterit justificari: iracundia enim animositatis illius subversio illius est.

text: But we know none other god: therefore we trust that he will not despise vs, nor any of our nation.
verse_text: Expectemus humiles consolationem ejus, et exquiret sanguinem nostrum de afflictionibus inimicorum nostrorum, et humiliabit omnes gentes, quaecumque insurgunt contra nos, et faciet illas sine honore Dominus Deus noster.

text: A fool will peep through the window into the house: but he that is well taught will stand without.
verse_text: He that is not wise in good, will not be taught.

text: Praecipita, Domine; divide linguas eorum: quoniam vidi iniquitatem et contradictionem in civitate.
verse_text: Leva manus tuas in superbias eorum in finem: quanta malignatus est inimicus in sancto !

text: They that feare the Lord, will not disobey his word, and they that loue him, will keepe his wayes.
verse_text: Vae dissolutis corde, qui non credunt Deo, et ideo non protegentur ab eo !

text: We are become a reproach to our neighbours: a scorne and derision to them that are round about vs.
verse_text: Thou makest vs a reproche to our neighbours, a iest and a laughing stocke to them that are round about vs.

text: A man of an ill tongue is dangerous in his citie, and he that is rash in his talke shall be hated.
verse_text: Longe abesto ab homine potestatem habente occidendi, et non suspicaberis timorem mortis.

text: And brought them to mount Sina, and Cades Barne, and cast forth all that dwelt in the wildernesse.
verse_text: Egressi vero mare Rubrum, deserta Sina montis occupaverunt, in quibus numquam homo habitare potuit, vel filius hominis requievit.

text: Let them praise his Name in the dance: let them sing praises vnto him with the timbrell and harpe.
verse_text: Praise him with the timbrell and dance: praise him with stringed instruments, and Organes.

text: Hear ye the word of the Lord, all ye men of Juda, that enter in at these gates, to adore the Lord.
verse_text: Hear ye the word of the Lord, all Juda, you that dwell in the land of Egypt:

text: Heare me, O ye great men of the people, and hearken with your eares ye rulers of the Congregation:
verse_text: Respicite quoniam non mihi soli laboravi, sed omnibus exquirentibus disciplinam.

text: Confirma verbum, et fideliter age cum illo: et in omni tempore invenies quod tibi necessarium est.
verse_text: Secundum virtutem tuam cave te a proximo tuo, et cum sapientibus et prudentibus tracta.

text: Receiue a stranger into thine house, and hee will disturbe thee, and turne thee out of thine owne.
verse_text: A scintilla una augetur ignis, et ab uno doloso augetur sanguis: homo vero peccator sanguini insidiatur.

text: Let nothing hinder thee to pay thy vowe in due time, and deferre not vntill death to be iustified.
verse_text: Non impediaris orare semper, et ne verearis usque ad mortem justificari, quoniam merces Dei manet in aeternum.

text: Tau Appropinquet deprecatio mea in conspectu tuo, Domine; juxta eloquium tuum da mihi intellectum.
verse_text: Vau Et veniat super me misericordia tua, Domine; salutare tuum secundum eloquium tuum.

text: How good is it when thou art reproued, to shew repentance? for so shalt thou escape wilfull sinne.
verse_text: sic qui facit per vim judicium iniquum.

text: Helpe thy neighbour according to thy power, and beware that thou thy selfe fall not into the same.
verse_text: Gratiam fidejussoris ne obliviscaris: dedit enim pro te animam suam.

text: I fainted in my mourning: I cause my bed euery night to swimme, and water my couch with my teares.
verse_text: For I haue eaten ashes like bread: and mingled my drinke with weeping.

text: Universae viae Domini, misericordia et veritas, requirentibus testamentum ejus et testimonia ejus.
verse_text: justitia et judicium praeparatio sedis tuae: misericordia et veritas praecedent faciem tuam.

text: Deus, Deus meus, respice in me: quare me dereliquisti? longe a salute mea verba delictorum meorum.
verse_text: Intende ad deprecationem meam, quia humiliatus sum nimis. Libera me a persequentibus me, quia confortati sunt super me.

text: Inimici autem mei vivunt, et confirmati sunt super me: et multiplicati sunt qui oderunt me inique.
verse_text: Non supergaudeant mihi qui adversantur mihi inique, qui oderunt me gratis, et annuunt oculis.

text: If thou sit at a bountifull table, bee not greedy vpon it, and say not, There is much meate on it.
verse_text: Supra mensam magnam sedisti? non aperias super illam faucem tuam prior.

text: For therein be strange and wonderous workes, varietie of all kindes of beasts, and whales created.
verse_text: In sermone ejus siluit ventus, et cogitatione sua placavit abyssum: et plantavit in illa Dominus insulas.

text: As a signet of an Emeraud set in a worke of gold, so is the melodie of musicke with pleasant wine.
verse_text: Ubi auditus non est, non effundas sermonem, et importune noli extolli in sapientia tua.

text: Deus, Deus meus, ad te de luce vigilo. Sitivit in te anima mea; quam multipliciter tibi caro mea !
verse_text: Fortitudinem meam ad te custodiam, quia, Deus, susceptor meus es:

text: O God, howe long shall the aduersarie reproche thee? shall the enemie blaspheme thy Name for euer?
verse_text: Lord, howe long wilt thou be angrie, for euer? shall thy gelousie burne like fire?

text: Many mightie men haue beene greatly disgraced: and the honourable deliuered into other mens hands.
verse_text: Multi potentes oppressi sunt valide, et gloriosi traditi sunt in manus alterorum.

text: My sonne, in thy sickenesse be not negligent: but pray vnto the Lord, and he will make thee whole.
verse_text: Fili, in tua infirmitate ne despicias teipsum: sed ora Dominum, et ipse curabit te.

text: Itaque ingressus est Jeremias in domum laci et in ergastulum: et sedit ibi Jeremias diebus multis.
verse_text: egressus est Jeremias de Jerusalem ut iret in terram Benjamin, et divideret ibi possessionem in conspectu civium.

text: For thou, Lord, hast made mee glad by thy workes, and I wil reioyce in the workes of thine handes.
verse_text: I will be glad, and reioyce in thy mercie: for thou hast considered my trouble; thou hast knowen my soule in aduersities;

text: aperi oculos tuos, et vide desolationem nostram, et civitatem super quam invocatum est nomen tuum:
verse_text: ne moreris propter temetipsum, Deus meus, quia nomen tuum invocatum est super civitatem et super populum tuum.

text: The Lord on high is mightier then the noise of many waters, yea then the mightie waues of the Sea.
verse_text: The riuers haue lifted vp their waues, aboue the voices of manie waters. The surges of the sea are meruelous; meruelous is our Lord on high.

text: Usque in aeternum praeparabo semen tuum, et aedificabo in generationem et generationem sedem tuam.
verse_text: Quoniam dixisti: In aeternum misericordia aedificabitur in caelis; praeparabitur veritas tua in eis.

text: Psalmus David, Jeremiae. Super flumina Babylonis illic sedimus et flevimus, cum recordaremur Sion.
verse_text: In finem. Psalmus David in rememorationem, quod salvum fecerit eum Dominus.

text: Hope in our Lord and doe good: and inhabite the land, and thou shalt be fed in the riches thereof.
verse_text: Tast ye, and see that our Lord is sweete: blessed is the man, that hopeth in him.

text: Hee declareth the things that are past, and for to come, and reueileth the steps of hidden things.
verse_text: Cognovit enim Dominus omnem scientiam, et inspexit in signum aevi, annuntians quae praeterierunt et quae superventura sunt, revelans vestigia occultorum.

text: Psalmus ipsi David. Dominus regnavit: irascantur populi; qui sedet super cherubim: moveatur terra.
verse_text: Confessio ejus super caelum et terram; et exaltavit cornu populi sui. Hymnus omnibus sanctis ejus; filiis Israel, populo appropinquanti sibi. Alleluja.

text: And if you be borne, you shall be borne to a curse: and if you die, a curse shall be your portion.
verse_text: Filiorum peccatorum periet haereditas, et cum semine illorum assiduitas opprobrii.

text: Laboravi in gemitu meo; lavabo per singulas noctes lectum meum: lacrimis meis stratum meum rigabo.
verse_text: Dixi: Custodiam vias meas: ut non delinquam in lingua mea. Posui ori meo custodiam, cum consisteret peccator adversum me.

text: For mine enemies speake against mee: and they that lay waite for my soule, take counsell together,
verse_text: All that hate me, whisper together against me; against me doe they deuise my hurt.

text: For thus saith the Lord, Beholde, he shall flee as an eagle, and shall spread his wings ouer Moab.
verse_text: Behold, he shall come vp and flie as the eagle, and spread his wings ouer Bozrah: and at that day shall the heart of the mightie men of Edom, be as the heart of a woman in her pangs.

text: I Daniel was grieued in my spirit in the midst of my body, and the visions of my head troubled me.
verse_text: Saw a dreame, which made me afraide, and the thoughtes vpon my bed, and the visions of mine head troubled me.

text: Wisedome hath beene created before all things, and the vnderstanding of prudence from euerlasting.
verse_text: Prior omnium creata est sapientia, et intellectus prudentiae ab aevo.

text: Who can finde out the height of heauen, and the breadth of the earth, and the deepe, and wisedome?
verse_text: sapientiam Dei praecedentem omnia, quis investigavit?

text: Hee was not pacified towards the olde giants, who fell away in the strength of their foolishnesse.
verse_text: In synagoga peccantium exardebit ignis, et in gente incredibili exardescet ira.

text: Againe, say not, I haue enough, and possesse many things; and what euill can come to me hereafter?
verse_text: Benedictio Dei in mercedem justi festinat, et in hora veloci processus illius fructificat.

text: The word of God most high, is the fountaine of wisdome, & her wayes are euerlasting commandements.
verse_text: Fons sapientiae verbum Dei in excelsis, et ingressus illius mandata aeterna.

text: Because thou hast deliuered my soule from death, mine eyes from teares, and my feete from falling.
verse_text: Because thou hast deliuered my soule from death, and my feete from falling: that I may please before God, in the light of the liuing.

text: Blessed is he that waiteth, and commeth to the thousand, three hundred and fiue and thirtie dayes.
verse_text: And from the time that the dayly sacrifice shalbe taken away, and the abomination that maketh desolate set vp, there shalbe a thousand two hundred and ninetie dayes.

text: and hee doth according to his will in the armie of heauen, and among the inhabitants of the earth:
verse_text: for he doth according to his wil, as wel in the powres of heauen, as in the inhabitants of the earth:

text: Jubilate Deo, omnis terra; servite Domino in laetitia. Introite in conspectu ejus in exsultatione.
verse_text: Omnes gentes, plaudite manibus; jubilate Deo in voce exsultationis:

text: I will praise thy name continually, and will praise it with thanksgiving, and my prayer was heard.
verse_text: I will give glory to thy name: for thou hast been a helper and protector to me.

text: If thou followest righteousnesse, thou shalt obtaine her, and put her on, as a glorious long robe.
verse_text: Ante sermonem non laudes virum: haec enim tentatio est hominum.

text: Prayse the Lord, all ye his workes, in all places of his dominion: my soule, prayse thou the Lord.
verse_text: Prayse the Lord, ye that feare him: magnifie ye him, all the seede of Iaakob, and feare ye him, all the seede of Israel.

text: And Moab shall be destroyed from being a people, because he hath set vp himselfe against the Lord.
verse_text: There shall bee no more prayse of Moab: in Heshbon they haue deuised euill against it; come and let vs cut it off from being a nation; also thou shalt bee cut downe, O Madmen, the sword shall pursue thee.

text: The man that is accustomed to opprobrious words, will neuer be reformed all the daies of his life.
verse_text: Est et alia loquela contraria morti: non inveniatur in haereditate Jacob.

text: Quoniam abscondit me in tabernaculo suo; in die malorum protexit me in abscondito tabernaculi sui.
verse_text: In tribulatione invocasti me, et liberavi te. Exaudivi te in abscondito tempestatis; probavi te apud aquam contradictionis.

text: Gilead is mine, Manasseh is mine, Ephraim also is the strength of mine head: Iudah is my Lawgiuer.
verse_text: Galaad is mine, and Manasses is mine: and Ephraim the protection of my head. Iuda is my king:

text: But Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah escaped from Iohanan with eight men, and went to the Ammonites.
verse_text: Then they tooke all the men, and went to fight with Ishmael the sonne of Nethaniah, and found him by the great waters that are in Gibeon.

text: and vpon the wrath of mine enimies thou hast extended thy hand, and thy right hand hath saued me.
verse_text: Though I walke in the mids of trouble, thou wilt reuiue me, thou shalt stretch foorth thine hand against the wrath of mine enemies:

text: Amicus si permanserit fixus, erit tibi quasi coaequalis, et in domesticis tuis fiducialiter aget.
verse_text: Omnis amicus dicet: Et ego amicitiam copulavi: sed est amicus solo nomine amicus. Nonne tristitia inest usque ad mortem?

text: He that getteth a wife, beginneth a possession, a helpe like vnto himselfe, and a pillar of rest.
verse_text: Species mulieris exhilarat faciem viri sui, et super omnem concupiscentiam hominis superducit desiderium.

text: My sonne, blemish not thy good deeds, neither vse vncomfortable words when thou giuest any thing.
verse_text: Fili, in bonis non des querelam, et in omni dato non des tristitiam verbi mali.

text: Admonish thy friend, it may be he hath not said it, and if he haue, that he speake it not againe.
verse_text: Corripe proximum, ne forte non dixerit: et si dixerit, ne forte iteret.

text: If children liue honestly, and haue wherwithall, they shall couer the basenesse of their parents.
verse_text: Cum dormiente loquitur qui enarrat stulto sapientiam: et in fine narrationis dicit: Quis est hic?

text: Benedicite, aquae omnes, quae super caelos sunt, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, cete, et omnia quae moventur in aquis, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Shee that is bold, dishonoureth both her father and her husband, but they both shall despise her.
verse_text: Patrem et virum confundit audax, et ab impiis non minorabitur: ab utrisque autem inhonorabitur.

text: And therefore praise ye the Lord with the whole heart and mouth, and blesse the Name of the Lord.
verse_text: Ignis, grando, fames, et mors, omnia haec ad vindictam creata sunt:

text: Hearken vnto me, ye holy children, and budde foorth as a rose growing by the brooke of the field:
verse_text: Non recedet memoria ejus, et nomen ejus requiretur a generatione in generationem.

text: Intellectus Asaph. Attendite, popule meus, legem meam; inclinate aurem vestram in verba oris mei.
verse_text: Oratio David. Exaudi, Domine, justitiam meam; intende deprecationem meam. Auribus percipe orationem meam, non in labiis dolosis.

text: There is one that laboureth and taketh paines, and maketh haste, and is so much the more behinde.
verse_text: Est homo laborans et festinans, et dolens: impius, et tanto magis non abundabit.

text: For princes sate, and they spake against me: but thy seruant was exercised in thy iustifications.
verse_text: Though my spirit was in perplexitie in me, yet thou knewest my path: in the way wherein I walked, haue they priuily layde a snare for me.

text: Dominus retribuet pro me. Domine, misericordia tua in saeculum; opera manuum tuarum ne despicias.
verse_text: ego autem in misericordia tua speravi. Exsultabit cor meum in salutari tuo. Cantabo Domino qui bona tribuit mihi; et psallam nomini Domini altissimi.

text: With the bread of vnderstanding shall she feed him, and giue him the water of wisedome to drinke.
verse_text: Cibabit illum pane vitae et intellectus, et aqua sapientiae salutaris potabit illum: et firmabitur in illo, et non flectetur:

text: Confessio et pulchritudo in conspectu ejus; sanctimonia et magnificentia in sanctificatione ejus.
verse_text: Confessio et magnificentia opus ejus, et justitia ejus manet in saeculum saeculi.

text: Tunc Nabuchodonosor, in furore et in ira, praecepit ut adducerentur Sidrach, Misach, et Abdenago:
verse_text: Daniel autem postulavit a rege, et constituit super opera provinciae Babylonis Sidrach, Misach, et Abdenago:

text: Lava a malitia cor tuum, Jerusalem, ut salva fias: usquequo morabuntur in te cogitationes noxiae?
verse_text: Haec sors tua, parsque mensurae tuae a me, dicit Dominus, quia oblita es mei, et confisa es in mendacio.

text: Yea they that feede of the portion of his meate, shall destroy him, and his armie shall ouerflow:
verse_text: And they that eate bread with him, shal destroy him, and his armie shal be oppressed:

text: If thou be inuited of a mighty man, withdraw thy selfe, and so much the more will he inuite thee.
verse_text: Humiliare Deo, et exspecta manus ejus.

text: Propter nomen tuum, Domine, vivificabis me: in aequitate tua, educes de tribulatione animam meam,
verse_text: In te, Domine, speravi; non confundar in aeternum: in justitia tua libera me.

text: Educ de custodia animam meam ad confitendum nomini tuo; me exspectant justi donec retribuas mihi.
verse_text: Suscipe me secundum eloquium tuum, et vivam, et non confundas me ab exspectatione mea.

text: He shall stretch foorth his hand also vpon the countreys, and the land of Egypt shall not escape.
verse_text: He shall enter also into the pleasant land, and many countreis shalbe ouerthrowen: but these shall escape out of his hand, euen Edom and Moab, and the chiefe of the children of Ammon.

text: Error et tenebrae peccatoribus concreata sunt: qui autem exsultant in malis consenescunt in malo.
verse_text: nam duplicia mala invenies in omnibus bonis quaecumque feceris illi, quoniam et Altissimus odio habet peccatores, et impiis reddet vindictam.

text: Sic faciam loco huic, ait Dominus, et habitatoribus ejus, et ponam civitatem istam sicut Topheth.
verse_text: Ecce ego praecipio, dicit Dominus, et reducam eos in civitatem hanc, et praeliabuntur adversus eam, et capient eam, et incendent igni: et civitates Juda dabo in solitudinem, eo quod non sit habitator.

text: Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleepe: and like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.
verse_text: And our Lord was raised vp as one that sleepeth: as a mightie man hauing surfited of wine.

text: muta fiant labia dolosa, quae loquuntur adversus justum iniquitatem, in superbia, et in abusione.
verse_text: Vana locuti sunt unusquisque ad proximum suum; labia dolosa, in corde et corde locuti sunt.

text: For mine iniquities are gone ouer mine head, and as a weightie burden they are too heauie for me.
verse_text: For innumerable euils haue compassed me about, mine iniquities haue taken hold vpon me, so that I am not able to looke vp: they are moe then the haires of mine head, therefore my heart faileth me.

text: and according to his will he worketh in the armie of heauen, and in the inhabitants of the earth:
verse_text: for he doth according to his wil, as wel in the powres of heauen, as in the inhabitants of the earth:

text: Pluviam voluntariam segregabis, Deus, haereditati tuae; et infirmata est, tu vero perfecisti eam.
verse_text: Dilexisti justitiam, et odisti iniquitatem; propterea unxit te Deus, Deus tuus, oleo laetitiae, prae consortibus tuis.

text: Sion heard, and was glad, and the daughters of Iudah reioyced: because of thy iudgements, O Lord.
verse_text: Let mount Zion reioyce, and the daughters of Iudah be glad, because of thy iudgements.

text: Returne vnto the Lord, and forsake thy sinnes, make thy prayer before his face, and offend lesse.
verse_text: In partes vade saeculi sancti, cum vivis et dantibus confessionem Deo.

text: The Lord is with mee among them that helpe me: therefore shall I see my desire vpon mine enemies.
verse_text: Behold, God is mine helper: the Lord is with them that vphold my soule.

text: My sonne, glorifie thy soule in meekenesse, and giue it honour according to the dignitie thereof.
verse_text: Servo sensato liberi servient: et vir prudens et disciplinatus non murmurabit correptus, et inscius non honorabitur.

text: There is no head aboue the head of a serpent, and there is no wrath aboue the wrath of an enemie.
verse_text: Beatus homo cui donatum est habere timorem Dei: qui tenet illum, cui assimilabitur?

text: Admonish thy friend, it may be he hath not said it, and if he haue, that he speake it not againe.
verse_text: Admonish a friend: for many times it is a slander, & beleeue not euery tale.

text: Praise ye the Lord. Praise ye God in his Sanctuarie: prayse ye him in the firmament of his power.
verse_text: Prayse ye him in his mightie Actes: prayse ye him according to his excellent greatnesse.

text: My teares haue bene my meate day and night; while they continually say vnto me, Where is thy God?
verse_text: Whiles my bones are broken, mine enemies that truble me haue vpbrayded me: Whiles they say to me day by day: Where is thy God?

text: Adde not more trouble to an heart that is vexed, and deferre not to giue to him that is in neede.
verse_text: Cor inopis ne afflixeris, et non protrahas datum angustianti.

text: Et reliquiae non erunt ex eis: inducam enim malum super viros Anathoth, annum visitationis eorum.
verse_text: Et visitabo super Bel in Babylone, et ejiciam quod absorbuerat de ore ejus: et non confluent ad eum ultra gentes, siquidem et murus Babylonis corruet.

text: Change not a friend for any good by no meanes: neither a faithfull brother for the gold of Ophir.
verse_text: Memento irae, quoniam non tardabit.

text: He brought them out of darkenes, and out of the shadowe of death, and brake their bandes asunder.
verse_text: Hee brought mee also out of the horrible pit, out of the myrie clay, and set my feete vpon the rocke, and ordered my goings.

text: Hide me from the secret counsel of the wicked: from the insurrection of the workers of iniquitie:
verse_text: Keepe me from the snare, which they haue set for me: and from the scandals of them that worke iniquitie.

text: Blessed is the nation, whose God is our Lord: the people whom he hath chosen for his inheritance.
verse_text: Because our Lord hath chosen Sion: he hath chosen it for an habitation to himself.

text: I haue cried to thee o Lord, I haue sayd: Thou art my hope, my portion in the land of the liuing.
verse_text: TO THEE o Lord I haue lifted vp my soule: my God in thee is my confidence, let me not be ashamed:

text: There can no good come to him that is alwayes occupied in euill: nor to him that giueth no almes.
verse_text: Non est enim ei bene qui assiduus est in malis, et eleemosynas non danti: quoniam et Altissimus odio habet peccatores, et misertus est poenitentibus.

text: Cor sapientis intelligitur in sapientia, et auris bona audiet cum omni concupiscentia sapientiam.
verse_text: Omnis astutus agnoscit sapientiam, et invenienti eam dabit confessionem.

text: Though the Lord be high, yet hath he respect vnto the lowly: but the proud he knoweth afarre off.
verse_text: Because thou wilt saue the humble people: and the eies of the proud thou wilt humble.

text: For thus saith the Lord, Behold, hee shall fly as an eagle, and shall spread his wings ouer Maob.
verse_text: Behold, he shall come vp, and flie as the Egle, and spreade his wings ouer Bozrah, and at that day shall the heart of the strong men of Edome be as the heart of a woman in trauaile.

text: Be not curious in vnnecessarie matters: for moe things are shewed vnto thee, then men vnderstand.
verse_text: Non est enim tibi necessarium ea, quae abscondita sunt, videre oculis tuis.

text: A drunken woman and a gadder abroad, causeth great anger, and shee will not couer her owne shame.
verse_text: dolor cordis et luctus, mulier zelotypa.

text: Answere not, before thou hast heard the cause: neither interrupt men in the midst of their talke.
verse_text: Priusquam audias, ne respondeas verbum: et in medio sermonum ne adjicias loqui.

text: In supervacuis rebus noli scrutari multipliciter, et in pluribus operibus ejus non eris curiosus.
verse_text: Noli avidus esse in omni epulatione, et non te effundas super omnem escam:

text: Alleluja. Laudate Dominum, quoniam bonus est psalmus; Deo nostro sit jucunda, decoraque laudatio.
verse_text: Alleluja. Confitemini Domino, quoniam bonus, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: TO THEE o Lord I haue lifted vp my soule: my God in thee is my confidence, let me not be ashamed:
verse_text: IN THEE o Lord haue I hoped, let me not be confounded for euer: in thy iustice deliuer me.

text: And he built his sanctuarie like high palaces: like the earth which he hath established for euer.
verse_text: Who established the earth ouer the waters: because his mercie is for euer.

text: Wisedome lifteth vp the head of him that is of low degree, and maketh him to sit among great men.
verse_text: Sapientia humiliati exaltabit caput illius, et in medio magnatorum consedere illum faciet.

text: Prepare what to say, and so thou shalt be heard, and binde vp instruction, and then make answere.
verse_text: Qui interrogationem manifestat parabit verbum, et sic deprecatus exaudietur: et conservabit disciplinam, et tunc respondebit.

text: Vidit ergo rex quod irruerent in eum vehementer: et necessitate compulsus, tradidit eis Danielem.
verse_text: Tunc rex praecepit, et adduxerunt Danielem, et miserunt eum in lacum leonum. Dixitque rex Danieli: Deus tuus, quem colis semper, ipse liberabit te.

text: Euery friend saieth, I am his friend also: but there is a friend which is onely a friend in name.
verse_text: Omnis amicus dicet: Et ego amicitiam copulavi: sed est amicus solo nomine amicus. Nonne tristitia inest usque ad mortem?

text: If thou be among the vndiscreet, obserue the time: but be continually among men of vnderstanding.
verse_text: Homo sanctus in sapientia manet sicut sol: nam stultus sicut luna mutatur.

text: Wilt not thou, O God, who hast cast vs off? and wilt not thou, O God, goe foorth with our hostes?
verse_text: Wilt not thou o God, which hast repelled vs, and wilt not thou goeforth o God in our hoastes?

text: I knowe, O Lord, that thy iudgements are right: and that thou in faithfulnesse hast afflicted me.
verse_text: For thou, O God, hast heard my desires: thou hast giuen an heritage vnto those that feare thy Name.

text: Is this house then, in which my name hath been called upon, in your eyes become a den of robbers?
verse_text: And you have come, and stood before me in this house, in which my name is called upon, and have said:

text: Heare my voice according vnto thy louing kindnesse: O Lord quicken me according to thy iudgement.
verse_text: Plead my cause, and deliuer me: quicken me according to thy word.

text: for it shall be no more inhabited, neither shall it be inhabited from generation vnto generation.
verse_text: and ostriches shall dwell therein, and it shall be no more inhabited for ever, neither shall it be built up from generation to generation.

text: He that is evil to himself, to whom will he be good? and he shall not take pleasure in his goods.
verse_text: Who will justify him that sinneth against his own soul? and who will honour him that dishonoureth his own soul?

text: For he shal stand at the right hand of the poore: to saue him from those that condemne his soule.
verse_text: For he shall deliuer the poore when he cryeth: the needie also, and him that hath no helper.

text: And I have sent to you all my servants the prophets from day to day, rising up early and sending.
verse_text: To give ear to the words of my servants the prophets, whom I sent to you rising up early:

text: Why doth one day excell another? when as all the light of euery day in the yeere is of the Sunne.
verse_text: Quare dies diem superat, et iterum lux lucem, et annus annum a sole?

text: An obstinate heart shall be laden with sorrowes, and the wicked man shall heape sinne vpon sinne.
verse_text: Cor durum habebit male in novissimo, et qui amat periculum in illo peribit.

text: Be willing to heare euery godly discourse, and let not the parables of vnderstanding escape thee.
verse_text: In multitudine presbyterorum prudentium sta, et sapientiae illorum ex corde conjungere, ut omnem narrationem Dei possis audire, et proverbia laudis non effugiant a te.

text: Plead my cause (O Lord) with them that striue with mee: fight against them that fight against me.
verse_text: Deliuer me from mine enemies, O my God: defend mee from them that rise vp against me.

text: She wil lye vpon him as a mightie stone of triall, and hee will cast her from him ere it be long.
verse_text: Quam aspera est nimium sapientia indoctis hominibus ! et non permanebit in illa excors.

text: For all things are not profitable for all men, neither hath euery soule pleasure in euery thing.
verse_text: Vita viri in numero dierum: dies autem Israel innumerabiles sunt.

text: Many have fallen by the edge of the sword, but not so many as have perished by their own tongue.
verse_text: For they that eat his bread, are of a false tongue. How often, and how many will laugh him to scorn!

text: The Lord ouerthrew countreys of the heathen: and destroyed them to the foundations of the earth.
verse_text: Propterea exhonoravit Dominus conventus malorum, et destruxit eos usque in finem.

text: And now I have given all these lands into the hand of Nabuchodonosor king of Babylon my servant:
verse_text: Behold I will send, and take all the kindreds of the north, saith the Lord, and Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon my servant:

text: To execute vpon them the iudgement written: This honour haue all his Saints. Praise ye the Lord.
verse_text: O loue the Lord, all yee his Saints: for the Lord preserueth the faithfull, and plentifully rewardeth the proud doer.

text: Therefore Daniel went vnto Arioch, whome the King had ordeyned to destroy the wise men of Babel:
verse_text: After these thinges Daniel being entered in to Arioch, whom the king had appoynted to destroy the wisemen of Babylon, spake thus vnto him:

text: In the beginning o Lord thou didst found the earth: and the heauens are the workes of thy hands.
verse_text: Thou hast aforetime layde the foundation of the earth, and the heauens are the worke of thine hands.

text: Medicina omnium in festinatione nebulae: et ros obvians ab ardore venienti humilem efficiet eum.
verse_text: Benedictio Dei in mercedem justi festinat, et in hora veloci processus illius fructificat.

text: Beare not hatred to thy neighbour for euery wrong, and do nothing at all by iniurious practises.
verse_text: Omnis injuriae proximi ne memineris, et nihil agas in operibus injuriae.

text: Number not thy selfe among the multitude of sinners, but remember that wrath will not tary long.
verse_text: Non oderis laboriosa opera, et rusticationem creatam ab Altissimo.

text: Be ashamed of whoredome before father and mother, and of a lie before a prince and a mighty man:
verse_text: Disciplinam in pace conservate, filii: sapientia enim abscondita, et thesaurus invisus, quae utilitas in utrisque?

text: My mouth shall daily rehearse thy righteousnesse, and thy saluation: for I knowe not the nomber.
verse_text: My tongue also shall talke of thy righteousnesse daily: for they are confounded and brought vnto shame, that seeke mine hurt.

text: And iudgement is come vpon the plaine countrey, vpon Holon, and vpon Iahazah, and vpon Mephaath,
verse_text: And vpon Kerioth, and vpon Bozrah, and vpon all the cities of ye land of Moab farre or neere.

text: Necessary patience in seeking the Lord, is better then he that leadeth his life without a guide.
verse_text: Sapientia absconsa, et thesaurus invisus, quae utilitas in utrisque?

text: To terrifie and doe wrong, will waste riches: thus the house of proude men shalbe made desolate.
verse_text: Quasi rhomphaea bis acuta omnis iniquitas: plagae illius non est sanitas.

text: My goodnes and my fortresse, my high tower and my deliuerer, my shield, and he in whome I trust:
verse_text: The Lord is my rocke, and my fortresse, and he that deliuereth me, my God and my strength:

text: There is an abasement because of glory; and there is that lifteth vp his head from a low estate.
verse_text: Est propter gloriam minoratio, et est qui ab humilitate levabit caput.

text: Sweet language will multiply friends: and a faire speaking tongue will increase kinde greetings.
verse_text: Verbum dulce multiplicat amicos et mitigat inimicos, et lingua eucharis in bono homine abundat.

text: I cried vnto thee, O Lord, I said, Thou art my refuge, and my portion in the land of the liuing.
verse_text: Vnto thee, O my Strength, wil I sing: for God is my defence, and my mercifull God.

text: Thus saith the Lord, Hearken not to the words of your prophets, that prophecie vnto you, saying;
verse_text: Therefore heare not the words of the prophets, that speake vnto you, saying, Ye shall not serue the King of Babel:

text: Behold the eies of our Lord be vpon them that feare him: and on them, that hope vpon his mercie.
verse_text: Al the wayes of our Lord, be mercie and truth, to them that seeke after his testament and his testimonies.

text: Praysed be the Lord, euen the God of our saluation, which ladeth vs dayly with benefites. Selah.
verse_text: Blessed be our Lord day by day: the God of our saluations wil make vs a prosperous iourney.

text: As the palate tasteth diuers kinds of venison: so doth an heart of vnderstanding false speeches.
verse_text: secundum benedictionem Aaron de populo tuo: et dirige nos in viam justitiae, et sciant omnes qui habitant terram quia tu es Deus conspector saeculorum.

text: There is that waxeth rich by his warinesse, and pinching, and this is the portion of his reward:
verse_text: Est qui locupletatur parce agendo, et haec est pars mercedis illius.

text: Teeth of wild beasts, and scorpions, serpents, & the sword, punishing the wicked to destruction.
verse_text: Bona bonis creata sunt ab initio: sic nequissimis bona et mala.

text: In diebus illis, et in tempore illo, ait Dominus, venient filii Israel ipsi et filii Juda simul:
verse_text: Ecce enim dies veniunt, dicit Dominus, et convertam conversionem populi mei Israel et Juda, ait Dominus:

text: and I will kindle a fire in the forrest thereof, and it shall deuoure all things round about it.
verse_text: and I will kindle a fire in his cities, and it shall devour all round about him.

text: He that holdeth her fast shall inherit glory, and wheresoeuer she entreth, the Lord will blesse.
verse_text: Et qui illam diligit, diligit vitam, et qui vigilaverint ad illam complectentur placorem ejus.

text: Iste pauper clamavit, et Dominus exaudivit eum, et de omnibus tribulationibus ejus salvavit eum.
verse_text: Exquisivi Dominum, et exaudivit me; et ex omnibus tribulationibus meis eripuit me.

text: The earth is mooued at the noyse of their fall: the crie of their voice is heard in the red Sea.
verse_text: At the noise of the taking of Babylon the earth is moued, and the cry is heard among the nations.

text: Now consider this, ye that forget God, lest I teare you in pieces, and there be none to deliuer.
verse_text: Least hee teare my soule like a lyon, renting it in pieces, while there is none to deliuer.

text: A slouthful man is compared to a filthy stone, and euery one will hisse him out to his disgrace.
verse_text: Who so casteth a stone at the birds, frayeth them away, and he that vpbraideth his friend, breaketh friendship.

text: As the Uine brought I foorth pleasant sauour, and my flowers are the fruit of honour and riches.
verse_text: I was exalted like a palme tree in Engaddi, and as a rose-plant in Iericho, as a faire oliue tree in a pleasant fielde, and grew vp as a planetree by the water.

text: Hee that is euill to himselfe, to whom will he be good? he shall not take pleasure in his goods.
verse_text: Who wil iustifie him that sinneth against his owne soule? and who will honour him that dishonoureth his owne life?

text: It shall go well with him that feareth the Lord, and in the days of his end he shall be blessed.
verse_text: He that feareth the Lord, will receive his discipline: and they that will seek him early, shall find a blessing.

text: And why haue they determined not to come and meet me, more then all the inhabitants of the West?
verse_text: et quare prae omnibus qui habitant in oriente, isti contempserunt nos, et non exierunt obviam nobis ut susciperent nos cum pace?

text: The congregation of sinners is like tow heaped together, and the end of them is a flame of fire.
verse_text: The heart of the foolish is like a cartwheele: and his thoughts are like a rolling axeltree.

text: Hast thou a wife after thy minde? forsake her not, but giue not thy selfe ouer to a light woman.
verse_text: Filiae tibi sunt? serva corpus illarum, et non ostendas hilarem faciem tuam ad illas.

text: As a father hath compassion on his children, so hath the Lord compassion on them that feare him.
verse_text: For as the heauen is high aboue the earth: so great is his mercy toward them that feare him.

text: Thou makest vs to turne backe from the aduersary, and they, which hate vs, spoile for theselues.
verse_text: Thou makest vs a strife vnto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselues.

text: Thou wilt bring me out of this snare, which they haue hid for me: because thou art my protector.
verse_text: Thou art my refuge from tribulation, which hath compassed me: my exultation, deliuer me from them that compasse me.

text: As the Uine brought I foorth pleasant sauour, and my flowers are the fruit of honour and riches.
verse_text: Quasi cedrus exaltata sum in Libano, et quasi cypressus in monte Sion:

text: A slouthful man is compared to a filthy stone, and euery one will hisse him out to his disgrace.
verse_text: In lapide luteo lapidatus est piger: et omnes loquentur super aspernationem illius.

text: Perde pecuniam propter fratrem et amicum tuum, et non abscondas illam sub lapide in perditionem.
verse_text: Et sicut qui dimittit avem de manu sua, sic dereliquisti proximum tuum, et non eum capies.

text: It is a good thing to giue thanks vnto the Lord, and to sing praises vnto thy Name, O most High:
verse_text: Praise the Lord, for the Lord is good: sing praises vnto his Name, for it is pleasant.

text: Thou hast exalted the righthand of them that oppresse him: thou hast made al his enimies ioyful.
verse_text: And thou hast girded me with strength to battel: and hast supplanted them that rise against me vnder me.

text: But mine enemies liue, and are confirmed ouer me: and they are multiplied that hate me vniustly.

text: He that feareth the Lord shall tremble at nothing, and shall not be afraid for he is his hope.

text: He shone in his days as the morning star in the midst of a cloud, and as the moon at the full.

text: O Lord, I haue loued the habitation of thine house, and the place where thine honour dwelleth.

text: The sacrifice of a iust man is acceptable, and the memoriall thereof shall neuer be forgotten.

text: A resistentibus dexterae tuae custodi me ut pupillam oculi. Sub umbra alarum tuarum protege me
verse_text: in manibus tuis sortes meae: eripe me de manu inimicorum meorum, et a persequentibus me.

text: Probasti cor meum, et visitasti nocte; igne me examinasti, et non est inventa in me iniquitas.

text: For thou hast deliuered my soule from death, mine eyes from teares, and my feete from falling.

text: Qui adorat Deum in oblectatione suscipietur, et deprecatio illius usque ad nubes propinquabit.

text: All they that hate me, whisper together against me: euen against me do they imagine mine hurt.

text: I wil praise thee, O Lord, with my whole heart: I will shewe foorth all thy maruellous workes.

text: For thou hast saued vs from them that afflict vs: and them that hate vs thou hast confounded.

text: Alleluia. SING ye to our Lord a new song: let his prayse be in the Church of sainctes.

text: Therefore hear ye the word of the Lord, all Juda, you that dwell in the land of Egypt:
verse_text: For this now hear the word of the Lord, ye remnant of Juda:

text: He hath set fire and water before thee: stretch forth thy hand vnto whether thou wilt.
verse_text: Si volueris mandata servare, conservabunt te, et in perpetuum fidem placitam facere.

text: Iustifie not thy selfe before the Lord, and boast not of thy wisedome before the king.
verse_text: Boast not of thy cloathing and raiment, and exalt not thy selfe in the day of honour: for the workes of the Lord are wonderfull, and his workes among men are hidden.

text: Shalt thou not leaue thy trauailes vnto another? and thy labours to be diuided by lot?
verse_text: Nonne aliis relinques dolores et labores tuos in divisione sortis?

text: If thou hast vnderstanding, answer thy neighbour, if not, lay thy hand vpon thy mouth.
verse_text: Esto firmus in via Domini, et in veritate sensus tui et scientia: et prosequatur te verbum pacis et justitiae.

text: Suspensus est itaque Aman in patibulo quod paraverat Mardochaeo: et regis ira quievit.
verse_text: Statimque rex: Quis est, inquit, in atrio? Aman quippe interius atrium domus regiae intraverat, ut suggereret regi, et juberet Mardochaeum affigi patibulo, quod ei fuerat praeparatum.

text: At his sight shall the mountains be shaken, and at his will the south wind shall blow.
verse_text: At his word the wind is still, and with his thought he appeaseth the deep, and the Lord hath planted islands therein.

text: quia misericordia tua magna est super me, et eruisti animam meam ex inferno inferiori.
verse_text: Intende ad deprecationem meam, quia humiliatus sum nimis. Libera me a persequentibus me, quia confortati sunt super me.

text: Thou wilt feede vs with the bread of teares: and giue vs drinke with teares in mesure.
verse_text: Thou hast shewed vnto thy people hard thinges: thou hast made vs drinke the wine of compunction.

text: Then they crie vnto the Lord in their trouble: he saueth them out of their distresses.
verse_text: Then they cryed vnto the Lord in their trouble: and he deliuered them out of their distresses.

text: A foolish mans foote is soone in his house: but a man of experience is ashamed of him.
verse_text: Compedes in pedibus, stulto doctrina: et quasi vincula manuum super manum dextram.

text: A foole lifteth vp his voyce with laughter, but a wise man doeth scarce smile a litle.
verse_text: Os prudentis quaeritur in ecclesia, et verba illius cogitabunt in cordibus suis.

text: Doctrine vnto fooles, is as fetters on the feete, and like manacles on the right hand.
verse_text: Narratio fatui quasi sarcina in via: nam in labiis sensati invenietur gratia.

text: They that eate mee shall yet be hungry, and they that drinke me shall yet be thirstie.
verse_text: et quasi storax, et galbanus, et ungula, et gutta, et quasi Libanus non incisus vaporavi habitationem meam, et quasi balsamum non mistum odor meus.

text: Testamentum aeternum constituit cum illis, et justitiam et judicia sua ostendit illis.
verse_text: Creavit illis scientiam spiritus, sensu implevit cor illorum, et mala et bona ostendit illis.

text: Then shall ye virgine reioyce in the dance, and the yong men and the old men together:
verse_text: thou shalt stil be adorned with thy timbrels, and shalt goe foorth in the dance of them that be ioyfull.

text: Et misi ad vos omnes servos meos prophetas, de nocte consurgens, mittensque et dicens:
verse_text: eo quod non audierint verba mea, dicit Dominus, quae misit ad eos per servos meos prophetas, de nocte consurgens et mittens:

text: Gather all the tribes of Iacob together, and inherit thou them, as from the beginning.
verse_text: In ira flammae devoretur qui salvatur: et qui pessimant plebem tuam inveniant perditionem.

text: I am feeble and sore broken; I haue roared by reason of the disquietnesse of my heart.
verse_text: I am troubled, I am bowed downe greatly; I goe mourning all the day long.

text: And put the feare of man vpon all flesh, and gaue him dominion ouer beasts and foules.
verse_text: Posuit timorem illius super omnem carnem, et dominatus est bestiarum et volatilium.

text: Turne vs againe, O Lord God of hosts, cause thy face to shine, and wee shall be saued.
verse_text: Turne vs againe, O God of hostes: cause thy face to shine, and we shalbe saued.

text: But I, as a deafe man, heard not; and I was as a dumbe man that openeth not his mouth.
verse_text: And I became as a man not hearing: and not hauing reproofes in his mouth.

text: Vau Et veniat super me misericordia tua, Domine; salutare tuum secundum eloquium tuum.
verse_text: Illustra faciem tuam super servum tuum; salvum me fac in misericordia tua.

text: Stirre vp thy selfe and awake to my iudgement, euen vnto my cause, my God and my Lord.
verse_text: Iudge me, O Lord my God, according to thy righteousnesse, and let them not reioyce ouer mee.

text: Who shall number the strength of his maiestie? and who shall also tel out his mercies?
verse_text: Non est minuere neque adjicere, nec est invenire magnalia Dei.

text: To whom hath the root of wisdome beene reuealed? or who hath knowen her wise counsels?
verse_text: To whom hath the discipline of wisdom been revealed and made manifest? and who hath understood the multiplicity of her steps?

text: Many are my persecutors, and mine enemies: yet doe I not decline from thy testimonies.
verse_text: The wicked haue layed a snare for mee: but I swarued not from thy precepts.

text: Mores hominum mendacium sine honore, et confusio illorum cum ipsis sine intermissione.
verse_text: homo qui jucundatur in filiis, vivens et videns subversionem inimicorum suorum.

text: Immitis animus illius conservabit verba tua: et non parcet de malitia, et de vinculis.
verse_text: Et Dominus non elongabit: et judicabit justos, et faciet judicium: et Fortissimus non habebit in illis patientiam, ut contribulet dorsum ipsorum:

text: Statuit ea in aeternum, et in saeculum saeculi; praeceptum posuit, et non praeteribit.
verse_text: Increpasti gentes, et periit impius: nomen eorum delesti in aeternum, et in saeculum saeculi.

text: Saying: God hath forsaken him, pursew, and take him: because there is none to deliuer.
verse_text: Least he deuoure my soule like a lion, and teare it in pieces, while there is none to helpe.

text: No heart can thinke vpon these things worthily: and who is able to conceiue his wayes?
verse_text: Et in omnibus his insensatum est cor, et omne cor intelligitur ab illo.

text: Who can number the sand of the sea, and the drops of raine, and the dayes of eternity?
verse_text: Arenam maris, et pluviae guttas, et dies saeculi, quis dinumeravit? altitudinem caeli, et latitudinem terrae, et profundum abyssi, quis dimensus est?

text: Noli verbosus esse in multitudine presbyterorum, et non iteres verbum in oratione tua.
verse_text: Ubi auditus non est, non effundas sermonem, et importune noli extolli in sapientia tua.

text: And hee led them forth by the right way: that they might goe to a citie of habitation.
verse_text: But hee made his people to goe out like sheepe, and led them in the wildernes like a flocke.

text: Spirits and soules of the iust blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Seruants of our Lord blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: And the Lord thundered from heauen, and with a great noise made his voice to be heard.
verse_text: In lege Domini congregationem judicavit, et vidit Deus Jacob: et in fide sua probatus est propheta,

text: Fear, and the pit, and the snare come upon thee, O inhabitant of Moab, saith the Lord.

text: The people asked, and he brought quailes: and satisfied them with the bread of heauen.
verse_text: And he rayned them Manna to eate, and bread of heauen he gaue to them.

text: And I sent to you all my servants the prophets, rising early, and sending, and saying:
verse_text: To give ear to the words of my servants the prophets, whom I sent to you rising up early:

text: And consider if there be any way of wickednes in me, and leade me in the way for euer.
verse_text: Let al be confounded that do vniust thinges in vayne. Lord shew me thy wayes: and teach me thy pathes.

text: veniat rex et Aman ad convivium quod paravi eis, et cras aperiam regi voluntatem meam.
verse_text: si inveni in conspectu regis gratiam, et si regi placet ut det mihi quod postulo, et meam impleat petitionem:

text: Set him to worke, as is fit for him; if he be not obedient, put on more heauy fetters.
verse_text: Servo malevolo tortura et compedes: mitte illum in operationem, ne vacet:

text: As the wilde asse is the lyons pray in the wildernesse: so the rich eate vp the poore.
verse_text: Omne animal diligit simile sibi, sic et omnis homo proximum sibi.

text: Let mount Zion reioyce, and the daughters of Iudah be glad, because of thy iudgements.
verse_text: Zion heard of it, and was glad: and the daughters of Iudah reioyced, because of thy iudgements, O Lord.

text: Consider that I laboured not for my selfe onely, but for all them that seeke learning;

text: Speake yong man, if there be need of thee: and yet scarsely when thou art twise asked:

text: By his great power hee maketh the cloudes firme, and the hailestones are broken small.

text: The poore laboureth in his poore estate, and when he leaueth off, hee is still needie.

text: For thou hast said, The Lord is mine hope: thou hast set the most High for thy refuge.

text: Because he shal deliuer the poore from the mightie: and the poore which had no helper.

text: I will bee glad and reioyce in thee: I will sing prayse to thy name, O thou most High.

text: they shall die, from the least euen vnto the greatest, by the sword and by the famine:

text: Which redeemeth thy life from the graue, and crowneth thee with mercy and compassions.

text: Corrupti sunt, et abominabiles facti sunt in iniquitatibus; non est qui faciat bonum.

text: Let them be ashamed and confounded together, that seeke after my soule to destroy it:
verse_text: Let them be confounded and put to shame that seeke after my soule:

text: Benedicite, sancti et humiles corde, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, fontes, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: For all the beastes of the forest are mine, and the beastes on a thousand mountaines.
verse_text: I haue knowne al the foules of the ayer: and the beauty of the fielde is with me.

text: For God is the King of all the earth: sing prayses euery one that hath vnderstanding.

text: By this I know that thou fauourest me: because mine enemie doeth not triumph ouer me.
verse_text: I wil be glad and reioyce in thy mercie: for thou hast seene my trouble: thou hast knowen my soule in aduersities,

text: He sanctified him in his faithfulnesse, and meekenesse, and chose him out of all men.
verse_text: In fide et lenitate ipsius sanctum fecit illum, et elegit eum ex omni carne.

text: Psalmus ipsi David, quarta sabbati. Deus ultionum Dominus; Deus ultionum libere egit.
verse_text: Canticum ipsi David, quando domus aedificabatur post captivitatem. Cantate Domino canticum novum; cantate Domino omnis terra.

text: Make way for euery worke of mercy: for euery man shall finde according to his workes.

text: I will praise thee with my whole heart: before the gods will I sing praise vnto thee.
verse_text: I will giue thankes vnto the Lord greatly with my mouth and praise him among ye multitude.

text: By him the ende of them hath prosperous successe, and by his word all things consist.

text: Surely the righteous shall prayse thy Name, and the iust shall dwell in thy presence.
verse_text: The righteous shalbe glad in the Lord, and shall trust in him; and all the vpright in heart shall glory.

text: Neque iniquitas mea, neque peccatum meum, Domine; sine iniquitate cucurri, et direxi.
verse_text: Os meum annuntiabit justitiam tuam, tota die salutare tuum. Quoniam non cognovi litteraturam,

text: And if any euill happen vnto me by him, euery one that heareth it will beware of him.

text: As the vapour and smoke of a furnace goeth before the fire: so reuiling before blood.

text: They made petition, and the quaile came: and he filled them with the bread of heauen.
verse_text: And had rained downe MAN vpon them for to eate, and had giuen them of the wheate of heauen.

text: His seede also will I make to endure for euer, and his throne as the dayes of heauen.
verse_text: Thou shalt giue the King a long life: his yeeres shalbe as many ages.

text: Pulchritudinem candoris ejus admirabitur oculus, et super imbrem ejus expavescet cor.
verse_text: Species mulieris exhilarat faciem viri sui, et super omnem concupiscentiam hominis superducit desiderium.

text: Adjutor meus, tibi psallam, quia Deus susceptor meus es; Deus meus, misericordia mea.

text: quia cogitavit Dominus, et fecit quaecumque locutus est contra habitatores Babylonis.
verse_text: quoniam magnus furor et indignatio est quam locutus est Dominus adversus populum hunc.

text: As the Lord overthrew Sodom and Gomorrha, and their neighbour cities, saith the Lord:
verse_text: As God ouerthrew Sodom and Gomorrah, and the neighbour cities thereof, sayth the Lord:

text: For the Lord is great, and greatly to be praised: hee is to be feared aboue all Gods.
verse_text: Great is the Lord, and greatly to be praised: and his greatnes is vnsearchable.

text: In finem, pro his qui immutabuntur, in tituli inscriptionem ipsi David, in doctrinam,
verse_text: In finem, ne disperdas. David in tituli inscriptionem, quando misit Saul et custodivit domum ejus ut eum interficeret.

text: that hath not geuen his money to vsurie, and hath not taken giftes vpon the innocent:
verse_text: He that putteth not out his money to vsury, nor taketh reward against the innocent:

text: Shal not al they know that worke iniquitie, that deuoure my people as foode of bread?
verse_text: Doe not all the workers of iniquitie know that they eate vp my people, as they eate bread? they call not vpon the Lord.

text: Deficiant peccatores a terra, et iniqui, ita ut non sint. Benedic, anima mea, Domino.
verse_text: Corripiet me justus in misericordia, et increpabit me: oleum autem peccatoris non impinguet caput meum. Quoniam adhuc et oratio mea in beneplacitis eorum:

text: Wisedome that is hidde, and treasure that is hoarded vp, what profit is in them both?
verse_text: Qui operatur terram suam inaltabit acervum frugum, et qui operatur justitiam, ipse exaltabitur: qui vero placet magnatis effugiet iniquitatem.

text: Laboravit dives in congregatione substantiae, et in requie sua replebitur bonis suis.
verse_text: Est qui vetatur peccare prae inopia, et in requie sua stimulabitur.

text: Permanet in aeternum in conspectu Dei: misericordiam et veritatem ejus quis requiret?
verse_text: Quia misericordiam et veritatem diligit Deus: gratiam et gloriam dabit Dominus.

text: the north, and the sea thou hast created. Thabor and Hermon shal reioice in thy name:
verse_text: Thou hast visited the earth, and hast inebriated it: thou hast multiplied to inrich it. The riuer of God is replenished with waters, thou hast prepared their meat: because so is the preparation therof.

text: Blessed is the man, whom thou shalt instruct o Lord: and shalt teach out of thy lawe.
verse_text: Blessed is the people, that can reioyce in thee: they shall walke in the light of thy countenance, O Lord.

text: To him which led his people through the wildernesse: for his mercy endureth for euer.
verse_text: And brought out Israel from among them: for his mercy endureth for euer.

text: Lorde, heare my voice: let thine eares be attentiue to the voice of my supplications.
verse_text: I haue cried, because thou hast heard me o God: incline thyne eare to me, and heare my wordes.

text: et ipse diriget consilium ejus, et disciplinam, et in absconditis suis consiliabitur.
verse_text: In his curans mitigabit dolorem: et unguentarius faciet pigmenta suavitatis, et unctiones conficiet sanitatis: et non consummabuntur opera ejus.

text: Vnto thee, O my strength, wil I sing: for God is my defence, and the God of my mercy.
verse_text: Because of his strength will I wait vpon thee: for God is my defence.

text: Deliuer me from mine enemies, O my God: defend mee from them that rise vp against me.
verse_text: Keepe me, O Lord, from the hands of the wicked, preserue me from the violent man: who haue purposed to ouerthrow my goings.

text: Deus noster refugium et virtus; adjutor in tribulationibus quae invenerunt nos nimis.
verse_text: Ecce enim Deus adjuvat me, et Dominus susceptor est animae meae.

text: As his wayes are plaine vnto the holy, so are they stumbling blockes vnto the wicked.
verse_text: Opera omnis carnis coram illo, et non est quidquam absconditum ab oculis ejus.

text: Posuerunt offendicula sua in domo in qua invocatum est nomen meum, ut polluerent eam:

text: Audite verbum Domini, omnis Juda, qui ingredimini per portas has ut adoretis Dominum.

text: Golde and siluer make the foote stand sure: but counsell is esteemed aboue them both.

text: How was he honoured in the midst of the people, in his comming out of the Sanctuarie?

text: Desiderium pauperum exaudivit Dominus; praeparationem cordis eorum audivit auris tua:

text: Et factus est Dominus refugium pauperi; adjutor in opportunitatibus, in tribulatione.
verse_text: Quoniam Dominus in generatione justa est: consilium inopis confudistis, quoniam Dominus spes ejus est.

text: Non in sacrificiis tuis arguam te; holocausta autem tua in conspectu meo sunt semper.

text: Therefore I will prayse thee, O Lord, among the nations, and wil sing vnto thy Name.

text: Al that passe by the way haue spoiled him: he is become a reproch to his neighbours.

text: Quoniam non est in morte qui memor sit tui; in inferno autem quis confitebitur tibi?

text: He hath said in his heart, I shall not be moued: for I shall neuer be in aduersitie.

text: Sic psalmum dicam nomini tuo in saeculum saeculi, ut reddam vota mea de die in diem.

text: Thine eye desireth fauour and beautie: but more then both, corne while it is greene.

text: A friend and companion neuer meet amisse: but aboue both is a wife with her husband.

text: etenim illum Dominus creavit, et non discedat a te, quia opera ejus sunt necessaria.

text: The Bee is little among such as flie, but her fruite is the chiefe of sweete things.

verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord of hosts to the prophets:

text: His seed shall bee mightie vpon earth: the generation of the vpright shalbe blessed.

text: Surget vero rex fortis, et dominabitur potestate multa, et faciet quod placuerit ei.

text: O keepe my soule and deliuer me: let me not bee ashamed, for I put my trust in thee.
verse_text: O my God, I trust in thee, let me not be ashamed: let not mine enemies triumph ouer me.

text: Et qui inquirebant mala mihi, locuti sunt vanitates, et dolos tota die meditabantur.
verse_text: Locuti sunt adversum me lingua dolosa, et sermonibus odii circumdederunt me: et expugnaverunt me gratis.

text: Commend not a man for his beautie, neither abhorre a man for his outward appearance.
verse_text: Non laudes virum in specie sua, neque spernas hominem in visu suo.

text: Non timebo millia populi circumdantis me. Exsurge, Domine; salvum me fac, Deus meus.
verse_text: Complaceat tibi, Domine, ut eruas me; Domine, ad adjuvandum me respice.

text: And these are the words that the Lord spake concerning Israel, and concerning Iudah.
verse_text: For thus saith the Lord to the men of Iudah, and to Ierusalem,

text: If thou hast heard a word, let it die with thee, and be bold it will not burst thee.
verse_text: Audisti verbum adversus proximum tuum? commoriatur in te, fidens quoniam non te dirumpet.

text: From the beginning I knewe of thy testimonies: that thou hast founded them for euer.
verse_text: Aboue mine enemies thou hast made me wise by thy commaundment: because it is to me for euer.

text: I wil not forget thy iustifications for euer: because in them thou hast quickned me.
verse_text: I wil meditate in thy iustifications: I wil not forget thy wordes.

text: Turne vs againe, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine, and we shall be saued.
verse_text: Turne vs againe, O Lord God of hostes: cause thy face to shine and we shalbe saued.

text: ut notam faciant filiis hominum potentiam tuam, et gloriam magnificentiae regni tui.

text: He wil hide his words for a time, and the lippes of many shall declare his wisedome.

text: O how comely is wisdom for the aged, and understanding and counsel to men of honour!
verse_text: In the treasures of wisdom is understanding, and religiousness of knowledge: but to sinners wisdom is an abomination.

text: The king cried aloud to bring in the Astrologers, the Caldeans, and the soothsayers:
verse_text: Then the King commanded to call the Magicians, and the Astrologers, and the Sorcerers, and the Caldeans, for to shew the King his dreames:

text: Cleaue vnto him, and depart not away, that thou mayest be increased at thy last end.

verse_text: Ecce dies veniunt, dicit Dominus, et visitabo super omnem qui circumcisum habet praeputium,

text: A gift hath grace in the sight of euery man liuing, and for the dead deteine it not.

text: And their sinnes were multiplied exceedingly, that they were driuen out of the land.
verse_text: Deus autem non derelinquet misericordiam suam: et non corrumpet, nec delebit opera sua, neque perdet a stirpe nepotes electi sui, et semen ejus qui diligit Dominum non corrumpet.

text: All these things liue and remaine for euer, for all vses, and they are all obedient.
verse_text: Quam desiderabilia omnia opera ejus ! et tamquam scintilla quae est considerare !

text: Shal they not al know that worke iniquitie, that deuoure my people as food of bread?
verse_text: Doe not all the workers of iniquitie know that they eate vp my people, as they eate bread? they call not vpon the Lord.

text: Et dixi: Forsitan tenebrae conculcabunt me; et nox illuminatio mea in deliciis meis.
verse_text: Laboravi clamans, raucae factae sunt fauces meae; defecerunt oculi mei, dum spero in Deum meum.

text: And gaue them the lands of the heathen: and they inherited the labour of the people:
verse_text: He cast out the heathen also before them, and diuided them an inheritance by line: and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.

text: Benedictus es in throno regni tui: et superlaudabilis, et superexaltatus in saecula.
verse_text: Benedictus es, Domine Deus patrum nostrorum: et laudabilis, et gloriosus, et superexaltatus in saecula. Et benedictum nomen gloriae tuae sanctum: et laudabile, et superexaltatum in omnibus saeculis.

text: In oculis suis lacrimatur inimicus, et si invenerit tempus, non satiabitur sanguine.
verse_text: Insatiabilis oculus cupidi in parte iniquitatis: non satiabitur donec consumat arefaciens animam suam.

text: Ye that stande in the House of the Lord, and in the courtes of the House of our God,
verse_text: in the courtes of the house of our Lord, in the middes of thee o Ierusalem.

text: And I heard, & vnderstood not. And I sayd: My Lord, what shal be after these things?
verse_text: And the king sayd to them: I saw a dreame: & being confounded in minde I know not what I saw.

text: He hath sent downe from aboue and taken mee: hee hath drawen mee out of many waters.
verse_text: Hee brought mee foorth also into a large place: hee deliuered mee because hee fauoured me.

text: Vir repromittit de proximo suo: et cum perdiderit reverentiam, derelinquetur ab eo.
verse_text: Qui diligit filium suum assiduat illi flagella, ut laetetur in novissimo suo, et non palpet proximorum ostia.

text: Omnem escam abominata est anima eorum, et appropinquaverunt usque ad portas mortis.

text: super misericordia tua et veritate tua; nequando dicant gentes: Ubi est Deus eorum?
verse_text: Dicat nunc Israel: Quoniam bonus, quoniam in saeculum misericordia ejus.

text: And he appointed it to Iacob for a precept: and to Israel for an eternal testament.
verse_text: And since hath confirmed it to Iaakob for a lawe, and to Israel for an euerlasting couenant,

text: There be two maner of nations which my heart abhorreth, and the third is no nation.
verse_text: det nobis jucunditatem cordis, et fieri pacem in diebus nostris in Israel per dies sempiternos:

text: He was as the morning starre in the midst of a cloud: and as the moone at the full.
verse_text: Quasi stella matutina in medio nebulae, et quasi luna plena, in diebus suis lucet:

text: Deus meus, eripe me de manu peccatoris, et de manu contra legem agentis, et iniqui:

text: Et semen servorum ejus possidebit eam; et qui diligunt nomen ejus habitabunt in ea.
