text: Ex usuris et iniquitate redimet animas eorum, et honorabile nomen eorum coram illo.
verse_text: Ponite corda vestra in virtute ejus, et distribuite domos ejus, ut enarretis in progenie altera.

text: When I was yet yong, or euer I went abroad, I desired wisedome openly in my prayer.
verse_text: Exaltasti super terram habitationem meam, et pro morte defluente deprecatus sum.

text: Fili, in tua infirmitate ne despicias teipsum: sed ora Dominum, et ipse curabit te.
verse_text: Fili, in vita tua tenta animam tuam, et si fuerit nequam non des illi potestatem:

text: Disciplina medici exaltabit caput illius, et in conspectu magnatorum collaudabitur.
verse_text: et ipse diriget consilium ejus, et disciplinam, et in absconditis suis consiliabitur.

text: And brought forth Israel through the middes therof: because his mercie is for euer.
verse_text: And made Israel to passe through the midst of it: for his mercy endureth for euer.

text: And he turned their riuers into bloude, & their showers that they might not drinke.
verse_text: He turned their waters into bloud: and killed their fishes.

text: The day is thine, and the night is thine: thou hast made the morning and the sunne.
verse_text: The heauens are thine, and the earth is thine, the round earth, and the fulnes therof thou hast founded:

text: and afterward when he seeth thee, he will forsake thee, and shake his head at thee.
verse_text: and when he hath lost all shame, he shall forsake him.

text: Homini fornicario omnis panis dulcis: non fatigabitur transgrediens usque ad finem.
verse_text: Narratio fatui quasi sarcina in via: nam in labiis sensati invenietur gratia.

text: Hee shall direct his counsell and knowledge, and in his secrets shall hee meditate.
verse_text: Aperiet os suum in oratione, et pro delictis suis deprecabitur.

text: Si autem dereliquerint filii ejus legem meam, et in judiciis meis non ambulaverint;
verse_text: si justitias meas profanaverint, et mandata mea non custodierint:

text: Benedicite Domino, omnes virtutes ejus; ministri ejus, qui facitis voluntatem ejus.
verse_text: Benedicite, gentes, Deum nostrum, et auditam facite vocem laudis ejus:

text: Because thou hast possessed my reynes: thou hast receiued me from my mothers wombe.
verse_text: Vpon thee I haue bene cast from the matrice: from my mothers wombe thou art my God,

text: Hee smote also all the first borne in their land: the chiefe of all their strength.
verse_text: The wrath of God came vpon them, and slew the fattest of them: and smote downe the chosen men of Israel.

text: The heart of fooles is in their mouth, but the mouth of the wise is in their heart.
verse_text: Stultus a fenestra respiciet in domum: vir autem eruditus foris stabit.

text: They that feare the Lord shall find iudgement, and shall kindle iustice as a light.
verse_text: et age conceptiones tuas, et non in delictis et verbo superbo:

text: Operamini opus vestrum ante tempus, et dabit vobis mercedem vestram in tempore suo.
verse_text: Videte oculis vestris, quia modicum laboravi, et inveni mihi multam requiem.

text: Mountaines and litle hilles blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Blesse our Lord ye fountaines: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: A lie is a foule blot in a man, yet it is continually in the mouth of the vntaught.
verse_text: Est qui perdet animam suam prae confusione, et ab imprudenti persona perdet eam: personae autem acceptione perdet se.

text: Who brought forth Israel out of the middes of them: because his mercie is for euer.
verse_text: And he redemed vs from our enemies: because his mercie is for euer.

text: A furious man cannot be iustified, for the sway of his fury shalbe his destruction.
verse_text: Corona sapientiae timor Domini, replens pacem et salutis fructum:

text: Quia delectasti me, Domine, in factura tua; et in operibus manuum tuarum exsultabo.
verse_text: ego autem in misericordia tua speravi. Exsultabit cor meum in salutari tuo. Cantabo Domino qui bona tribuit mihi; et psallam nomini Domini altissimi.

text: Yet haue thou patience with a man in poore estate, and delay not to shew him mercy.
verse_text: sin autem, fraudabit illum pecunia sua, et possidebit illum inimicum gratis:

text: And he destroyed the rulers of the Tyrians, and all the princes of the Philistines.
verse_text: et cognitus est in verbis suis fidelis, quia vidit Deum lucis.

text: Et locuti sunt sacerdotes et prophetae ad principes, et ad omnem populum, dicentes:
verse_text: Et dixerunt principes et omnis populus ad sacerdotes et ad prophetas:

text: Magna est gloria ejus in salutari tuo; gloriam et magnum decorem impones super eum.
verse_text: Impleat Dominus omnes petitiones tuas; nunc cognovi quoniam salvum fecit Dominus christum suum. Exaudiet illum de caelo sancto suo, in potentatibus salus dexterae ejus.

text: Neque irrideant me inimici mei: etenim universi qui sustinent te, non confundentur.
verse_text: nequando dicat inimicus meus: Praevalui adversus eum. Qui tribulant me exsultabunt si motus fuero;

text: Alleluja. Laudate Dominum in sanctis ejus; laudate eum in firmamento virtutis ejus.
verse_text: Laudate eum in sono tubae; laudate eum in psalterio et cithara.

text: And I will persecute them with the sword, with the famine, and with the pestilence:
verse_text: Behold I will send upon them the sword, and the famine, and the pestilence:

text: To him that excelleth. A Psalme of David. Holde not thy tongue, O God of my praise.
verse_text: To him that excelleth on Neginoth. A Psalme of David. Heare my cry, O God: giue eare vnto my prayer.

text: Riches and treasures shalbe in his house, and his righteousnesse endureth for euer.
verse_text: He hath dispersed, he hath giuen to the poore: his righteousnesse endureth for euer; his horne shalbe exalted with honour.

text: She shall leaue her memorie to be cursed, and her reproch shall not be blotted out.
verse_text: Tenebrae circumdant me, et parietes cooperiunt me, et nemo circumspicit me: quem vereor? delictorum meorum non memorabitur Altissimus.

text: Praise is not seemly in the mouth of a sinner, for it was not sent him of the Lord:
verse_text: Tarry not in the error of the ungodly, give glory before death. Praise perisheth from the dead as nothing.

text: Ye that feare the Lord, trust in the Lord: for he is their helper and their shield.
verse_text: O house of Aaron, trust ye in the Lord: for he is their helpe and their shielde.

text: Da mihi intellectum, et scrutabor legem tuam, et custodiam illam in toto corde meo.
verse_text: ut facerem voluntatem tuam. Deus meus, volui, et legem tuam in medio cordis mei.

text: Their eyes saw the maiestie of his glory, and their eares heard his glorious voyce.
verse_text: Viae illorum coram ipso sunt semper: non sunt absconsae ab oculis ipsius.

text: Exalt thy self, O God, aboue the heauens, and let thy glorie be vpon all the earth,
verse_text: Be axalted aboue the heauens o God: and thy glorie vpon al the earth.

text: Turne vs againe, O Lord God of hostes: cause thy face to shine and we shalbe saued.
verse_text: O God of hosts conuert vs: and shew thy face, and we shal be saued.

text: The Lord knoweth the dayes of the vpright: and their inheritance shall be for euer.
verse_text: But the saluation of the righteous men shalbe of the Lord: he shalbe their strength in the time of trouble.

text: And all the Kings of Arabia, and all the Kings of Arabia, that dwell in the desert,
verse_text: And all the kings of Tyrus, and all the kings of Zidon, and the kings of the yles which are beyond the sea:

text: The Persians quaked at her boldnesse, and the Medes were daunted at her hardinesse.
verse_text: Unxit faciem suam unguento, et colligavit cincinnos suos mitra; accepit stolam novem ad decipiendum illum.

text: Thus they turned their glory into the similitude of a bullocke, that eateth grasse.
verse_text: They haue furie according to the similitude of a serpent: as of the aspe that is deafe, and stoppeth his eares.

text: Benedictus Dominus, quoniam mirificavit misericordiam suam mihi in civitate munita.
verse_text: Et scitote quoniam mirificavit Dominus sanctum suum; Dominus exaudiet me cum clamavero ad eum.

text: Divites eguerunt, et esurierunt; inquirentes autem Dominum non minuentur omni bono.
verse_text: Edent pauperes, et saturabuntur, et laudabunt Dominum qui requirunt eum: vivent corda eorum in saeculum saeculi.

text: Sicut in percussura cribri remanebit pulvis, sic aporia hominis in cogitatu illius.
verse_text: Narratio fatui quasi sarcina in via: nam in labiis sensati invenietur gratia.

text: He exalted Aaron an holy man like vnto him, euen his brother, of the tribe of Leui.
verse_text: Et dedit illi coram praecepta, et legem vitae et disciplinae, docere Jacob testamentum suum, et judicia sua Israel.

text: He saw and perceiued their end to be euill, therefore he multiplied his compassion.
verse_text: Miseratio hominis circa proximum suum: misericordia autem Dei super omnem carnem.

text: Miserere mei, Deus, quoniam conculcavit me homo; tota die impugnans, tribulavit me.
verse_text: In die tribulationis meae Deum exquisivi; manibus meis nocte contra eum, et non sum deceptus. Renuit consolari anima mea;

text: Quia in humilitate nostra memor fuit nostri, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus;
verse_text: Qui dat escam omni carni, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: Benedicite, omnes virtutes Domini, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, sacerdotes Domini, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Audi me, fili, et disce disciplinam sensus, et in verbis meis attende in corde tuo:
verse_text: Audi, fili, et accipe consilium intellectus, et ne abjicias consilium meum.

text: I said: Lord haue haue mercie on me: heale my soule, because I haue sinned to thee.
verse_text: I haue cried, because thou hast heard me o God: incline thyne eare to me, and heare my wordes.

text: The furnace prooueth the potters vessell: so the triall of man is in his reasoning.
verse_text: Sicut in percussura cribri remanebit pulvis, sic aporia hominis in cogitatu illius.

text: A dishonest woman contemneth shame, but an honest woman will reuerence her husband.
verse_text: Fundamenta aeterna supra petram solidam, et mandata Dei in corde mulieris sanctae.

text: If thou wilt, to keepe the Commandements, and to performe acceptable faithfulnesse.
verse_text: adjecit mandata et praecepta sua.

text: Hee himselfe made man from the beginning, and left him in the hand of his counsell,
verse_text: Deus ab initio constituit hominem, et reliquit illum in manu consilii sui:

text: Behold I will feed this people with wormwood, and give them water of gall to drink.
verse_text: for the Lord our God hath put us to silence, and hath given us water of gall to drink:

text: Audite verbum Domini, gentes, et annuntiate in insulis quae procul sunt, et dicite:
verse_text: Audite verbum Domini, reges Juda, et omnis Juda, cunctique habitatores Jerusalem, qui ingredimini per portas istas.

text: Riches are not comely for a niggard: and what should an enuious man doe with money?
verse_text: Viro cupido et tenaci sine ratione est substantia: et homini livido ad quid aurum?

text: Exalt thy selfe, O God, aboue the heauens, and let thy glory be vpon all the earth.
verse_text: O Lord our Lord, how excellent is thy name in all the earth! who hast set thy glory aboue the heauens.

text: He was as the morning starre in the midst of a cloud: and as the moone at the full.
verse_text: As the Sunne shining vpon the Temple of the most High, and as the rainebow giuing light in the bright cloudes.

text: For the yoke thereof is a yoke of yron, and the bands thereof are bandes of brasse.
verse_text: Qui respicit illam non habebit requiem, nec habebit amicum in quo requiescat.

text: The house of Israel hath hoped in our Lord: he is their helper and their protector.
verse_text: Blessed is he, whose helper is the God of Iacob, his hope in our Lord his God:

text: Neither spared he the place where Lot soiourned, but abhorred them for their pride.
verse_text: Non exoraverunt pro peccatis suis antiqui gigantes, qui destructi sunt confidentes suae virtuti.

text: Then an herald cried aloude, Be it knowen to you, O people, nations, and languages,
verse_text: And forthwith when he had opened the doore, the king looking on the table, cried out with a lowd voice: Great art thou o Bel, and there is not any deceite with thee.

text: Alleluja. Confitemini Domino, quoniam bonus, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: Confitemini Deo deorum, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: Deus, iniqui insurrexerunt super me, et synagoga potentium quaesierunt animam meam:
verse_text: Locuti sunt adversum me lingua dolosa, et sermonibus odii circumdederunt me:

text: But I as a deafe man heard not, and am as a dumme man, which openeth not his mouth.
verse_text: And I became as a man not hearing: and not hauing reproofes in his mouth.

text: In circuitu impii ambulant: secundum altitudinem tuam multiplicasti filios hominum.
verse_text: A fortitudine manus tuae ego defeci in increpationibus: propter iniquitatem corripuisti hominem. Et tabescere fecisti sicut araneam animam ejus: verumtamen vane conturbatur omnis homo.

text: O Lord God of hosts, how long wilt thou bee angry against the prayer of thy people?
verse_text: O God, why hast thou cast vs off for euer? why doeth thine anger smoke against the sheepe of thy pasture?

text: Surely his saluation is nigh them that feare him; that glory may dwell in our land.
verse_text: Hee will fulfill the desire of them that feare him: he also will heare their cry, and will saue them.

text: cor autem eorum non erat rectum cum eo, nec fideles habiti sunt in testamento ejus.
verse_text: Corrupti sunt, et abominabiles facti sunt in iniquitatibus; non est qui faciat bonum.

text: The discourse of fooles is irksome, and their sport is in the wantonnesse of sinne.
verse_text: In medio insensatorum serva verbum tempori: in medio autem cogitantium assiduus esto.

text: Desire not a multitude of vnprofitable children, neither delight in vngodly sonnes.
verse_text: Ne jucunderis in filiis impiis, si multiplicentur: nec oblecteris super ipsos, si non est timor Dei in illis.

text: Set thy heart aright, and constantly endure, and make not haste in time of trouble.
verse_text: Deprime cor tuum, et sustine: inclina aurem tuam, et suscipe verba intellectus: et ne festines in tempore obductionis.

text: Filii autem ejus provocabuntur, et congregabunt multitudinem exercituum plurimorum:
verse_text: Convertetur enim rex aquilonis, et praeparabit multitudinem multo majorem quam prius:

text: Praise is not seemly in the mouth of a sinner, for it was not sent him of the Lord:
verse_text: Non est speciosa laus in ore peccatoris,

text: Be stedfast in thy couenant, and be conuersant therein, and waxe olde in thy worke.
verse_text: et nescit quod tempus praeteriet, et mors appropinquet, et relinquat omnia aliis, et morietur.

text: Thou hast broken downe all his hedges: thou hast brought his strong holds to ruine.
verse_text: Thou hast destroied him from emundation: and his seat thou hast broken downe to the ground.

text: Prayse the Lord with harpe: sing vnto him with viole and instrument of ten strings.
verse_text: Let them prayse his Name with the flute: let them sing prayses vnto him with the timbrell and harpe.

text: Thou wilt keepe them, O Lord: thou wilt preserue him from this generation for euer.
verse_text: But thou, O Lord, shalt endure for euer: and thy remembrance vnto all generations.

text: O Lord my God, if I haue done this thing, if there be any wickednes in mine handes,
verse_text: And consider if there be any way of wickednes in me, and leade me in the way for euer.

text: And I will persecute them with the sword, and with famine, and pith the pestilence:
verse_text: but I will consume them by the sword, and by the famine, and by the pestilence.

text: and none of them shall remaine or escape from the euil that I will bring vpon them.
verse_text: Behold I will bring in evils upon them, which they shall not be able to escape:

text: He shewed what should come to passe for euer, and secret things or euer they came.
verse_text: nam fecit Ezechias quod placuit Deo, et fortiter ivit in via David patris sui, quam mandavit illi Isaias, propheta magnus, et fidelis in conspectu Dei.

text: While he openeth his hand he shal reioyce: so shall transgressours come to nought.
verse_text: In aperiendo manus suas laetabitur: sic praevaricatores in consummatione tabescent.

text: Then trembled their hearts and handes, and they were in paine as women in trauell.
verse_text: Ezechias munivit civitatem suam, et induxit in medium ipsius aquam: et fodit ferro rupem, et aedificavit ad aquam puteum.

text: At the brightnes of his presence his clouds passed, haylestones and coles of fire.
verse_text: The Lord also thundred in the heauen, and the Highest gaue his voyce, haylestones and coales of fire.

text: Haereditate acquisivi testimonia tua in aeternum, quia exsultatio cordis mei sunt.
verse_text: Quoniam dixisti: In aeternum misericordia aedificabitur in caelis; praeparabitur veritas tua in eis.

text: Cumque loqueretur mihi hujuscemodi verbis, dejeci vultum meum ad terram, et tacui.
verse_text: Cumque loqueretur ad me, collapsus sum pronus in terram: et tetigit me, et statuit me in gradu meo,

text: And made Israel to passe through the mids of it: for his mercie endureth for euer:
verse_text: Who led his people through the desert: because his mercie is for euer.

text: For thy mercy is great aboue the heauens: and thy trueth reacheth vnto the clouds.
verse_text: Thy mercy, O Lord, reacheth vnto the heauens, and thy faithfulnesse vnto the cloudes.

text: Viro cupido et tenaci sine ratione est substantia: et homini livido ad quid aurum?
verse_text: Homo acharis quasi fabula vana, in ore indisciplinatorum assidua erit.

text: I WIL confesse to thee o Lord with al my hart: I wil tel al thy meruelous thinges.
verse_text: O God thou hast taught me from my youth: and vntil now I wil pronounce thy meruelous workes.

text: Ego Daniel multum cogitationibus meis conturbabar, et facies mea mutata est in me:
verse_text: Tunc facies regis commutata est, et cogitationes ejus conturbabant eum:

text: If he that is but flesh nourish hatred, who will intreat for pardon of his sinnes?
verse_text: Ipse cum caro sit reservat iram, et propitiationem petit a Deo: quis exorabit pro delictis illius?

text: Gressus meos dirige secundum eloquium tuum, et non dominetur mei omnis injustitia.
verse_text: Os meum annuntiabit justitiam tuam, tota die salutare tuum. Quoniam non cognovi litteraturam,

text: Except thy Lawe had bene my delite, I should now haue perished in mine affliction.
verse_text: I haue preuented in maturitie, and haue cried: because I hoped much in thy wordes.

text: A loude crying woman, and a scolde, shall be sought out to driue away the enemies.
verse_text: et qui transgreditur a justitia ad peccatum: Deus paravit eum ad rhomphaeam.

text: Qui timet Dominum honorat parentes, et quasi dominis serviet his qui se genuerunt.
verse_text: Deus enim honoravit patrem in filiis: et judicium matris exquirens, firmavit in filios.

text: All that hate me, whisper together against me; against me doe they deuise my hurt.
verse_text: For mine enemies speake of mee, and they that lay waite for my soule, take their counsell together,

text: The house of Aaron hath hoped in our Lord: he is their helper and their protector.
verse_text: Our soule expecteth our Lord: because he is our helper and protector.

text: Cave tibi, et attende diligenter auditui tuo, quoniam cum subversione tua ambulas:
verse_text: Attende tibi a pestifero, fabricat enim mala, ne inducat super te subsannationem in perpetuum.

text: Benedicite, omnes volucres caeli, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, filii hominum, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Exaltabo te, Domine, quoniam suscepisti me, nec delectasti inimicos meos super me.
verse_text: Custodi animam meam, quoniam sanctus sum; salvum fac servum tuum, Deus meus, sperantem in te.

text: Thou art my God, and I will praise thee, euen my God: therefore I will exalt thee.
verse_text: Vnto thee, O my Strength, wil I sing: for God is my defence, and my mercifull God.

text: Priusquam interroges, ne vituperes quemquam: et cum interrogaveris, corripe juste.
verse_text: Amico et inimico noli narrare sensum tuum: et si est tibi delictum, noli denudare:

text: Deprecatus sum faciem tuam in toto corde meo; miserere mei secundum eloquium tuum.
verse_text: Suscipe me secundum eloquium tuum, et vivam, et non confundas me ab exspectatione mea.

text: Who before him so stood to it? for the Lord himselfe brought his enemies vnto him.
verse_text: Quam gloriam adeptus est in tollendo manus suas, et jactando contra civitates rhomphaeas !

text: Qui fundasti terram super stabilitatem suam: non inclinabitur in saeculum saeculi.
verse_text: Qui firmavit terram super aquas, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: O let not the oppressed returne ashamed: let the poore and needie praise thy name.
verse_text: Let mee not be ashamed, O Lord, for I haue called vpon thee: let the wicked be ashamed, and let them be silent in the graue.

text: Thou hast rebuked the prowde: cursed are they that decline from thy commandmentes.
verse_text: Thou hast despised al that reuolt from thy iudgementes: because their cogitation is vniust.

text: Noli consiliari cum eo qui tibi insidiatur, et a zelantibus te absconde consilium.
verse_text: Non te justifices ante Deum, quoniam agnitor cordis ipse est: et penes regem noli velle videri sapiens.

text: My sonne, hast thou sinned? doe so no more, but aske pardon for thy former sinnes.
verse_text: Fili, peccasti, non adjicias iterum: sed et de pristinis deprecare, ut tibi dimittantur.

text: Gladius ad divinos ejus, qui stulti erunt: gladius ad fortes illius, qui timebunt.
verse_text: Gladius ad equos ejus, et ad currus ejus, et ad omne vulgus quod est in medio ejus: et erunt quasi mulieres: gladius ad thesauros ejus, qui diripientur.

text: Dominus custodiat introitum tuum et exitum tuum, ex hoc nunc et usque in saeculum.
verse_text: in Jerusalem. Montes in circuitu ejus; et Dominus in circuitu populi sui, ex hoc nunc et usque in saeculum.

text: Trouble and anguish haue taken hold on me: yet thy commaundements are my delights.
verse_text: Horrour hath taken holde vpon me, because of the wicked that forsake thy Law.

text: Desiderium cordis ejus tribuisti ei, et voluntate labiorum ejus non fraudasti eum.
verse_text: Exaltasti dexteram deprimentium eum; laetificasti omnes inimicos ejus.

text: Amico et inimico noli narrare sensum tuum: et si est tibi delictum, noli denudare:
verse_text: Noli consiliari cum eo qui tibi insidiatur, et a zelantibus te absconde consilium.

text: He gaue vp their cattel also to the haile: and their flockes to hot thunder-bolts.
verse_text: He destroied their vines with haile, and their wilde figge trees with the hailestone.

text: Tu autem, Domine, ne elongaveris auxilium tuum a me; ad defensionem meam conspice.
verse_text: Non timebo millia populi circumdantis me. Exsurge, Domine; salvum me fac, Deus meus.

text: Is it not a griefe vnto death, when a companion and friend is turned to an enemie?
verse_text: sodalis autem et amicus ad inimicitiam convertentur.

text: The grace of a wife delighteth her husband, and her discretion will fat his bones.
verse_text: In filia non avertente se, firma custodiam, ne inventa occasione utatur se.

text: HE. Teach mee, O Lord, the way of thy statutes, and I will keepe it vnto the ende.
verse_text: Make me to goe in the path of thy commandements: for therein doe I delight.

text: Watching for riches, consumeth the flesh, and the care therof driueth away sleepe.
verse_text: Sound sleepe commeth of moderate eating: he riseth early, and his wits are with him, but the paine of watching and choller, and pangs of the bellie are with an vnsatiable man.

text: Say not thou, He hath caused mee to erre, for hee hath no need of the sinfull man.
verse_text: Non dicas: Ille me implanavit: non enim necessarii sunt ei homines impii.

text: Neuerthelesse in those daies, saith the Lord, I will not make a full end with you.
verse_text: For thus saith the Lord, That after seuentie yeeres be accomplished at Babylon, I will visite you, and performe my good word towards you, in causing you to returne to this place.

text: Super populum tuum malignaverunt consilium, et cogitaverunt adversus sanctos tuos.
verse_text: Supra dorsum meum fabricaverunt peccatores; prolongaverunt iniquitatem suam.

text: The grace of a wife delighteth her husband, and her discretion will fat his bones.
verse_text: A vertuous woman reioyceth her husband, and he shall fulfill the yeeres of his life in peace.

text: let them bee clothed with confusion and shame, that lift vp themselues against me.
verse_text: let them be couered with reproofe and confusion, that seeke mine hurt.

text: For a while hee will abide with thee, but if thou begin to fall, he wil not tarie.

text: Therefore thus saith the Lord of the men of Anathoth, that seeke thy life, saying;

text: Et pluit super eos sicut pulverem carnes, et sicut arenam maris volatilia pennata.
verse_text: Fiant tamquam pulvis ante faciem venti, et angelus Domini coarctans eos.

text: But thou hast saued vs from our enemies, and hast put them to shame that hated vs.
verse_text: Through thee haue we thrust backe our aduersaries: by thy Name haue we troden downe them that rose vp against vs.

text: I will bee glad, and reioyce in thee: I will sing praise to thy Name, O most High,
verse_text: Therefore I will prayse thee, O Lord, among the nations, and wil sing vnto thy Name.

text: For dreames haue deceiued many, and they haue failed that put their trust in them.
verse_text: multos enim errare fecerunt somnia, et exciderunt sperantes in illis.

text: et plantabo eos in terra ista in veritate, in toto corde meo et in tota anima mea.
verse_text: et timorem meum dabo in corde eorum, ut non recedant a me.

text: Blame not before thou hast examined the trueth: vnderstand first, and then rebuke.
verse_text: Priusquam interroges, ne vituperes quemquam: et cum interrogaveris, corripe juste.

text: From the habitation of his dwelling he beholdeth all them that dwell in the earth.
verse_text: The Lord looketh from heauen: he beholdeth all the sonnes of men.

text: Gaze not on a maide, that thou fall not by those things, that are pretious in her.
verse_text: Virginem ne conspicias, ne forte scandalizeris in decore illius.

text: Wherefore wil ye pleade with me? ye all haue rebelled against me, sayeth the Lord.
verse_text: Why will you contend with me in judgement? you have all forsaken me, saith the Lord.

text: Watching for riches, consumeth the flesh, and the care therof driueth away sleepe.
verse_text: Vigilia honestatis tabefaciet carnes, et cogitatus illius auferet somnum.

text: But thou, O Lord, shalt endure for euer: and thy remembrance vnto all generations.
verse_text: Thy Name, O Lord, endureth for euer: O Lord, thy remembrance is from generation to generation.

text: We shal reioyce in thy saluation: and in the name of our God we shal be magnified.
verse_text: In thy name shall they reioyce all the day: and in thy righteousnes shall they be exalted.

text: A consort of musicke in a banket of wine, is as a signet of Carbuncle set in gold.
verse_text: primum verbum diligenti scientia, et non impedias musicam.

text: Who is this, that commeth vp, as a flood, whose waters are mooued like the riuers?
verse_text: Egypt riseth vp like the flood, and his waters are mooued like the riuers, and he sayth, I wil goe vp, and will couer the earth: I wil destroy the citie with them that dwell therein.

text: Lord, howe long wilt thou be angrie, for euer? shall thy gelousie burne like fire?
verse_text: How long o Lord wilt thou be angrie for euer: shal thy zele be kindled as a fire?

text: O God, arise, therefore iudge thou the earth: for thou shalt inherite all nations.
verse_text: Before the Lord: for he is come to iudge the earth: with righteousnesse shall hee iudge the world, and the people with equitie.

text: Because our Lord is great, and exceeding laudable: he is terrible aboue al goddes.
verse_text: Great is our Lord, and great is his power: his wisdome is infinite.

text: Because our Lord hath chosen Sion: he hath chosen it for an habitation to himself.
verse_text: Because our Lord hath chosen Iacob to himself, Israel for his owne possession.

text: The humble shall see this, and be glad: and your heart shall liue that seeke good.
verse_text: Let the poore see and reioyce: seeke ye God, and your soule shal liue.

text: Praise him with the sound of the Trumpet: Prayse him with the Psalterie and Harpe.
verse_text: Prayse ye him in the sound of trumpet : prayse ye him on psalter, and harpe.

text: He claue the rockes in the wildernes, and gaue them drinke as of the great depths.
verse_text: He rebuked the Red sea also, and it was dried vp: so hee led them through the depthes, as through the wildernes.

text: Unto thee, O my helper, will I sing, for thou art God my defence: my God my mercy.
verse_text: Because thou o Lord art my hope: thou hast made the Highest thy refuge.

text: Giue vnto the Lord, ye families of the people: giue vnto the Lord glory and power.
verse_text: Afferte Domino, familiae populorum: afferte Domino gloriam et imperium.

text: From the depth of the belly of hel, from an vncleane tongue, and from lying words.

text: But vpon the earth was no man created like Enoch, for he was taken from the earth.

text: The root of wisedome is to feare the Lord, and the branches thereof are long life.

text: but some of them hath hee cursed, and brought low, and turned out of their places.

text: A consort of musicke in a banket of wine, is as a signet of Carbuncle set in gold.
verse_text: Delicates powred vpon a mouth shut vp, are as messes of meat set vpon a graue.

text: Exalt thy selfe, O God, aboue the heauen, and let thy glory be vpon all the earth.
verse_text: O Lord our Lord, how excellent is thy name in all the earth! who hast set thy glory aboue the heauens.

text: Whatsoeuer thou takest in hand, remember the end, and thou shalt neuer doe amisse.

text: Vnto thee, O my Strength, wil I sing: for God is my defence, and my mercifull God.

text: Blessed is the man whome thou chastenest, O Lord: and teachest him out of thy Law:

text: Turne not away thine eye from the needy, and giue him none occasion to curse thee:

text: Let them be confounded and ashamed together, that seeke my soule, to take it away.

text: Exquisivi Dominum, et exaudivit me; et ex omnibus tribulationibus meis eripuit me.

text: Verba iniquorum praevaluerunt super nos, et impietatibus nostris tu propitiaberis.

text: Fili, eleemosynam pauperis ne defraudes, et oculos tuos ne transvertas a paupere.

text: Libera eum qui injuriam patitur de manu superbi, et non acide feras in anima tua.

text: Pride was not made for men, nor furious anger for them that are borne of a woman.

text: erubescebant enim indicare sibi concupiscentiam suam, volentes concumbere cum ea.

text: A wise man shall inherite glory among his people, and his name shalbe perpetuall.

text: For grace is not giuen him from the Lord: because he is depriued of all wisedome.

text: For excesse of meates, bringeth sicknesse, and surfetting will turne into choler.

text: Si crediderit ei, haereditabit illam, et erunt in confirmatione creaturae illius:

text: I haue waited on the Lord: my soule hath waited, and I haue trusted in his worde.

text: The moone and the starres to gouerne the night: for his mercie endureth for euer:

text: His glory is great in thy saluation: dignitie and honour hast thou laid vpon him.

text: In hoc cognovi quoniam voluisti me, quoniam non gaudebit inimicus meus super me.

text: Because my loynes are filled with illusions: and there is no health in my flesh.

text: The heauens declare the glory of God: and the firmament sheweth his handy worke.

text: I was cast vpon thee, euen from ye wombe: thou art my God from my mothers belly.

text: Reioyce the soule of thy seruant: for vnto thee (O Lord) doe I lift vp my soule.
verse_text: Vnto thee, O Lord, doe I lift vp my soule.

text: Custodi me a laqueo quem statuerunt mihi, et a scandalis operantium iniquitatem.

text: Doe with thy seruant according to thy mercie: and teachet me thy iustifications.
verse_text: Heare my voice according vnto thy louing kindnesse: O Lord quicken me according to thy iudgement.

text: Signatum est super nos lumen vultus tui, Domine: dedisti laetitiam in corde meo.

text: I was oft times in danger of death, yet I was deliuered because of these things.

text: Ante mortem ne laudes hominem quemquam: quoniam in filiis suis agnoscitur vir.
verse_text: Ne jucunderis in filiis impiis, si multiplicentur: nec oblecteris super ipsos, si non est timor Dei in illis.

text: Restore vnto me the ioy of thy saluation: and vphold mee with thy free Spirit.
verse_text: Heare my voyce according to thy louing kindenesse: O Lord, quicken me according to thy iudgement.

text: Est autem sapientia quae abundat in malo, et non est sensus ubi est amaritudo.
verse_text: Est correptio mendax in ira contumeliosi, et est judicium quod non probatur esse bonum: et est tacens, et ipse est prudens.

text: For of the most High commeth healing, and he shall receiue honour of the King.
verse_text: A Deo est enim omnis medela, et a rege accipiet donationem.

text: And they remembred that God was their rocke: and the high God, their redeemer.
verse_text: O Israel, trust thou in the Lord: for he is their helpe and their shielde.

text: Regnabit Dominus in saecula; Deus tuus, Sion, in generationem et generationem.
verse_text: Dominus regnabit in aeternum, et in saeculum saeculi; peribitis, gentes, de terra illius.

text: Ye that feare the Lord, waite for his mercie, and goe not aside, lest ye fall.
verse_text: Metuentes Dominum, sustinete misericordiam ejus: et non deflectatis ab illo, ne cadatis.

text: O Lord, rebuke me not in thy wrath: neither chasten me in thy hot displeasure.
verse_text: LORD rebuke me nor in thy furie: nor chastise me in thy wrath.

text: Fili, a juventute tua excipe doctrinam, et usque ad canos invenies sapientiam.
verse_text: Ante languorem adhibe medicinam: et ante judicium interroga teipsum, et in conspectu Dei invenies propitiationem.

text: and their mightie ones are beaten downe, & are fled apace, and looke not back:
verse_text: Also her hired men are in the midst of her, like fatted bullocks, for they also are turned backe, and are fled away together;

text: Quoniam haec dicit Dominus: Vocem terroris audivimus: formido, et non est pax.
verse_text: Haec dicit Dominus: Vox in excelso audita est lamentationis: luctus, et fletus Rachel plorantis filios suos, et nolentis consolari super eis, quia non sunt.

text: It is God that giueth me power to auenge me, and subdueth the people vnder me.
verse_text: It is he that giueth saluation vnto kings: who deliuereth Dauid his seruant from the hurtfull sword.

text: With Isaac did he establish likewise the blessing of all men and the couenant,
verse_text: Ideo jurejurando dedit illi gloriam in gente sua, crescere illum quasi terrae cumulum,

text: Ideo adimplevit propitiationem suam in illis, et ostendit eis viam aequitatis.
verse_text: Et quaesivit omnes nequitias, usque dum perveniret ad illos defensio, et ab omnibus peccatis liberavit eos.

text: Likewise in the beloued citie he gaue mee rest, and in Ierusalem was my power.
verse_text: et omnium excellentium et humilium corda virtute calcavi. Et in his omnibus requiem quaesivi, et in haereditate Domini morabor.

text: Let them bee confounded, and put to shame together, that reioyce at mine hurt:
verse_text: Let them be confounded and put to shame, that seeke my soule:

text: In justitia tua libera me, et eripe me: inclina ad me aurem tuam, et salva me.
verse_text: ut liberentur dilecti tui. Salvum fac dextera tua, et exaudi me.

text: Saue me out of the lions mouth: and my humilitie from the hornes of vnicornes.
verse_text: Deliuer, o God, my soule from the sword: and myne onlie one from the hand of the dog.

text: Qui traduxit populum suum per desertum, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: Qui percussit AEgyptum cum primogenitis eorum, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: The enuious man hath a wicked eye, he turneth away his face and despiseth men.
verse_text: Nequam est oculus lividi: et avertens faciem suam, et despiciens animam suam.

text: O Lord the God of hoastes conuert vs: and shew thy face, and we shal be saued.
verse_text: Turne vs againe, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine, and we shall be saued.

text: for he is the fourmer of all things, and Israel is the rod of his inheritance:
verse_text: The portion of Iacob is not like them, for he is the former of all things, and Israel is the rod of his inheritance:

text: The feare of the Lord is a fruitfull garden, and couereth him aboue all glory.
verse_text: Non est in timore Domini minoratio: et non est in eo inquirere adjutorium.

text: Who wast taken vp in a whirlewinde of fire, and in a charet of fierie horses:
verse_text: qui receptus es in turbine ignis, in curru equorum igneorum:

text: Hee created mee from the beginning before the world, and I shall neuer faile.
verse_text: Et in omni terra steti: et in omni populo,

text: In the holy Tabernacle I serued before him: and so was I established in Sion.
verse_text: et in omni gente primatum habui:

text: Et dimisi eos secundum desideria cordis eorum; ibunt in adinventionibus suis.
verse_text: Et irritaverunt eum in adinventionibus suis, et multiplicata est in eis ruina.

text: Reges Tharsis et insulae munera offerent; reges Arabum et Saba dona adducent:
verse_text: Increpa feras arundinis; congregatio taurorum in vaccis populorum: ut excludant eos qui probati sunt argento. Dissipa gentes quae bella volunt.

text: Arise, O Lord, let not man preuaile: let the heathen bee iudged in thy sight.
verse_text: Iudge me, O Lord my God, according to thy righteousnesse, and let them not reioyce ouer mee.

text: Honour and maiestie are before him: strength and beauty are in his sanctuary.
verse_text: Cloudes and darkenes are round about him: righteousnesse and iudgement are the foundation of his throne.

text: Qui divisit mare Rubrum in divisiones, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus;
verse_text: Qui fecit caelos in intellectu, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: In benedictione Dei et ipse speravi, et quasi qui vindemiat replevi torcular.
verse_text: Et radicavi in populo honorificato, et in parte Dei mei haereditas illius, et in plenitudine sanctorum detentio mea.

text: Laudate eum in cymbalis benesonantibus; laudate eum in cymbalis jubilationis.
verse_text: Laudent nomen ejus in choro; in tympano et psalterio psallant ei.

text: Watch ouer an impudent eye: and marueile not, if shee trespasse against thee.
verse_text: Mulier ebriosa ira magna, et contumelia: et turpitudo illius non tegetur.

text: Quoniam pater meus et mater mea dereliquerunt me; Dominus autem assumpsit me.
verse_text: Miserere mei, Deus, quoniam conculcavit me homo; tota die impugnans, tribulavit me.

text: Qui denudat arcana amici fidem perdit, et non inveniet amicum ad animum suum.
verse_text: Beatus qui invenit amicum verum, et qui enarrat justitiam auri audienti.

text: videns oculis et ingemiscens, sicut spado complectens virginem, et suspirans.
verse_text: quasi oliva pullulans, et cypressus in altitudinem se extollens, in accipiendo ipsum stolam gloriae, et vestiri eum in consummationem virtutis.

text: Narratio fatui quasi sarcina in via: nam in labiis sensati invenietur gratia.
verse_text: Sine mendacio consummabitur verbum legis, et sapientia in ore fidelis complanabitur.

text: Psalmus Asaph. Deus stetit in synagoga deorum; in medio autem deos dijudicat.
verse_text: Psalmus Asaph. Deus, venerunt gentes in haereditatem tuam; polluerunt templum sanctum tuum; posuerunt Jerusalem in pomorum custodiam.

text: How he had wrought his signes in Egypt: and his wonders in the field of Zoan:
verse_text: They shewed his signes among them: and wonders in the land of Ham.

text: Fidem posside cum amico in paupertate illius, ut et in bonis illius laeteris.
verse_text: Ne fueris mediocris in contentione ex foenore, et est tibi nihil in sacculo: eris enim invidus vitae tuae.

text: For thus saith the Lord: Thy bruise is incurable, thy wound is very grievous.
verse_text: Thus saith the Lord: after this manner will I make the pride of Juda, and the great pride of Jerusalem to rot.

text: Who geueth to beastes their foode: and to the young rauens that cal vpon him.
verse_text: The eies of al hope in thee o Lord: and thou geuest their meate in time conuenient.

text: O how desireable are all his workes: and that a man may see euen to a sparke.
verse_text: neque minuitur, et non eget alicujus consilio.

text: Et vias illius quis intelligit, et procellam quam nec oculus videbit hominis?
verse_text: disciplina sapientiae cui revelata est et manifestata? et multiplicationem ingressus illius quis intellexit?

text: Al workes of our Lord blesse ye our Lord, prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Priests of our Lord blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Tibi dixit cor meum: Exquisivit te facies mea; faciem tuam, Domine, requiram.
verse_text: Ego autem dixi in excessu mentis meae: Projectus sum a facie oculorum tuorum: ideo exaudisti vocem orationis meae, dum clamarem ad te.

text: Cognovi, Domine, quia aequitas judicia tua, et in veritate tua humiliasti me.
verse_text: Deus, docuisti me a juventute mea; et usque nunc pronuntiabo mirabilia tua.

text: Teach me, O Lord, the way of thy Statutes: and I shall keepe it vnto the end.
verse_text: Make me to goe in the path of thy commandements: for therein doe I delight.

text: Ante orationem praepara animam tuam, et noli esse quasi homo qui tentat Deum.
verse_text: Noli avidus esse in omni epulatione, et non te effundas super omnem escam:

text: Ante mortem benefac amico tuo, et secundum vires tuas exporrigens da pauperi.
verse_text: Si benefeceris, scito cui feceris, et erit gratia in bonis tuis multa.

text: Stultus acriter improperabit: et datus indisciplinati tabescere facit oculos.
verse_text: Cor pravum dabit tristitiam, et homo peritus resistet illi.

text: Horrour hath taken holde vpon me, because of the wicked that forsake thy Law.
verse_text: Faynting possessed me, because of sinners forsaking thy law.

text: For at the last thou shalt finde her rest, and that shalbe turned to thy ioy.
verse_text: Investiga illam, et manifestabitur tibi: et continens factus, ne derelinquas eam:

text: Verumtamen justi confitebuntur nomini tuo, et habitabunt recti cum vultu tuo.
verse_text: Beati qui habitant in domo tua, Domine; in saecula saeculorum laudabunt te.

text: Datio Dei permanet justis, et profectus illius successus habebit in aeternum.
verse_text: Qui possidet mulierem bonam inchoat possessionem: adjutorium secundum illum est, et columna ut requies.

text: Memoriam abundantiae suavitatis tuae eructabunt, et justitia tua exsultabunt.
verse_text: Laetetur mons Sion, et exsultent filiae Judae, propter judicia tua, Domine.

text: This thou hast seene (O Lord) keepe not silence: O Lord be not farre from me.
verse_text: But be not thou farre from mee, O Lord; O my strength, hast thee to helpe me.

text: Quam magna multitudo dulcedinis tuae, Domine, quam abscondisti timentibus te;
verse_text: Non erubescant in me qui exspectant te, Domine, Domine virtutum;

text: My mouth shall shew foorth thy righteousnesse, and thy saluation all the day:
verse_text: My tongue also shall talke of thy righteousnesse all the day long:

text: Work your work before the time, and he will give you your reward in his time.
verse_text: Let your soul rejoice in his mercy, and you shall not be confounded in his praise.

text: Tu exsurgens misereberis Sion, quia tempus miserendi ejus, quia venit tempus:
verse_text: Qui percussit reges magnos, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus;

text: How shall wee be able to magnifie him? for hee is great aboue all his workes.
verse_text: Propter ipsum confirmatus est itineris finis, et in sermone ejus composita sunt omnia.

text: Direct my steppes in thy worde, and let none iniquitie haue dominion ouer me.
verse_text: Stay my steps in thy paths, that my feete doe not slide.

text: Hee hath made a pitte and digged it, and is fallen into the pit that he made.
verse_text: The heathen are sunken downe in the pit that they made: in the nette that they hid, is their foote taken.

text: Nec conclusisti me in manibus inimici: statuisti in loco spatioso pedes meos.
verse_text: Dilatasti gressus meos subtus me, et non sunt infirmata vestigia mea.

text: Be thou exalted, O God, aboue the heauens: and thy glory aboue all the earth:
verse_text: Exalt thy self, O God, aboue the heauens, and let thy glorie be vpon all the earth,

text: Haec dicit Dominus: Descende in domum regis Juda, et loqueris ibi verbum hoc,
verse_text: Et dixit Dominus ad me: Vociferare omnia verba haec in civitatibus Juda, et foris Jerusalem, dicens: Audite verba pacti hujus, et facite illa,

text: In carne ejus stare fecit testamentum, et in tentatione inventus est fidelis.
verse_text: Statuit ei testamentum aeternum, et dedit illi sacerdotium gentis, et beatificavit illum in gloria:

text: Quoniam ipse cognovit figmentum nostrum; recordatus est quoniam pulvis sumus.
verse_text: Cognoscetur Dominus judicia faciens; in operibus manuum suarum comprehensus est peccator.

text: Facite judicium et justitiam, et liberate vi oppressum de manu calumniatoris:
verse_text: Judicate mane judicium, et eruite vi oppressum de manu calumniantis, ne forte egrediatur ut ignis indignatio mea, et succendatur, et non sit qui extinguat, propter malitiam studiorum vestrorum.

text: That thy beloued may bee deliuered: saue with thy right hand, and answere me.
verse_text: That thy beloued may be deliuered, helpe with thy right hand and heare me.

text: To him which diuided the red sea into parts: for his mercy endureth for euer.
verse_text: To him that made great lights: for his mercy endureth for euer.

text: Then stood vp Phinehas, and executed iudgement: and so the plague was stayed.
verse_text: And Phinees stood, and pacified: and the slaughter ceased.

text: He that sinneth before his maker, let him fal into the hand of the Phisitian.
verse_text: Qui delinquit in conspectu ejus qui fecit eum, incidet in manus medici.

text: He sanctified him in his faith, and meekness, and chose him out of all flesh.
verse_text: So in ten thousand did he glorify him, and praised him in the blessings of the Lord, in offering to him a crown of glory:

text: Forget not thy friend in thy mind, and be not unmindful of him in thy riches.
verse_text: My son, in thy good deeds, make no complaint, and when thou givest any thing, add not grief by an evil word.

text: Sing to our Lord ye his sainctes: and confesse to the memorie of his holines.
verse_text: Sing ye to our Lord in confession: sing ye to our God on harpe.

text: Sacrificium salutare est attendere mandatis, et discedere ab omni iniquitate.
verse_text: Sapiens cor et intelligibile abstinebit se a peccatis, et in operibus justitiae successus habebit.

text: et comedit omne foenum in terra eorum, et comedit omnem fructum terrae eorum.
verse_text: Et percussit omne primogenitum in terra eorum, primitias omnis laboris eorum.

text: He made a way to the path of his wrath, he spared not their liues from death:
verse_text: he spared not their soule from death, but gaue their life to the pestilence,

text: In te, Domine, speravi; non confundar in aeternum: in justitia tua libera me.
verse_text: Custodi animam meam, et erue me: non erubescam, quoniam speravi in te.

text: Quoniam iniquitatem meam ego cognosco, et peccatum meum contra me est semper.
verse_text: Respice inimicos meos, quoniam multiplicati sunt, et odio iniquo oderunt me.

text: Praecordia fatui quasi rota carri, et quasi axis versatilis cogitatus illius.
verse_text: Quasi rhomphaea bis acuta omnis iniquitas: plagae illius non est sanitas.

text: Blesse our Lord al ye powers of our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Seruants of our Lord blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: O giue thanks vnto the Lord, for he is good: for his mercy endureth for euer.
verse_text: Praise ye the Lord. O giue thankes vnto the Lord, for he is good: for his mercie endureth for euer.

text: Ye that feare the Lord trust in the Lord: he is their helpe and their shield.
verse_text: O house of Aaron, trust ye in the Lord: for he is their helpe and their shielde.

text: Because strgers haue risen vp against me, & the strong haue sought my soule:
verse_text: O God the wicked are risen vp vpon me, and the synagogue of the mightie haue sought my soule:

text: Circumdederunt me dolores mortis, et torrentes iniquitatis conturbaverunt me.
verse_text: Locuti sunt adversum me lingua dolosa, et sermonibus odii circumdederunt me: et expugnaverunt me gratis.

text: Qui audit illam judicabit gentes: et qui intuetur illam permanebit confidens.
verse_text: Qui credit Deo attendit mandatis: et qui confidit in illo non minorabitur.

text: That thy beloued may be deliuered, saue me with thy right hand; and heare me.
verse_text: That thy beloued may be deliuered, helpe with thy right hand and heare me.

text: They continue euen to this day by thine ordinances: for all are thy seruants.
verse_text: By thy ordinance the day contineweth: because al thinges serue thee.

text: The stone which the builders refused: is become the head stone of the corner.
verse_text: The stone, which the builders reiected: the same is made into the head of the corner.

text: Est enim amicus secundum tempus suum, et non permanebit in die tribulationis.
verse_text: Homo sapiens tacebit usque ad tempus: lascivus autem et imprudens non servabunt tempus.

text: In omnibus operibus tuis memorare novissima tua, et in aeternum non peccabis.
verse_text: et in justitia aedificabitur tibi, et in die tribulationis commemorabitur tui, et sicut in sereno glacies, solventur peccata tua.

text: Of whom, some did that which was pleasing to God, and some multiplied sinnes.
verse_text: In omnibus istis non poenituit populus, et non recesserunt a peccatis suis, usque dum ejecti sunt de terra sua, et dispersi sunt in omnem terram:

text: vnto all flesh, both man and beast, and that is seuen fold more vpon sinners.
verse_text: cum omni carne, ab homine usque ad pecus, et super peccatores septuplum.

text: Benedicite, rores et pruina, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, fontes, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: There is no riches aboue a sound body, and no ioy aboue the ioy of the heart.
verse_text: Non est census super censum salutis corporis, et non est oblectamentum super cordis gaudium.

text: Open not thine heart to euery man, least he requite thee with a shrewd turne.
verse_text: Cum iracundo non facias rixam, et cum audace non eas in desertum: quoniam quasi nihil est ante illum sanguis, et ubi non est adjutorium, elidet te.

text: Be swift to heare, and let thy life be sincere, & with patience giue answere.
verse_text: Non ventiles te in omnem ventum, et non eas in omnem viam: sic enim omnis peccator probatur in duplici lingua.

text: so shall no man dwell theere, neither shall the sonne of man remaine therein.
verse_text: there shall no man dwell there, nor the sonnes of men remaine in it.

text: Fire, and haile, and famine, and death: all these were created for vengeance:
verse_text: Quomodo convertit aquas in siccitatem, et siccata est terra, et viae illius viis illorum directae sunt, sic peccatoribus offensiones in ira ejus.

text: Therefore he gaue their power vnto others, & their glory to a strange nation.
verse_text: Praeter David et Ezechiam et Josiam, omnes peccatum commiserunt:

text: Sing vnto the Lord with the harpe: with the harpe, and the voice of a Psalme.
verse_text: Sing prayse to the Lord vpon the harpe, euen vpon the harpe with a singing voyce.

text: Haec dicit Dominus: Ecce quasi aquila volabit, et extendet alas suas ad Moab.
verse_text: Ecce quasi aquila ascendet, et avolabit, et expandet alas suas super Bosran: et erit cor fortium Idumaeae in die illa quasi cor mulieris parturientis.

text: Et ne avertas faciem tuam a puero tuo; quoniam tribulor, velociter exaudi me.
verse_text: Ego clamavi, quoniam exaudisti me, Deus; inclina aurem tuam mihi, et exaudi verba mea.

text: Ecce ego visitabo regem Babylonis et terram ejus, sicut visitavi regem Assur:
verse_text: Et visitabo super Bel in Babylone, et ejiciam quod absorbuerat de ore ejus:

text: Quoties exacerbaverunt eum in deserto; in iram concitaverunt eum in inaquoso?
verse_text: In iram concitaverunt eum in collibus suis, et in sculptilibus suis ad aemulationem eum provocaverunt.

text: Restore to me the ioy of thy saluation, and stablish me with thy free Spirit.
verse_text: Remember me, O Lord, with the fauour of thy people: visite me with thy saluation,

text: lunam et stellas in potestatem noctis, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: Qui dat escam omni carni, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: Loue him that made thee with all thy strength, and forsake not his ministers.
verse_text: memento quoniam nisi per illos natus non fuisses: et retribue illis, quomodo et illi tibi.

text: Whether hee bee rich, noble, or poore, their glorie is the feare of the Lord.
verse_text: Non est creata hominibus superbia, neque iracundia nationi mulierum.

text: Servavi mandata tua et testimonia tua, quia omnes viae meae in conspectu tuo.
verse_text: Revela oculos meos, et considerabo mirabilia de lege tua.

text: Sin Principes persecuti sunt me gratis, et a verbis tuis formidavit cor meum.
verse_text: Longe fecisti notos meos a me; posuerunt me abominationem sibi. Traditus sum, et non egrediebar;

text: Benedicite, lux et tenebrae, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, fulgura et nubes, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Et factus est mihi Dominus in refugium, et Deus meus in adjutorium spei meae.
verse_text: praevenerunt me in die afflictionis meae: et factus est Dominus protector meus.

text: That all the children of Israel might see that it is good to follow the Lord.
verse_text: Et ipsi duo constituti a periculo liberati sunt a numero sexcentorum millium peditum, inducere illos in haereditatem, in terram quae manat lac et mel.

text: Quoniam magnus Dominus, et laudabilis nimis: terribilis est super omnes deos.
verse_text: quoniam Deus magnus Dominus, et rex magnus super omnes deos.

text: Quoniam lumbi mei impleti sunt illusionibus, et non est sanitas in carne mea.
verse_text: et omnes vias meas praevidisti, quia non est sermo in lingua mea.

text: Take the song and bring forth the timbrel, the pleasant harpe with the viole.
verse_text: Sing vnto the Lord with the harpe: with the harpe, and the voice of a Psalme.

text: Which led his people through the wildernes: for his mercie endureth for euer:
verse_text: And made Israel to passe through the mids of it: for his mercie endureth for euer:

text: Benedicite, ignis et aestus, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, omnis imber et ros, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Multi qui persequuntur me, et tribulant me; a testimoniis tuis non declinavi.
verse_text: Eripuit me de inimicis meis fortissimis, et ab his qui oderunt me. Quoniam confortati sunt super me;

text: Paratum cor meum, Deus, paratum cor meum; cantabo, et psallam in gloria mea.
verse_text: Lauda, anima mea, Dominum. Laudabo Dominum in vita mea; psallam Deo meo quamdiu fuero. Nolite confidere in principibus,

text: Dewes and hore frost blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Colde and heate blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Seeke not of the Lord preheminence, neither of the King the seate of honour.
verse_text: Noli quaerere a Domino ducatum, neque a rege cathedram honoris.

text: And they shall fight against thee, but they shall not preuaile against thee:
verse_text: and they shall fight against thee, and shall not prevail:

text: These things are created for the wicked, and for their sakes came the flood.
verse_text: super iniquos creata sunt haec omnia: et propter illos factus est cataclysmus.

text: What fellowship hath the wolfe with the lambe? so the sinner with the godly.
verse_text: audiens vero illa, quasi in somnis vide, et vigilabis.

text: Auribus percipe, Domine, orationem meam, et intende voci deprecationis meae.
verse_text: Domine Deus virtutum, exaudi orationem meam; auribus percipe, Deus Jacob.

text: Hee that doeth lodge neere her house, shall also fasten a pin in her walles.
verse_text: qui respicit per fenestras illius, et in januis illius audiens:

text: Doe good in thy good pleasure vnto Sion: build thou the walles of Ierusalem.
verse_text: Deale fauorably o Lord in thy good wil with Sion: that the walles of Ierusalem may be built vp.

text: Quoniam misericordia tua ante oculos meos est, et complacui in veritate tua.
verse_text: Vau Et veniat super me misericordia tua, Domine; salutare tuum secundum eloquium tuum.

text: Expecta Dominum, viriliter age: et confortetur cor tuum, et sustine Dominum.
verse_text: Exspecta Dominum, et custodi viam ejus, et exaltabit te ut haereditate capias terram: cum perierint peccatores, videbis.

text: Qui sibi nequam est, cui alii bonus erit? et non jucundabitur in bonis suis.
verse_text: homo qui jucundatur in filiis, vivens et videns subversionem inimicorum suorum.

text: Alleluja. Credidi, propter quod locutus sum; ego autem humiliatus sum nimis.
verse_text: Annuntiavi justitiam tuam in ecclesia magna; ecce labia mea non prohibebo: Domine, tu scisti.

text: And walked about from nation to nation, from one kingdome to another people,
verse_text: And they passed from nation into nation, & from kingdom to an other people.

text: sin autem, fraudabit illum pecunia sua, et possidebit illum inimicum gratis:
verse_text: Si autem oberraverit, derelinquet eum, et tradet eum in manus inimici sui.

text: Gloria et divitiae in domo ejus, et justitia ejus manet in saeculum saeculi.
verse_text: Initium sapientiae timor Domini; intellectus bonus omnibus facientibus eum: laudatio ejus manet in saeculum saeculi.

text: Use not thy mouth to vntemperate swearing, for therein is the word of sinne.
verse_text: Et si frustraverit, delictum illius super ipsum erit: et si dissimulaverit, delinquit dupliciter:

text: I wil put his seed for euer and euer: and his throne as the daies of heauen.
verse_text: His seede shall endure for euer, and his throne shalbe as the sunne before me.

text: Hee pitied not the people of perdition, who were taken away in their sinnes.
verse_text: Et non pepercit peregrinationi Lot, et execratus est eos prae superbia verbi illorum.

text: Thou hast seene it, O Lord: keepe not silence: be not farre from me, O Lord.
verse_text: Goe not farre from me, O God: my God, haste thee to helpe me.

text: Homo sapiens in omnibus metuet, et in diebus delictorum attendet ab inertia.
verse_text: Beatus vir qui in sapientia morabitur, et qui in justitia sua meditabitur, et in sensu cogitabit circumspectionem Dei:

text: Wisedome shall praise her selfe, and shall glory in the midst of her people.
verse_text: Sapientia laudabit animam suam, et in Deo honorabitur, et in medio populi sui gloriabitur,

text: Respice inimicos meos, quoniam multiplicati sunt, et odio iniquo oderunt me.
verse_text: quoniam ecce inimici tui sonuerunt, et qui oderunt te extulerunt caput.

text: Make not an hungry soule sorrowfull, neither prouoke a man in his distresse.
verse_text: Animam esurientem ne despexeris, et non exasperes pauperem in inopia sua.

text: Water will quench a flaming fire, and almes maketh an attonement for sinnes.
verse_text: Synagogae superborum non erit sanitas, frutex enim peccati radicabitur in illis, et non intelligetur.

text: Get thy selfe the loue of the congregation, and bow thy head to a great man.
verse_text: Congregationi pauperum affabilem te facito: et presbytero humilia animam tuam, et magnato humilia caput tuum.

text: Quoniam tu es qui extraxisti me de ventre, spes mea ab uberibus matris meae.
verse_text: Libera me de sanguinibus, Deus, Deus salutis meae, et exsultabit lingua mea justitiam tuam.

text: Hear ye the word of the Lord, all Juda, you that dwell in the land of Egypt:
verse_text: Hear the word of the Lord, ye kings of Juda, and all Juda, and all the inhabitant of Jerusalem, that enter in by these gates.

text: Et erunt interfecti Domini in die illa, a summo terrae usque ad summum ejus:
verse_text: cadent in gladio, et in fame, et consumentur a minimo usque ad maximum:

text: And I will bring back the captivity of Juda, and the captivity of Jerusalem:
verse_text: And I will bring back the captivity of Moab in the last days, saith the Lord.

text: Glory not in the dishonour of thy father: for his shame is no glory to thee.
verse_text: Envy not the glory and riches of a sinner: for thou knowest not what his ruin shall be.

text: Est nequitia, et in ipsa execratio, et est insipiens qui minuitur sapientia.
verse_text: Melior est homo qui minuitur sapientia, et deficiens sensu, in timore, quam qui abundat sensu, et transgreditur legem Altissimi.

text: Datus insipientis non erit utilis tibi: oculi enim illius septemplices sunt.
verse_text: Noli anxius esse in divitiis injustis: non enim proderunt tibi in die obductionis et vindictae.

text: Quoniam cogitaverunt unanimiter; simul adversum te testamentum disposuerunt:
verse_text: Quia dixerunt inimici mei mihi, et qui custodiebant animam meam consilium fecerunt in unum,

text: And his eyes are vpon them that feare him, & hee knoweth euery worke of man.
verse_text: quoniam multa sapientia Dei, et fortis in potentia, videns omnes sine intermissione.

text: The word of the Lord that came to Jeremias the prophet against the Gentiles,
verse_text: The word that came to Jeremias from the Lord, saying:

text: Prayse ye him in the sound of trumpet : prayse ye him on psalter, and harpe.
verse_text: Praise him with the sound of the Trumpet: Prayse him with the Psalterie and Harpe.

text: Admonish a friend: for many times it is a slander, & beleeue not euery tale.
verse_text: Corripe amicum, saepe enim fit commissio:

text: Al beasts and cattel blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Seas and riuers blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: The fear of the Lord is honour, and glory, and gladness, and a crown of joy.
verse_text: The perfection of the fear of God is wisdom and understanding.

text: Juxta est Dominus iis qui tribulato sunt corde, et humiles spiritu salvabit.
verse_text: Multae tribulationes justorum; et de omnibus his liberabit eos Dominus.

text: ne propitieris iniquitati eorum, et peccatum eorum a facie tua non deleatur:
verse_text: quia propitiabor iniquitati eorum, et peccati eorum non memorabor amplius.

text: And weigh thy words in a ballance, and make a doore and barre for thy mouth.
verse_text: mors illius mors nequissima: et utilis potius infernus quam illa.

text: For thou hast possessed my reines: thou hast couered me in my mothers wombe.
verse_text: I was cast vpon thee from the wombe: thou art my God from my mothers belly.

text: Praevaricantes reputavi omnes peccatores terrae; ideo dilexi testimonia tua.
verse_text: Haec facta est mihi, quia justificationes tuas exquisivi.

text: Super omnes vias deserti venerunt vastatores, quia gladius Domini devorabit:
verse_text: Omnes pastores tuos pascet ventus, et amatores tui in captivitatem ibunt:

text: there shall not a man dwell there, and there shall no son of man inhabit it.
verse_text: there shall no man dwell there, nor the sonnes of men remaine in it.

text: Altissimus creavit de terra medicamenta, et vir prudens non abhorrebit illa.
verse_text: etenim illum Dominus creavit, et non discedat a te, quia opera ejus sunt necessaria.

text: quia magna est super caelos misericordia tua, et usque ad nubes veritas tua.
verse_text: Domine, Dominus noster, quam admirabile est nomen tuum in universa terra ! quoniam elevata est magnificentia tua super caelos.

text: Quoniam laudatur peccator in desideriis animae suae, et iniquus benedicitur.
verse_text: Laetabitur justus cum viderit vindictam; manus suas lavabit in sanguine peccatoris.

text: Filii sapientiae ecclesia justorum, et natio illorum obedientia et dilectio.
verse_text: Corona senum multa peritia, et gloria illorum timor Dei.

text: Their seed shall remaine for euer, and their glory shall not be blotted out.
verse_text: et filii eorum propter illos usque in aeternum manent: semen eorum et gloria eorum non derelinquetur.

text: a facie impiorum qui me afflixerunt. Inimici mei animam meam circumdederunt;
verse_text: Quoniam gratis absconderunt mihi interitum laquei sui; supervacue exprobraverunt animam meam.

text: But these were mercifull men, whose righteousnesse hath not beene forgotten.
verse_text: Sed illi viri misericordiae sunt, quorum pietates non defuerunt.

text: Nisi quod lex tua meditatio mea est, tunc forte periissem in humilitate mea.
verse_text: Super omnes docentes me intellexi, quia testimonia tua meditatio mea est.

text: Amicus fidelis protectio fortis: qui autem invenit illum, invenit thesaurum.
verse_text: Amicus fidelis medicamentum vitae et immortalitatis: et qui metuunt Dominum, invenient illum.

text: Obducam enim cicatricem tibi, et a vulneribus tuis sanabo te, dicit Dominus.
verse_text: et convertam luctum eorum in gaudium, et consolabor eos, et laetificabo a dolore suo.

text: cum hominibus operantibus iniquitatem, et non communicabo cum electis eorum.
verse_text: Ne simul trahas me cum peccatoribus, et cum operantibus iniquitatem ne perdas me;

text: Who so feareth the Lord, shall not feare nor be afraid, for hee is his hope.
verse_text: Spiritus timentium Deum quaeritur, et in respectu illius benedicetur.

text: Fons sapientiae verbum Dei in excelsis, et ingressus illius mandata aeterna.
verse_text: Scientia sapientis tamquam inundatio abundabit, et consilium illius sicut fons vitae permanet.

text: Praise no man before thou hearest him speake, for this is the triall of men.
verse_text: Sicut rusticatio de ligno ostendit fructum illius, sic verbum ex cogitatu cordis hominis.

text: Date gloriam Deo super Israel; magnificentia ejus et virtus ejus in nubibus.
verse_text: Dicat nunc domus Aaron: Quoniam in saeculum misericordia ejus.

text: Euerie shower, & dew blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Yse and snowes blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Olivam uberem, pulchram, fructiferam, speciosam, vocavit Dominus nomen tuum:
verse_text: Ego autem plantavi te vineam electam, omne semen verum:

text: Psalmus ipsi David. Misericordiam et judicium cantabo tibi, Domine; psallam,
verse_text: Psalmus ipsi David. Cantate Domino canticum novum, quia mirabilia fecit. Salvavit sibi dextera ejus, et brachium sanctum ejus.

text: Nubes et caligo in circuitu ejus; justitia et judicium correctio sedis ejus.
verse_text: Confessio et pulchritudo in conspectu ejus; sanctimonia et magnificentia in sanctificatione ejus.

text: Thou shalt hide them in the secrete of thy face from the disturbance of men.
verse_text: thou keepest them secretly in thy Tabernacle from the strife of tongues.

text: To him that rideth vpon ye most high heauens, which were from the beginning:
verse_text: extoll him that rideth vpon the heauens, by his Name Iah, and reioyce before him.

text: And let thy mercie come vpon me o Lord: thy saluation according to thy word.
verse_text: Heare my voice according vnto thy louing kindnesse: O Lord quicken me according to thy iudgement.

text: Much experience is the crown of old men, and the fear of God is their glory.
verse_text: A man of understanding is faithful to the law of God, and the law is faithful to him.

text: Shall they escape by iniquitie? in thine anger cast downe the people, O God.
verse_text: Destroy thou them, O God, let them fall by their owne counsels: cast them out in the multitude of their transgressions, for they haue rebelled against thee.

text: Let them be turned backe for a rewarde of their shame, which said, Aha, aha.
verse_text: Yea they opened their mouth wide against me, and saide, Aha, Aha, our eye hath seene it.

text: Benedicite, gelu et frigus, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, rores et pruina, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: The troubles of my heart are inlarged: O bring thou me out of my distresses.
verse_text: The tribulations of my hart are multiplied: deliuer me from my necessities.

text: The Lord vpholdeth all that fall, and lifteth vp all that are ready to fall.
verse_text: Though hee fall, he shall not be vtterly cast downe: for the Lord vpholdeth him with his hand.

text: My sonne, if thou come to serue the Lorde, prepare thy soule for temptation.
verse_text: Fili, accedens ad servitutem Dei sta in justitia et timore, et praepara animam tuam ad tentationem.

text: To feare the Lord, is fulnesse of wisedome, and filleth men with her fruits.
verse_text: Initium sapientiae timor Domini: et cum fidelibus in vulva concreatus est: cum electis feminis graditur, et cum justis et fidelibus agnoscitur.

text: Turne thee vnto me, and haue mercy vpon me: for I am desolate and afflicted.
verse_text: And hide not thy face from thy seruant, for I am in trouble: make haste and heare me.

text: Deliuer me out of the handes of my enemies, and from them that persecute me.
verse_text: deliuer me from them that hate me, and from the depthes of waters.

text: Benedices coronae anni benignitatis tuae, et campi tui replebuntur ubertate.
verse_text: Salvum fac populum tuum, Domine, et benedic haereditati tuae; et rege eos, et extolle illos usque in aeternum.

text: The Lord executeth righteousnesse: and iudgement for all that are oppressed.
verse_text: And the Kings power, that loueth iudgement: for thou hast prepared equitie: thou hast executed iudgement and iustice in Iaakob.

text: Seruants of our Lord blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Al workes of our Lord blesse ye our Lord, prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Protexisti me a conventu malignantium, a multitudine operantium iniquitatem.
verse_text: Abscondes eos in abscondito faciei tuae a conturbatione hominum; proteges eos in tabernaculo tuo, a contradictione linguarum.

text: So the kingdome was diuided, and out of Ephraim ruled a rebellious kingdome.
verse_text: et inclinasti femora tua mulieribus: potestatem habuisti in corpore tuo.

text: But God shall shoote at them: with an arrowe, sodenly shall they be wounded.
verse_text: So they shall make their owne tongue to fall vpon themselues: all that see them, shall flee away.

text: His goods shall be established, and the congregati shall declare his almes.
verse_text: Ideo stabilita sunt bona illius in Domino, et eleemosynas illius enarrabit omnis ecclesia sanctorum.

text: Watching care will not let a man slumber, as a sore disease breaketh sleepe.
