text: Sende him to labour that hee be not idle: for idlenesse teacheth much euill.
verse_text: Jugum et lorum curvant collum durum, et servum inclinant operationes assiduae.

text: Dixi iniquis: Nolite inique agere: et delinquentibus: Nolite exaltare cornu:
verse_text: nolite extollere in altum cornu vestrum; nolite loqui adversus Deum iniquitatem.

text: For the Lord hath made all things, and to the godly hath hee giuen wisedome.
verse_text: Benedicentes Dominum, exaltate illum quantum potestis: major enim est omni laude.

text: Beholde, I was borne in iniquitie, and in sinne hath my mother conceiued me.
verse_text: Behold, he trauelleth with iniquitie, and hath conceiued mischiefe, and brought forth falshood.

text: Heare ye the worde of the Lord that he speaketh vnto you, O house of Israel.
verse_text: Heare ye the word of the Lord, O house of Iacob, and all the families of the house of Israel.

text: Ecce quasi aquila ascendet, et avolabit, et expandet alas suas super Bosran:
verse_text: vox eorum quasi mare sonabit, et super equos ascendent, sicut vir paratus ad praelium contra te, filia Babylon.

text: Canticum graduum. Saepe expugnaverunt me a juventute mea, dicat nunc Israel;
verse_text: saepe expugnaverunt me a juventute mea: etenim non potuerunt mihi.

text: Canticum graduum. Beati omnes qui timent Dominum, qui ambulant in viis ejus.
verse_text: Psalmus David. Exsultate, justi, in Domino; rectos decet collaudatio.

text: Nihil proficiet inimicus in eo, et filius iniquitatis non apponet nocere ei.
verse_text: Observabit peccator justum, et stridebit super eum dentibus suis.

text: Goe not in a way wherein thou maiest fall, and stumble not among the stones.
verse_text: Qui timent Dominum invenient judicium justum, et justitias quasi lumen accendent.

text: Repleatur os meum laude, ut cantem gloriam tuam, tota die magnitudinem tuam.
verse_text: ut cantet tibi gloria mea, et non compungar. Domine Deus meus, in aeternum confitebor tibi.

text: And say vnto the house of the King of Iudah, Heare ye the worde of the Lord.
verse_text: Thus said the Lord, Goe downe to the house of the King of Iudah, and speake there this thing,

text: Then the people fell downe, and worshipped God, and cryed vnto God, saying,
verse_text: Cum vero Dominus Deus noster dederit hanc libertatem servis suis, sit et tecum Deus in medio nostri: ut sicut placuerit tibi, ita cum tuis omnibus converseris nobiscum.

text: In finem. Psalmus David in rememorationem, quod salvum fecerit eum Dominus.
verse_text: Psalmus David, in rememorationem de sabbato.

text: quoniam humiliasti nos in loco afflictionis, et cooperuit nos umbra mortis.
verse_text: Quoniam humiliata est in pulvere anima nostra; conglutinatus est in terra venter noster.

text: Blessed are they that saw thee, and slept in loue, for we shal surely liue.
verse_text: Beati sunt qui te viderunt, et in amicitia tua decorati sunt.

text: How shall we magnifie Zorobabel? euen he was as a signet on the right hand.
verse_text: Nam commemoratus est inimicorum in imbre, benefacere illis qui ostenderunt rectas vias.

text: That I may shew foorth all thy prayse in the gates of the daughter of Sion:
verse_text: That I may see the good of thy chosen, that I may reioyce in the gladnesse of thy nation:

text: Deus, docuisti me a juventute mea; et usque nunc pronuntiabo mirabilia tua.
verse_text: Confitebor tibi, quia terribiliter magnificatus es; mirabilia opera tua, et anima mea cognoscit nimis.

text: Great is the Lord that made it, and at his commandement it runneth hastily.
verse_text: Magnus Dominus qui fecit illum, et in sermonibus ejus festinavit iter.

text: Blesse our Lord al ye foules of heauen: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Al things that spring in the earth blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: And they passed from nation into nation, & from kingdom to an other people.
verse_text: And walked about from nation to nation, from one kingdome to another people,

text: I haue hated many things, but nothing like him, for the Lord will hate him.
verse_text: denudare autem amici mysteria, desperatio est animae infelicis.

text: Daniel autem factus est magnus in conspectu populi a die illa, et deinceps.
verse_text: Erat autem Daniel conviva regis, et honoratus super omnes amicos ejus.

text: quantum distat ortus ab occidente, longe fecit a nobis iniquitates nostras.
verse_text: Leva manus tuas in superbias eorum in finem: quanta malignatus est inimicus in sancto !

text: Splendidum cor et bonum in epulis est: epulae enim illius diligenter fiunt.
verse_text: decor enim vitae est in illa, et vincula illius alligatura salutaris.

text: Sing vnto him, sing prayse vnto him, and talke of all his wonderous workes.
verse_text: Sing vnto God, and sing prayses vnto his name: exalt him that rideth vpon the heauens, in his Name Iah, and reioyce before him.

text: Blessed are they that keepe iudgement, and doe righteousnesse at all times.
verse_text: Blessed are they that keepe his testimonies: and that seeke him with the whole heart.

text: In filia non avertente se, firma custodiam, ne inventa occasione utatur se.
verse_text: nequando polluatur in virginitate sua, et in paternis suis gravida inveniatur: ne forte cum viro commorata transgrediatur, aut certe sterilis efficiatur.

text: Paulominus consummaverunt me in terra; ego autem non dereliqui mandata tua.
verse_text: Annuntiavi justitiam tuam in ecclesia magna; ecce labia mea non prohibebo: Domine, tu scisti.

text: Be in peace with many: neuerthelesse haue but one counseller of a thousand.
verse_text: Multi pacifici sint tibi: et consiliarius sit tibi unus de mille.

text: An hastie contention kindleth a fire, and an hasty fighting sheddeth blood.
verse_text: Homo enim iracundus incendit litem, et vir peccator turbabit amicos, et in medio pacem habentium immittet inimicitiam.

text: Secundum enim magnitudinem ipsius, sic et misericordia illius cum ipso est.
verse_text: Misericordia enim et ira est cum illo: potens exoratio, et effundens iram.

text: I wil chaunte to our Lord in my life: I wil sing to my God as long as I am.
verse_text: but I haue hoped in thy mercie. My hart shal reioyce in thy saluation: I wil sing to our Lord which geueth me good thinges: and I wil sing to the name of our Lord most high.

text: Ne avertas faciem a proximo tuo, et ab auferendo partem et non restituendo.
verse_text: Et sicut qui dimittit avem de manu sua, sic dereliquisti proximum tuum, et non eum capies.

text: dereliquit me virtus mea, et lumen oculorum meorum, et ipsum non est mecum.
verse_text: periit fuga a me, et non est qui requirat animam meam.

text: O God thou knowest my foolishnes: and mine offences are not hide from thee.
verse_text: Thou hast knowen my reproofe and my shame, and my dishonour: all mine aduersaries are before thee.

text: Enuy not the glory of a sinner: for thou knowest not what shall be his end.
verse_text: Speciem mulieris alienae multi admirati, reprobi facti sunt: colloquium enim illius quasi ignis exardescit.

text: The idoles of the Gentiles are siluer, and gold, the workes of mens handes.
verse_text: Their idoles are siluer and gold: the worke of mens hands.

text: O Ierusalem, wash thine heart from wickednesse, that thou mayest bee saued:
verse_text: woe vnto thee, O Ierusalem, wilt thou not bee made cleane?

text: Benedictus Deus, qui non amovit orationem meam, et misericordiam suam a me.
verse_text: Exaudi, Deus, orationem meam, et ne despexeris deprecationem meam:

text: That thy beloued may be deliuered; saue with thy right hand, and heare mee.
verse_text: That thy beloued may be deliuered: helpe with thy right hand and heare me.

text: Tristitiam non des animae tuae, et non affligas temetipsum in consilio tuo.
verse_text: Miserere animae tuae placens Deo, et contine: congrega cor tuum in sanctitate ejus, et tristitiam longe repelle a te.

text: My soule hath fainted for thy saluation: and I haue much hoped in thy word.
verse_text: Mine eies haue fayled after thy saluation: and for the word of thy iustice.

text: O wicked imagination, whence camest thou in to couer the earth with deceit?
verse_text: O praesumptio nequissima, unde create es cooperire aridam malitia et dolositate illius?

text: It is great glory to follow the Lord, & to be receiued of him is long life.
verse_text: et non cognovit quoniam oculi Domini multo plus lucidiores sunt super solem, circumspicientes omnes vias hominum, et profundum abyssi, et hominum corda, intuentes in absconditas partes.

text: Ne oblecteris in turbis nec in modicis: assidua enim est commissio illorum.
verse_text: Communionem mortis scito, quoniam in medio laqueorum ingredieris, et super dolentium arma ambulabis.

text: Heare mee your father, O children, and doe thereafter, that ye may be safe.
verse_text: Filii sapientiae ecclesia justorum, et natio illorum obedientia et dilectio.

text: Cor durum habebit male in novissimo, et qui amat periculum in illo peribit.
verse_text: Qui docet filium suum in zelum mittit inimicum, et in medio amicorum gloriabitur in illo.

text: Mine helpe commeth from the Lord, which hath made the heauen and the earth.
verse_text: Which made heauen and earth, the sea, and all that therein is: which keepeth his fidelitie for euer:

text: He turned the riuers into a desert: and the issues of waters into drinesse.
verse_text: He brought floods also out of the stonie rocke; so that hee made the waters to descend like the riuers.

text: Noli citatus esse in lingua tua, et inutilis, et remissus in operibus tuis.
verse_text: Nominatio vero Dei non sit assidua in ore tuo, et nominibus sanctorum non admiscearis, quoniam non erit immunis ab eis.

text: I came out of the mouth of the most High, and couered the earth as a cloud.
verse_text: et in medio populi sui exaltabitur, et in plenitudine sancta admirabitur,

text: Generatio et generatio laudabit opera tua, et potentiam tuam pronuntiabunt.
verse_text: Scribantur haec in generatione altera, et populus qui creabitur laudabit Dominum.

text: Relinque proximo tuo nocenti te, et tunc deprecanti tibi peccata solventur.
verse_text: et si humiliatus vadat curvus, adjice animum tuum, et custodi te ab illo.

text: Et cadent interfecti in terra Chaldaeorum, et vulnerati in regionibus ejus.
verse_text: Ideo cadent juvenes ejus in plateis ejus, et omnes viri praelii conticescent in die illa, ait Dominus exercituum.

text: Glorie, and riches in his house: and his iustice abideth for euer and euer.
verse_text: His worke is honourable and glorious: and his righteousnesse endureth for euer.

text: Benedicite, filii hominum, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, sancti et humiles corde, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: All that passe by the way; spoile him: hee is a reproach to his neighbours.
verse_text: We are become a reproach to our neighbours: a scorne and derision to them that are round about vs.

text: Praise the Lord, ye house of Leui: ye that feare the Lord, praise the Lord.
verse_text: Praise ye the Lord. Praise, O ye seruants of the Lord, prayse the Name of the Lord.

text: The disposition of a liar is dishonourable, and his shame is euer with him.
verse_text: Opprobrium nequam in homine mendacium: et in ore indisciplinatorum assidue erit.

text: Behold, I haue longed after thy precepts: quicken me in thy righteousnesse.
verse_text: Behold I haue coueted thy commandments: in thine equitie quicken me.

text: The whordome of a woman may be knowen in her haughtie lookes, and eye lids.
verse_text: In muliere zelotypa flagellum linguae, omnibus communicans.

text: Audi, fili, et accipe consilium intellectus, et ne abjicias consilium meum.
verse_text: Audi me, fili, et disce disciplinam sensus, et in verbis meis attende in corde tuo:

text: Euen an heritage vnto Israel his seruant: for his mercie endureth for euer:
verse_text: And he gaue their land for an inheritance: because his mercie is for euer.

text: Non inveniemus Danieli huic aliquam occasionem, nisi forte in lege Dei sui.
verse_text: Inveni hominem de filiis transmigrationis Juda, qui solutionem regi annuntiet.

text: Quia factus sum sicut uter in pruina; justificationes tuas non sum oblitus.
verse_text: Funes peccatorum circumplexi sunt me, et legem tuam non sum oblitus.

text: Humilia valde spiritum tuum, quoniam vindicta carnis impii ignis et vermis.
verse_text: Miserere animae tuae placens Deo, et contine: congrega cor tuum in sanctitate ejus, et tristitiam longe repelle a te.

text: Non contendas cum viro locuplete, ne forte contra te constituat litem tibi:
verse_text: Non omni homini cor tuum manifestes, ne forte inferat tibi gratiam falsam, et convicietur tibi.

text: Cito fecerunt; obliti sunt operum ejus: et non sustinuerunt consilium ejus.
verse_text: Et tentaverunt, et exacerbaverunt Deum excelsum, et testimonia ejus non custodierunt.

text: I haue not sate with vaine persons, neither will I goe in with dissemblers.
verse_text: Gather not my soule with sinners, nor my life with bloody men.

text: Thy soule couered the whole earth, and thou filledst it with dark parables.
verse_text: Salomon imperavit in diebus pacis, cui subjecit Deus omnes hostes, ut conderet domum in nomine suo, et pararet sanctitatem in sempiternum. Quemadmodum eruditus es in juventute tua,

text: Deus, cum egredereris in conspectu populi tui, cum pertransires in deserto,
verse_text: Quam magna multitudo dulcedinis tuae, Domine, quam abscondisti timentibus te; perfecisti eis qui sperant in te in conspectu filiorum hominum !

text: Behold I will send, and take Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon my servant:
verse_text: as I delivered Sedecias king of Juda into the hand of Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon his enemy, and that sought his life.

text: Priests of our Lord blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Al spirits of God blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Let them, that feare the Lord, nowe say, That his mercie endureth for euer.
verse_text: Let Israel now say that he is good: that his mercie is for euer.

text: All iniquitie is as a two edged sword, the wounds whereof cannot be healed.
verse_text: Dentes leonis dentes ejus, interficientes animas hominum.

text: Regina quoque Esther nullum alium vocavit ad convivium cum rege praeter me:
verse_text: Aman quoque surrexit ut rogaret Esther reginam pro anima sua:

text: The first man knew her not perfectly: no more shall the last finde her out.
verse_text: Memoria mea in generatione saeculorum.

text: Behold I will send upon them the sword, and the famine, and the pestilence:
verse_text: but I will consume them by the sword, and by the famine, and by the pestilence.

text: Benedicite, angeli Domini, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, omnes virtutes Domini, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Benedicite, stellae caeli, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, glacies et nives, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: And hath rescued vs from our oppressours: for his mercie endureth for euer:
verse_text: Which smote great Kings: for his mercie endureth for euer:

text: Benedicite, noctes et dies, Domino laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, rores et pruina, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Of these things be not thou ashamed, and accept no person to sinne thereby.
verse_text: Non duplices sermonem auditus de revelatione sermonis absconditi: et eris vere sine confusione, et invenies gratiam in conspectu omnium hominum. Ne pro his omnibus confundaris, et ne accipias personam ut delinquas:

text: A whisperer defileth his owne soule, and is hated wheresoeuer hee dwelleth.
verse_text: Labia imprudentium stulta narrabunt; verba autem prudentium statera ponderabuntur.

text: Ecce ego ad te, mons pestifer, ait Dominus, qui corrumpis universam terram:
verse_text: cum exaltaveris quasi aquila nidum tuum, inde detraham te, dicit Dominus.

text: Ipsi vero in vanum quaesierunt animam meam: introibunt in inferiora terrae;
verse_text: nequando dicat inimicus meus: Praevalui adversus eum. Qui tribulant me exsultabunt si motus fuero;

text: Et sicut abominatio est superbo humilitas, sic et execratio divitis pauper.
verse_text: super furem enim est confusio et poenitentia, et denotatio pessima super bilinguem: susurratori autem odium, et inimicitia, et contumelia.

text: Thou crownest ye yeere with thy goodnesse, and thy steppes droppe fatnesse.
verse_text: For thou preuentest him with the blessings of goodnesse: thou settest a Crowne of pure gold on his head.

text: Which my lippes haue promised, and my mouth hath spoken in mine affliction.
verse_text: My lippes will reioyce when I sing vnto thee, and my soule, which thou hast deliuered.

text: Enuy not the glory of a sinner: for thou knowest not what shall be his end.
verse_text: Be not anxious for goods unjustly gotten: for they shall not profit thee in the day of calamity and revenge.

text: Omne execramentum erroris odit Dominus, et non erit amabile timentibus eum.
verse_text: quoniam ab eo qui fecit illum recessit cor ejus, quoniam initium omnis peccati est superbia. Qui tenuerit illam adimplebitur maledictis, et subvertet eum in finem.

text: Come vnto her with thy whole heart, and keepe her wayes with all thy power.
verse_text: Subjice humerum tuum, et porta illam, et ne acedieris vinculis ejus.

text: Non accipiet Dominus personam in pauperem, et deprecationem laesi exaudiet.
verse_text: Da misericordi, et ne suscipias peccatorem: et impiis et peccatoribus reddet vindictam, custodiens eos in diem vindictae.

text: misericordiam autem meam non dispergam ab eo, neque nocebo in veritate mea,
verse_text: Benedictus Deus, qui non amovit orationem meam, et misericordiam suam a me.

text: Qui retribuunt mala pro bonis detrahebant mihi, quoniam sequebar bonitatem.
verse_text: Si non humiliter sentiebam, sed exaltavi animam meam: sicut ablactatus est super matre sua, ita retributio in anima mea.

text: The workes of all flesh are before him, & nothing can be hid from his eyes.
verse_text: Florete flores quasi lilium: et date odorem, et frondete in gratiam: et collaudate canticum, et benedicite Dominum in operibus suis.

text: Et dabo vobis pastores juxta cor meum, et pascent vos scientia et doctrina.
verse_text: Ecce ego obducam eis cicatricem et sanitatem, et curabo eos, et revelabo illis deprecationem pacis et veritatis.

text: Ne perdas cum impiis, Deus, animam meam, et cum viris sanguinum vitam meam:
verse_text: Libera me de sanguinibus, Deus, Deus salutis meae, et exsultabit lingua mea justitiam tuam.

text: Spiritus plenus ex his veniet mihi, et nunc ego loquar judicia mea cum eis.
verse_text: Propterea haec dicit Dominus exercituum: Ecce ego conflabo, et probabo eos: quid enim aliud faciam a facie filiae populi mei?

text: Deale with thy seruant according to thy mercie, and teache me thy statutes.
verse_text: Heare my voice according vnto thy louing kindnesse: O Lord quicken me according to thy iudgement.

text: I wil praise the name of God with canticle: and wil magnifie him in prayse.
verse_text: I wil confesse to our Lord excedingly with my mouth: and in the middes of manie I wil prayse him:

text: Galaad is mine, and Manasses is mine: and Ephraim the strength of my heade.
verse_text: Gilead is mine, Manasseh is mine, Ephraim also is the strength of mine head: Iudah is my Lawgiuer.

text: Ye mountaines leaped as rammes, and ye litle hilles as the lambes of shepe.
verse_text: Yee mountaines, that yee skipped like rammes: and yee little hilles like lambes?

text: They haue eares, and shal not heare: they haue nosthrels and shal not smel.
verse_text: They haue eares, but they heare not: noses haue they, but they smell not.

text: Tulitque rex annulum, quem ab Aman recipi jusserat, et tradidit Mardochaeo.
verse_text: Aman quippe interius atrium domus regiae intraverat, ut suggereret regi, et juberet Mardochaeum affigi patibulo, quod ei fuerat praeparatum.

text: And there was none that gaue her an ill worde; for shee feared God greatly.
verse_text: Et erat haec in omnibus famosissima, quoniam timebat Dominum valde, nec erat qui loqueretur de illa verbum malum.

text: for I will consume them by the sword, and by famine, and by the pestilence.
verse_text: And I will send among them the sword, and the famine, and the pestilence:

text: As neere as thou canst, ghesse at thy neighbour, and consult with the wise.
verse_text: Ne derelinquas amicum antiquum: novus enim non erit similis illi.

text: I was exalted like a cedar in Libanus, and as a cypress tree on mount Sion.
verse_text: I was exalted like a palme tree in Engaddi, and as a rose-plant in Iericho, as a faire oliue tree in a pleasant fielde, and grew vp as a planetree by the water.

text: Ego mater pulchrae dilectionis, et timoris, et agnitionis, et sanctae spei.
verse_text: Timor Domini gloria, et gloriatio, et laetitia, et corona exsultationis.

text: Ornamentum aureum prudenti doctrina, et quasi brachiale in brachio dextro.
verse_text: Gemmula carbunculi in ornamento auri, et comparatio musicorum in convivio vini.

text: Exortum est in tenebris lumen rectis: misericors, et miserator, et justus.
verse_text: Lex Domini immaculata, convertens animas; testimonium Domini fidele, sapientiam praestans parvulis.

text: But foolish men shall not attaine vnto her, and sinners shall not see her.
verse_text: Homines stulti non apprehendent illam, et homines sensati obviabunt illi. Homines stulti non videbunt eam: longe enim abest a superbia et dolo.

text: Gratia mulieris sedulae delectabit virum suum, et ossa illius impinguabit.
verse_text: Medicina omnium in festinatione nebulae: et ros obvians ab ardore venienti humilem efficiet eum.

text: For thy mercie is great vnto the heauens, and thy trueth vnto the cloudes.
verse_text: Because thy mercie is magnified euen to the heauens, and thy truth euen to the cloudes.

text: There take thy pastime, & do what thou wilt: but sinne not by proud speach
verse_text: In multis esto quasi inscius, et audi tacens simul et quaerens.

text: But feare not thou, O my seruant Iaakob, and be not thou afraid, O Israel:
verse_text: Feare thou not, O Iaakob my seruant, saith the Lord:

text: Trouble and anguish are come vpon me: yet are thy commandements my delite.
verse_text: I wil be glad and reioyce in thy mercie: for thou hast seene my trouble: thou hast knowen my soule in aduersities,

text: The idols of the gentiles are siluer, and gold, the workes of mens handes.
verse_text: Their idoles are siluer and gold: the worke of mens hands.

text: O thou daughter dwelling in Egypt, make thee geare to goe into captiuitie:
verse_text: Goe vp into Gilead, and take balme, O virgine, the daughter of Egypt:

text: Confesse ye to our Lord because he is good: becaus his mercie is for euer.
verse_text: Alleluia. CONFESSE ye to our Lord because he is good because his mercie is for euer.

text: et Deus caeli regnum, et fortitudinem, et imperium, et gloriam dedit tibi:
verse_text: Regnum autem, et potestas, et magnitudo regni, quae est subter omne caelum, detur populo sanctorum Altissimi:

text: Yea they turned backe and tempted God: and limited the holy one of Israel.
verse_text: And they tempted, and exasperated God the highest, and they kept not his testimonies.

text: That thy beloued may be deliuered: helpe with thy right hand and heare me.
verse_text: That thy beloued may be deliuered; saue with thy right hand, and heare mee.

text: goeth by it shalbe astonished, and shall hisse at all the plagues thereof,
verse_text: euery one that goeth by Babylon shall be astonished, and hisse at all her plagues.

text: Ecce ego adducam super vos gentem de longinquo, domus Israel, ait Dominus:
verse_text: Ecce ego ad te, mons pestifer, ait Dominus, qui corrumpis universam terram:

text: And he gaue their land for an inheritance: because his mercie is for euer.
verse_text: Euen an heritage vnto Israel his seruant: for his mercie endureth for euer:

text: Exaudi, Domine, vocem meam, qua clamavi ad te; miserere mei, et exaudi me.
verse_text: Domine, exaudi orationem meam, et clamor meus ad te veniat.

text: He made an euerlasting couenant with them, and shewed them his iudgements.
verse_text: Et mandavit illis unicuique de proximo suo.

text: Then King Ahashuerosh answered, and said vnto the Queene Ester, Who is he?
verse_text: And hee wrote in the King Ahashuerosh name, and sealed it with the Kings ring:

text: Thus will I magnifie thee all my life, and lift vp mine hands in thy name.
verse_text: To the end that my glory may sing prayse to thee, and not be silent: O Lord my God, I will giue thankes vnto thee for euer.

text: To him that by wisedome made the heauens: for his mercy endureth for euer.
verse_text: Which hath stretched out the earth vpon the waters: for his mercie endureth for euer:

text: For my dayes are consumed like smoke: and my bones are burnt as an hearth.
verse_text: For my life is spent with griefe, and my yeeres with sighing: my strength faileth, because of mine iniquitie, and my bones are consumed.

text: Qui credit Deo attendit mandatis: et qui confidit in illo non minorabitur.
verse_text: Qui audit illam judicabit gentes: et qui intuetur illam permanebit confidens.

text: Ipse invocabit me: Pater meus es tu, Deus meus, et susceptor salutis meae.
verse_text: Dicet Domino: Susceptor meus es tu, et refugium meum; Deus meus, sperabo in eum.

text: Be not surety aboue thy power: for if thou be surety, take care to pay it.
verse_text: Non incendas carbones peccatorum arguens eos, et ne incendaris flamma ignis peccatorum illorum.

text: Dixit ergo Sedecias ad Jeremiam: Nullus sciat verba haec, et non morieris.
verse_text: Et locutus est Jeremias propheta ad Sedeciam regem Juda universa verba haec in Jerusalem.

text: The meeke will he guide in iudgement: and the meeke will he teach his way.
verse_text: For the Lord taketh pleasure in his people: hee will beautifie the meeke with saluation.

text: Benedicite, servi Domini, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.
verse_text: Benedicite, omnes spiritus Dei, Domino: laudate et superexaltate eum in saecula.

text: Starres of heauens blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Sonnes of men blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: What is man, and whereto serueth he? what is his good, & what is his euil?
verse_text: Numerus dierum hominum, ut multum centum anni, quasi gutta aquae maris deputati sunt: et sicut calculus arenae, sic exigui anni in die aevi.

text: et redemit nos ab inimicis nostris, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: et eduxit Israel per medium ejus, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus;

text: ego Daniel territus sum in his, et visiones capitis mei conturbaverunt me.
verse_text: Ego Daniel multum cogitationibus meis conturbabar, et facies mea mutata est in me:

text: Mementote mirabilium ejus quae fecit; prodigia ejus, et judicia oris ejus:
verse_text: Non sunt occultata a filiis eorum in generatione altera, narrantes laudes Domini et virtutes ejus, et mirabilia ejus quae fecit.

text: they shall not be lamented, and they shall not be gathered up, nor buried:
verse_text: They shal die of grieuous deaths, they shall not bee lamented, neither shall they be buried:

text: Nolite audire verba prophetarum vestrorum, qui prophetant vobis, dicentes:
verse_text: ubi sunt prophetae vestri, qui prophetabant vobis, et dicebant:

text: That thy beloued may be deliuered, helpe with thy right hand and heare me.
verse_text: That thy beloued may bee deliuered: saue with thy right hand, and answere me.

text: The Lord is mercifull and gracious: slow to anger, and plenteous in mercy.
verse_text: But thou, O Lord, art a God full of compassion, and gracious: long suffering, and plenteous in mercy and trueth.

text: Tituli inscriptio, ipsi David. Conserva me, Domine, quoniam speravi in te.
verse_text: Ipsi David. Benedic, anima mea, Domino: Domine Deus meus, magnificatus es vehementer. Confessionem et decorem induisti,

text: quia propitiabor iniquitati eorum, et peccati eorum non memorabor amplius.
verse_text: Nunc recordabitur iniquitatum eorum, et visitabit peccata eorum.

text: Beware thou slide not by it, lest thou fall before him that lieth in wait.
verse_text: Perseverantia illius non permanebit, sed obtinebit vias injustorum, et in flamma sua non comburet justos.

text: quia ecce ego convocabo omnes cognationes regnorum aquilonis, ait Dominus:
verse_text: quia ab aquilone venient ei praedones, ait Dominus.

text: Noli avidus esse in omni epulatione, et non te effundas super omnem escam:
verse_text: Et si coactus fueris in edendo multum, surge e medio, evome, et refrigerabit te, et non adduces corpori tuo infirmitatem.

text: O Israel, trust thou in the Lord: for he is their helpe and their shielde.
verse_text: Ye that feare the Lord trust in the Lord: he is their helpe and their shield.

text: Blesse our Lord ye Angels of our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Sonnes of men blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Minimum pro magno placeat tibi, et improperium peregrinationis non audies.
verse_text: Attende in illis, ne forte cadas, et adducas animae tuae inhonorationem:

text: I sought the Lord, and hee heard me; and deliuered mee from all my feares.
verse_text: This poore man cryed, and the Lord heard him, and saued him out of all his troubles.

text: Dominus in caelo paravit sedem suam, et regnum ipsius omnibus dominabitur.
verse_text: Dominus diluvium inhabitare facit, et sedebit Dominus rex in aeternum.

text: And when this people, or the prophet, or a priest shall aske thee, saying;
verse_text: And when thou shalt tell this people all these words, and they shall say to thee:

text: The law of thy mouth is good vnto me, aboue thousands of gold, and siluer.
verse_text: More to bee desired are they then gold, yea, then much fine gold: sweeter also then hony, and the hony combe.

text: et dedit terram eorum haereditatem, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus;
verse_text: Qui dat escam omni carni, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: Thou shalt hide them in the secret of thy presence, from the pride of man:
verse_text: thou keepest them secretly in thy Tabernacle from the strife of tongues.

text: Laetati sumus pro diebus quibus nos humiliasti; annis quibus vidimus mala.
verse_text: nonne Deus requiret ista? ipse enim novit abscondita cordis. Quoniam propter te mortificamur tota die; aestimati sumus sicut oves occisionis.

text: Obmutui, et humiliatus sum, et silui a bonis; et dolor meus renovatus est.
verse_text: Pauper sum ego, et in laboribus a juventute mea; exaltatus autem, humiliatus sum et conturbatus.

text: Behold, I was shapen in iniquitie: and in sinne did my mother conceiue me.
verse_text: Behold, he trauelleth with iniquitie, and hath conceiued mischiefe, and brought forth falshood.

text: The law of thy mouth is better vnto me: then thousands of gold and siluer.
verse_text: I haue reioyced in the way of thy testimonies: as much as in all riches.

text: Ergo sine causa justificavi cor meum, et lavi inter innocentes manus meas,
verse_text: Judica me, Domine, quoniam ego in innocentia mea ingressus sum, et in Domino sperans non infirmabor.

text: Cogitaverunt et locuti sunt nequitiam; iniquitatem in excelso locuti sunt.
verse_text: Vana locuti sunt unusquisque ad proximum suum; labia dolosa, in corde et corde locuti sunt.

text: Gustate et videte quoniam suavis est Dominus; beatus vir qui sperat in eo.
verse_text: Laudate Dominum, quia bonus Dominus; psallite nomini ejus, quoniam suave.

text: Secundum misericordiam tuam vivifica me, et custodiam testimonia oris tui.
verse_text: Illustra faciem tuam super servum tuum; salvum me fac in misericordia tua.

text: For all the gods of the nations are idoles: but the Lord made the heauens.
verse_text: Because al the goddes of the Gentiles are diuels, but our Lord made the heauens.

text: Et erit Chaldaea in praedam: omnes vastantes eam replebuntur, ait Dominus.
verse_text: Et veniet praedo ad omnem urbem, et urbs nulla salvabitur: et peribunt valles, et dissipabuntur campestria, quoniam dixit Dominus:

text: Ego autem cantabo fortitudinem tuam, et exsultabo mane misericordiam tuam:
verse_text: Exsultabo, et laetabor in misericordia tua, quoniam respexisti humilitatem meam;

text: A mari enim abundavit cogitatio ejus, et consilium illius ab abysso magna.
verse_text: Abyssum et cor hominum investigavit, et in astutia eorum excogitavit.

text: Because I haue knowne that our Lord is great, and our God aboue al goddes.
verse_text: Because our Lord is high, terrible; a great king ouer al the earth.

text: in manu potenti et brachio excelso, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: haereditatem Israel, servo suo, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: Domine, Dominus noster, quam admirabile est nomen tuum in universa terra !
verse_text: quoniam magnificasti super omne, nomen sanctum tuum.

text: Euery day wil I blesse thee: and I will praise thy Name for euer and euer.
verse_text: Therefore shall my tongue praise thee and not cease: O Lord my God, I will giue thankes vnto thee for euer.

text: ne forte cum viro commorata transgrediatur, aut certe sterilis efficiatur.
verse_text: nequando polluatur in virginitate sua, et in paternis suis gravida inveniatur:

text: Omni homini noli intendere in specie, et in medio mulierum noli commorari:
verse_text: Amico et inimico noli narrare sensum tuum: et si est tibi delictum, noli denudare:

text: In manus tuas commendo spiritum meum; redemisti me, Domine Deus veritatis.
verse_text: Quia ad te, Domine, Domine, oculi mei; in te speravi, non auferas animam meam.

text: Illustra faciem tuam super servum tuum; salvum me fac in misericordia tua.
verse_text: Convertere, Domine, et eripe animam meam; salvum me fac propter misericordiam tuam.

text: in sterquilinium super faciem terrae erunt, et gladio et fame consumentur:

text: Fiant tamquam pulvis ante faciem venti, et angelus Domini coarctans eos.

text: qui posuit animam meam ad vitam, et non dedit in commotionem pedes meos.

text: My dayes are like a shadow, that declineth: & I am withered like grasse.

text: Viros potentes gyrans migrare fecit, et vagati sunt in gentibus alienis.

text: Dominus illuminat caecos. Dominus erigit elisos; Dominus diligit justos.
verse_text: Qui custodit veritatem in saeculum; facit judicium injuriam patientibus; dat escam esurientibus. Dominus solvit compeditos;

text: et deduxit eos in spe, et non timuerunt, et inimicos eorum operuit mare.

text: Magnus Dominus, et laudabilis nimis, et magnitudinis ejus non est finis.
verse_text: Quoniam magnus Dominus, et laudabilis nimis: terribilis est super omnes deos.

text: Res Vide humilitatem meam, et eripe me, quia legem tuam non sum oblitus.
verse_text: Ego autem in innocentia mea ingressus sum; redime me, et miserere mei.

text: Faciem tuam illumina super servum tuum, et doce me justificationes tuas.

text: My soule hath cleaued to the pauement: quicken me according to thy word.
verse_text: My soule hath slumbered for tediousnes: confirme me in thy wordes.

text: cum omni carne, ab homine usque ad pecus, et super peccatores septuplum.

text: et statuit illud Jacob in praeceptum, et Israel in testamentum aeternum,

text: Concerning propitiation, bee not without feare to adde sinne vnto sinne.

text: O God, my heart is fixed: I will sing & giue praise, euen with my glory.

text: Ab omnibus iniquitatibus meis erue me: opprobrium insipienti dedisti me.

text: Thou crownest the yeere with thy goodnesse; and thy paths drop fatnesse.

text: When all is safe, he awaketh, and marueileth that the feare was nothing.

text: For he heard and obserued thee, and when time commeth he will hate thee.

text: no man shall dwell there, neither shall the sonnes of men remaine in it.

text: For she is farre from pride, and men that are liers cannot remember her.

text: Faile not to bee with them that weepe, and mourne with them that mourne.

text: et nunc quare non increpasti Jeremiam Anathothiten, qui prophetat vobis?

text: Prayse our God, ye people, and make the voyce of his prayse to be heard.

text: Beside this he gaue them knowledge, and the law of life for an heritage.

text: And these are the words that the Lord hath spoken to Israel and to Juda:

text: for I am mercifull, saith the Lord, and I will not keepe anger for euer.
verse_text: for I haue taken my peace, from this people, saith the Lord, euen mercy and compassion.

text: Duo genera abundant in peccatis, et tertium adducit iram et perditionem.
verse_text: quoniam ab eo qui fecit illum recessit cor ejus, quoniam initium omnis peccati est superbia. Qui tenuerit illam adimplebitur maledictis, et subvertet eum in finem.

text: When one prayeth, and another curseth, whose voice will the Lorde heare?
verse_text: Qui offert sacrificium ex substantia pauperum, quasi qui victimat filium in conspectu patris sui.

text: quia ego consumam cunctas gentes ad quas ejeci te, te vero non consumam:

text: I will wash mine handes in innocencie, O Lord, and compasse thine altar,

text: O Lord God of hostes, heare my prayer: giue eare, O God of Iacob. Selah.
verse_text: Euen thou, O Lord God of hostes, O God of Israel awake to visit all the heathen, and be not merciful vnto all that transgresse maliciously. Selah.

text: Dicat nunc Israel: Quoniam bonus, quoniam in saeculum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: Dicant nunc qui timent Dominum: Quoniam in saeculum misericordia ejus.

text: et tibi, Domine, misericordia: quia tu reddes unicuique juxta opera sua.
verse_text: Et tu, Domine, Domine, fac mecum propter nomen tuum, quia suavis est misericordia tua.

text: When they were but a few men in number: yea very few, & strangers in it.
verse_text: Albeit they were fewe in nomber, yea, very fewe, and strangers in the land,

text: Which remembred vs in our base estate: for his mercie endureth for euer:
verse_text: And slewe mightie Kings: for his mercie endureth for euer:

text: then said I; Behold I come In the head of the booke it is written of me,
verse_text: Then sayd I, Loe, I come: in the volume of the booke it is written of me:

text: To execute vengeance vpon the heathen, and corrections among the people:
verse_text: To doereuenge in the nations: chastisements among the peoples.

text: quae distinxerunt labia mea: et locutum est os meum in tribulatione mea.

text: Intret postulatio mea in conspectu tuo; secundum eloquium tuum eripe me.

text: Let them now that feare the Lord, say: that his mercy endureth for euer.

text: His blessing couered the dry land as a riuer, and watered it as a flood.

text: it deuoured and brake in pieces and stamped the residue vnder his feete:

text: The idoles of the heathen are siluer and golde: the worke of mens hands.

text: for I will bring upon Moab the year of their visitation, saith the Lord.

text: Defecerunt oculi mei in eloquium tuum, dicentes: Quando consolaberis me?

text: How wise wast thou in thy youth, & as a flood filled with vnderstanding.

text: And he shut vp his people in the sword: and he dispised his inheritance.

text: I haue found Dauid my seruant: with myne holie oyle haue I anointed him.

text: Cum aliena muliere ne sedeas omnino, nec accumbas cum ea super cubitum:

text: A woman will receiue euery man, yet is one daughter better then another

text: Stumble not at the beautie of a woman, and desire her not for pleasure.

text: Dixi Domino: Deus meus es tu; exaudi, Domine, vocem deprecationis meae.
verse_text: Exaudi, Deus, orationem meam cum deprecor; a timore inimici eripe animam meam.

text: Bona enim in mala convertens insidiatur, et in electis imponet maculam.
verse_text: Mittens lapidem in volatilia, dejiciet illa: sic et qui conviciatur amico, dissolvit amicitiam.

text: Wisedome exalteth her children, and layeth hold of them that seeke her.
verse_text: et eris tu velut filius Altissimi obediens, et miserebitur tui magis quam mater.

text: Because thou o Lord art my hope: thou hast made the Highest thy refuge.
verse_text: Unto thee, O my helper, will I sing, for thou art God my defence: my God my mercy.

text: A froward heart shall depart from me, I will not knowe a wicked person.
verse_text: I wil set no wicked thing before mine eyes: I hate the worke of them that fall away: it shall not cleaue vnto me.

text: Deliuer me from them that worke iniquitie: and from bloudy men saue me.
verse_text: Keepe me from the snare, which they haue set for me: and from the scandals of them that worke iniquitie.

text: I haue found Dauid my seruant: with mine holy oyle haue I anoynted him.
verse_text: There will I make the horne of Dauid to bud: for I haue ordeined a light for mine Anoynted.

text: We will enter into his Tabernacles, and worship before his footestoole.
verse_text: We wil enter into his tabernacle: we wil adore in the place where his feete stood.

text: Our fathers trusted in thee: they trusted, and thou didst deliuer them.
verse_text: They called vpon thee, and were deliuered: they trusted in thee, and were not confounded.

text: every one that shall pass by it, shall be astonished, and wag his head.
verse_text: every one that shall pass by it, shall be astonished, and shall hiss because of all the plagues thereof.

text: Let mine vprightnes and equitie preserue me: for mine hope is in thee.
verse_text: And as for me, thou vpholdest me in mine integritie, and doest set me before thy face for euer.

text: Let your soule reioyce in his mercy, and be not ashamed of his praise.
verse_text: Venter meus conturbatus est quaerendo illam: propterea bonam possidebo possessionem.

text: Alleluia. PRAYSE our Lord ye children: praise ye the name of our Lord.
verse_text: Alleluia. PRAYSE ye our Lord in his holies : prayse ye him in the firmament of his strength.

text: et factus est mihi sermo Domini in opprobrium, et in derisum tota die.
verse_text: factus sum in derisum tota die;

text: Canticum graduum. Memento, Domine, David, et omnis mansuetudinis ejus:
verse_text: Canticum ipsi David, quando domus aedificabatur post captivitatem. Cantate Domino canticum novum; cantate Domino omnis terra.

text: Haec requies mea in saeculum saeculi; hic habitabo, quoniam elegi eam.
verse_text: Sic psalmum dicam nomini tuo in saeculum saeculi, ut reddam vota mea de die in diem.

text: laetifica animam servi tui, quoniam ad te, Domine, animam meam levavi.
verse_text: et nomen Domini invocavi: o Domine, libera animam meam.

text: By her he shall be couered from heat, and in her glory shall he dwell.
verse_text: Protegetur sub tegmine illius a fervore, et in gloria ejus requiescet.

text: Rise vp betimes, and be not the last: but get thee home without delay.
verse_text: Si bis interrogatus fueris, habeat caput responsum tuum.

text: Quasi cedrus exaltata sum in Libano, et quasi cypressus in monte Sion:
verse_text: quasi palma exaltata sum in Cades, et quasi plantatio rosae in Jericho:

text: Their Priestes fel by the sworde: and their widowes were not wept for.
verse_text: The fire deuoured their chosen men, and their maides were not praised.

text: let them be couered with reproofe and confusion, that seeke mine hurt.
verse_text: Let them be ashamed and brought to confusion together, that reioyce at mine hurt:

text: this is the city to be visited, all oppression is in the midst of her.
verse_text: Shout against her, she hath every where given her hand, her foundations are fallen, her walls are thrown down, for it is the vengeance of the Lord.

text: It is better to trust in the Lord, then to haue confidence in princes.
verse_text: It is good to hope in our Lord, rather then to hope in man.

text: Et ascendit super cherubim, et volavit; volavit super pennas ventorum.
verse_text: Educens nubes ab extremo terrae, fulgura in pluviam fecit; qui producit ventos de thesauris suis.

text: Quoniam declinaverunt in me iniquitates, et in ira molesti erant mihi.
verse_text: congregata sunt super me flagella, et ignoravi.

text: I wil be glad and reioyce in thee: I wil sing to thy name o most High.
verse_text: I wil confesse to thee among peoples o Lord: and I wil say a Psalme to thee among the Gentiles.

text: Daleth Adhaesit pavimento anima mea: vivifica me secundum verbum tuum.
verse_text: Caph Defecit in salutare tuum anima mea, et in verbum tuum supersperavi.

text: Fire and heate blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Seas and riuers blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Rex somnium dicat servis suis, et interpretationem illius indicabimus.
verse_text: Somnium itaque dicite mihi, ut sciam quod interpretationem quoque ejus veram loquamini.

text: Confitebor tibi in populis, Domine, et psalmum dicam tibi in gentibus:
verse_text: Nam et ego confitebor tibi in vasis psalmi veritatem tuam, Deus; psallam tibi in cithara, sanctus Israel.

text: Cessa prior causa disciplinae: et noli nimius esse, ne forte offendas.
verse_text: Cum saltatrice ne assiduus sis, nec audias illam, ne forte pereas in efficacia illius.

text: Ego autem in innocentia mea ingressus sum; redime me, et miserere mei.
verse_text: Intende ad deprecationem meam, quia humiliatus sum nimis. Libera me a persequentibus me, quia confortati sunt super me.

text: Exaudiat te Dominus in die tribulationis; protegat te nomen Dei Jacob.
verse_text: Mittat tibi auxilium de sancto, et de Sion tueatur te.

text: In via testimoniorum tuorum delectatus sum, sicut in omnibus divitiis.
verse_text: Laetabor ego super eloquia tua, sicut qui invenit spolia multa.

text: Who led his people through the desert: because his mercie is for euer.
verse_text: And brought forth Israel through the middes therof: because his mercie is for euer.

text: And they set against me euil thinges for good: and hatred for my loue.
verse_text: They repayed me euil things for good, sterilitie to my soule.

text: Make thy face to shine vpon thy seruant: saue me for thy mercies sake.
verse_text: Returne, O Lord, deliuer my soule: oh saue mee, for thy mercies sake.

text: haereditatem Israel, servo suo, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: Qui fecit caelos in intellectu, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.

text: Remooue from me reproch and contempt: for I haue kept thy testimonies.
verse_text: Deliuer mee from the oppression of men, and I will keepe thy precepts.

text: Myne eies haue fayled for thy word, saying: When wilt thou comfort me?
verse_text: My bones are cut asunder, while mine enemies reproch me, saying dayly vnto me, Where is thy God?

text: and the priests shall be astonished, and the prophets shall be amazed.
verse_text: then the men shall cry, and all the inhabitants of the land shall howl,

text: Goe not after thy lustes, but refraine thy selfe from thine appetites.
verse_text: Post concupiscentias tuas non eas, et a voluntate tua avertere.

text: Beholde, I desire thy commandements: quicken me in thy righteousnesse,
verse_text: I cried vnto thee, saue me: and I shall keepe thy testimonies.

text: Et dedit eis petitionem ipsorum, et misit saturitatem in animas eorum.
verse_text: et dedit eos in misericordias, in conspectu omnium qui ceperant eos.

text: Use not to make any maner of lie: for the custome thereof is not good.
verse_text: Noli amare mendacium adversus fratrem tuum, neque in amicum similiter facias.

text: In thee, O Lord, doe I put my trust, let me neuer be put to confusion.
verse_text: TO THEE o Lord I haue lifted vp my soule: my God in thee is my confidence, let me not be ashamed:

text: Domus Israel speravit in Domino; adjutor eorum et protector eorum est.
verse_text: Anima nostra sustinet Dominum, quoniam adjutor et protector noster est.

text: Frost and cold blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Yse and snowes blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Yse and snowes blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.
verse_text: Seas and riuers blesse ye our Lord: prayse and superexalt him for euer.

text: Et tentaverunt Deum in cordibus suis, ut peterent escas animabus suis.
verse_text: Et clamaverunt ad Dominum cum tribularentur, et de necessitatibus eorum eripuit eos;

text: Redde mihi laetitiam salutaris tui, et spiritu principali confirma me.
verse_text: Libera me de sanguinibus, Deus, Deus salutis meae, et exsultabit lingua mea justitiam tuam.

text: De praeparato habitaculo suo respexit super omnes qui habitant terram:
verse_text: Quia prospexit de excelso sancto suo; Dominus de caelo in terram aspexit:

text: Audivit Dominus, et misertus est mei; Dominus factus est adjutor meus.
verse_text: Et scitote quoniam mirificavit Dominus sanctum suum; Dominus exaudiet me cum clamavero ad eum.

text: Lord, why castest thou off my soule? why hidest thou thy face from me?
verse_text: Why doest thou o Lord reiectmy prayer: turnest away thy face from me?

text: And gaue their land for an heritage: for his mercie endureth for euer:
verse_text: Which made great lightes: for his mercie endureth for euer:

text: Shall not the deaw asswage the heate? so is a word better then a gift.
verse_text: Nonne ardorem refrigerabit ros? sic et verbum melius quam datum.

text: Misericordiae tuae multae, Domine; secundum judicium tuum vivifica me.
verse_text: Humiliatus sum usquequaque, Domine; vivifica me secundum verbum tuum.

text: Vinum et musica laetificant cor: et super utraque dilectio sapientiae.
verse_text: spiritus enim meus super mel dulcis, et haereditas mea super mel et favum.

text: And he lifted vp his hand ouer them: to ouerthrowe them in the desert:
verse_text: And the wrath of God ascended vpon them. And he killed their fat ones, and the chosen of Israel he hindered.

text: let them be couered with confusion, and shame, that seeke euils to me.
verse_text: let them bee clothed with confusion and shame, that lift vp themselues against me.

text: Ne projicias me a facie tua, et spiritum sanctum tuum ne auferas a me.
verse_text: in manibus tuis sortes meae: eripe me de manu inimicorum meorum, et a persequentibus me.

text: Exitus aquarum deduxerunt oculi mei, quia non custodierunt legem tuam.
verse_text: Quoniam alieni insurrexerunt adversum me, et fortes quaesierunt animam meam, et non proposuerunt Deum ante conspectum suum.

text: Judica judicium meum, et redime me: propter eloquium tuum vivifica me.
verse_text: In justitia tua libera me, et eripe me: inclina ad me aurem tuam, et salva me.

text: Yee that feare the Lord, beleeue him, and your reward shall not faile.
verse_text: Qui timetis Dominum, credite illi, et non evacuabitur merces vestra.

text: Suavis Dominus universis, et miserationes ejus super omnia opera ejus.
verse_text: Confiteantur Domino misericordiae ejus, et mirabilia ejus filiis hominum.

text: Qui fecit caelos in intellectu, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus.
verse_text: et dedit terram eorum haereditatem, quoniam in aeternum misericordia ejus;

text: In Deo laudabimur tota die, et in nomine tuo confitebimur in saeculum.
verse_text: praeoccupemus faciem ejus in confessione, et in psalmis jubilemus ei:

text: Because for thy sake I haue borne reproch: shame hath couered my face.
verse_text: Thou hast knowen my reproofe and my shame, and my dishonour: all mine aduersaries are before thee.

text: He iudged the cause of the poore and needy, then it was well with him:
verse_text: He judged the cause of the poor and needy for his own good:

text: Vp Lord: let not man preuaile: let the heathen be iudged in thy sight.
verse_text: O let not the oppressed returne ashamed: let the poore and needie praise thy name.

text: O house of Aaron, trust in the Lord: he is their helpe & their shield.
verse_text: Ye that feare the Lord trust in the Lord: he is their helpe and their shield.

text: Non te pigeat visitare infirmum: ex his enim in dilectione firmaberis.
verse_text: Non impediaris orare semper, et ne verearis usque ad mortem justificari, quoniam merces Dei manet in aeternum.

text: giue mee vnderstanding therefore, that I may learne thy commandements.
verse_text: Giue me vnderstanding, and I shall keepe thy Law:

text: for yee haue kindled a fire in mine anger, which shall burne for euer.
verse_text: for a fire is kindled in my rage, it shall burn upon you.

text: Initio tu, Domine, terram fundasti, et opera manuum tuarum sunt caeli.
verse_text: Tui sunt caeli, et tua est terra: orbem terrae, et plenitudinem ejus tu fundasti;

text: Evertisti testamentum servi tui; profanasti in terra sanctuarium ejus.
verse_text: Respice in testamentum tuum, quia repleti sunt qui obscurati sunt terrae domibus iniquitatum.

text: Quoniam exsultatis, et magna loquimini, diripientes haereditatem meam:
verse_text: et ingressi contaminastis terram meam, et haereditatem meam posuistis in abominationem.

text: Praeparamini contra Babylonem per circuitum, omnes qui tenditis arcum:
verse_text: Caedite lignum ejus, et fundite circa Jerusalem aggerem.

text: Before man is life and death, and whether him liketh shalbe giuen him.
verse_text: Apposuit tibi aquam et ignem, ad quod volueris porrige manum tuam.

text: At the end of twelue moneths, he walked in the royall palace of Babel.
verse_text: And at the end of ten dayes, their countenances appeared fayrer, and in better liking then all the childrens, which did eate the portion of the Kings meate.

text: shewe thy seruants thy dreame, and wee shall shewe the interpretation.
verse_text: therefore shewe me the dreame, and the interpretation thereof.

text: Domus Levi, benedicite Domino; qui timetis Dominum, benedicite Domino.
verse_text: Qui timetis Dominum, laudate eum; universum semen Jacob, glorificate eum.

text: Custodi animam meam, et erue me: non erubescam, quoniam speravi in te.
verse_text: Quia ad te, Domine, Domine, oculi mei; in te speravi, non auferas animam meam.

text: They that make them are like vnto them: so are all that trust in them.
verse_text: Let them that make them become like to them: and al that haue confidence in them.

text: My knees are weake through fasting, and my flesh hath lost all fatnes.
verse_text: Because my loynes are filled with illusions: and there is no health in my flesh.

text: Because in thee o Lord haue I hoped, thou wilt heare me o Lord my God.
verse_text: But I haue hoped in thee o Lord: I sayd: Thou art my God:

text: I wil be exercised in thy commandmentes: and I wil consider thy waies.
verse_text: Helpe me, and I shal be saued: and I wil meditate in thy iustifications alwayes.

text: et nemo est adjutor meus in omnibus his, nisi Michael princeps vester.
verse_text: et ecce Michael, unus de principibus primis, venit in adjutorium meum, et ego remansi ibi juxta regem Persarum.

text: Plenitudo sapientiae est timere Deum, et plenitudo a fructibus illius.
verse_text: et da locum timori Altissimi: quia omnis sapientia timor Dei, et in illa timere Deum, et in omni sapientia dispositio legis.

text: Cast me not away from thy face: and thy Holie spirit take not from me.
verse_text: Forsake me not, O Lord: O my God, be not farre from me.

text: Pone, Domine, custodiam ori meo, et ostium circumstantiae labiis meis.
verse_text: Ghimel Retribue servo tuo, vivifica me, et custodiam sermones tuos.

text: Let them be confounded and consumed, that are aduersaries to my soule:
verse_text: Let them be confounded and put to shame, that seeke my soule:

text: they hide themselues, they marke my steps when they wait for my soule.
verse_text: and they that lay waite for my soule, take counsell together,

text: The mountaines skipped like rammes: and the little hilles like lambes.
verse_text: Yee mountaines, that yee skipped like rammes: and yee little hilles like lambes?

text: the tumult of those that rise vp against thee, increaseth continually.
verse_text: For strangers are risen vp against me, and tyrants seeke my soule:

text: Let my prayer enter into thy presence: incline thine eare vnto my cry.
verse_text: Let my request enter in thy sight: according to thy word deliuer me.

text: Fiat cor meum immaculatum in justificationibus tuis, ut non confundar.
verse_text: Anima mea in manibus meis semper, et legem tuam non sum oblitus.

text: Extraneus factus sum fratribus meis, et peregrinus filiis matris meae.
verse_text: Super omnes inimicos meos factus sum opprobrium, et vicinis meis valde, et timor notis meis; qui videbant me foras fugerunt a me.

text: Est propter gloriam minoratio, et est qui ab humilitate levabit caput.
verse_text: Sapientia humiliati exaltabit caput illius, et in medio magnatorum consedere illum faciet.

text: Praise the Lord, because he is good: for his mercie endureth for euer.
verse_text: O giue thankes vnto the Lord, for hee is good: because his mercie endureth for euer.

text: Blessed is he whose transgression is forgiuen, whose sinne is couered.
verse_text: A Psalme of David to give instruction. Blessed is he whose wickednes is forgiuen, and whose sinne is couered.

text: Pavor, et fovea, et laqueus super te, o habitator Moab, dicit Dominus.
verse_text: super omnia tecta Moab, et in plateis ejus, omnis planctus: quoniam contrivi Moab sicut vas inutile, ait Dominus.

text: When he iudged the cause of the afflicted and the poore, he prospered:
verse_text: they iudge not the cause, the cause of the fatherlesse, yet they prosper:

text: introibo in potentias Domini; Domine, memorabor justitiae tuae solius.
verse_text: ego autem in misericordia tua speravi. Exsultabit cor meum in salutari tuo. Cantabo Domino qui bona tribuit mihi; et psallam nomini Domini altissimi.

text: Exsultabunt labia mea cum cantavero tibi; et anima mea quam redemisti.
verse_text: Educ de custodia animam meam ad confitendum nomini tuo; me exspectant justi donec retribuas mihi.

text: That hee would confirme his mercy with vs, and deliuer vs at his time.
verse_text: Et nunc orate Deum omnium, qui magna fecit in omni terra, qui auxit dies nostros a ventre matris nostrae, et fecit nobiscum secundum suam misericordiam:

text: And I will give them up to the rage of all the kingdoms of the earth:
verse_text: For behold I will call together all the families of the kingdoms of the north:

text: Doe nothing without aduice, and when thou hast once done, repent not.
verse_text: Qui quaerit legem replebitur ab ea, et qui insidiose agit scandalizabitur in ea.

text: Et posuerunt adversum me mala pro bonis, et odium pro dilectione mea.
verse_text: Circumdederunt me sicut apes, et exarserunt sicut ignis in spinis: et in nomine Domini, quia ultus sum in eos.

text: Be exalted aboue the heauens o God, and thy glorie ouer al the earth:
verse_text: Be thou exalted, O God, aboue the heauens: and thy glory aboue all the earth:

text: And al kinges of the earth shal adore him: al nations shal serue him.
verse_text: And the Gentiles shal feare thy name o Lord, and al the kinges of the earth thy glorie.

text: Fiant nati ejus in interitum; in generatione una deleatur nomen ejus.
verse_text: Vir linguosus non dirigetur in terra; virum injustum mala capient in interitu.

text: Of exactnesse of ballance, and waights: or of getting much or little:
verse_text: Of theft, and of the truth of God, and the covenant: of leaning with thy elbow over meat, and of deceit in giving and taking:

text: Be axalted aboue the heauens o God: and thy glorie vpon al the earth.
verse_text: Be thou exalted, O God, aboue the heauens: and thy glory aboue all the earth:

text: The Lord hateth all abomination, and they that feare God loue it not.
verse_text: Omne execramentum erroris odit Dominus, et non erit amabile timentibus eum.

text: What is heauier then lead? and what is the name thereof, but a foole?
verse_text: Cum stulto ne multum loquaris, et cum insensato ne abieris.

text: None of them hindreth another, and they shall neuer disobey his word.
verse_text: Unusquisque proximum sibi non angustiabit in aeternum:

text: For they sought out all wickednes, till the vengeance came vpon them.
verse_text: Dedit autem reliquum Jacob, et David de ipsa stirpe.

text: To declare the Name of the Lord in Zion: and his praise in Ierusalem:
verse_text: O giue thankes vnto the Lord, call vpon his name: make knowen his deeds among the people.

text: for I am with thee to save thee, and to deliver thee, saith the Lord.
verse_text: for I am with thee to saue thee, and to deliuer thee, sayth the Lord.

text: They haue opened their mouth vpon me, as a lion rauening and roaring.
verse_text: Like as a lyon that is greedie of his pray, and as it were a yong lyon lurking in secret places.

text: Deus virtutum, converte nos, et ostende faciem tuam, et salvi erimus.
verse_text: Converte nos, Deus salutaris noster, et averte iram tuam a nobis.

text: Our soule expecteth our Lord: because he is our helper and protector.
verse_text: They that feare our Lord, haue hoped in our Lord: he is their helper and their protector.

text: And the waters couered their enemies: there was not one of them left.
verse_text: Egypt was glad when they departed: for the feare of them fell vpon them.

text: With all these I sought rest: and in whose inheritance shall I abide?
verse_text: Ego in altissimis habitavi, et thronus meus in columna nubis.

text: Omnis plaga tristitia cordis est, et omnis malitia nequitia mulieris.
verse_text: Cor humile, et facies tristis, et plaga cordis, mulier nequam.

text: He chose Dauid also his seruant, and tooke him from the sheepe-folds:
verse_text: Euen from behinde the ewes with yong brought he him to feede his people in Iaakob, and his inheritance in Israel.

text: Quia ipse super maria fundavit eum, et super flumina praeparavit eum.
verse_text: quoniam ipsius est mare, et ipse fecit illud, et siccam manus ejus formaverunt.

text: Then I acknowledged my sinne vnto thee, neither hid I mine iniquitie:
verse_text: for I thought, I will confesse against my selfe my wickednesse vnto the Lord, and thou forgauest the punishment of my sinne.

text: and he shal stand in a noble land, & it shal be consumed in his hand.
verse_text: And the king of the South shal be made strong, & there shal of his princes preuaile aboue him, and he shal rule in dominion:

text: Their sacrifices shall be wholy consumed euery day twise continually.
verse_text: Corona aurea super mitram ejus expressa signo sanctitatis, et gloria honoris: opus virtutis, et desideria oculorum ornata.

text: They breake in pieces thy people, O Lord: and afflict thine heritage.
verse_text: They haue burnt thy sanctuarie with fire: they haue polluted the tabernacle of thy name in the earth.

text: And they that be wise, shall shine, as ye brightnes of the firmament:
verse_text: and they that turne many to righteousnes, shall shine as the starres, for euer and euer.

text: Be exalted aboue the heauens o God: and thy glorie vpon al the earth.
verse_text: Be thou exalted, O God, aboue the heauens: and thy glory aboue all the earth:

text: Dominus custodit te; Dominus protectio tua super manum dexteram tuam.
verse_text: etenim illuc manus tua deducet me, et tenebit me dextera tua.

text: Canticum graduum. Ad Dominum cum tribularer clamavi, et exaudivit me.
verse_text: Alleluja. Dilexi, quoniam exaudiet Dominus vocem orationis meae.

text: and the Lord will repent of the evil that he hath spoken against you.
verse_text: I will repent of the good that I have spoken to do unto it.

text: Videbunt recti, et laetabuntur; et omnis iniquitas oppilabit os suum.
verse_text: Laetabitur justus in Domino, et sperabit in eo, et laudabuntur omnes recti corde.

text: Non avertas faciem tuam a me, et similis ero descendentibus in lacum.
verse_text: avertisti faciem tuam a me, et factus sum conturbatus.

text: multos enim errare fecerunt somnia, et exciderunt sperantes in illis.
verse_text: multos quoque supplantavit suspicio illorum, et in vanitate detinuit sensus illorum.

text: Spiritus timentium Deum quaeritur, et in respectu illius benedicetur.
verse_text: Timenti Dominum bene erit, et in diebus consummationis illius benedicetur.

text: Speravit in Domino, eripiat eum: salvum faciat eum, quoniam vult eum.

text: Arise, O Lord God: lift vp thine hande: forget not the poore.
verse_text: Arise, O God, plead thine owne cause: remember how the foolish man reprocheth thee daily.

text: This is the word that came to Jeremias from the Lord, saying:
verse_text: And the word of the Lord came to Jeremias the prophet, saying:

text: And Ieremiah said; The word of the Lord came vnto me, saying;
verse_text: Then came the word of the Lord vnto the Prophet Ieremiah, saying,

text: And Hananiah spake in the presence of all the people, saying;
verse_text: And Jeremias said to all the people, and to all the women:

text: Bonus es tu, et in bonitate tua doce me justificationes tuas.
verse_text: Vias meas enuntiavi, et exaudisti me; doce me justificationes tuas.

text: Arise my glorie, arise psalter, and harpe: I wil arise early.
verse_text: Awake vp my glory, awake psalterie and harpe; I my selfe will awake early.

text: Misit rex, et solvit eum; princeps populorum, et dimisit eum.

text: O God be not farre from me: my God haue respect to mine ayde.
verse_text: But thou Lord prolong not thy helpe from me: looke toward my defense.

text: Auditam fac mihi mane misericordiam tuam, quia in te speravi.

text: For from garments commeth a moth, and from women wickednesse.
verse_text: de vestimentis enim procedit tinea, et a muliere iniquitas viri.

text: Ab omni via mala prohibui pedes meos, ut custodiam verba tua.
verse_text: Dixi: Custodiam vias meas: ut non delinquam in lingua mea. Posui ori meo custodiam, cum consisteret peccator adversum me.

text: Feare the Lord with all thy soule, and reuerence his priests.
verse_text: honora patrem tuum, et gemitus matris tuae ne obliviscaris:

text: sed castigabo te in judicio, nec quasi innocenti parcam tibi.
verse_text: cum exaltaveris quasi aquila nidum tuum, inde detraham te, dicit Dominus.

text: And Ieremiah said, The word of the Lord came vnto me, saying,

text: Who onlie doth great meruels: because his mercie is for euer.

text: or who will stand vp for me against the workers of iniquitie?
verse_text: Who will rise vp for mee against the euill doers?

text: Et nunc, reges, intelligite; erudimini, qui judicatis terram.

text: Lord let me not be confounded, because I haue inuocated thee.

text: Et ero immaculatus cum eo; et observabo me ab iniquitate mea.

text: Miserere mei, Domine: vide humilitatem meam de inimicis meis,
verse_text: Deus, Deus meus, respice in me: quare me dereliquisti? longe a salute mea verba delictorum meorum.

text: Goe not farre from me, O God: my God, haste thee to helpe me.
verse_text: But be not thou farre from mee, O Lord; O my strength, hast thee to helpe me.

text: ut ponat civitates Juda solitudinem, et habitaculum draconum.

text: Quid est, quod dilectus meus in domo mea fecit scelera multa?

text: Let them be ashamed and confounded that seeke after my soule:
verse_text: Let them be confounded and put to shame, that seeke my soule:

text: Et dissipatum est vas quod ipse faciebat e luto manibus suis:

text: Cantate ei canticum novum; bene psallite ei in vociferatione.

text: factus est cursus eorum malus, et fortitudo eorum dissimilis.

text: My soule cleaueth vnto thee: for thy right hand vpholdeth me.

text: Let them be confounded and put to shame, that seeke my soule:
verse_text: Let them be ashamed and confounded that seeke after my soule:

text: And Daniel continued euen vnto the first yeere of king Cyrus.
verse_text: So this Daniel prospered in the reigne of Darius, and in the reigne of Cyrus the Persian.

text: et dejecit de fortitudine, et de stellis, et conculcavit eas.

text: Death is better then a bitter life, or continuall sickenesse.
verse_text: Melior est mors quam vita amara, et requies aeterna quam languor perseverans.

text: Vnto the end for the morning enterprise, the Psalme of Dauid.
verse_text: Vnto the end in songs, the Psalme of Dauid for the octaue.

text: Dominus solus sustinentibus se in via veritatis et justitiae.
verse_text: Poenitentibus autem dedit viam justitiae, et confirmavit deficientes sustinere, et destinavit illis sortem veritatis.

text: neque alliges duplicia peccata, nec enim in uno eris immunis.

text: Feare is come vpon mee for the wicked, that forsake thy Lawe.

text: Our Lord is iust in al his wayes: and holie in al his workes.
verse_text: The feare of our Lord is holie, permanent for euer and euer: the iudgmentes of our Lord be true, iustified in themselues.

text: quoniam magna potentia Dei solius, et ab humilibus honoratur.
verse_text: Terribilis Dominus, et magnus vehementer, et mirabilis potentia ipsius.

text: Non te justifices ante Deum, quoniam agnitor cordis ipse est:
verse_text: nec oblecteris super ipsos, si non est timor Dei in illis.

text: Mei autem pene moti sunt pedes, pene effusi sunt gressus mei:

text: for behold, I wil bring euill vpon all flesh, saith the Lord:

text: Seeke the Lord and his strength: seeke his face continually.

text: Thus speaketh the Lord of hostes, the God of Israel, saying;
verse_text: For thus sayth the Lord of hostes, the God of Israel:

text: Because they beleued not in God, nor hoped in his saluation.

text: Non reliquit hominem nocere eis: et corripuit pro eis reges.

text: O Lord my God, I cried vnto thee, and thou hast restored me.

text: Et dilexerunt eum in ore suo, et lingua sua mentiti sunt ei;

text: Non credas vitae illorum, et ne respexeris in labores eorum.

text: I dwelt in high places, and my throne is in a cloudy pillar.

text: My soule fainteth for thy saluation: but I hope in thy word.

text: Montes exsultaverunt ut arietes, et colles sicut agni ovium.

verse_text: In petra exaltavit me, et nunc exaltavit caput meum super inimicos meos. Circuivi, et immolavi in tabernaculo ejus hostiam vociferationis; cantabo, et psalmum dicam Domino.
